o create an XML document, it is necessary to fully understand the XML components and the basic syntax Linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:33','2025-04-18 20:11:33'),(599,'197','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 12  XML components',NULL,'6802b20ebbd92.png','/storage/tables/6802b20ebbd92.png','2025-04-18 20:11:33','2025-04-18 20:11:58'),(600,'197','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b20ed445a.png','/storage/tables/6802b20ed445a.png','2025-04-18 20:11:33','2025-04-18 20:11:58'),(601,'153','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 13  XML components',NULL,'6802b20ee582b.png','/storage/tables/6802b20ee582b.png','2025-04-18 20:11:33','2025-04-18 20:11:58'),(602,'153','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 6] Structure and components of the XML processor',NULL,'6802b20f01f5a.png','/storage/figures/6802b20f01f5a.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(603,'154','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 7] XML creation procedure',NULL,'6802b20f16423.png','/storage/figures/6802b20f16423.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(604,'155','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 14  Types of DTD declaration',NULL,'6802b20f2a35f.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f2a35f.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(605,'155','App\\Models\\Section','Text','DTD is a file that explicitly declares the structure of an XML document by defining the structure and contents of th document: There are several types of DTD declaration, as shown in the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(606,'198','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b20f37f25.png','/storage/code/6802b20f37f25.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(607,'200','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Determines whether the DTD declaration and definition part will be created inside XML or saved as an external Interal declaration: Defines the DTD in an XML document. External declaration: Applies the DTD (Document type declaration) part to an XML document,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(608,'157','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 15  Comparison of the XML Schema and DTD',NULL,'6802b20f4a85e.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f4a85e.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(609,'157','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The existing DTD cannot limit or extend the data type or range of certain information, ad the DTD description grammar differs from the XML description grammar, which requires understanding of both the DTD ad XML grammars As a result, the XML schema was introduced to replace the DTD and to enable the creation of a data type that can process document more easilv Supporting data types: More complex types of data than the existing DTD can be created, and new types can be created and used. Supporting complex structure definition: Another schema document can be included in a schema document the Schema location directive: Supporting a namespace: XML Schema supports a namespace Namespace: An abstract entity that can distinguish elements when extracting elements from an XML document tvpe and combining them with other documents and when processing multiple documents at the same time using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(610,'158','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 16  Characteristics of XQuery',NULL,'6802b20f5fd44.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f5fd44.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(611,'158','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b20f6dc36.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f6dc36.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(612,'158','App\\Models\\Section','Text','XQuery is a query language that is used to search a XML-based database, and can extract information from XML files as if using a database:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(613,'159','App\\Models\\Section','Text','XLL is a standard language that performs link functions in an XML document, such as XML documents and setting specific locations within an XML document. XLL was introduced to overcome the limitations of HTML-based simple hyperlinks and to provide various approaches to using resources on the web XLL supports various hyperlink methods and two-way links between link resources XLL can use some of the required web resources by using XPointer or XPath, and is used as a core technology in X-Internet, etc, Supports two types, ie. Xpointer when moving within the same document, and Xlnik when moving between different pages, etc Provides a two-way link between resources Provides an extended pointer (XPointer) for resource locating: Linl tuno Cimnlo Fvtondod | ocator Groun Documant llinking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(614,'160','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 17  Building a multimedia database',NULL,'6802b20f81b8c.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f81b8c.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(615,'160','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The multimedia database was developed to efficiently search and manage unstructured multimedia data characterized by their large capacity and complexity, such as text, image, audio, video, etc. Existing databases face limitations due to the exponential increase of unstructured multimedia data, and an object-oriented approach,, the synchronized representation of multimedia, and the concept of time-dependent modeling were used to model various tvpes of unstructured data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(616,'161','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Unlike general commercial databases in which a database is stored on a disk the main memory database manages and manipulates a database by keeping it in the memory: The current trend is that the main memory database is actively used due to business demands, such as securing the competitiveness of an enterprise through quick decision-making, and the revolutionary development of related technologies such as the release of 64-bit OS, the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(617,'161','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tcuuclon 0i Tctu } piiCcd, CLC The MMDB has the following characteristics due to the fact that the database runs in the main memory: Disk IO does not occur because all operations are performed in the main memory: Performance is good because disk IJO, which degrades performance in the disk-based database, is rare Hardware-based error recovery techniques are used due to the volatility of the main memory: A disk is used for backup and logging: Hashing and T-tree indexing algorithm optimized for a memory environment is used. Types of commercial main memory databases can be updated at [https:Ilen.wikipedia orghiki List_of_in-memor} databases]','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(618,'162','App\\Models\\Section','Text','General commercial databases are not suitable for the embedded system, which has limited memory and special performance goals. The embedded database was developed for the embedded system, so as to allow specific functions to be used in a limited embedded environment Asa result, the embedded database has the following technical characteristics It provides essential functions only after reducing overheads to use minimum RAM and disk It supports communication between different devices to allow communication with the database in a central server It supports porting to the various platforms of the embedded system: It satisfies the performance requirements of the real-time OS of the embedded system: The list of commercial embedded databases can be updated at [http Ilembedded-databasescom','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(619,'163','App\\Models\\Section','Text','he mobile database is exclusively used by mobile devices The mobile database,, which is installed in a mobile device, rocesses the data generated field work ad sends them to the central server for synchronization Due to ne distinct characteristics of installation in a mobile device, mobile database should be independent from various latforms and operation systems, should recover quickly from failures, and should be optimized for a limited mobile during The mobile database is exclusively used by mobile devices: The mobile database, which is installed in a mobile device, processes the data generated field work ad sends them to the central server for synchronization Due to the distinct characteristics of installation in a mobile device, a mobile database should be independent from various platforms and operation systems, should recover quickly from failures, and should be optimized for a limited mobile environment As a result, the mobile database has the following characteristics. The database can be installed in a small capacity device equipped with a limited CPU and memory: It is provided as an embedded form that integrates data and applications It has the function of data replication and synchronization with the database of the existing server Commercial mobile databases include Sybase SQL Anywhere, Oracle Lite, Microsoft SQL Server Compact, SQLite, and IBM DB2 Everyplace during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(620,'164','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A spatial database is a set of non-spatial data represented by letters and numbers and spatial data represented by coordinate values The spatial database was initially developed because a technology for processing unstructured data\" , such as the geographic information system was needed as a core technology for a type of guided missile that strikes a preset target by tracking the targets location using geographical information: Thereafter, the database was introduced full scale, as the market was expanded to include services that store and manage values for specific locations using geographical information,, such as GIS and location information check spatial','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(621,'164','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Geometry, a geographical object, and topology for the relationship between objects are included Unstructured data can be processed, large amounts of data can be processed quickly: Spatial (topological, geometric) characteristics are reflected New index and operation (R-tree index) are used to sort data that cannot be sorted Expressive data model that can express complex information Supports the combination of spatial data and non-spatial data spatial','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(622,'165','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 18  Comparison of the column base database and row base database',NULL,'6802b20f9524c.png','/storage/tables/6802b20f9524c.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(623,'165','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b20fb7e9e.png','/storage/tables/6802b20fb7e9e.png','2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(624,'165','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A column base database physically stores data based on columns The data storage method of the relational database is not defined as row base or column base, but general relational databases use a physical storage structure based on rows However, a way to store data with this structure reached the limit in analyzing large-scale data at high because its physical structure required that unnecessary data should be also read The concept of column storage did not suddenly appear recently: Rather, this concept was studied relatively early on, including TAXIR which was developed in 1969 for searching biological information Recently, as the demand for the rapid processing of large amounts of data increased, a function that partially borrowed the concept of the column store such as the column store index, column store base DBMS, and hybrid DBMS supporting both structures were developed from the mid 2000s. Column base database technology is now actively used in the DBMS market, together with the main memory database The column base database has the following structure and characteristics compared to the row-based database speed being The list of commercial column-oriented databases is updated at [https:Ilen wikipedia orglwiki/List_of_column oriented_DBMSes]:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(625,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(626,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Text','In the past, many databases were built to create a \"paperless\" environment in which data recorded on paper are digitalized and stored in a database. Recently, there have been many cases in which databases have been elaborately built from a digital environment to a digital environment: Instead of simply managing data with a fixed format or length, there is an increasing number of cases in which data are stored and processed as various types of unstructured data regardless of the data format or size','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(627,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(628,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the database design and build process: 2 To be able to explain the matters to take into consideration when designing a database','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(629,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(630,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Requirements analysis, conceptual data modeling, logical data modeling, physical data modeling, data modeling subject, deliverables for analysis, impact of design','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(631,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(632,'17','App\\Models\\Module','Text','There are many cases in which a database is used like an existing file system, and tables are created in the database, but each table is actually dependent on individual applications, screens, and reports For example, when developing a book management system for each team, a booklist table can be created for each team during implementation of database in the same way as books are managed using Excel files. If tables are designed in the same way as Excel files, the advantages of the database, including integration,, storage, operation, and sharing, cannot be utilized at all In this case, the complexity of the application program also increases, causing symptoms that can lead to serious problems, such as an increase in development costs, problems with data integrity (lack of consistency due to data duplication), and the deterioration of data processing performance: Therefore, these problems should be prevented and the advantages of the database can be maximized and to the development of a system only when we understand the definition and characteristics of the database (integration, storage, neration charino) and the Advantaoec of the datahace and then annlv them tonnctical hucinecs applied','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:34','2025-04-18 20:11:34'),(633,'202','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Static structure requirements: Entity, property, relationship, constraint, etc Dynamic structure requirements: Transaction type, frequency, etc:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(634,'203','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Abstract conceptualization of the information structure appearing in the real world The entity, entity identifier relationship between entities, number and sequence of corresponding relationship entity properties, etc can be identified Generally represented by an entity-relationship (ER) model','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(635,'204','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Conversion of the result of the conceptual design, which is created for human understanding, into a logical structure that can be easily stored in a database There are the relational, network, hierarchical and object-oriented models, of which the relational model is most generally used. In case of the relational model, the table name, primary (PK), foreign (FK), etc. are determined in the logical design phase. A logical schema is created as a phase deliverable Normalization is performed according to the requirement level key key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(636,'205','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Determination of the physical storage structure of the database created using logical structure design Definition of the data type of the column, constraints, and access method and for specific data. A technology for converting the structure according to the performance requirements is needed Specifically, transaction analysis,view design, index design, capacity design, and approach design are performed A physical schema is created as a phase deliverable. path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(637,'167','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 19  Types of data modeling',NULL,'6802b20fd1c02.png','/storage/tables/6802b20fd1c02.png','2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(638,'167','App\\Models\\Section','Text','data model is a design document for building a database that has a clear goal. In the real world, a database created over time, as shown below: Depending on the level of abstraction, the design can be divided into a conceptuz data model, a logical data model, and physical data. From the real world to the database. Real world Conceptual world  Conceptual data modeling Entity Conceptual structure Logical data Physical (computer) world modeling Storage Physical data modeling Logical structure database First, conceptual data modeling is performed to embody the database at the higher level that has a high level of abstraction in the real world. The conceptual data model has a high level of abstraction, focuses on business, and performs modeling at the comprehensive level. This model is frequently used for enterprise data modeling ad EA establishment: For reference, when deploying EA-based enterprise data modeling: general data modeling, which is a higher level, is performed first, after which conceptual data modeling is performed for each business area. When a entity-centered data model is completed at the higher level, a data model with a focus on concrete business can be created according to a concrete business aspect and flow, which is called \"logical data modeling\". In addition, a method that considers the tablespace according to the storage structure of the database is called \"physical data modeling\".','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(639,'206','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Creation of a database that can accommodate the user requirements by writing and executing SQL statements needed to configure a database.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(640,'209','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','D Continuous maintenance and follow-up evaluation: Deliverables to be analyzed, design subject, impact of design.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(641,'53','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 8] Database design and build process',NULL,'6802b20fe1d89.png','/storage/figures/6802b20fe1d89.png','2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:59'),(642,'53','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','In general, the database design and build process is performed in the phases of collecting and analyzing the requirements, designing the database, building the database, and operating and maintaining it: In particular, the analysisldesign phase is performed in detailed stages, as conceptual design, logical design, and physical design The details of the three design phases will be described in greater detail in the next topic [Data modeling]: such','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(643,'210','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The meaning of data and the rules of the correlation between data are defined in this phase A conceptual dat model should be created as a deliverable by defining the subject area, key entity and relationships in this phase','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(644,'211','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Attributes and should be defined based on the previously created conceptual data model, entities should be specified accordingly: and a final entity-relationship diagram should be created after defining history management keys','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(645,'212','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','physical schema is implemented in a physical data model to implement a database. Semi-normalization can be performed in consideration of performance in this phase. A table definition document reflecting these requirements is created','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(646,'171','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A data architect (DA) plays the most important role in the database design phase The data architect, who is directly involved from the phase of requirement collection, establishes a data management and defines the data standards In addition, the data architect manages the overall data models that are created by conceptual, logical, and physical modeling: However, the performance aspect should be considered in the physical modeling phase, to ensure that the database concerned will work well regardless of whether the user requirements are implemented. At this time, the database administrator (DBA) may review and reflect the physical structure area, such as the indexes partitions, as well as the clustering storage space, and denormalization That is, the data architect and the database administrator should discuss and determine the final physical model which as the best from their own perspectives in the physical modeling phase, so as to achieve efficient and stable performance system they - regard','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(647,'54','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Database design is the area in the process of database build. The possibility of a problem arising can be minimizec when proceeding with the next phase only when each phase is clearly arranged and the deliverables are accurately produced key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(648,'55','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b20ff40bc.png','/storage/figures/6802b20ff40bc.png','2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(649,'55','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Data modeling can be clearly defined in the project lifecycle because it is separated into the analysis phase and the design phase: Usually, business-oriented logical data modeling is performed in the aalysis phase, and physical data modeling is performed by considering hardware and performance in the methodology, based on information engineering or structural models In the spiral model, the logical data model and the physical data model are performed on both sides according to the size of the task in the analysis and design phase: The logical data model is performed more frequently in the analysis phase. Explanation The left-hand side corresponds to the database design and build field, whereas the right- hand side corresponds to the application design and build field. ~In general, physical data modeling is performed in the planning or analysis phase, conceptual data modeling in the analysis phase, and logical data modeling in the design phase. ~In real projects, conceptuall logical data modeling is mostly performed (without conceptual data modeling) in the analysis phase.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(650,'55','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The left-hand side corresponds to the database design and build field, whereas the right- hand side corresponds to the application design and build field. IIn general, physical data As a project is implemented by separating it into the data axis and the application axis, matters identified by both sides are mutually verified in order to increase the completeness by phase However, the object-oriented concept is performed in an integrated way without separating data modeling and processing modeling, because modeling is performed by','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(651,'55','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','considering data and process at the same time: (The representative example is a class that has both data (attributes) and process (method) )','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:35','2025-04-18 20:11:35'),(652,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b2101430e.png','/storage/figures/6802b2101430e.png','2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(653,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(654,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Text','The data modeling technique represented by individual entities ad relationships has been used widely: In recent times, however there has been an increase in practical business techniques that try to express the composition or workflow of a business more elaborately in terms of the data modeling expression method Among these, the extended data model supplements the shortcomings of the traditional data model which expresses the composition with simple entities and relationships only and has the strengths of the object- oriented data model. This model expresses the object-oriented inheritance structure as a super-type and a sub-type of data modeling, ad designates a grouping type that has multiple attribute values in a single entity. An analysis of commonly implemented projects showed that about 70% of them use the super-type and sub-type method As a result,, even though data modeling is deployed, there are many cases in which the physical data model is created without a clear standard. Therefore, concrete data modeling techniques, which developer can understand accurately and apply to practical business, need to be acquired and applied in the field. Actually, if the following knowledge and techniques, which are frequently mentioned in actual projects, are known or learned, can be applied usefully: It is essential to fully know and apply the normalization rules, which are the starting of creating a database. Do not casually think that inquiry perforance is slow in normalized models Denormalization technology should be applied based on a proper understanding: A user-independent conceptual schema should be applied to data modeling from the viewpoint of data independence The meaning ad effect of identifier relationships ad non-identifier relationships should be understood before applying them Conversion should be performed after understanding the concepts of super-type and sub-type and after considering performance Do not create a data model with a missing relationship. History data modeling (occurrence, change, progress) in consideration of performance should be available When setting primary the performance and index characteristics should be considered. they point keys,','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(655,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(656,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the concept of data modeling: 2 To be able to design a database according to the data modeling procedure 3 To be able to design entities, attributes, and identifiers in data modeling according to the business requirements 4 To be able to design relationships in data modeling according to the business requirements 5. To be able to explain and solve the problem of the connection 6. To be able to explain how to convert object-relational mapping (ORM): 7. To be able to how to express the Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD): 8. To be able to explain the extended entity-relationship (ER) type 9. To be able to explain data integrity: 10. To be able to designate primary keys and foreign trap: explain keys:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(657,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(658,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Data modeling, entity property relationship, identifier, connection ERD, extended ER trap,','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(659,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(660,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Text','A data model that is as complex as a maze can ruin a project. A complex maze, like the one shown below left,, means that countless trials and errors will be required to find a fast path: Such a data model does not consider business characteristics and physical characteristics As a result, the model has to undergo countless trials and errors to obtain the desired result because the to the data is not clear Also, even if the same number of paths is passed, join operations are generated by checking additional conditions only, without passing through the optimized path: In the end, multiple join operations further degrade performance In addition, if an entity is expressed unnecessarily in large numbers, data are processed inefficiently because an SQL statement should read several tables, while the intended result can be obtained by reading and processing data from one table alone. path','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(661,'18','App\\Models\\Module','Text','we Clieck lie uala Uly, Uie Lwu Kilius Ul plobiers lal alse uue LO |licleaseu Uala Cai Ue SulialLeu as follows: Increased data Data duplication Problems occur in data consistency: Increased data 54 Fall in SQL response L Performance declines These two problems become more important as the number of data grows, and can be solved by optimizing data modeling, which is the ideal way to fundamentally resolve the problem. However, data modeling cannot be performed at any time Therefore, when data modeling is performed again, it should be optimized for efficiently processing data. speed','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(662,'172','App\\Models\\Section','Text','phase in which ambiguity is removed from the requirements by collecting and analyzing the busines: equirements. required specification (or job description) is produced as a deliverable','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(663,'173','App\\Models\\Section','Text','sign in the order of conceptual modeling - logical modeling ~ physical modeling:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:36','2025-04-18 20:11:36'),(664,'213','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Conceptual modeling is the phase in which an ERD is produced, whereas logical modeling is the phase in which the structural drawing of the table is produced. These two phases are clearly separated Therefore, the entities and relationships of the ERD are identified in the conceptual modeling phase, and the primary and foreign of the table are identified in the logical modeling phase Normalization that handles table structure should be performed in the logical modeling phase For reference, \"physical modeling\" refers to the process of creating tables suitable for an actual DBMS. The Chen type of ERD is mainly used The relationship itself can have its own properties in the ERD. keys keys','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(665,'214','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 21  Differences in the understanding of data modeling',NULL,'6802b2102ee09.png','/storage/tables/6802b2102ee09.png','2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(666,'214','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An ERD is produced during logical modeling: Conceptual modeling further abstracts the ERD and summarizes it at a comprehensive level including the subjec area, core entity, core relationship, and core attribute: Conceptual modeling is not studied in the academic world The Crows Foot type of ERD is mainly used.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(667,'214','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If the relationship has its own attributes, are included in the connected or included by identifying a relationship entity: For your reference, \"physical modeling\" refers to the process of converting an ERD into a table structure In general, normalization is performed in the logical data modeling phase, and denormalization is performed in the physical data modeling phase they entity','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(668,'175','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Process modeling\" refers to the task of finding missing or unnecessary tasks to satisfy the functions required by the target system, by analyzing a given task efficiently within a specified period of time, When analyzing large and complex tasks In addition, it is regarded as most important to develop a high-quality system by classifying the analyzed tasks systematically and by designing the menu of the target system and program system. When a task is analyzed using & methodology, the task can be arranged systematically in order to find most of missing or unnecessary tasks, which is helpful when creating a data model The process hierarchy diagram is a frequently used process model, and the task process is subdivided into the function area, function, process, and unit process according to the size of the task','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(669,'176','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Correlation modeling is a method of analyzing what is happening (process) to something (data) that exists within the task concerned and what is affected by which event, when developing an information system: Correlation modeling is performed by using the entity type identified from data modeling ad the unit process identified from process modeling: Whether or not data are generated by the entity type and the unit process can be verified using the CRUD matrix which enables the developer to verify the task for the data model and the process model in the analysis phase, and which can be used to understand the test and task data exchange in the future development phase','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(670,'56','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'<Table 20  Characteristics of modeling',NULL,'6802b21044f77.png','/storage/tables/6802b21044f77.png','2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(671,'56','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','\"Data modeling\"\' refers to the process of abstracting the real world to create a database &nd is performed according to the following procedure: requirements analysis, conceptual modeling, logical modeling, and physical modeling That is, modeling refers to a technique of expression that uses a certain notation to abstract, simplify, and clarify the real NO','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(672,'177','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The phase of abstractly conceptualizing and expressing the information structure appearing in the real world Conceptual modeling begins with analyzing and finding the data requirements of the organization and user, and includes the process of determining which data are important and the form of maintaining that data. Such data requirements are used to describe the phases to be performed in subsequent phases, to give shape to the conceptual data model, which is a set of low relevance, and to discuss the initial requirements with business stakeholders, Finding the core entities ad the relationships between them is most important, and the relationships should be expressed as an entity relationship diagram: The entity, entity identifier, relationship between entities, number and sequence of corresponding relationships, entity properties, etc, can be identified.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(673,'178','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Logical modeling is the key part of the data modeling process, which is a technique or process that clearly expresses the logical structure and rules of business information In this phase, the result of conceptual design, Which is created for human understanding, is converted into a logical structure that can be easily stored in a database. The phase in which normalization is performed to store data efficiently: The relational model is mainly used, and the deliverables of conceptual modeling are converted into the table structure drawing: Table name, primary key, foreign key, etc, are defined','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(674,'179','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The phase that plans how to express logical data modeling in a computer hardiware as a data repository: The structure of physical storage that is expressed in tables and columns, the storage device to be used, and the approach used to extract data are determined in the physical modeling phase Performance is one of the most important factors to consider in this phase, and a denormalization review is considered, The data constraint and index of the col are defined system tvpe','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:11:37'),(675,'58','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 11] Data model notation',NULL,'6802b21062a37.png','/storage/tables/6802b21062a37.png','2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(676,'58','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b21086cca.png','/storage/figures/6802b21086cca.png','2025-04-18 20:11:37','2025-04-18 20:12:00'),(677,'58','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','In 1976, Peter Chen created a form of notation for data models called an entity-relationship model (ER model). This not