relational algebra need to be clearly understood. Therefore, this module introduces set operation and relation operation, which constitute the basic relational algebra, and the extended relational algebra operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:11:43'),(926,'248','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 36  Set operators',NULL,'6802b21481e1f.png','/storage/tables/6802b21481e1f.png','2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(927,'248','App\\Models\\Section','Text','et operators include Union, Intersect, Difference, and Cartesian Product','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:11:43'),(928,'249','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 37  Relation operators',NULL,'6802b2149200d.png','/storage/tables/6802b2149200d.png','2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(929,'249','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b214a5938.png','/storage/tables/6802b214a5938.png','2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(930,'249','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Relation operators include Select, Project, Join, and Division','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:11:43'),(931,'82','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Relational algebra is a set of operations for processing relations in a relational database and all operands of each operation, and the result of the operation is relations. Basic relational algebra operations are usually divided into set operations and relation operations','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:11:43'),(932,'83','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'<Table Extended relational algebra operations 387',NULL,'6802b214babc2.png','/storage/tables/6802b214babc2.png','2025-04-18 20:11:43','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(933,'83','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Useful operations can be defined by extending the basic relational algebra operations Extended relational alge operations such as outer join, semi join, outer union, etc. are generally used.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(934,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b214c82e2.png','/storage/code/6802b214c82e2.png','2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(935,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(936,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Even though the types of databases have been diversified recently, most of the information systems used by corporations and organizations are still running on relational databases Therefore, software developers should be familiar with relational database language and query processing methods and should be able to use them proficiently in order to process data efficiently: SQL was developed by IBM researchers Donald D. Chamberlain and F Raymond Boyce in the early 1970s. SQL began with the name of SEQUEL (Structured English Query Language) and was devised to manipulate and receive the data stored in System R, which was the semi-relational database management system of IBM Recently, interest in acquiring SQL-related certifications has been increasing because the importance of SQL has been highlighted','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(937,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(938,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to utilize a Data Definition Language (DDL). 2 To be able to utilize a Data Control Language (DCL): 3. To be able to utilize the basic operation, group function, and advanced join of a Data Manipulation Language (DML):','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(939,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(940,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Text','SQL, Data Definition Language (DDL) , Data Control Language (DCL), Data Manipulation Language (DML)','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(941,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(942,'23','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Since most of the recent information systems store data in a database, an adequate database processing language is needed to process values by a program to a database. In particular as more than 90% of the databases adopted by a project are mostly relational databases in the majority of cases, developers should be familiar with the relational database language. So how well should developers familiarize themselves with the relational database language? Objects such as tables and views are managed by the data architect (DA) or the database administrator (DBA) in some large-scale projects, however developers manage everything table creation/change/delete to data processing in most projects. Therefore it is desirable for the developer to know all of the data definition language (DDL) , data control language (DCL) , and data manipulation language (DML) of the relational database, in order to perform those tasks smoothly: That is, relational database languages are one of the database build and operation areas that developers should know well, and it is recommended for developers to leam those languages to such a level that thev can Uce the cvntay quite free linking from key\'','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(943,'250','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 39  Types of relational database languages',NULL,'6802b214da163.png','/storage/tables/6802b214da163.png','2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(944,'250','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The relational database language processes the structure and value stored in a relational database and can be classified into the Data Definition Language (DDL), Data Control Language (DCL) , and Data Manipulation Language (DML)_','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(945,'343','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 40  Changes in SQL',NULL,'6802b214ed9d4.png','/storage/tables/6802b214ed9d4.png','2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:12:04'),(946,'343','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SQL was developed by IBM researchers Donald D. Chamberlain and F Raymond Boyce in the early 1970s, and its standards have been changed periodically by the ANSI, as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(947,'344','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 41  Characteristics of SQL3',NULL,'6802b2150a26b.png','/storage/tables/6802b2150a26b.png','2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(948,'344','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The object-oriented characteristics of SQL3 can be seen as the common characteristics of the object relational DBMS','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(949,'345','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A table, view, index schema, function, etc can be defined using the CREATE statement: A primary and foreign key can be defined when creating a table, and the object should not be the same as other created objects. key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(950,'346','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Once a table has been created, it is best to keep its structure intact However it may be necessary to add or delete columns and constraints while the table due to changes in the work requirements or the need for systen operation At this time, the structure of the table can be changed using the ALTER statement using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(951,'347','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This command is used to delete all data and structures of the table when it has been created incorrectly or is no longer needed. However, the referenced constraint related to the table concerned should be deleted first before deleting - a table. In Oracle, the CASCADE CONSTRAINT option can be used to delete it at the same time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(952,'349','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This command is used to change the table name','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(953,'85','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','data definition language is used to describe the database schema in such a way that computers can understand it Specifically, it manages the creation, change, and deletion of a table structure The main statements of the data definition language include CREATE, DROP ALTER and RENAME','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:44','2025-04-18 20:11:44'),(954,'253','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 42  Roles of the data control language',NULL,'6802b21518340.png','/storage/tables/6802b21518340.png','2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(955,'350','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This statement is used to grant privileges related to an object to a user Example: When granting the privilege of searching the customer table to user ABC GRANT SELECT ON customer TO ABC ,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(956,'351','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This statement is used to cancel a users privileges related to an object Example: When withdrawing the privilege of searching the customer table from user ABC. REVOKE SELECT ON customer FROM ABC ,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(957,'352','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This statement is used to deny the users privilege related to an object: If both GRANT and DENY are assigned at same time, DENY takes precedence Example: When denying the user ABCs privilege of searching the customer table ~  DENY SELECT ON customer TO ABC,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(958,'353','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','his statement is used to complete a transaction and confirm a data change','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(959,'354','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This statement is used to cancel a transaction and restore data to their original state before the change','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(960,'86','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','A data control language is used to define and describe data controls, in order to use the database in common: The main statements include GRANT, REVOKE, COMMIT, and ROLLBACK Sometimes, COMMIT and ROLLBACK, which are used to control nested transactions, are separated and called TCL (Transaction Control Language):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(961,'255','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 43  Basic DML operations',NULL,'6802b21527437.png','/storage/tables/6802b21527437.png','2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(962,'255','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b2153c5ba.png','/storage/tables/6802b2153c5ba.png','2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(963,'255','App\\Models\\Section','Text','DML basic operations consist of statements such as INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT, FROM, and WHERE, and are used for input, modification, deletion, and search operations Among them, FROM ad WHERE are used together with the INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and SELECT statements. FROM is used to designate the target table and WHERE is used to set the conditions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(964,'256','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 44  Aggregate DML operations',NULL,'6802b2155010a.png','/storage/tables/6802b2155010a.png','2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(965,'256','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 39] Utilization of aggregate operations',NULL,'6802b21564f13.png','/storage/figures/6802b21564f13.png','2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(966,'256','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Aggregate operations can be performed by the AVE, SUM, and COUNT statements of the DML. The GROUP BY clause is specified after the FROM clause ad the WHERE clause in the SQL statement This clause is used to group data and to obtain statistical information on each group item. Aggregate operations are generally used with the GROUP BY clause: However if a entire table is a group, an aggregate operation can be performed without the GROUP BY clause On the other hand, the HAVING clause can be used to set the condition for the GROUP BY clause In addition, the DISTINCT can be used to consider the same value as the same data using option xample of calculation of no. of employees by department/total employee salarylaverage salary from the Emnlovocl blo beloi','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(967,'355','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NL Join performs join operations in a similar way to the nested statement used in programming: The table outside the loop is called the \"preceding table\" or the \"outer table\"\', and the table inside the loop is called the \"following table\" or the \"inner table\". NL Join first extracts the rows that meet the conditions of the preceding table and performs a join operation while reading the following table. This operation is repeated as many times as the number of rows that meets the conditions of the preceding table: As the join operation of the following table is repeated as many times as the number of rows that meet the conditions of the preceding table, it is recommended to select a table with fewer result rows as the preceding table in consideration of performance It is advantageous to NL Join to have a narrow processing range because data are accessed randomly: loop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(968,'356','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Sort Merge Join performs a join operation by sorting data based on the join column Sort Merge Join is advantageous when processing a wide range of data as it mainly reads data using the scan method, unlike NL Join: However','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(969,'356','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','performance deteriorates if all sorting operations cannot be performed in the memory due to there being too many data to be sorted.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(970,'357','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Hash Join performs a join operation using the hashing technique: The hash function is executed using the join column of the table to perform a join operation: The join operation is performed while checking whether the data with the same hash value actually have the same value: Hash Join was introduced as an alterative for solving the random- access problem of NL Join and sorting the workload of Sort Merge Join','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(971,'87','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','A data manipulation language is used to input,, modify, delete, and search data in a database This section introduces the data manipulation language by subdividing it into basic operations, aggregate operations, and advanced operations join','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:45','2025-04-18 20:11:45'),(972,'24','App\\Models\\Module','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b21573f23.png','/storage/code/6802b21573f23.png','2025-04-18 20:11:46','2025-04-18 20:12:05'),(973,'24','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:46','2025-04-18 20:11:46'),(974,'24','App\\Models\\Module','Text','SQL is the most important and powerful tool in a relational database: It is not an exaggeration to say that the strengths of the relational database are being increasingly highlighted thanks to the strong function of SQL, which prevents the relational database from being changed to the object-oriented DBMS or another DBMS easily: Prior to the introduction of SQL, the procedural programming language had to be used for simple data processing only by writing a programming code: Since the introduction of SQL, however the productivity of database programming has improved significantly, because the DBMS manages everything when the desired data are specified long',