 which guarantees the physical data independence of the database and finds the method of executing the users SQL queries efficiently, is making a significant contribution to the commercial success of the relational database path path get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1000,'271','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 47  Roles of the optimizer in each query processing phase',NULL,'6802b21601ee1.png','/storage/tables/6802b21601ee1.png','2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1001,'271','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 34] Five phases of handling RDBMS queries',NULL,'6802b2160f754.png','/storage/figures/6802b2160f754.png','2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1002,'271','App\\Models\\Section','Text','processing is divided into 5 phases parsing, query rewriting, query optimization, QEP generation, &nd query execution The optimizer acts in the query rewriting and query optimization phase: QEP (Query Execution Plan) refers to a query execution plan, which is the detailed information necessary to execute a query: Query','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1003,'366','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The rule-based optimizer sets the optimal based on the according to the index structure or comparison operator It enables the user to accurately predict the because the optimizers decision is very regular and clear However, it has the limitation that a serious judgment error may occur in terms of execution performance because the realistic factor (statistical information) is not considered. path ranking path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1004,'367','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The cost-based optimizer calculates the cost of each processing method and selects the method that costs the least Even though there is the advantage of guaranteeing minimum performance without having to have a deep understanding of the optimizer through optimization control based on statistical information management and decision-making in consideration of reality, it has a limitation in that a execution plan cannot be forecast ad controlled easily:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1005,'91','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Query optimization refers to the process of making a DBMS select one optimal strategy by systematically evaluating several strategies for executing query statements It is used by systems that support advanced relational query languages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1006,'368','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Tne GI executapie Tlle metnoa executes tne aatapase appilcation program as acol (Common Gateway interrace) executable file. The CGI directly accesses the DBMS to retrieve data. One application process is created for each request. This method has the advantage that the structure is simple, and the method can be implemented most programming languages In addition, users can select one of the connection methods provided by various database vendors, and it is very convenient because the user only has to modify the CGI program when expanding the system: However, this method has the disadvantages that the cost of content replacement increases exponentially when using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1007,'368','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','the web client makes requests frequently or when the application program to link with the web is and that performance deteriorates significantly when there are too many connections large,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1008,'369','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The CGI application server method separates and executes the application program accessing the database a5 daemon and transfers the user\'s requests by application processor: The CGI module is composed of a small executable file and transfers the request received from the web server to the application server only: The application process includes the fork, pre-fork, and multithread methods. In particular, the multithread method has the advantage of a fast response speed by system resources most efficiently: The CGI application server method has the advantage of easy with middleware such as CORBA and TP Monitor, while reducing the size of the process and keeping the existing system intact, but it also has the limitation of being difficult to implement using linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1009,'370','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When the extended API method is used, a database application program is executed as a process by linking it with the web server As the web server provides APIs with extended functions, it solves the problem of the existing CGI method wherein a new process should be created each time & request is received. Microsofts ISAPI,, Netscape\'s NSAPI, and Oracles Web Request Broker (WRB) belong to this method. The extended API method has the advantage of more system resources reducing more system load, and providing faster speed than the CGI method, because the routine created with the extended API of the web server is used a5 part of the server program: However this method has the problem that it is difficult to create a routine using an extended API and becomes dependent on a specific web server or browser saving','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1010,'371','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The servlet method is similar to the extended API method but is platform independent JDBC (Java DataBase Connectivity) or another database access class is used to connect a database: The servlet method has attracted the attention of many Java developers because it provides continuous processing and a fast response speed Java\'s multi-thread features using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1011,'273','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The server extension method is also called a stateless method. A database is connected through the web server, and connection is established each time a request is made These methods include the CGI executable file method, CGI application server method, extended API method, and servlet method','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1012,'372','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A method of directly connecting a database server from a Java applet or ActiveX control. Specifically, some methods use Java solutions such as JDBC and JavaBeans When this method is used, the limitations of the web that occur when with mission-critical systems can be overcome by connecting a database server continuously: JDBC is an API for the programming language Java, which is designed to implement an independent Java application program: JDBC uses an integrated SQL server, and another database can be connected without modifying the source by replacing the driver or a module that can be linked to it only: linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1013,'373','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ADO, a Microsoft solution, is an ActiveX control that provides a database interface and manages connection with database in the Inter or clientlserver environment','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1014,'374','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Although OLE DB provides access to all types of data including relational data (ISAM, VSAM, Excel Data, etc) using a consistent API, it is limited to MS operating systems only:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1015,'274','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The browser extension method processes data while maintaining the connection by directly connecting a database from a browser It is also called the direct (state) method. JDBC, ADO (ActiveX Data Object), and OLE DB belong to this method.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1016,'92','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Web browser components and a gateway that connects the DBMS are required to link the web and database Depending on the method of implementing the gateway, the methods of linking the web and database are dividec into server extension methods and browser extension methods,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:47','2025-04-18 20:11:47'),(1017,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1018,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Most of the databases we experience in the field are running in a multi-user environment:  Therefore, the atomicity of transactions should be guaranteed by controlling interactions among transactions when multiple transactions are executed in a database simultaneously: To this end, concurrency control methods are used Most of the DBMSs we use have these methods Therefore, if transactions are wrongly designed due to a lack of understanding of the concurrency control technique, such as the locking mechanism to the DBMS, problems may occur due to a transaction such as processing performance degradation, deadlock and so on And users who are accustomed to the fast processing of information systems may raise complaints about the service delay: The recent DBMS has several adivanced features such as a function that internally ensures the isolation of transactions and considers concurrent processing performance or the inclusion of an algorithm that detects and handles deadlocks quickly: However, those features are minimal and provisional measures, not a fundamental solution: Therefore, the concepts of transaction, concurrency control, and deadlock need to be clearly understood in order to develop a system that delivers high performance in a multi-user environment applied delay,','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1019,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1020,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the concept and characteristics of a transaction 2 To be able to explain the transaction-commit operation and the rollback operation for aborting transaction 3 To be able to explain the purposes, necessity, and techniques of concurrency control. 4 To be able to explain 2-phase locking (2-PL): 5. To be able to explain and apply a transaction isolation level.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1021,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1022,'25','App\\Models\\Module','Text','T Gnoaclio ACID properties: Atomicity consistency, isolation, durability Commit operation rollback operation Lost update, dirty read, unrepeatable read, inconsistency cascade rollback Serializable schedule Concurrency control techniques lock-based technique, optimistic or validation-based technique, timestamp-based technique, multi-version technique Transaction isolation level: Read uncommitted, read committed, repeatable read, serialization Causes of deadlock occurrence: Mutual exclusion, block & wait, non-preemption, circular wait Solutions for breaking deadlock, deadlock avoidance, deadlock prevention, deadlock detection & recovery','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1023,'275','App\\Models\\Section','Text','roblems that arise when a transaction and ncurrency control are not properly understood','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1024,'275','App\\Models\\Section','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1025,'275','App\\Models\\Section','Text','There are some cases in which a set of operations executed in a database is viewed is viewed as a unit from the viewpoint of the database user For example, transferring money from account A to account B may look like a single operation at first glance. However, the transaction is internally composed of two update operations, ie changing the balance of account A and changing that of account B, respectively: What if this operation fails in the middle of processing, and the balance of account A has been changed while that of account B remains unchanged? If any operation fails, all operations relating to the account transfer task should be either performed normally as whole or returned to the original state prior to the operations. As explained previously, a set of operations that constitute a logical work unit is called a \'transaction\". The important here is that all operations of the transaction should be completely executed or returned to the original state before any transaction if an error occurs. What if the of the data shared between transactions cannot be controlled in a database system that executes several transactions simultaneously? For example, what happens if you transfer KRW 1,000 online from an account with a balance of KRW 1,000 and withdraw KRW 1,000 from a ATM at the same time? In reality, it is naturally impossible, because the database system controls these transactions As explained so far the database system provides a concurrency control method to secure the isolation of a transaction, which ensures that the transaction is not affected by the change made by another transaction at the same time. However if the level of transaction isolation is high, simultaneous access to the database (concurrency) becomes difficult and performance is negatively affected. Therefore, the isolation level should be selected appropriately by considering the nature of the transaction In fact, service failure occurs frequently in the field due to the problem with concurrency control including the case of the college course registration crisis that occurred due to the application of the isolation level of the banking system, which requires strict transaction isolation, to the course registration system: Therefore, the concept of transaction and concurrency control should be correctly understood to determine the \"appropriate\" level of the to be developed and transaction isolation thing update college system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1026,'375','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A transaction is a set of several operations constituting a logical task unit, which converts a consistent state of the database to another consistent state. A transaction is also a unit of performing a series of read and write operations in a database, which should be nerformed At the came time atabase to another consistent state','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1027,'376','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 42] Conceptual diagram of a transaction',NULL,'6802b2161bbe6.png','/storage/figures/6802b2161bbe6.png','2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1028,'376','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','performed at the same time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1029,'277','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 48  Transaction properties',NULL,'6802b21632d05.png','/storage/tables/6802b21632d05.png','2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1030,'377','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','all SQL statements in the transaction to the database','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1031,'378','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','saction rollback operation: An operation that restores all data values that have been moditied by a transactior 0 the state to executing the transaction (that is, aborting the transaction), when the transaction canno prior','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1032,'378','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','continue due to a fatal error in the middle of the transaction or because the user issues a rollback command.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:48','2025-04-18 20:11:48'),(1033,'278','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ation: An operation that completes a transaction after permanently ref