ck occurrence conditions within a system (Deadlock occur',NULL,'6802b2169bfee.png','/storage/tables/6802b2169bfee.png','2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1056,'289','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 53  Solutions to deadlock',NULL,'6802b216ad590.png','/storage/tables/6802b216ad590.png','2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1057,'289','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b216bd78c.png','/storage/tables/6802b216bd78c.png','2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1058,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1059,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Text','A database has the property that once it has been built, it should process actual business data stably However, data can be corrupted due to a certain problem when are digitalized and saved: In this case it is vital to have a technology that can restore the database This chapter explains how to process database stably and the concept and techniques of backing up and restoring data The recent DBMS essentially operates database backup policies for stable data processing: In addition backup methods are also evolving continuously to enable backup, such as the VTL (Virtual Library). they stably: rapid Tape using','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1060,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1061,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Text','To be able to the concept and types of database failures. To be able to explain the concept and methods of database recovery: To be able to explain how to recover a distributed database To be able to explain and apply the types and characteristics of database backup methods explain','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1062,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1063,'26','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Database failure: Transaction failure, media failure, system failure Recovery, redundancy, redo undo, log Database recovery techniques: Log-based recovery technique (deferred immediate update) , checkpoint recovery technique, shadow paging recovery technique 2-Phase commit protocol Database backup methods: Full backup, differential backup, incremental backup, archive log backup, hot backun cold backun update,','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1064,'290','App\\Models\\Section','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1065,'290','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It has been reported that IT-related losses accounted for 16% (approximately USD 7 billion) of the total financial losses sustained the 09.11 WTC attack in New York, even though there were also numerous casualties Some enterprises suffered serious damages due to the loss of data and subsequently experienced difficulty resuming their online work because it took a couple of to recover the lost data. As such, if the duplicated data and archives of a business system are not available, damages can be caused not only by simple system shutdown but also by the loss of the most important information essential to the survival of the company in an instant In fact, the incident served as a timely reminder for all enterprises of the overriding importance of database backup ad recovery, and led many enterprises to adopt disaster recovery system, which is a non-disruptive recovery system. Although may not be the result of a terrorist attack as in the above example, failures frequently occur in the field, which cannot ensure transaction atomicity and durability due to various reasons such as hardware failure broken hard drive) , power outage, DBMS software defects, and s0 forth: Therefore, all database systems need a method of maintaining the atomicity ad persistence of transactions The recovery techniques used to restore a system to its previous state after the occurrence of a database failure (consistent state) should ensure high availability so that service downtime caused by the failure of the datahace canhe minimized during days ` they (e.g:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:49','2025-04-18 20:11:49'),(1066,'291','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Data recovery refers to the restoration f the consistency and integrity of a database before the occurrence of an unexpected (database) failure while operating the database','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1067,'292','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 54  Types of database failures',NULL,'6802b216d0902.png','/storage/tables/6802b216d0902.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1068,'387','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','and store a database to another storage device Copy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1069,'388','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','al: Record the old values and new values of changing data each time a database is changed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1070,'390','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','f the contents of the database itself are damaged, the most recent copy is loaded, and any changes made af making the copy are read the log and executed again so that the contents of the database can be restored: This corresponds to the completed transaction at the time of failure occurrence Changed values are stored in a disk (forward recovery) by executing the write operation from again','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1071,'391','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If contents that are being changed or have been changed cannot be trusted even though the contents of the database itself have not been damaged, the database is restored to its original state by cancelling all changes This corresponds to the transaction in progress at the time of failure occurrence (incomplete transaction): Previous values are restored by cancelling the write operation (backward recovery):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1072,'295','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 55  Comparison of database recovery techniques',NULL,'6802b216e7e22.png','/storage/tables/6802b216e7e22.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:06'),(1073,'295','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 46] Types of database recovery techniques',NULL,'6802b2170413d.png','/storage/figures/6802b2170413d.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1074,'392','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This transaction accesses more than two databases, ad each DBMS can use different recovery techniques and transaction managers The atomicity of transactions is an important issue when building multiple database systems. If a certain transaction is executed across two sites and the transaction is not professionally designed, an inconsistent state can be caused when one site completes the transaction while the other site cancels the transaction The 2-phase commit protocol should be used to maintain the atomicity of multiple database transactions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1075,'392','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Either all participating databases should complete the transaction, or none of them should complete it Even though a failure occurs in any participating database, recovery to the transaction completion state or cancellation state is possible.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1076,'393','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'<Table 56  Execution of the 2-phase commit protocol',NULL,'6802b21712775.png','/storage/figures/6802b21712775.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1077,'393','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','nis is the transaction completion protocol that is most widely used to maintain the atomicity of transactions in stributed database.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1078,'393','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Step 1: When a transaction is started by transaction coordinator C, coordinator C sends a message whether the transaction can be completed to databases A and B, and database A and B reply with the \"ready\" status. 2: If all participating databases are \"ready\" , the coordinator sends a \"completion (commit)\" signal If one or more participating databases signals a \'not ready (abort)\" signal, the coordinator sends a \"cancellation (abort)\" signal. asking Step','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1079,'394','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The task of storing all or a part of a database in duplicate in order to recover the database in the event of a failure In general, the database is backed up every week, or month in units of incremental, differential, or full:. day,`','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1080,'395','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Prevent data loss: Recovers a database using duplicated data in the event of a failure. Secure business continuity: Minimizes business disruption caused by IT failure while processing business','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:11:50'),(1081,'396','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 57  Requirements by item',NULL,'6802b21724e09.png','/storage/tables/6802b21724e09.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1082,'397','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 58  Contents of backup management',NULL,'6802b2173f1ff.png','/storage/tables/6802b2173f1ff.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1083,'299','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 59  Types and characteristics of database methods',NULL,'6802b21752610.png','/storage/tables/6802b21752610.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1084,'299','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b21772169.png','/storage/tables/6802b21772169.png','2025-04-18 20:11:50','2025-