days','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:11:51'),(1093,'301','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A data warehouse is an integrated system or database that enables the user to instantly analyze internal data and external data generated by the operation system of a enterprise over time, without the need for separate programming multiple points of view, by integrating data by subject: from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:11:51'),(1094,'302','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 60  Characteristics of the data warehouse',NULL,'6802b21794761.png','/storage/tables/6802b21794761.png','2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1095,'302','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Inlike the data repository of OLTP for OLTP systems, the data warehouse generally has the following characteristics','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:11:51'),(1096,'303','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 61  Components of data warehouse modeling',NULL,'6802b217a653f.png','/storage/tables/6802b217a653f.png','2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1097,'303','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b217b2ef8.png','/storage/tables/6802b217b2ef8.png','2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1098,'303','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Unlike general ER modeling for OLTP systems, data warehouse modeling refers to a data modeling technique that,, from data analysis perspective, enables users to analyze large-scale data from various viewpoints Data are generally organized into fact tables and dimension tables so that end users or analysts can easily analyze information. The table below shows the main components of data warehouse modeling:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:11:51'),(1099,'304','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 62  Data warehouse techniques',NULL,'6802b217ceaf7.png','/storage/tables/6802b217ceaf7.png','2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1100,'304','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802b217e9588.png','/storage/tables/6802b217e9588.png','2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:12:07'),(1101,'304','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A data warehouse model organizes data using fact tables and dimension tables to facilitate the analysis information The technique can be divided into the \'star schema\' and the \'snowflake\' depending on the dimension table normalization status','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:51','2025-04-18 20:11:51'),(1102,'105','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'<Table 63  Work of each phase in ETL',NULL,'6802b2180d289.png','/storage/tables/6802b2180d289.png','2025-04-18 20:11:52','2025-04-18 20:12:08'),(1103,'105','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','ETL refers to the entire process by which data are extracted from the source system and stored in the data warehouse after cleansing ad conversion It plays the role of maintaining data consistency and integrity among the components of the data warehouse, and is also called ETT (Extraction Transformation, Transportation).','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:52','2025-04-18 20:11:52'),(1104,'305','App\\Models\\Section','Text','OLAP refers to the process by which the end user accesses multi-dimensional information without an intermediary or medium, and then analyzes the information interactively and uses it for decision making That is, when the operational data extracted and converted by ETL are stored in the data warehouse or data mart, the end user analyzes them using OLAP','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:52','2025-04-18 20:11:52'),(1105,'306','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 64  Main OLP search techniques',NULL,'6802b21823e20.png','/storage/tables/6802b21823e20.png','2025-04-18 20:11:52','2025-04-18 20:12:08'),(1106,'306','App\\Models\\Section','Text','OLAP provides various search techniques that allow end users to analyze data from diverse perspectives an summary levels The table below shows the main search techniques of OLAP','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 20:11:52','