12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1184,'416','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An information is a that uses information technology (IT): The information system provides services a computer, and a computer operates with combination of hardware and software. Implementing an information system used inside an enterprise, or provided as a service to users, requires the design and construction of IT infrastructures, such as hardware and software design and development, Software designs the software components and operations, such as the connection of the software components and constraints based on software architecture Hardware, like software, designs and develops the hardware architecture System architecture refers to the architecture for a to provide services, based on hardware and software architecture In a broader definition, it refers to all architecture, including the application architecture (AA), data architecture (DA), and technical architecture (TA), for constructing an information system A narrow definition refers to the document that defines the configuration and relationship of hardware, such as a server, storage, network and security, and certain software parts, such as OS and middleware system system using system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1185,'417','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c041300b9.png','/storage/tables/6802c041300b9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1186,'417','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 1] Definition of System Architecture',NULL,'6802c0414ac37.png','/storage/figures/6802c0414ac37.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1187,'417','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Definition as defined by the International Council on Systems Engineering (INCOSE) The fundamental and unifying system structure defined in terms of system elements, interfaces, processes, constraints, and behaviors.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1188,'417','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DIUau uemii itui ui syslemii aiciilecluie A system architecture is a document that defines the structure of an information system provided to support the business process required to achieve the objective of an enterprise. A system architecture is divided into TA which defines the structure of hardware, such as a server, network, ad security, as well as the distributed structure of middleware operating on the hardware, DA, which defines the data structure to assure data integrity, and AA, which defines the software components and the relationship and constraints of said defined components Narrow detinition of system architecture A system architecture refers to the structure of an information system, which includes principles and guidelines that define the components, such as hardware, software, security, interactions, and constraints. In other words, it refers to TA and defines the layout and connection mode of the middleware, such as the DB server and WAS, to distribute the application programs of the developed and hardware, such as a server, storage, and network The following table shows the types of detailed architecture defined in system architecture system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1189,'418','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 2] Information System Components',NULL,'6802c04168e93.png','/storage/figures/6802c04168e93.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1190,'418','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 3] Storage Type According to Connection Method',NULL,'6802c04186541.png','/storage/figures/6802c04186541.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1191,'418','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','System components are a configuration of items to provide the functions of information system services include a server that provides the computing power of an information system, storage that stores the data, a network that provides communication between each component, such as a server and storage, and security to provide confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the information system: The detailed components include computer hardware, OS, and middleware operating on physical server The following diagram shows the details of each component They A server provides the computing power of an information system. The information system uses this computing power to process the business logic and data by running the application programs. Server components include the stacked structures of the computer\'s hardware, OS, middleware, and application programs.  The system architecture design defines the server capacity, count, layout, and role, and the network facilitates communication between the servers. Mainframes, Unix servers, and x86 servers are the most commonly used server types, and the x86 servers using Intel CPUs have been used more often as the cloud services expand For example, the servers of an information system providing web services include a webserver that responds to user requests through a web browser organizes web pages, ad provides a screen to display the contents to users, web application server (WAS) that processes business logic, according to the user request ad delivers the results to a database server for storage, or to a WAS for display, ad a database server that creates, requests, modifies, and deletes data. A network connects the information system components for communication Network devices process communication between servers, between servers and storage units ad between the enterprise\'s internal and','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1192,'418','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','external networks. A networks devices ad roles vary, based on the OSI layer 7 standard. Network devices include switches, routers, load balancers (L4/L7 load balancers) , and bridges. Additionally, AP (access point) is used in wireless networks There is an overlap between the network domain and the security domain: Since most of the hacking attacks intrude through the network the internal network (LAN) connected to the external network (WAN) , is protected by a security device. gate, A storage system holds the data of an information system. It is categorized into three types according to how it stores data. Block storage saves data in fixed block units, like 16KB and 64KB. It stores the OS, such as MS Windows, Linux, and Unix File storage saves data in file units, instead of in fixed blocks. Network attached storage (NAS), widely used as the shared file repository, is a type of file storage Object storage saves data in object units, instead of in fixed blocks or files. It is mostly used in cloud storage Storage types can also be categorized by their connection method. Direct access storage (DAS) is mounted in each server, NAS is connected through a network and storage area network (SAN) is connected through the network used exclusively for storage DAS can only be used with a filesystem and includes IDE, SATA, and SAS. SAN is provided to the OS through an SAN network ad it requires the creation of a filesystem before it can be used as DAS. It includes SAN, iSCSI, and FCoE. NAS becomes usable after it is mounted to the OS.It includes NFS, CIFS, and AFS.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1193,'418','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Occunily Information security is configured through the network connection. Some security hardware is installed between the external Internet section and the internal network to protect the internal systems while some are installed in the internal network It includes the DDoS defense system to defend against DDoS attacks, firewalls to protect the system through monitoring logging, ad blocking network traffic, and IPSJIDS to prevent abnormal traffic or abuse. It also includes web firewalls protect webservers by logging, monitoring, blocking web service traffic, and access control solutions to provide management functions that allow or to deny access to servers','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1194,'332','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Various ways of configuring a system are provided. System configuration is changing in various ways, according to the changes in hardware ad software technology, &d the changes to the user environment: As the use of mobile devices, such as smartphones, has recently increased, most systems provide services based on the system architecture centered around a web service: Moreover, the system layout is also changing into a centralized structure, as the cloud services have expanded','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1195,'419','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 4] Centralized Architecture',NULL,'6802c0419d3e9.png','/storage/figures/6802c0419d3e9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1196,'419','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 5] Multi-region Distributed System Architecture',NULL,'6802c041c9541.png','/storage/figures/6802c041c9541.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1197,'419','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A centralized architecture stores and operates the system ad data from an integrated center It configures an integrated database on a large-capacity server and it has a relatively simple configuration. Having an integrated database makes it easy to assure data integrity, and having all components in one place makes them convenient to manage and operate. It can also quickly respond to system failures. However all business services are terminated if the integrated center fails. Moreover, the load is concentrated during time system peak','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1198,'419','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Multi-region distributed system architecture The multi-region distributed architecture operates the systems, and the application systems are distributed regionally: Each region manages the distributed data using small or medium-sized servers. This structure can reduce the load of each server, since it distributes the user load. When there is a failure, only the regional business services','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1199,'419','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','are terminated. However the distributed databases make it difficult to manage the data integrity, and both the svstem configuration and management become complex','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1200,'333','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Architecture types can be classified according to the information system layout The centralized architecture arranges all the systems in a centralized place. Multi-region distributed architecture operates the system by distributing regional and application systems regionally:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1201,'420','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 6] Client-Server Architecture',NULL,'6802c041de2a8.png','/storage/figures/6802c041de2a8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:33'),(1202,'420','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 7] Web System Architecture',NULL,'6802c0420143d.png','/storage/figures/6802c0420143d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1203,'420','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The architecture places system functions in the servers and clients ad configures them to use the service, depending on the business size or environment: The server and client\'s role differs, depending on where the system functions, such as data management, business processes, and presentation, are located. It can provide the convenience of a graphical user interface by running the application program from the client side: However, the configuration is complex ad the development and management are difficult because the architecture is separated into servers and clients Service types include games chatting, messenger FTP servers, and terminal servers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1204,'420','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','WVCd syslemn aici iecluie The architecture runs the server s application programs, and the client uses the service with a web browser: It generally consists of a webserver, a web application server, and a database server The middleware assures stable performance,, and the program reusability is high. Although the web system architecture was limited by only providing web services with a static display, the introduction of HTML5, and the performance enhancement of PC environments, have enabled them to provide services in an impressive GUI environment: Most recent information systems use web system architecture The client can use all the services with a PC or mobile device, if the environment runs a web browser','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1205,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0422a8f1.png','/storage/tables/6802c0422a8f1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1206,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 8] Types of Information System Architectures Tier',NULL,'6802c0424cec0.png','/storage/figures/6802c0424cec0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1207,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The function and role of each system component are classified by tier or layer The most widely known layer is the OSI 7 \'layer which shows the network structure: Layers and tiers are considered similar concepts because they both represent functions and rules in a tiered structure. The most common difference is that layers refer to structures from a logical point of view, and tiers refer to structures from a physical perspective An information system is divided into a presentation layer, a business logic layer, and a data layer This logical layer architecture can be divided into an N-tier structure as a physical system architecture The typical N-tier structures are a two-tier structure and a three- tior ctri','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1208,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Text','WO-ter arcnitecture Two-tier architecture stores and processes data in the server and processes business logic and presentation for the Two-tier architecture stores and processes data in the server and processes business logic and presentation for the','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1209,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Text','client It is generally the same structure as the client-server architecture Since the client processes most logic, it can be fast ad easily implemented when the number of users is small However, the performance becomes poor as the number of users increases, and the architecture is disadvantageous in terms of scalability, reusability, and resource use. Actual cases include application implemented with 4GL tools, such as PowerBuilder Visual Basic, and Delphi:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1210,'335','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ee-lel aiclileclule Three-tier architecture is a structure created to overcome the limitations of two-tier architecture, and it is also called multi-tier architecture This structure has an additional tier between the presentation tier and the data tier, in order to process business logic to be flexible ad scalable The problems of two-tier structures include security problems due to the clients\' ability to access the database through the network, the difficulty of user authority management, and the difficulty of changing programs: In three-tier architecture, the client does not have database access information. It is easy to manage the database object reference authority through the application server The distribution of the separate presentation tier becomes flexible: However, the development environment is complex, and the cost increases because of the need to procure middleware and additional hardware','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1211,'336','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 9] Information System Server\'s Stack Structure',NULL,'6802c04264cc2.png','/storage/figures/6802c04264cc2.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1212,'336','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Server\" refers to a computer or program that provides information or services to users through a network It provides the computer power needed for the information system services. The concept of the server was created when IBM started making a server called the mainframe: The term mainframe refers to a steel enclosure, like a cabinet, large','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1213,'336','App\\Models\\Section','Text','that houses the CPU ad the main memory: The mainframe features excellent stability and performance, but it is very expensive because a enterprise made all the elements from the CPU to OS, the development language, and the application programs. The mainframe began downsizing gradually in 1997 when the attention to super Unix servers, such as HP, Sun, and Silicon Graphics, increased. Downsizing refers to replacing a mainframe server with a super Unix server While Unix servers were generally equipped with a Power CPU, it is worth noting that more mid- to large-sized servers began featuring Pentium CPU in the server market in 1997. It was around this time that Windows NT servers, using Intel CPU, were on the sharp rise: Twenty years later, in 2017,x86 servers, featuring Intel CPU, are dominating the Unix server market  Currently, the server market is divided into x86 servers ad non-x86 servers Although the market is divided into two major server types in terms of sales,x86 servers account for more than 70% when comparing the number of server units sold. This server has a stack structure The computer hardware, consisting of a CPU, main memory, and auxiliary memory is at the bottom An OS that abstracts computer hardware and provides services to software is located above it On top of the OS, middleware, such as a webserver, WAS, and DBMS server to support the flexibility of convenient expansion, as well as the reduction of application programs ad independence of computer hardware, is located. Application programs provide services to users this middleware using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1214,'337','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c042774e9.png','/storage/tables/6802c042774e9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1215,'337','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 10] ENIAC, the First Electronic Vacuum Tube Computer',NULL,'6802c042a05fb.png','/storage/figures/6802c042a05fb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1216,'337','App\\Models\\Section','Text','While some argue that an abacus used in calculations in ancient times is the origin of computers, the Machine, devised by the English mathematician Allen Turing in 1936, is generally regarded as the beginning of modern computers  This Machine proved the mathematical concepts and calculation processes. Afterward, ENIAC, created in 1946, is known as the first programmable general-purpose computer Using 18,000 vacuum tubes, it weighed 30 tons and was literally as large as a house. Later, EDSAC, the first computer that embedded the program Turing Turing in a memory unit, as proposed by John von Neumann, was developed in 1949. While computers were mostly usec for military purposes in the past,, the popularization of computers began in the 1980s when a PC, developed by IBM_ and the Windows operating system, developed by MS, were successful: In recent years, mobile computers installed smartphones have become popular and opened the era of handheld computers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:07','2025-04-18 21:12:07'),(1217,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1218,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Text','In network technology have evolved from data communication, through existing S6kbps wired media, to wireless networks and mobile communication of hundreds of Mbps and even Gbps. Moreover, the advent of various connected terminals has led people to in an inseparable relationship with communication in their daily lives, as well as in more diverse business areas Accordingly, software used in a terminal or system has close relationship with a network, and it is based on mutual communication It is necessary to understand and utilize the standard protocols used by networks to design and develop organic and optimized software,, based on this network concept','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1219,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1220,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the concept of the Internet and the open protocol: 2 To be able to explain how the OS manages processes. 3 To be able to explain the concept of virtual memory and management techniques 4 To be able to explain the storage unit, file systems, and input/output (O): 5. To be able to explain the latest OS technologies and trends.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1221,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1222,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Protocol, Internet, IETF, 3GPP, 3GPP2, ITU-T, OSI reference model, Application layer, Presentation layer, Session layer, Transport layer, Network Datalink layer Physical layer, Internet protocol layer Application layer, Internet layer, Network interface layer, Internet address scheme, MAC address, IP address, Port number, IPv4 address, IPv6 address, Private network, NAT, CIDR, RFC layer,','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1223,'31','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1224,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'(Table 1) Web Use Scenario by User A',NULL,'6802c042c809f.png','/storage/tables/6802c042c809f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1225,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c042efd94.png','/storage/tables/6802c042efd94.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:34'),(1226,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 10] Network between Users and Servers',NULL,'6802c04315b1b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04315b1b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1227,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'Figure 11] Web Use by User A',NULL,'6802c04325e4b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04325e4b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1228,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','[Figure 10] shows a virtual network connection in a situation where user A connects to a webserver (my servercom) and uses a computer to locate the data. Although the situation frequently occurs inhomes schools, or workplaces, many people use their computer network information without knowing it  The following examnle shows a situation of usino a network senvice in detail','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1229,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','[Figure 11] shows user a connecting to a webserver (myservercom) and searching for the data. <Table 1  describes, in detail, which changes occur in the network at each stage of the operation in [Figure 11]. The standard protocol used at stage is described in parentheses, and its concept ad detailed operation are described in the following chapters. This example shows how a simple network service, as shown in [Figure 11], is executed. each Network operation procedure to \"OHomepage request\" 1) User A enters Ilmy servercom/ on the web browser and presses the Enter key http:/ Step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1230,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Step 2) The web browser intends to send User A\'s request to the webserver, my servercom, but cannot do it because my servercom is an arbitrary domain name for users to recognize easily. The web browser requests the IP address of my.server.com to the domain name server to solve the nroblem (DNS) 3) On receiving the IP address of myservercom, 220.17.23.15, from the DNS, the web browser connects to the webserver using the address and requests data in the document route TTP) Step 3-1 The web browser hands over the requested information to the TCP protoc to request myservercom: The information is properly capsulized and delivere to the webserver program of myservercom (TCP): Step Step 3-2 Information created by the TCP protocol is capsulized to be routed to th 220.17.23.0 network in which my servercom is present, through several hoops\' 3-3 An initial packet that contains the information for routing between networks is created. However, it must be further modified to be transferred between networks. The IPv4 address of user A\'s computer is 192.168.11.5 and cannot be transmitted to myservercom directly: It must be transmitted to the computers gateway wiredjwireless router B (192.168.11.1). However, an IP address cannot be used for data transfer within a network so the MAC address is needed for this. After finding the MAC address corresponding to 192.168.11.1, the gateways IP address, through network broadcasting, the packet is transmitted to wired/ wirolocc routor R (ADD Fthornot nrileto notwiorv andMA Step','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1231,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Step 3-4) On receiving the packet - user A\'s computer, wiredjireless router B, aware that the packet is not sent to the router as the final destination, examines the address to which the packet must be transmitted. The IP header indicates that the packet\'s final destination is myservercom, and since it does not belong to network 192.168.11.0 or 14.32.172.0, to which wiredjwireless router B belongs it transmits the packet to router C, to which it belongs (routing protocol) from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1232,'118','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Step 3-5) On receiving the packet, router C recognizes that the packet is sent to network 220.17.23.0,to which the router belongs, and intends to transmit it to the webserver\'s IP address 220.17.23.15. As in Step 3.3, since the packet movement in a network requires the physical address of my servercom, the MAC address, it obtains the MAC address corresponding to the IP address of myservercom, 220.17.23.15, though the network broadcasting, and 3-6) On receiving the packet, my servercom examines the IP address and recognizes that the packet was sent to it: It removes the header data, such as the IP address, and sends the remaining data up to the higher protocol layer (IP). Step Step 3-7) It determines which application of my servercom to which the packet should be transmitted, removes unneeded data, and sends the remaining data to the intended webserver application (TCP). 3-8) The webserver application recognizes that the message is requesting information in the document route, and it sends the information to user A\'s computer Step Step _ On receiving information in the document route from the webserver, the web browser displays the contents for user A\'s viewing: The user can select the desired hyperlink in the document to view, including videos on a web browser (HTTP HTML):','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1233,'119','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 12] Virtual Network Reflecting Protocol Layer Concept',NULL,'6802c0433a15d.png','/storage/figures/6802c0433a15d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1234,'119','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','<Table 1  above showed many standard protocols, such as ARP, IP, TCP, HTTP, DNS, and NAT. A protocol is a standardized communication rule for sending ad receiving data through a network: The Internet,, as we know, is large group of networks that connect multiple PCs and servers. For tens or hundreds of thousands of PCs, servers, and routers that connect them to exchange data, it is necessary to have a common protocol that can be found by each other, and there are several interational organizations that standardize these protocols IETF (Internet Engineering Task Force) is responsible for most Internet-related standard protocols. 3GPP (Third Generation Partnership Project) and 3GPP2 are responsible for wireless communication protocols such as GSM, CDMA, UMTS, LTE, and LTE-A ITU-T (International Telecommunication Union Telecommunication Standardization Sector) is responsible for protocols related to telephones. Therefore, it is necessary to have the competitiveness to understand and implement (if necessary) the standard protocols enacted by these standardization organizations to develop software in the network/communication sector [Figure 12] below shows the details of [Figure 11] by reflecting the network protocol concepts described above When a user searches through a web browser, data requests and response data flow in the network through devices, such as the users computer, a wiredjireless router, a switching hub, and a router, the related protocols. While the physical layer is directly connected with hardware, such as wires and switches, and operates with electric signals, the protocol layer above the data link layer is implemented and operated in software Understanding how many software components are connected to each other for operation should enable application programs or system software over a network Later sections describe in detail how each protocol layer shown in [Figure 12] works with the others in each stage using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1235,'421','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Application programs, such as web (HTTP) , DNS, telnet, FTP, and email sendinglreceiving (SMTPIPOPBJIMAP4) , allow access to services on other layers In the OSI reference model, this layer\'s concept includes the presentation layer and the session layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1236,'422','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the host-to-host transport layer the transport layer is responsible for data exchange between abstract ports, managed by application programs such as TCP, UDP and SCTP protocols It is equivalent to the transport layer in the OSI reference layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1237,'423','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the network layer, it is responsible for addressing ad routing functions. It is equivalent to the network layer in the OSI reference layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1238,'424','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 14] TCPIIP Protocol Layers: Based on the ARPANET Reference Model [10]',NULL,'6802c0434f43b.png','/storage/figures/6802c0434f43b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1239,'424','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 15] Example of Network Protocol Header and Data Configuration',NULL,'6802c0435f0f9.png','/storage/figures/6802c0435f0f9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1240,'424','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Also called the network access layer, the network interface layer has the role of actually sending and receiving TCPIIF packets through physical media, such as IEEE 802.3 and IEEE 802.11 WiFi. It includes the data link layer responsible fo the MAC function in the OSI reference model, as well as the physical layer that defines electric signals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1241,'424','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 13], these protocols specify communication with the same protocol layers of other hosts connected through a network For communication, a header for the exchanging of data between protocols of the same layer with data downloaded the layer immediately above are generally required. As shown in [Figure 15], an application layer can transmit the user data through a transport protocol TCP (or UDP), which is an end-to-end protocol connected to the other host: It requires a TCP header (or UDP header): The transmission of user data, including a TCP header, uses IP which is a network layer protocol that has routing information to the network of the other host, and the IP head has the information The network considers both the TCP header and the user data received from the transport layer as data. The data link protocol, which has the necessary information for physical delivery to other hosts in the same network mostly uses Ethemet: In that case, both the TCP header ad the user data, including the Etheret header with the necessary information and the IP header downloaded from the network layer, are regarded as data. It should be noted that laver uces Onlv the header that correcnonds to the oiven fiinction from layer each','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1242,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'(Table 2) Protocol and Function of Each Layer of the OSI Reference Model',NULL,'6802c04372a88.png','/storage/tables/6802c04372a88.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1243,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04381e3f.png','/storage/tables/6802c04381e3f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1244,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 13] Communication Concept of OSI Reference Model Containing Relay Open System',NULL,'6802c0438e50c.png','/storage/figures/6802c0438e50c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1245,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','[Figure 13] shows the concept of the OSI reference model communication, which includes the open relay system described in the standard document ISOJIEC 7498-1:1994E) [8]. The diagram is often used when discussing ISOs OSI reference model, or OSI layer, which is commonly referred to when dealing with networks Here, ISO is derived from the Greek word \"iooG (isos) , meaning \"identical , and should not be confused with the English name of the Interational Organization for Standardization (IOS). OSl is an abbreviation of Open Systems Interconnection','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1246,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','<Table 2  shows in detail the protocol and its function of each OSl reference model layer [1].','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1247,'120','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','As shown in [Figure 5], the Interet protocol layer is based on the ARPANET reference model, which was released before the OSI layer model [3J[9][IO] While documents use slightly different terms for each layer, this section uses the most commonly used terms:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1248,'425','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IP address: The IP address is the address system of the network layer to transfer datagram between two hosts/ routers It facilitates data to be transferred from the source node to the destination node, through multiple Internet networks While the MAC address is a physical address, the IP address is a logical address. Existing IP addresses, or','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:08','2025-04-18 21:12:08'),(1249,'426','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Pv4 addresses based on the 32-bit address system, faced exhaustion as Internet use increased rapidly worldwide Ilthough the IPv6 address system based on 128 bits was introduced to solve the problem, IPv4 addresses are nainly used Although the IANA (Internet Assigned Numbers Authority) was responsible for IP address allocation in the ast, the ICANN (International Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers) is currently in charge still','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:09'),(1250,'427','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Port number: The port number used to transfer messages between two processes (running applications) is responsible for the connection between the web browser on user As computer, shown in [Figure 10], and the webserver program on my.servercom: The 16-bit number system can identify up to 65,535 application programs. The port numbers from 0 to 1023 are called well-known ports and are allocated by the IANA Application programs, such as telnet and email, use it for sending and receiving data: The port numbers 1024 to 49,151 are called registration and, like well- known ports, are mostly used by servers. The Internet chatting protocol, IRC (TCP port number 6667), and Git version control system (TCP port number 9418) are examples The port numbers from 49,152 to 65,535 are mostly used as a temporary number by clients, and are called dynamic ports or temporary ports. from ports','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:09'),(1251,'121','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Internet users come across many terms related to numbers, such a5 a MAC address, an IP address, and a port number It is unnecessary to memorize these numbers, but understanding the numbers helps figure out each layer protocol. The MAC address, IP address, and port number in the Interet address system have the following meanings: MAC address: The MAC (medium access control) address, or the address system used by the data link layer, is used to transfer frames between the physically connected nodes. The information is generally stored on the LAN expansion card hardware, called NIC. It is also called the physical address or Ethernet hardware address (EHA) It is formed by48 bits. The first 24 bits represent the hardware manufacturer\'s unique ID, and the remaining 24 bits represent the NIC-','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:09'),(1252,'122','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'(Table 3) Internet Standardization Organizations',NULL,'6802c043a3ced.png','/storage/tables/6802c043a3ced.png','2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1253,'122','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The IETF (Intemet Engineering Task Force) is a leading organization responsible for Internet-related standards. defines the basic protocols for Internet transmissions, such as IP, TCP, and UDP, as well as the most widely used protocols in the Internet application layer protocols, such as HTTP, SSH, FTP, SMTP, POP3, and IMAP <Table 3  lists other international organizations responsible for Internet-related standardization.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:09'),(1254,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:09','2025-04-18 21:12:09'),(1255,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Merely ten years ago, nobody could have imagined web surfing, shopping, or watching movies in bed The introduction of the smartphone made these things possible, as it was a computer for your hand A smartphone is also a computer system that runs on the OS. Most mobile operating systems have recently disappeared, and iOS ad Android have become the two dominant operating systems on the market These two operating systems are in a heated battle for the diversity of functions and user-friendliness Apple and Google, who provide these two operating systems, are two global enterprises among the top ten global companies in market value. In the past, when smartphones were unknown, Microsoft, who provided operating systems for personal computers, and IBM who provided operating systems for servers, such as mainframes and UNIX, were in the top ten companies in the world in terms of market value. The operating system (OS) is the base platform of a computer system for providing information services company that can monopolize this platform can tremendous added value this platform. As such, the essential knowledge for understanding the system architecture, is the operating system. Any gain using','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1256,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1257,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the concept and role of the OS. 2 To be able to explain how the OS manages processes 3 To be able to explain the concept of virtual memory and management technique: 4 To be able to explain the storage unit, file system and input/output (O). 5. To be able to explain the latest OS technoloqies and trends','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1258,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1259,'32','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Flynn\'s taxonomy, parallel processing technology, parallel program technology, disk scheduling, SAN, NAS, DAS, LTO, VTL, RAID, GPGPU, video compression standards','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1260,'123','App\\Models\\Lesson','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1261,'123','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','As of 2016, Korea s computer user rate was 85.7%, meaning that more than 8 out of 10 people were using computers During the same period, the smartphone user rate grew much faster than PCs, reaching 88.5%. With the rapid proliferation of mobile devices, the PC user rate is gradually decreasing, ad the us of laptopswhich have gradually replaced desktops, have also continued to decline after exceeding 30% for the first time in 2014. Smartphones and tablet PCs are increasingly taking over the place of computers. Electronic devices, such as desktops, laptops, and smartphones, are collectively referred to as \"computers\" and have things that are commonly applied to them: contain indispensable software, an operating system (OS) , and major hardware: Having the best processor and components is useless without an OS. The OS is a medium that delivers close to 100% of the outstanding performance of a manufacturers computer to users they They The elements, such as the CPU, mainboard, memory, graphics card, and storage device, that make up a computer cannot do anything by themselves Users can work done with a word processor and can enjoy playing World of Warcraft, only when the OS gives the commands of what to do to each piece of hardware The operating system, which is software, is responsible for the device operation from start to finish It is the OSs role from the moment it recognizes the power supply, until it shuts off the power on command Without an OS, the user must manually turn the power on or off in an analog way, like the older products. Commands for device operation are mechanical, and the device can only perform one function with &n input. In todays electronic devices, which have been mostly converted to operate electronically, the volume and power buttons remain manual get','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1262,'340','App\\Models\\Section','Text','S is a system software that provides a computer resource interface to users or application programs by efficiently nanaging the limited resources of computer hardware \"he first computers were set to operate single-purpose programs, as did not have an OS. The programs they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1263,'340','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ran slowly and were difficult to develop in this torm, since the developer needed to implement every intertace tor accessing the computers resources and allocating and recovering resources: OS implements input, control, memory, operation, and output functions to provide services in order to use computer resources efficiently: In other words, an OS controls the computers resources ad implements usage policies to allocate resources to users through scheduling: It exchanges data through inputfoutput devices, or outputs exceptions or errors. The purposes of using the operating system are as follows Abstraction: Provides standardized API to application programs by abstracting the complexity of the computers hardware. Virtualization: Provides a virtualization function to enable application programs and users to share computer resources, and to use a single virtual computer hardware Management: Maximizes computer resource performances and provides them to application programs, while','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1264,'429','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In simple terms, a process is a running program: However it is actually more than just a program, as a process is & system work unit that allocates, uses, and recovers various resources, such as the CPU, storage unit, and input/ output units to perform its tasks An OS manages processes and performs the following tasks: Creating and disposing of user and svstem processes files, In Simpie lerms, & process IS & runniing progrram, hiowevel, Il IS aclually More lan just & PIe system work unit that allocates, uses, and recovers various resources, such as the CPU, stora output units to perform its tasks An OS manages processes and performs the following task Creating and disposing of user and system processes Terminating and re-running processes Providing a technique for process communication and synchronization Providing techniaues to prevent deadlock','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1265,'430','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A hard disk (HDD) is the hardware that most people think of when consider a storage unit. However the main memory is a different type of storage. The main memory is a depository that allows the CPU to fetch commands and data to use the instructions, The addresses that the CPU uses to access data are only available in the main memory: Even if the CPU intends to retrieve data in an HDD, it cannot read the data if it is not stored in the main memory The main memory must handle the following management functions to provide data to the CPU: Tracking and managing the space and the users that use the storage device they from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1266,'431','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS can store data through various physical devices. It is necessary to abstract media with different physical characteristics such as magnetic tape, magnetic disks optical disks, and flash memory, for the OS to use them: File management provides the function of abstracting these physical characteristics into files, the logical storage units It handles the following tasks:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1267,'431','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Creating and disposing of files Creating and disposing of the directory Providing primitive files and directory management Mapping for the OS to use the file in the auxiliary memory unit Storing the file in a nonvolatile storage medium','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1268,'432','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The OS helps users use a device, even if do not know its characteristics Here, a device refers to an input/output device and includes a mouse, keyboard, printer, and speaker Users can easily use these devices with the functions provided by the OS. they \'','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1269,'433','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The volume of data used by a computer system is growing larger, from gigabytes and even to terabytes However the data used by a computer\'s CPU is that which is in the main memory unit: The main memory does not provide the capacity at the terabyte level. The OS hands the following auxiliary memory unit management function to store the managed data: Empty space management The volume of data used by a comput the data used by a computer\'s CPU is capacity at the terabyte level. The OS managed data: Empty space management Storage allocation Disk scheduling','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1270,'434','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','distributed system is a set of memory units or separate processors Each processor communicates at a high spee rough the network The network integrates scattered computer resources into a system to improve the calculatic eed, share data, and to enhance reliability:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1271,'435','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','command-interpreter is one of the programs that enables users to access the main OS function MS-DOS of UNIX shell, a user can enter a command with a keyboard in order to run an OS function system system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1272,'341','App\\Models\\Section','Text','OS abstracts and virtualizes computer hardware to provide resources to application programs, or to manage ther efficiently: Therefore, OS can be understood by the functions of managing main hardware components. The mair functions of OS are described as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1273,'342','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 4} Types of Main OS',NULL,'6802c043ba696.png','/storage/tables/6802c043ba696.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1274,'342','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c043cce78.png','/storage/tables/6802c043cce78.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1275,'436','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 16] Process Status Change',NULL,'6802c043dafd1.png','/storage/figures/6802c043dafd1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1276,'436','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A process has a distinct process status during its lifecycle, as shown in [Figure 16]','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1277,'436','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Created: A process is created but is not running by the OS. Preparing: The process is waiting for the CPU allocation to run:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1278,'439','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Kunning: ine process nas tne CPU allocaion: Finished: The process has completed its running, and the CPU allocation is released Standby: The process ran after getting the CPU allocation, and is waiting for an event, such as the completion of input or output.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1279,'442','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PCB stores information necessary for process management. A unique PCB is generated when a process is createc and the PCB is removed from the process completion A PCB includes a process identification number (PIC) , a proces status, program counter (the value that indicates the instruction to run next) , a scheduling priority, registere information, and main memory unit information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1280,'343','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Early computer systems could only execute one application program at a time. In other words, one program occupied all the system\'s resources. However modern computer systems run multiple programs concurrently: The OS must manage computer resources so that multiple programs share resources and operate in stable condition at the same time: A process refers to a running program, and in todays concurrent multi-process environment, it is a work unit of a time-sharing system.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1281,'443','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c043ecad5.png','/storage/figures/6802c043ecad5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:35'),(1282,'443','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 17] Process Tree Structure in the UNIX OS (Example)',NULL,'6802c04405093.png','/storage/code/6802c04405093.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1283,'443','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Processes must be able to run in parallel, and also be created and removed dynamically: A process can create other new processes through the \"fork()\" system call while it runs. The process that creates other processes is called a parent process, and a newly created process is called a child process. A child process can create another child process, and this relationship is formed in a tree structure, as shown in [Figure 17].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1284,'444','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 18] Process Creation and Termination in the UNIX OS',NULL,'6802c04410e69.png','/storage/figures/6802c04410e69.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1285,'444','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','After completing the last code of the program, the process requests the to delete the process with the \"exit()\" system call, as shown in [Figure 18]. At that point, the child process returs data to the parent process with the \'wait()\" system call, and the OS recollects all the resources allocated to the deleted process OS','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1286,'445','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 19] Relationship between Thread and Process',NULL,'6802c0441e1dc.png','/storage/figures/6802c0441e1dc.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1287,'445','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A thread is a basic unit for using a CPU and is all called a lightweight process As shown in [Figure 19], a proces generally has one or more threads. A thread shares the memory unit, such as codes, data, and files, and create its own register and stack While processes use more CPU time than threads for context exchange, threads ca exchange context more economically because threads share the memory unit','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1288,'446','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 20] Single Thread and Multi-thread',NULL,'6802c0442a765.png','/storage/figures/6802c0442a765.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1289,'446','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 20], a single-thread process is a case in which a thread exists for a process, and a process, having multiple threads, is called a multi-threaded process A thread operates with the status of \"ready\" , \'blocked\" , \"running\" , and \"terminated\". A CPU can occupy only one thread at a time: In other words, only one thread runs at a time, and the status of the other threads is \"blocked \" When a thread is blocked, other threads can run There are certain benefits to using multi-threads','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1290,'446','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The memory occupied by a process can be shared, and another thread can access the same memory addres multi-thread system: The cost of thread creation and context exchange is more economical than the process Threads increase the parallel attributes of the process and enable the utilization of multiprocessors.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1291,'346','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A race condition refers to two or more parallel processes simultaneously accessing and changing the same dat or the order of manipulating the data affecting the execution result: In a race condition, only one process must protected to manipulate data, and process synchronization is necessary for its protection','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1292,'347','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'[Figure 21] Critical Section Structure in a Process Code',NULL,'6802c04435e99.png','/storage/code/6802c04435e99.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1293,'347','App\\Models\\Section','Text','For process synchronization, each process defines a critical section in a part of the code and performs the task of changing the data that is shared with other critical section processes. Two or more processes that are mutually exclusive cannot run in the critical section at the same time. [Figure 21] shows the structure of the critical and remainder sections.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1294,'347','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The critical area problem is to establish rules so that the processes cooperate with each other Each process must request permission to enter, even if it enters its critical section The part of the code that implements such a request is called the entry section The exit section is after the critical section, and the rest of the code is collectively called the remainder section, Solving the critical section problem requires satisfying the following conditions: Mutual exclusion: If a process runs in its critical section, the other processes cannot run their own critical section Progress: Only processes that are not running in the remainder section can enter a critical section without a running process Bounded waiting: After a process makes a request to enter its critical section, the time allowed for other processes to enter the critical section should be limited until the process enters the critical section','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1295,'348','App\\Models\\Section','Text','One of the ways to solve the critical section problem is to configure the synchronization hardware, not to allow the interruption of generation while the shared data in the critical section is changed. However, the hardware method is not feasible, since it deteriorates the system efficiency in a multiprocessor environment Another way is to use a semaphore, which is a synchronization tool. The semaphore, \'S\', is an integer variable, and only the P operation (wait) and V operation (signal) are enabled  If one process modifies the semaphore value, the other processes cannot modify the same semaphore value at the same time. It works by setting the semaphore value to \"wait\" when a process enters the critical section and changing the value to \"signal\" when the process exits the critical section: Another process checks the semaphore value and does not enter the critical section if the value isin the \"wait\" state, preventing multiple processes from simultaneously accessing the shared data being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1296,'349','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 5} Conditions Causing Deadlock',NULL,'6802c04444e85.png','/storage/tables/6802c04444e85.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1297,'349','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 6) Ways to Solve Deadlock State',NULL,'6802c04452c42.png','/storage/tables/6802c04452c42.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1298,'349','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In a multi-, programming environment, the processes compete with each other to use limited resources. When process requests a resource, it obtains a \"standby\" status if the resource is not available There may be a case Wher the status of a process in \"standby\" is never changed because the requested resource is allocated to other standby processes. This state is called the deadlock The deadlocked processes cannot finish the running program, and the system cannot start other tasks because the resource is tied to other processes <Table 5  shows the conditions that can cause deadlock include mutuz exclusion, hold & wait, non-preemption, and circular wait The deadlock occurs when these four conditions are met They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1299,'349','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 6  shows how to solve the deadlock state','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1300,'350','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A CPU uses scheduling to improve the utilization rate as if multiple programs share it at the same time A CPU can only execute the instruction and read data when are stored in the memory: Therefore, multiple processes must be stored in a memory unit for them to run. Virtual memory is the technique of running processes, even if are not present in the memory unit: This technique allows a user program that is larger than the physical memory unit to run: This section describes various techniques for managing the storage unit: they they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1301,'447','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 7) Techniques of Allocating Memory Unit',NULL,'6802c044655e4.png','/storage/tables/6802c044655e4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1302,'447','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is the technique of searching for the best way to allocate processes to the available main memory area when process requests the memory unit for a new use. As shown in <Table 7  , the first-fit, best-fit, and worst-fit are the generally used techniques for selecting the available areas a set of available areas. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1303,'448','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 22] Case f External Fragmentation',NULL,'6802c044756d9.png','/storage/figures/6802c044756d9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1304,'448','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 23] Case of Internal Fragmentation',NULL,'6802c04485d8c.png','/storage/figures/6802c04485d8c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1305,'448','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Memory space is allocated when the memory is requested and recollected after use. Repetition of the allocation and','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1306,'448','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','recollection can result in memory space that is wasted without being used   Using the first-fit, best-fit, and worst- fit techniques to allocate the memory unit can cause external fragmentation, as shown in [Figure 22]. Let us assume that a process requests 64,450 bytes when there are 64,500 bytes of available space In that case, 50 bytes of available space remains after allocating the requested space: If the memory is partitioned into a fixed size to provide multiple fixed-sized available spaces to processes, it may be slightly larger than the required space The remaining space is called the internal fragmentation as shown in [Figure 231.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1307,'449','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 24] Solving Fragmentation Problem through Compaction Technique',NULL,'6802c04494a7d.png','/storage/figures/6802c04494a7d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1308,'449','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 25] Solving Fragmentation Problem through Coalescing Technique',NULL,'6802c044a145e.png','/storage/figures/6802c044a145e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1309,'449','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','compaction lecitique The compaction technique merges small-sized available memory: It is used to remove the exteral fragmentation that generated in a variable-size memory partition system, as shown in [Figure 24]. The technique is not used because it is complex to implement,, and it causes overload as it requires a time widely long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1310,'449','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The coalescing technique merges spaces with adjacent addresses in the unused empty space list in order to create a larger space and to prevent multiple small spaces, as shown in [Figure 25].','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1311,'352','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Faimess to processes Maximizing throughput per unit time Minimizing response time Predictable execution time Preventing system overload Balanced resource utilization Preventing indefinite process execution Implementing priority schemes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:10'),(1312,'353','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Type 8) Types and Characteristics of Scheduling Algorithms',NULL,'6802c044b9637.png','/storage/tables/6802c044b9637.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1313,'353','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c044cde10.png','/storage/tables/6802c044cde10.png','2025-04-18 21:12:10','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1314,'353','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 8  shows the types and characteristics of scheduling algorithms Preemptive scheduling: A process can take CPU resources while another process is occupying them Non-preemptive scheduling: If a CPU resource is allocated to a process, it cannot be allocated to another process until the task has been completed.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1315,'128','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','supporting multiple programming uses scheduling to allocate processes to the CPU efficiently','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1316,'354','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 26] Comparison of Paging and Segmentation Memory Allocations',NULL,'6802c044de8ee.png','/storage/figures/6802c044de8ee.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1317,'354','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A virtual memory unit includes the virtual address that processes refer to and the physical address that points to the available main memory: Whenever a process accesses a virtual address, the system must quickly convert it into the physical address through the memory management unit (MMU) It is divided into a paging technique and segmentation technique, according to the block configuration Some systems may use a combination of both techniques (see [Figure 26]). Paging technique: This technique partitions the main memory unit into fixed sizes, called frames, and also partitions the task to the process stored in the virtual memory unit into fixed sizes, called pages, and loads them into the frame to run the task Segmentation technique: This technique partitions the task to the process stored in the virtual memory unit into size segments, which are logical units of various sizes, and then loads them into the main memory unit to run:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1318,'355','App\\Models\\Section','Text','f all pages are filled in the paging virtual memory unit, free space must be created before loading new memory page from the auxiliary memory unit The system selects a page to replace the page replacement technique, affecting th svstem efficiencv and performance Optimal technique: This technique replaces a page that is not Iikely to be used for the longest time. Although it is the optimal replacement technique wth the minimum absent page rate, it is not a realistic technique, since it is difficult to predict behavior First In First Out (FIFO) technique: This technique tracks the order of loading in the main memory and replaces the first loaded page Least Recently Used (LRU) technique: This technique replaces the page that has been unused for the longest time: Least Frequently Used (LFU) technique: This technique tracks each page s utilization frequency and replaces the least used or least intensively used page Not Used Recently (NUR) technique: This technique uses the tendency that the page not used recently is less likely to be used in the near future, so it replaces the page','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1319,'356','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Locality: A tendency to intensively reter to only some pages while & process IS running: It IS divided into temporal locality and spatial locality: Working Set: A set of frequently referred to page lists for a certain period to execute a process efficiently It reduces page absence and page replacement by placing the frequently referred to working sets in the main memory: Thrashing: A phenomenon in which the CPU utilization rate decreases because page replacement takes longer than the processing time The degree of multi-programming is reduced, the CPU utilization rate is increased, or a working set is used to prevent thrashing:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1320,'129','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The technique to solve the OSs limited memory space problem uses the main memory with a small capacity, as a large capacity with a large amount of free space. The virtual memory unit is not a physical device, but it logically uses a large-capacity auxiliary memory device as the main memory device: Therefore, it is necessary to map the address of the virtual memory unit to the address of the main memory unit in order to execute a program stored in the virtual memory unit:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1321,'450','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a set of data with & name and stored in an auxiliary memory unit, such as a disk or tape The OS maps files to physical devices. In other words, when the OS writes a program or data to a file, it is permanently stored in a nonvolatile physical device','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1322,'451','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Files have several properties to enable the ability to identify and manage them. The most common is the file name, which is expressed as a single string: A process or user can independently create and access files the file name attribute The types of file attributes are described as follows: Name: Should be maintained in a legible form by users. Location: Points to the device and location of the file and includes the directory Size: Includes the current file size (in bytes, words, or blocks) and the maximum allowable size Protection: Controls who can read, write, or run the file Time, date, and user identification: Include the data related to the creation time, recent information, and recent usage using path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1323,'357','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A file system stores related data to find and access the OS data and programs quickly: It is a directory structure tha provides information on an aggregation of files and all files in the system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1324,'358','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A directory is a logical structure to manage tens of thousands of files managed by a file system, and can be the t size of gigabytes or terabytes It records the information about all files The following actions are performed directory: File search: A user can search a file from the directory structure File creation: A new file is created and added to the directory: File delete: Unneeded files are removed the file Directory list: Lists files in a directory and shows the directory item: from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1325,'358','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Renaming file: A file name must be changeable, and a renamed file should exist at a within the directory structure point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1326,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 27] Contiguous Allocation',NULL,'6802c044ec924.png','/storage/figures/6802c044ec924.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:36'),(1327,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 28] Linked Allocation',NULL,'6802c045054a0.png','/storage/figures/6802c045054a0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1328,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 29] Indexed Allocation',NULL,'6802c04512bbb.png','/storage/figures/6802c04512bbb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1329,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Text','file system should consider which space on the disk to use and quickly access the files. An OSs file generally uses the contiguous allocation, linked allocation, or indexed allocation. syster TC \'yslcmmi |iiuulu cun Siuci Wi CI space Un LC UiSn LU USC aru yuickiy GCCC)) CIIC TC). An U5) iC PyslC generally uses the contiguous allocation, linked allocation, or indexed allocation. Contiguous allocation: This method arranges files as a set of contiguous addresses on the physical disk, as shown in [Figure 27] below: disk addresses of stored files are defined linearly This method has the advantage of a relatively high reading spee since the files are stored in contiguous addresses However, it creates an external fragmentation problem','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1330,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This method stores files in block units and links each block to a list, as shown in [Figure 28] below The directory keeps pointers to the first and last blocks of the files As shown in the figure, the directory contains 9 and 25,which are the first and last block pointers, respectively: Block 9 is linked to blocks 16, 1, .9, 10, and 25 in that order This method can solve the external fragmentation problem of the contiguous allocation method. However, the linked allocation method is slow to read ad requires the area to store the pointers separately, since data blocks are scattered on the physical disk Moreover it can cause data errors if the linked pointer data is lost or corrupt','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1331,'359','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Utocu The linked allocation cannot support direct access and is difficult to manage the loss, since the block pointer addresses are scattered throughout the disk The indexed allocation solves the problem by managing all pointer data of a file in a index block, as shown in [Figure 29]. The indexed allocation does not create external fragmentation and supports the direct addresses. However, the waste of storage space is larger than the linked allocation method,','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1332,'360','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0451fcdc.png','/storage/tables/6802c0451fcdc.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1333,'361','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0452ce5e.png','/storage/tables/6802c0452ce5e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1334,'361','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0453a8c8.png','/storage/figures/6802c0453a8c8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1335,'361','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In a UNIX system, i-node has the role of allocation, application, creation, link, and deleting through the file/directory data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1336,'131','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The input/output system includes an input/output device and the system s input/output module (controller): A physical inputloutput device handles the inputs and outputs of data and between the actual processor and the computer user, ad the input/output module provides the functions of input/output device control,, timing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1337,'131','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','coordination, communication with the processor communication with inputloutput devices, data buffering, and error detection, so the process can easily control multiple input/output devices','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:11','2025-04-18 21:12:11'),(1338,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1339,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Text','In computer engineering, computer architecture is a conceptual design and the operational structure that is the basis for computer systems It is a blueprint that functionally describes the design portability and requirements (especially speed and interconnection) of various parts of a computer It mainly focuses on how the central processing unit (CPU) performs and accesses memory addresses internally: Modern computer structures are based on the Von Neumann architecture, and the basic instruction processing structure has not changed much Though parallel processing and other technologies have improved in their performance, only recently have new concepts, such as neuromorphic and quantum computers, been introduced chips','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1340,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1341,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able t0 explain the computer structure and the operational principle 2 To be able to explain the memory hierarchy and operational principle. 3. To be able to explain the latest computer structure technologies and trends:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1342,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1343,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Von Neumann architecture, Harvard architecture, CPU, Memory unit, Input/Output device, CISS, RISC, Neuromorphic chip, quantum computer','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1344,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1345,'33','App\\Models\\Module','Text','John Doe, who works for company A is a software engineer with four years of development experience. Java is the programming language he generally uses, but he was recently given a task that required him to program using C Since the Java language managed memory in a runtime environment, called the Java Virtual Machine (JVM), it was not necessary to pay much attention to memory programming When developing with the C language, he had to learn the concept of memory, such as memory allocation and return: Most importantly, he had to learn the memory address system through pointers. He had to be familiar with computer structure to be able to develop software in  effectively: This chapter describes the omnutor ctructure in detail during','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1346,'362','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 30] Computer Structure',NULL,'6802c04545149.png','/storage/figures/6802c04545149.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1347,'362','App\\Models\\Section','Text','he basic function of a computer is to run a program code in the specified sequence. In other words, it reads, rocesses, and stores the needed data: [Figure 30] shows the main components of a computer Central Processing Unit (CPU): Also, commonly known as a processor, it plays a role of the program running and data nrocecsino key aala processing: Memory: Main memory: Closely located to the CPU, it consists of memory semiconductor chips. It can be accessed at a high speed and can be used only as temporary storage because it has no permanent storage capabilities Auxiliary storage device: The secondary storage device can be accessed at a low because it includes mechanical devices. It has a high storage density, and it is moderately priced. Disks and magnetic tapes are some examples speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1348,'362','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IO device: consists of an input device and an output device to be used as the tool for interaction between the users and computers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1349,'363','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 31] Von Neumann Architecture and Harvard Architecture',NULL,'6802c045513fe.png','/storage/figures/6802c045513fe.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1350,'363','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 32] Computer Structure Applying Both Architectures',NULL,'6802c0456034b.png','/storage/figures/6802c0456034b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1351,'363','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The types of computer architecture include the von Neumann architecture, which is a structure that applies the stored-program design principle\' suggested by von Neumann in 1945,and the Harvard architecturewhich separates instruction memory and data memory: As shown in [Figure 31], these two types have different memory structures, and each has advantages and disadvantages Von Neumann architecture: The CPU can read commands from the memory and can read and write data both from the memory and to the memory: Instructions and data cannot be accessed simultaneously because use the same signal bus and memory: Harvard architecture: It solves computer bottlenecks by storing commands and data in different memories and improves performance by reading and writing commands in parallel However, the bus system design becomes complex they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1352,'363','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1 A memory unit is attached next to the CPU, and programs ad data stored in the memory unit are sequentially fetched and processed according to the execution instructions.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1353,'363','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since the von Neumann &nd Harvard architectures each has advantages ad disadvantages, the most recent high- performance CPUs apply both architectures in their design. In other words, separate the cache memory for instruction and data, and apply the Harvard architecture inside the CPU (CPU and cache) and the von Neumann architecture outside CPU (CPU and memory), as shown in [Figure 32] they they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1354,'364','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The CPU is the most important part of computers, as it interprets instructions and handles arithmetic or logica operations and data processing It plays the key role of running programs and processing data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1355,'365','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 9) CPU Execution',NULL,'6802c045741aa.png','/storage/tables/6802c045741aa.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1356,'365','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in <Table 9  , the CPU operation is divided into a function that commonly runs for all instructions, and function that runs only when necessary, according to the instructions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1357,'452','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','(instructions) and run them y element of the CPU to execute arithmetic operations? and logical operations','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1358,'453','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Register: A temporary storage area that temporarily stores instructions waiting to be processed by the CPU or the intermediate result values of the CPU operation. The register types include, PC (program counter) , IR (instruction register), AC (accumulator), MAR (memory address register), MBR (memory buffer register) , and SP (stack pointer): Bus: A common transmission line that connects the CPU, memory, IO unit, etc, in order to exchange necessary data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1359,'454','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 33] CPU Structure',NULL,'6802c04581ee1.png','/storage/figures/6802c04581ee1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1360,'454','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Duoco Cc Cicooiicc 0o TOo 0 Address bus: A set of signal lines that transmits address data generated by the CPU. Data bus: A set of signal lines that transmits data from the CPU to a memory unit or an IO unit. Control bus: A set of signal lines that are necessary for the CPU to control various elements. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1361,'366','App\\Models\\Section','Text','shown in [Figure 33], a CPU consists of a control unit, an arithmetic logic unit (ALU), registers, and buses that','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1362,'366','App\\Models\\Section','Text','connect them in order to deliver the data. trol unit: A hardware module that sequentially generates control signals to interpret the program codes ructions) and run them','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1363,'367','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 10} Relationship between Instruction Cycle Types and CPU Components',NULL,'6802c04591c66.png','/storage/tables/6802c04591c66.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1364,'367','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 34] Instruction Cycle Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c045a1bd5.png','/storage/figures/6802c045a1bd5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1365,'367','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This is the entire process required for the CPU to execute a instruction: The CPU repeats it from the moment the CPU starts executing the program, until the power is turned off or a irrecoverable error occurs to terminate the execution The instruction cycle from the fetching of the instruction to the completion of the operation consists of a fetch cycle, an indirect an execution and an interrupt cycle, as shown in [Figure 34]. cycle, cycle, 2 Arithmetic operation: Addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division 3 Logic operation: AND, OR, NOT, XOR, etc [able 10  shows the entire instruction cycle. The CPU components needed in each cycle are different','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1366,'368','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 11) Comparison of CISC and RISC',NULL,'6802c045b5082.png','/storage/tables/6802c045b5082.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1367,'368','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Instruction set, or instruction set architecture (ISA), refers to the machine language instructions that a microprocessor can recognize, understand its function, and execute The ISA is part of the programming-related computer architecture, and it includes data types, instructions, registers, addressing modes, memory structures interruptions exception handling, ad external inputloutput The ISAs are the complex instruction set computer (CISC) and the Reduced instruction set computer (RISC): <Table 4  shows the concepts and differences in these structures. CISC:A complex instruction-type computer that embeds many complex instructions into the hardware in order to process the complex instructions as a single instruction: RISC: A reduced instruction-type computer that embeds a few simple instructions into the hardware to process complex instructions as a set of simple instructions leading','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1368,'369','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 35] Memory Unit s Hierarchical Structure',NULL,'6802c045c577a.png','/storage/figures/6802c045c577a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1369,'369','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 35], the memory unit at a higher level has a higher price per bit, less capacity, a shorter acce: time, ad a higher access frequency by the CPU:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1370,'370','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Capacity Access time Cycle time Bandwidth of storage unit Data transportation Cost','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1371,'371','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 12) Types of Memory Units',NULL,'6802c045df0f0.png','/storage/tables/6802c045df0f0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1372,'371','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Memory units can be classified according to the use, physical storing method, data retention, and content preservation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1373,'372','App\\Models\\Section','Text','address is the location in the main memory where data is stored. Various addressing methods are available tc signate instructions, using limited instruction bits and using the memory unit capacity efficiently An address is the location in the main memory Where data is stored. Various addressing methods are available to designate instructions, using limited instruction bits and using the memory unit capacity efficiently: Direct addressing mode Indirect addressing mode Implied addressing mode','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1374,'372','App\\Models\\Section','Text','MCuialC auuiessinismiuuc Displacement addressing mode: Relative addressing mode, indexed addressing mode, and base-register addressing mode','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1375,'373','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The locality is a tendency in which programs intensively refer to a area in the moment, rather than uniformly accessing information in the memory device Temporal locality: Recently accessed programs or data are more likely to be accessed in the near future. Spatial locality: Data stored adjacent to the storage device is more likely to be accessed continuously: Sequential locality: Instructions are fetched and executed in the order in which were stored, unless branched (about 20%) specific again they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1376,'374','App\\Models\\Section','Text','device is necessary to perform an input operation that stores data to be processed by the CPU in the memory t, as well as an output operation that transfers the processing results from the main memory to a output medium:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1377,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 36] IO Controller Structure',NULL,'6802c045f2bbd.png','/storage/figures/6802c045f2bbd.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:37'),(1378,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 37] Allocation of Memory Mapped I/O Address',NULL,'6802c04609a1f.png','/storage/figures/6802c04609a1f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1379,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 38] Address Allocation by IJO Mapped IO',NULL,'6802c04613adf.png','/storage/figures/6802c04613adf.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1380,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Text','AnIO controller is necessary to process inputs and outputs, as shown in [Figure 36], and it plays the following roles: VO device control and coordination Communication with the CPU Communication with the IJO device 0 9 ffo timing Gn','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1381,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Each device needs two addresses (a status/control register address and a data register address) for IO control, anc the same two addresses are required for each device. It is divided into the memory mapped IJO and the IJO mapped O,depending on how the addresses are allocated. Memory mapped IO: It is a method of allocating a part of the address area in the memory to the register addresses in the I/O controller, as shown in [Figure 37]. It has the advantage of easy programming, but the disadvantage 0= reducing the available memory space','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1382,'375','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IO mapped I/O: It is a method of allocating the I/0 device address space separately from the memory address space, as shown in [Figure 38]. It has the advantage of not reducing the available memory address space, but the disadvantage of making it difficult to program','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1383,'455','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 39] System Structure Including DMA',NULL,'6802c04624458.png','/storage/figures/6802c04624458.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1384,'455','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DMA is a method of the IO device directly accessing the memory without the assistance of the CPU. The DMA controller controls the bus, and the IO device and memory transfer information directly: [Figure 39] shows the system structure that includes the DMA controller:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1385,'455','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With DMA high-speed IJO devices can increase system efficiency by minimizing the interruption overhead that reduces the CPU\'s actual processing time:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1386,'456','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IO interface requests a DMA service from the DMA controller: The bus request is transferred to the CPUs HOLD pin,, so that the DMA acquires the control of the bus (Active High): The bus grant is retured the CPUs HLDA (Hold Acknowledge) pin, to the DMAC (Active High): The DMAC loads the contents of the address register into the address bus. The DMAC transfers the DMA acknowledgment to the IJO interface in order to load the data into the data bus. The address bus transfers the data bytes to the identified memory location The IO interface maintains the data transfer (Latch): The DMAC returns the bus grant as the bus request is dropped, and the HOLD becomes a low state The bus grant is dropped, and HLDA becomes a low state. Afterward, the address register increases by increments pf 1, and the byte count decreases by decrements of 1. The process returns to if the byte count is not 0, and otherwise stops. from Step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:12'),(1387,'457','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c046353b3.png','/storage/tables/6802c046353b3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:12','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1388,'377','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c046447c1.png','/storage/figures/6802c046447c1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1389,'377','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Neuromorphic chip, a core technology for neuromorphic computing, is a new semiconductor type that processes information in a way that is similar to human thinking, by implementing brain behavior in silicon as much as possible There are several cores in a semiconductor chip, and electronic devices, such as transistors ad memory, are embedded into the core Some of the devices in the core play the role of neurons and neural cells in the brain, and the memory chip plays synaptic function that links neurons. Since the core, which acts as an artificial neuron,, is configured in parallel like the human brain, it can process a large amount of data with little power and increase the ability to lear and operate like the human brain.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1390,'378','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 40] Comparison of Conventional Semiconductor and Neuromorphic Chip',NULL,'6802c04653a5a.png','/storage/tables/6802c04653a5a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1391,'378','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Neuromorphic computers do not only operate in a preprogrammed way, like conventional semiconductor-based computers, but can develop their processing power by detecting the surrounding context and learning autonomously: Since devices equipped with the neuromorphic chip can increase learning, operation capability, and power efficiency, can apply intelligence to all computing, ranging from loT, smartphones, robots, automobiles, cloud computing, and supercomputing: However, there is still a lack of understanding of how human neural circuits process data at the level, and neuromorphic computers still remain at a level that simulates single neurons There are many problems to resolve they they system','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1392,'378','App\\Models\\Section','Text','from the technical aspect in order for them to have the same level of complex and highly integrated structure as the human brain. Research on neuromorphic processors with various materials and structures is ongoing worldwide, but there is no clear leading group with clear superior competitiveness','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1393,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 13) Comparison of Conventional and Quantum Computers',NULL,'6802c0466cc6f.png','/storage/tables/6802c0466cc6f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1394,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 14) Types of Quantum Computer and Comparison',NULL,'6802c04681794.png','/storage/tables/6802c04681794.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1395,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0468d802.png','/storage/tables/6802c0468d802.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1396,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c046ab4e4.png','/storage/tables/6802c046ab4e4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1397,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A quantum computer is a new conceptual computer that can simultaneously process a large volume of information at a high speed, based on the principle of ultra-high-speed, large-capacity computing technology optimized for specific operations, according to the principle of overlapping and entanglement inherent in quantum mechanics Quantum parallel processing, which uses quantum bits (qubits) as a basic unit of information processing, exponentially increases information processing and computation speed. <Table 13  shows the difference conventional omnuter structures from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1398,'379','App\\Models\\Section','Text','quantum computer can be an analog or digital type  <Table 14  shows the characteristics of each type','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1399,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1400,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Technologies that have recently become issues in system architecture are cloud computing, Al, and big data: The learning subject related to these is data processing technology: The subject closely related to Al is the parallel processing system: The subject related to big data is storage technology: The subjects related to cloud computing are storage, high availability storage devices, and graphics','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:13','2025-04-18 21:12:13'),(1401,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objective','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1402,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the parallel processing technology and operational principle 2 To be able to explain Ihe storage technology and operational principle. 3. To be able to explain the image and image compression technology, and graphics processing technology:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1403,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1404,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Flynns taxonomy, parallel processing technology, parallel program technology, disk scheduling, SAN, NAS, DAS, LTO, VTL, RAID, GPGPU, video compression standards','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1405,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business \'Intel vs. NVIDIA vs. Google, who will win the Al market? Targeting based on parallel processing capability and market domination, Google looking to improve power efficiency using TPU\" , Monthly Electronic Parts News','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1406,'34','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Competition in parallel processing technology is intensifying as Al has emerged as a core technology of the 4th Industrial Revolution While existing programs were implemented by a CPU-based serial (sequential_ processing method, GPU-based programs use parallel processing technology, which simultaneously processes multiple instructions and is used to implement deep learning of Al. Google is increasing the parallel processing capability by adding its own processor called TPU. [Source: Monthly Electronic Components News]','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1407,'380','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Parallel processing refers to one or more independent operating systems managing multiple processors and performing multiple tasks There are separate programming languages and syntax for parallel processing: Parallel processing is very fast and can share the memory unit. Since several processors operate it, the impact of failed hardware parts on the entire system is small It is widely used in the field of Al, consisting of a lot of data and repetitive complex operations, military equipment that is needed to obtain accurate results in a short time, and searching services that extract results from a wide range of data in a short time Flynn s taxonomy and classification by memory structure are leading examples of parallel processing system classification','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1408,'458','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SISD is a single processor that sequentially processes an instruction and data, one at a time. It is the conventional computer architecture that follows von Neumann\'s concept The controller interprets an instruction and operates the processor in order to run the instruction while fetching a piece of data from the memory unit and processing it: The performance may deteriorate, since it requires reading the instruction each time it acquires the processing data The performance may be improved by using simultaneous processing techniques, such as pipelining and cunerccalar system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1409,'459','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c046be5ef.png','/storage/figures/6802c046be5ef.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1410,'459','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 43] SIMD Structure',NULL,'6802c046c8fb9.png','/storage/figures/6802c046c8fb9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1411,'459','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The structure of processing multiple data with an instruction to simultaneously perform the same operation on multiple data It is also called an array processor, as it enables synchronous parallel processing Intels processor made in the SIMD structure, is the Pentium processor with the MMX instruction set: The name is \"multimedia acceleration,\" which is the code that can quickly process frequently-used arithmetic operations The processing speed is high because it can process multiple operations with an instruction floating\" point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1412,'460','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c046d4305.png','/storage/figures/6802c046d4305.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1413,'460','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 44] MISD Structure',NULL,'6802c046de8a0.png','/storage/figures/6802c046de8a0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1414,'460','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Tvuicipic Ioli ucliun| Bli caind Tnuitpic uala \"u caitt, iviuilipic Iol ucliui Jli caii iviuicipic Data Jlicai| (vid| In a MIMD structure, multiple processors process different programs and different data, and most parallel computers fall into this category: It can be classified into a shared memory model and a distributed memory model, depending on how it uses the memory: According to the degree of data interaction, the shared memory model is called a tightly- Inloc cucton and bc Aictriku tod Oaonen modclic cleccificd 3c lcecel_counled cucton','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1415,'381','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 41] Structure of Parallel Computer Processor',NULL,'6802c046ed9d5.png','/storage/figures/6802c046ed9d5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:38'),(1416,'461','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 45] MIMD Structure',NULL,'6802c04707f13.png','/storage/figures/6802c04707f13.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1417,'461','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SMP is a tightly-coupled system in which all processors use the main memory as the shared memory: It is easy to program since the data transfer can use shared memory: On the other hand, it has poor scalability and may experience a bus bottleneck, since it uses an internal bus to access the main memory and share the data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1418,'462','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 47] MMP Structure',NULL,'6802c04713c59.png','/storage/figures/6802c04713c59.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1419,'462','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MPP is a distributed memory type in which each processor has an independent memory: The loosely coupled exchanges data between processors through a network, such as Ethernet  The structure of connecting nodes, like the CPU, memory, and IJO device, each of which has its own system resources, through a network offers excellen scalability and programming difficulty: systent','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1420,'463','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 48] NUMA Structure',NULL,'6802c0471fb5d.png','/storage/figures/6802c0471fb5d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1421,'463','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NUMA is a structure the combines the advantages of the SMP, which is a shared memory structure that makes it easier to develop programs and the MPP structure, which offers excellent scalability: Each processor has a separate local memory and the global memory address space that all processors can access.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1422,'464','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 49] Pipelining',NULL,'6802c0472e860.png','/storage/figures/6802c0472e860.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1423,'464','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technology improves the CPU performance by dividing a operation into several stages and configuring a hardware unit for processing each stage separately in order to process different instructions simultaneously: In other words, it does not process only one instruction at a time, but it processes multiple instructions simultaneously by','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1424,'464','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','processing aother instruction while still processing an original instruction: There are several types of pipelines: a two-stage instruction pipeline, a four-stage instruction pipeline, and a six-stage instruction pipeline The four-stage instruction pipeline is the most widely used Although the instruction set consists of two stages in the four-stage instruction pipeline, the processing time of the stages is divided into 4 in order to prevent efficiency degradation, which occurs because the processing time of the pipeline stages is not the same The stages of the four-stage instruction pipeline are instruction fetching (IF), instruction decoding (ID) , operand fetching (OF), and execution (EX):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1425,'464','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IF stage is a process that fetches instructions from the memory unit It fetches an instruction from the program counter\'s memory unit address and transfers it to the register The ID stage interprets the fetched instruction using an instruction decoder The OF stage fetches an operand that becomes a variable or data, to be used in operation, the memory unit: The EX stage runs the operation specified by the instruction from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1426,'465','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 50] Superscalar Process',NULL,'6802c0473caec.png','/storage/figures/6802c0473caec.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1427,'465','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Superscalar process is a structure that includes a number of instruction pipelines to speed up the central processing unit: It can run instructions out of order, since it independently processes instructions using multiple pipelines. The superscalar process has a basic configuration in which several functional units,that are implemented as superscalar pipelines, support the parallel processing of instructions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1428,'466','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A pipeline hazard refers to the pipeline exceptionally slowing down: Pipeline hazards include the data hazard, the control hazard, and the structural hazard. Data hazards occur when the next instruction execution has to be delayed until the previous instruction has been completed because of the dependency between instruction operands. Control hazards are generated by branch instructions, like branch and jumpwhich change the execution order of the instructions. Structural hazards are generated when instructions cannot be processed in parallel in the same clock cycle, due to hardware limitations. In other words,it means the hardware cannot support the combination of instructions in the same clock speed cycle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1429,'467','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OpenMP is a compiler directive-based parallel programming API. Here, directive-based means processing only the desired parts in parallel, by adding a directive to a program written sequentially without parallel processing: The execution model of OpenMP is the forkljoin model. A program initially operates as a master thread, and when it encounters a directive, it creates threads and independently executes them: When the parallel processing is finished (when the area selected as a directive is finished), are joined into one master thread in order to run the code sequentially: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1430,'468','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The message passing interface is a parallel programming model suitable to a distributed memory system structure Since MPI is not a memory sharing mode, the nodes share the information by transferring messages over the network Therefore, the network communication speed is the most important factor for performance, and it is widely used by supercomputers that require a high-speed operation. Parallel programming tools for message passing include High Performance FORTRAN (HPF), Parallel Virtual Machine (PVM) , and Message Passing Interface (MPI): MPI has become the standard.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1431,'469','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Load balancing adequately distributes jobs to the cores in order to increase the multi-core performance: The multiprocessing models include asymmetric multiprocessing (AMP) , symmetric multiprocessing (SMP) , and bound multiprocessing (BMP): AMP: An OS is executed independently in each processor core SMP: An OS manages all processor cores simultaneously: Application programs can operate in any core BMP model: An OS manages all process cores simultaneously, ad an application program can run on a specific core','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1432,'470','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The hardware specializes in computer graphics calculation and is mainly used for the rendering of 3D graphics Since a GPU is configured with thousands of small cores that perform floating-point operations processed in parallel, its performance is superior to a CPU that is configured with a small number of cores A GPU dedicated to processing capacity image data generates results through parallel jobs using multiple cores. Although recent GPUs were mainly used for graphics processing functions, they are evolving into more flexible, programmable GPUs large-(','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1433,'471','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 51] Difference of CPU and GPU Structures',NULL,'6802c0474a4d4.png','/storage/figures/6802c0474a4d4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1434,'471','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Based on the fact that a GPU shows high computational performance in matrix and vector operations that are mostly used for graphic rendering, the computing intends to utilize GPUs in the general computing domain as well Many models supporting GPGPU programming have appeared. include CUDA and OpeACC NVIDIA, OpenCL from Khronos Group and Ct  AMP from Microsoft. system They \' from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1435,'472','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In 2006, NVIDIA introduced CUDA, a tool for GPU development. CUDA is a parallel computing platform and a programming model that can significantly improve computing with a large number of GPU cores It provides speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1436,'472','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','intuitive GPI programming, based on the C language, and it enables quick operation using shared memory: CUDA consists of CUDA Runtime API and Driver API. Runtime API provides user-friendliness by automatically allocating necessary values for settings ad others. Driver API, which helps the Runtime API to operate, allows the programs to directly manage memory or devices without using Runtime API. The CUDA is expected to show an excellent performance improvement when to performing tasks suitable for parallel processing operations in various fields that require a large amount of computation, such as simulation Excellent performance can also be expected applied','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1437,'473','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OpenCL, maintained and managed by Khronos Group, is an open, general-purpose parallel computing framework developed by Apple, AMD, IBM, Intel, and NVIDIA It is an industry standard programming model for heterogeneous computer systems, consisting of GPUs, CPUs, and other processors It is a parallel programming model based on data and tasks and has characteristics of the open specification to use GPU, CPU, and DSP OpenCL mainly consists of the OpenCL compiler &d the OpenCL runtime library: Programs running on a computational processor (accelerator) are written in OpenCL C language, and the OpenCL compiler gathers the source code to convert it into a binary code Moreover, a control program to run or manage programs running on a CPU is necessary: It can be written using  or Ctt through the OpenCL runtime library:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1438,'474','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Ct  AMP was developed by Microsoft in an open programming language for heterogeneous computing, using CPU and GPU. Ct  AMP, when added to Visual Studio 2021, can increase the execution of Ct  codes using GPU: The C   language-based Ct  AMP intends to help developers create general-purpose programs using GPU without a high level of understanding or application capability about DirectX APL. speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1439,'475','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Although the concept and usefulness of GPU programming have been widely known with the emergence of platforms like CUDA, it is not easy to write a program that can expect a significant performance improvement by making use of parallel computing: NVIDIA introduced OpenACC, a programming model based on compiler directives that abstract CUDA Open ACC is a programming model for higher productivity, since it provides a relatively simple programming environment for developers It has another advantage of having lower dependence on an OS and platform, since it is a cross-platform model, unlike the above programming models. good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1440,'387','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Computer systems use a storage unit to access data and run commands. Although a system uses main memory for the main storage unit, it uses auxiliary memory to permanently store and utilize data The web server WAS, and the database of information systems also need a storage unit as the permanent auxiliary memory unit. The web server WAS requires a storage unit to store its OS or the binary files of its application program Although the data used by an information system is stored and managed through a database, the storage unit is necessary to ensure that data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1441,'387','App\\Models\\Section','Text','is not corrupted or lost','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1442,'476','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 52] DAS',NULL,'6802c04757575.png','/storage/figures/6802c04757575.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1443,'476','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The storage connects a computer system with disks directly through a fiber channel or SCSI cable in order to utilize the storage capacity: It allows the computer system to manage the file directory: Since the storage is directly connected to the computer system, it works like a external hard disk at high speed. Its advantage is that its configuration is simple, and the cost is low without a separate switch, but there is a limitation in the number of disks that can be connected: Moreover, files in the storage cannot be shared with other computers since it is directly connected to a computer system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1444,'477','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 53] NAS',NULL,'6802c0476aac5.png','/storage/figures/6802c0476aac5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1445,'477','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The storage has a separate file management server (controller) to manage the storage media such as HDD and SSD. It is connected to a computer system through an Ethernet network interface like LAN or WAN. Since it has separate file system management server, it is easier to manage data, and multiple servers can share the storage Moreover, multiple computer systems on the same network can use the storage, regardless of the physical location As the storage is connected over a network its speed and capacity are limited by the network speed. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1446,'478','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 54] SAN',NULL,'6802c04779ceb.png','/storage/figures/6802c04779ceb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1447,'478','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A disadvantage of the DAS type is the limitation of the number of disks, ad the difficulty of management, while the NAS type has a problem of possible depending on the network connection. SAN was developed to overcome the disadvantages It uses a dedicated fiber channel switch for fast connection, and it enabled the ability to scale up the number of connected servers and storage, with less impact to the connected network load. Using the channel allows the connection to speed up to 8Gbps 16Gbps. However, it increases costs since it requires the dedicated switch and expensive cables, and it can cause a consistency problem, due to locking, when multiple computer systems share a specific file speed delay, fiber','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1448,'388','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia services using a large volume of data, led to computer systems storing an increased volume of data. A large-capacity storage system is necessary, since a single disk cannot support the increasing data capacity A storage system logically groups multiple disks in order to store large capacity data that a single disk cannot handle It is classified into DAS, NAS, and SAN, depending on how it is connected to the computer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1449,'479','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This type of SAN uses the gigabit Ethernet Internet protocol (IP), instead of a fiber channel. While the SAN requires SAN switch and SAN storage disks, it increases interconnectivity, since it is connected using the existing Ethernet network It can unify the network management and overcome the distance limitation of SAN, since it can use an IP IP-SAN includes FCIP, iFCP, and iSCSI, while iSCSI is the most widely-used type','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1450,'480','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 55] FCIP',NULL,'6802c047834b8.png','/storage/figures/6802c047834b8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1451,'480','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','FCIP is used to connect a remote SAN. It encapsulates data to TCPIIP for interconnection when transferring a frame to a remote location. It groups the scattered SANs into a massive fiber channel fabric A failure of a SAN can affect SANs in other regions included in the fabric','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1452,'481','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 56] iFCP',NULL,'6802c0478f099.png','/storage/figures/6802c0478f099.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1453,'481','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','iFCP provides a TCPIIP connection dedicated to regional SAN, using the iFCP gateway Unlike FCIP, a SAN failure does not affect SAN in other regions, since it does not create a massive fabric Since it converts protocols using a gateway and can be implemented without changing the infrastructure, it provides highly compatible interconnectivity in both hardware and software','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1454,'482','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 57] iSCSI',NULL,'6802c0479aa91.png','/storage/figures/6802c0479aa91.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1455,'482','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','iSCSI encapsulates SCSI commands into IP packets and transfer the IO block data through TCPIIP Technologies like IPSec ensure reliability: It reduces the network storage implementation cost, since it can use the existing network environment asis.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1456,'483','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c047aa2b8.png','/storage/figures/6802c047aa2b8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1457,'483','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The existing fixed-allocation storage technology uses a thick logical unit number (LUN) wasted data storage spac Thin provisioning is a storage virtualization technology that allocates data by mapping actual data space into a th LUN It can flexibly expand the disk space required by users in cloud computing, and it offers a higher data utilizatic rate than the conventional thick LUN tvpe','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1458,'484','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technology provides a high efficiency of disk space used by removing any duplicated data when saving the dat The removal methods include an inline method, which immediately removes redundant data as it enters the storag system, and an offline method, which removes the redundant data after storing the new data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1459,'485','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A disk drive that stores data is a device using a rotating magnetic disk When inputs and outputs are requested to disk drive, the system performance varies significantly, according to which request is processed first, and the proc in moving the head to access the data. Disk scheduling is a technique of efficiently processing IJO requests, V multiple users request them, in order to process different tasks Using disk scheduling has the following purposes: Maximization of IO requests to service during a unit time Maximization throughput per unit time Minimization of the mean response time Minimization of response time Minimization of the variation of response time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1460,'486','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 58] Inexpensive Thin Provisioning',NULL,'6802c047b81fc.png','/storage/figures/6802c047b81fc.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1461,'486','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Disk scheduling can be compared with the indicators that measure disk performance Disk performance measuremen indicators include the access time, seeking time, rotational delay or rotational latency and data transfer time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1462,'486','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The seeking time indicates how it takes to move the head from the current head position, to the track containing the data The rotational latency indicates how it takes from the moment the head begins rotating to move to the track containing the data, to the moment it reaches the sector that contains the data Seeking time is the time it takes to move the head the current head position, to the track containing the data. Recent disk drives minimize the rotational latency by having an interal buffer and by storing al the data in the track long long from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1463,'486','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','within the buffer The data transfer time indicates how it takes to transfer the read data to the main memory: The access time is the sum of the seeking time, the rotational latency, and the data transfer time This section describes techniques to minimize the access time by minimizing the seeking time ad the rotational latency long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1464,'487','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 60] FCFS Disk Scheduling',NULL,'6802c047c2df7.png','/storage/figures/6802c047c2df7.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1465,'487','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','FCFS services the requests in the order are received. The head position moves in the order of the requested tracks in the disk standby queue. It is easy to program and provides fair service to all requests. However, the head movement may be inefficient, and it can unnecessarily increase the response time The execution sequence does not even when it receives a priority request they change,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1466,'488','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 61] SSTF Disk Scheduling',NULL,'6802c047cd81b.png','/storage/figures/6802c047cd81b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1467,'488','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The scheduling technique first services the request that is closest to the current head position, among the requested services waiting in the queue It minimizes head movement because it takes a lot of time to move the head in the disk drive: It maximizes the service response rate per unit time by minimizing the head movement in order to process the queue requests The response time variation can increase depending on where the requested input or output data is on the disk It can cause starvation for the requests seeking data that are positioned in the inner or outer cylinder It offers a higher processing rate and a shorter mean response time than FCFS.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1468,'489','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 62] SCAN Disk Scheduling',NULL,'6802c047d779d.png','/storage/figures/6802c047d779d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1469,'489','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The scheduling technique first services the request that has the shortest seeking distance from the current direction','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1470,'489','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','of the moving head. It can reduce the response time variation of SSTF, and it generally offers excellent throughput per unit time ad mean response time. On determining the heading direction, the head services all the requests waiting in the request queue in the same direction as the order of the shortest search distance, ad it changes the seeking direction after it reaches the outermost or innermost cylinder It has improved both the throughput per unit time and the response time significantly compared to SSTF, and it solved the starvation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1471,'490','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 63] LOOK Disk Scheduling',NULL,'6802c047e1eb9.png','/storage/figures/6802c047e1eb9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1472,'490','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The technique is the same as the SCAN disk scheduling, except that the head changes its direction before reaching the outermost or innermost cylinder It checks the waiting queue while moving the head, and it does not move furtherlt changes direction when there are no more requests in the moving direction:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1473,'491','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The SCAN technique moves the head by connecting the inner and outer tracks in a circular model Like SCAN disk scheduling, the head services the request with the shortest distance in its moving direction first, then it moves to the initial direction to service requests after all the requests in the moving direction are serviced It services all requests in a predetermined service direction Since it responds equally to input and output requests by improving the SCAN scheduling, the response time variation is very small, making it easy to predict the response time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1474,'492','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ike C-SCAN,itis a LOOK scheduling technique that connects the inner and outer tracks in an annular model in order make the head move. The head moves to the initial beginning position and services the next requests, if there are','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1475,'492','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','10 more requests in the moving direction, even when the head does not reach the end.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:14'),(1476,'493','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 64] RAID-0',NULL,'6802c047ee235.png','/storage/figures/6802c047ee235.png','2025-04-18 21:12:14','2025-04-18 21:12:39'),(1477,'493','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-0 consists of two or more drives and uses disk striping, which stores data by dividing it into pieces of a specific size and saves it on multiple disks at once. Although it increases the IJO it cannot protect data because there is no redundancy: A stripe, which means the size of the stored data, is a unit for dividing data into pieces of a specific size. RAID-0 can reduce the IJO time by enabling parallel processing of IO requests However, data is lost if any drive fails. Although the technology is not used much in business environments, RAID-I0 uses it by taking its advantages and overcoming its disadvantages. speed,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1478,'494','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 65] RAID-1',NULL,'6802c04805079.png','/storage/figures/6802c04805079.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1479,'494','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-1 uses & mirroring technique that redundantly stores data on two drives. Since data is stored in redundancy data can be restored, even if a drive fails. It can improve the reading performance, but the writing performance is somewhat low, since it performs reading operations on a drive with low IO. Although the system is highly stable, the cost is high because only half of the physical capacity can be used, as the other half is used for redundant storage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1480,'495','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 66] RAID-5',NULL,'6802c04811800.png','/storage/figures/6802c04811800.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1481,'495','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-4 has a separate parity drive and collects and stores parities for data verification and recovery RAID-5 is an improvement of RAID-4 by distributing the load of the drive that stores the parities. At least three drives are required, and the data and parity are stored by distributing them to different drives. It is highly effective in cost and performance, and recently, most SSDs are configured in RAID-5. If three drives are configured, data cannot be restored if two or more drives fail,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1482,'496','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 67] RAID-6',NULL,'6802c0481e4a0.png','/storage/figures/6802c0481e4a0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1483,'496','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-6 is similar to RAID-5, except that while RAID-5 stores one parity, RAID-6 redundantly stores a parity in two drives The configuration is more durable than RAID-5 and can store data safely: In a RAID-5 configuration, the rebuild time restores data to the new drive when a drive fails and is replaced. The rebuilding takes a time in a storage system with a large storage capacity: If another drive fails this rebuilding time, there is a possibility of data loss Therefore, RAID-6 is recommended, long during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1484,'497','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 68] RAID-10',NULL,'6802c0482ae35.png','/storage/figures/6802c0482ae35.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1485,'497','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','RAID-10 requires at least four drives and is a combination of RAID-0 and RAID-1 to improve IJO speed while providing data stability It eliminates the concern with stability, which is an important drawback of RAID-0, and it can significantly improve performance, which is the biggest drawback of RAID-1. However its disadvantage is that the cost is high RAID 1 0 configures two drives in mirroring first, then RAID-1 drives, configured of two drives, are configured in RAID-0. RAID 0 1 divides the drives to be configured in half configures them in RAID-0, and reconfigures Vz of the drives and the remaining 1/2 of the drives in RAID-1. The RAID-10 configuration features better stability and generally uses RAID-10 more than RAID-0 1.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1486,'392','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Large-capacity storage systems generally have an error controller and backup tunction to sately store the massive volume of data RAID technology is a storage technology that minimizes the factors that can cause failure, ad it improves access performance by arranging a number of disks, and by creating a separate disk unit by them with each other The main features of RAID are improved availability, increased capacity, and increased Firstly, the improved availability feature provides a hot-swap function to replace a failed disk without shutting down the system, and it recovers the original data to the replaced disk online Secondly, the increased capacity feature organizes several disks into a large virtual disk, and it recognizes them as large-capacity storage disks Thirdly, the increased speed improves the overall data transfer rate by partitioning reading and writing data, and by transferring it to multiple disks in parallel RAID implementation includes RAID-0, 1,2,3,4 5,6,and 10. RAID-0, RAID-I, RAID-5, RAID-6, and RAID-I0 (1 0 or 0 1) are widely used technologies, while RAID-2, RAID-3,and RAID-4 are rarely used. linking speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1487,'498','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','LTO is a standard open tape drive technology that supports high-speed data processing and a large capacity: Although LTO refers to physical devices and technology, are also used interchangeably: It is also called the tape backup machine, tape media machine, LTO machine, LTO library, and LTO. LTO-1, first released in 2000, provided a maximum speed of 20 MB/s at a uncompressed capacity of 100 GB. The LTO-8 that is currently available, supports the performance of a maximum of 427MB/s based on a uncompressed capacity of 12.8TB. The LTO-10 is expected to provide a maximum speed of 1IOOMBIs at an uncompressed capacity of 48TB. they speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1488,'499','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 69] VTL Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c0483724c.png','/storage/figures/6802c0483724c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1489,'499','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','VTL is a backup solution that emulates disk storage and makes it into a virtual tape device to compensate problems such as limited performance, scalability, ad the recovery time of existing tape backup devices. Backup simplified, and high-speed backup is enabled through tape virtualization.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1490,'500','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 15) Lossless Compression',NULL,'6802c04848dad.png','/storage/tables/6802c04848dad.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1491,'500','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Since the compression and decompression algorithms are exactly the opposite of each other, the compression method preserves the original data\'s integrity, and no part of the data is lost processing: Leading lossless compression methods include run-length decoding, dictionary decoding, Huffman coding, dictionary coding, and arithmetic coding: during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1492,'501','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The lossy compression method compromises some accuracy to increase the compression rate, by allowing the loss of redundant or unnecessary data. There are two types of compression methods: prediction coding ad transform coding: The prediction coding method is used for digitizing the analog signal. Instead of separately quantizing the PCM (Pulse Code Modulation) samples it quantizes the difference: The difference values are smaller than the actual sample values, so fewer bits are required. The transform coding method transforms a signal from one domain (mainly a time and space domain) to another domain (mainly a frequency domain), then compresses it lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1493,'394','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data compression, which accounts for most of the traffic in a multimedia network, can be divided into lossless compression (reversible compression) and lossy compression (irreversible compression): Lossless compression is also called reversible compression.lt refers to a method of restoring a compressed image without information loss from the original data while decompressing: It is characterized by a lower compression rate than compression. Lossy compression is also called irreversible compressionlt refers to a compression method when the compressed data is restored, but it does not match the original data before the compression because some data is lost lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1494,'502','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 16  Compression Format and Additional Standard',NULL,'6802c0485d59e.png','/storage/tables/6802c0485d59e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1495,'502','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Moving Picture Experts Group (MPEG) is a international standardization organization The official name of the standard is ISOJIEC JTCI/SCZINGII. MPEG created the following compression formats and additional standards','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1496,'502','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Ivanced video coding (AVC) and high efficiency video coding (HVEC','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1497,'503','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','AVC codec is a video compression technology jointly proposed by the international standard organizations ITU-L and ISO. It uses the name H.264, proposed by ITU-T, or MPEG4 PartIOJAVC, proposed by ISO. The standard name fo HEVC is ISOJIEC 23008-2 by ISOJIEC','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1498,'395','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 70] Image Data Transformation Process',NULL,'6802c0486d833.png','/storage/figures/6802c0486d833.png','2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1499,'395','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia data includes text,, image, video, and audio data. The text has the form of plain text and non-linear hypertext: The basic language is Unicode for expressing symbols, and it uses a lossless compression method In multimedia, an image is called a still image and refers to a photo, fax page, or a video frame As shown in [Figure 70], an image is transmitted as data through a transformation process, a quantization process, and an encoding process, before converted back into an image through the reverse process In the transformation process the JPEG uses DCT (Discrete Cosine Transform) in the first stage of compression, and the decompression uses the inverse DCT method. The transformation and inverse transformation apply 8 X 8 blocks. The quantization process creates integers from the real number of the DCT transform output ad converts some values to zero The coding process arranges data in a zigzag order after quantization and before encoder input, then lossless compression is performed using run-length decoding and arithmetic coding [1]. binary being Video data is composed of several frames Since each frame is an image, a video file requires a high transmission rate Video data can be compressed with a spatial compression or a temporal compression method. JPEG performs spatial compression of each frame, and each frame is compressed independently: Temporal compression removes redundant frames and configures each frame into I-frames, which are independent frames, B-frames, and P-frames, which reference other I-frames to compress data temporally: Analog audio signals are digitized using a analog-to-digital converter (ADC) , and the ADC consists of two processes: sampling and quantization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1500,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1501,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Text','With the advent of the loT (Internet of Things), represented by technological innovation in various industries, the embedded system market is expected to grow explosively, due to the increased demand in the automobile (or connected car) and medical fields A market research firm predicts that the global embedded systems market will grow by 5.6% per year reaching $2,587 billion by 2023. The reason for this growth is that the demand for embedded systems in the automotive and medical fields is expected to increase rapidly, thanks to the recently emerged loT: Embedded systems are widely utilized in information home appliances, information terminals, communication equipment, aviationmmilitary, logistics/finance, vehicle/transportation, office work, industriall control, medical care, games, and robots. In other words, embedded systems have become an integral part of any industry: Among various applications, the automotive and medical industries are expected to drive the growth of the embedded system market in the future However, solving security problems that may arise from linking various embedded systems, through technological innovation, has emerged as a challenge Embedded systems mostly operate home appliances transportation, aviation, machinery, medical equipment, automobiles, and communication devices Recently, all equipment, machines, and vehicles are connected to an OS, a webserver, a remote control, and smart devices. Among these, medical equipment and automobiles are very important because their security vulnerabilities can have a impact on safety: It is essential to protect embedded systems from unauthorized software and other vulnerabilities, such as theft and privacy protection. Accordingly, continuous efforts are made to protect the systems from theft and data hackers and to solve them being public great being','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1502,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:15','2025-04-18 21:12:15'),(1503,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain system structure and characteristics 2 To be able to explain embedded OS.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1504,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1505,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Embedded hardware, Microprocessor Microcontroller Low power, Lightweight,, Small form factor RTOS Embedded Linux Windows CE','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1506,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1507,'35','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Company A specializes in developing embedded systems that control industrial equipment and home appliances. Since embedded systems are applicable to a wide range of devices, such as sensors controllers, and loT devices, are the core technology required from the market development stage An embedded is a solution built into a product to perform specific tasks. Developers of such systems must have a broad knowledge of software and hardware functions This chapter describes embedded systems in detail they system','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1508,'396','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 17) Examples of Embedded System',NULL,'6802c04880633.png','/storage/tables/6802c04880633.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1509,'396','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 71] Embedded System Configuration',NULL,'6802c0488cf9d.png','/storage/figures/6802c0488cf9d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1510,'396','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system is a computer system that performs a specific function for controlling a machine or other systems requiring control, and an electronic system in the device In more detail, it is a with a built-in microprocessor and a program that drives the microprocessor to perform specific function, more than just simple circuits in various electronic devices, home appliances, and control devices used in our daily life An embedded system is configured of a set of hardware and software, as shown in [Figure 71]. Embedded hardware: Embedded hardware consists of a microprocessorlmicrocontroller, equivalent to a CPU, memory, input/output device, network device, sensor, driver, etc Embedded software: Embedded software consists of an operating system (OS) that directly controls hardware and manages the software, software, ad application software: Unlike conventional software, the main purpose of the embedded software is to provide a appropriate response to the physical world. Therefore, embedded software has the characteristics of the physical world, such as time, energy, and permanence system system Embedded systems control many devices used in everyday life. As shown in <Table 17  , embedded systems are usec in a wide range of areas, portable digital watches and health bands, to large fixed facilities, such as traffic lights factory control devices, and nuclear power plant control systems from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1511,'504','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','embedded systems are mass-produced in units of millions and the reduction of production costs is one of the crucial factors. Some embedded systems that do not require high processing performance or resources can have relatively slow processor and small memory in order to reduce costs Many','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1512,'505','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many embedded system have low performance: Here, being slow does not simply refer to a slow clock speed. In parts','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1513,'505','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','general, an embedded system\'s overall structure is intentionally simplified to reduce cost, compared to the hardware of general-purpose computer systems For example, embedded systems often use peripherals controlled by a serial bus that is 1024 times slower than the conventional peripheral interfaces that are used in personal computers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1514,'506','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Programs on embedded systems usually operate with real-time constraints on limited hardware resources There is ften no disk drive, operating system, keyboard, or screen on the system. It may not have a file system, or it may use  flash drive as a storage medium: Even if there is a user interface, it could be a small keypad or LCD.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1515,'507','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded systems are designed to run reliably, without error, for many years. Therefore, firmware goes through a more careful development and testing process than the software used in personal computers Most embedded systems avoid the use of parts damaged by mechanical actions, such as disk drives, switches, and buttons Instead, use chip materials that are relatively free from physical damage, such as flash memory: they \'.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1516,'508','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded systems may be applied in places where it is difficult for humans to immediately and directly control, such as oil boreholes ad outer space: Therefore, an embedded system must be able to restart itself even in the worst- case scenario An electronic part, called a watchdog timer\' enables such an emergency recovery:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1517,'397','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since an embedded system performs a specific mission, engineers can optimize the design in order to reduce the size and production cost and to increase reliability and performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1518,'398','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 18) Detailed Tasks of Embedded System Development',NULL,'6802c048a33b0.png','/storage/tables/6802c048a33b0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1519,'398','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c048c35d9.png','/storage/tables/6802c048c35d9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1520,'398','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 72] Embedded System Development Procedure',NULL,'6802c048da376.png','/storage/figures/6802c048da376.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1521,'398','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system is developed by the procedure, shown in [Figure 72] Unlike conventional information system development, it includes a hardware development process 5 Watchdog Timer (WDT): An electronic timer used to detect ad recover computer failure Computers in normal operation restart the watchdog timer periodically to prevent a timeout <Table 18  below shows details of the above development procedure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1522,'399','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 19) Embedded Processor Types',NULL,'6802c048e953c.png','/storage/tables/6802c048e953c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:40'),(1523,'399','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded system can handle more functions and performance because the processor provides the performance required to drive the device. Early microprocessor units (MPUs) were made in a single chip, in which registers data processing, arithmetic logic unit (ALU) for mathematical operation, and for storing result values were integrated into a chip. Although CPU and MPU were separated according to use ad purpose in the past, the boundaries now are somewhat ambiguous Since then, microcontrollers, with a built-in processor, memory, and control interface on single chip, have emerged to be used for real-time operating systems or automatic controls flags t is not far-fetched to consider that the MPU is included in all the electronic devices that are open to user ntervention in its use or configuration It is currently used in smartphones, smart bands, and tablet PCs that are used','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1524,'399','App\\Models\\Section','Text','in daily life It is also used in mechanical keyboards that provide functions, such as various shortcut and infinite inputs. It is also in a TV or air conditioneras well as in the remote control that controls the TV and air conditioner: Moreover, it is in game consoles, car trip computers, and smart While Intel and AMD are everything when it comes to CPU for computers, many companies make MPUs. Many companies, like Broadcom, Mediatek, Samsung Electronics, Apple, Nvidia, Qualcomm, and Texas Instruments, make MPUs used in electronic devices As shown in <Table 19  , various CPU architectures, 8-bit to 64-bit, such as ARM, MIPS, ColdFire/68K, PowerPC, x86, PIC microcontroller, and 8051, are used for embedded systems That is what differentiates the embedded system market from the personal computer market Moreover, one of the latest trends of embedded systems is the System on Chip (SoC) concept that integrates all ICs for a specific field into a single CPU chip in order to eliminate the need to mount separate peripheral chips on the board keys key\' keys: from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1525,'509','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Studies of applying connectivity technologies, such as WiFi, LTE, BLE, and ZigBee,, used by mobile devices and servers/PCs, to embedded systems, have increased with the convergence of the IT industry Traditional industries and interoperability between devices, such as loT and MZM sensor networks, have also become important','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1526,'510','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Processors for embedded systems were mostly converted from 8 bits to 32 bits. As such, the number of embedded systems using an OS has rapidly increased, and the portion of general-purpose OS, like Linux has significantlvincreased','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1527,'511','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Embedded operating systems, supporting wearables and loT devices, require lighter weight and lower power consumption, while operating systems applied to conventional embedded devices include middleware, related to high functionality and stability and convenience functions like 3D acceleration GUl and multimedia As a result, technology polarization is accelerating,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1528,'401','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 20} Technology Fields and Examples of Embedded Software',NULL,'6802c049080c8.png','/storage/tables/6802c049080c8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1529,'401','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software refers to software installed in embedded systems. As the application fields of embedded systems diversify, embedded software is becoming increasingly complex to handle various functions As shown in <Table 20  , the main technology fields of embedded software can be classified into basic embedded applications, embedded middleware,, embedded system software,, embedded system development tools, and embedded software platforms','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1530,'402','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 21) Characteristics of Embedded Software',NULL,'6802c0491af9e.png','/storage/tables/6802c0491af9e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1531,'402','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c049298bb.png','/storage/tables/6802c049298bb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1532,'402','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software is embedded in a physical product and continuously interacts with the physical environment: In other words, it must continuously receive and process signals from the physical environment. In some cases, it is necessary to receive the user\'s requirements and respond to them, by considering changes in the physical environment. There are also cases, such as computers and smartphones, where it only responds to user requirements Therefore, embedded software has characteristics, such as reactivity, timeliness, concurrency heterogeneity, liveness, resource and environmental constraints, and determinism. <Table 21  below shows features of each characteristic,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1533,'403','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An embedded OS is an operating system that is optimized to execute the application programs running on a computer that perform specific functions for controlling a machine or other systems It is optimized for a specific system that has hardware with a built-in microprocessor, and it performs set purposes. In the early embedded systems the hardware was directly controlled using the assembly language, ad it operated without a separate OS. However, as the embedded system applications have diversified, the need to use a OS has increased system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1534,'404','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 22) Embedded OS Application',NULL,'6802c0493b33a.png','/storage/tables/6802c0493b33a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1535,'404','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 73] Embedded OS Structure',NULL,'6802c0494d81f.png','/storage/figures/6802c0494d81f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1536,'404','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 73], an embedded OS generally has a structure to support the stable application program execution with a low-specification processor, a limited memory and storage device, and poor operating environment conditions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1537,'404','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Technologies applied to embedded OS can be characterized by real-time, small/lightweight, and low power consumption, as shown in <Table 22  .','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1538,'405','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'[Figure 74] Status of Embedded OS Use (2017)',NULL,'6802c04960ec8.png','/storage/code/6802c04960ec8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1539,'405','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Embedded software runs in a wide range of devices and supports many operating systems: However, it is largely divided into real-time operating systems that must satisfy conditions to operate within a set time, and operating systems that do not Real-time OS (RTOS): Mainly focuses on controlling application programs or hardware affected by a limited amount of time: The operating systems include VxWorks, VRTX, QNX, and pSOS. Non real-time OS: Mainly focuses on development convenience, scalability, and diverse operating environments. The leading operating systems include Linux series, embedded Window XP and Windows CE leading \" Traditionally an embedded OS was used because systems, such as satellites ad missile controllers, that must have flawless protection errors needed to have an OS optimized for real-time systems In that case, the systems used RTOS, instead of a general-purpose OS. However, one of the latest trends in embedded OS technology is that the portion of Linux and free RTOS is steadily increasing, when compared to traditional embedded RTOS, such as VxWorks, pSOS, QNX, and VRTX, which have led the existing information home appliance market and other embedded application industries (see [Figure 74]). Linux is installed in about 65% of all embedded devices and is still growing very fast, at an annual average of 17%. Meanwhile, the UK\'s FreeRTOS is rapidly expanding its base The market share is around 50%,which makes it the de- facto standard. In addition to FreeRTOS, ARMs mbed, which was recently acquired by Softbank in Japan, is spreading rapidly: Of course, commercial products are still leading in markets that require a high degree of safety, such as in tomobiloc Jircnftc 9n ia against','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:16','2025-04-18 21:12:16'),(1540,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1541,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Text','With the advent of the infomation age, the social demand to construct information system infrastructure is increasing, and various information systems are being implemented for business efficiency ad custome service improvement: These information systems generally consist of hardware, software, and humar resources It is necessary to understand the concept, architecture, and structure of the information tc implement a successful information system. Recent information systems tend to adopt a large number of web-based structures: In that regard theinformation system projects of the planners (public institutions) and implementers (systems integrators and hardware manufacturers) need to procure hardware resources that suit the project scope in order improve the efficiency of investment in information systems Information system infrastructure is generally implemented by purchasing servers, storage, and network devices separately from each vendor, then integrating them for the project: Moreover, also purchase software separately, and thus need to test and verify if it works properly with the hardware The complex structures and procedures of constructing information system infrastructure have inevitabl resulted in inefficiency in construction time and system management. The converged infrastructure that integrates the hardware,such as storage, servers, and networks, with the virtualization solution anc the management software into a product, ad validates it in advance for supply to customers, has beer introduced to compensate for it: Moreover the hyper-converged infrastructure that complements the high investment cost has also appeared These efforts to increase the efficiency of system implementation are ongoing they','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1542,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1543,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain information system structures 2 To be able to calculate information system capacity: 3 To be able to explain the latest OS technologies &nd trends,','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1544,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1545,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Server, storage, network equipment, webserver WAS server, DB server, hardware capacity calculation, OLTF capacity calculation, webWAS capacity calculation, memory capacity calculation, disk capacity calculation, storage capacity calculation, converged infrastructure, hyper-converged infrastructure','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1546,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1547,'36','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Company A has recently launched a new system, but recognized that its hardware capacity is about 30% insufficient during a service An investigation found that the concurrent user calculation of some services was inaccurate, leading to incorrect hardware capacity selection: The current infrastructure is expected to face inadequacy within three to four months if the company operates the system as is. Therefore, Company As Planning Team decided to allocate the additional budget to expand the infrastructure in two months This case shows the practical importance of calculating the information capacity, according to its structural design and system structure This chapter describes information structure and size calculation in detail . system','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1548,'406','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 75] Information System and IT-Based Structure',NULL,'6802c04970f20.png','/storage/figures/6802c04970f20.png','2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1549,'406','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An information system uses information technology (IT) to perform business procedures, such as providing necessary information, or business processing required by enterprises It creates a system that enables IT personnel to provide IT services by using IT components, such as hardware ad software, to perform organizational business procedures As shown in [Figure 75], the information system provides services by using the technology resources of the IT infrastructure The IT infrastructure includes computing platforms, such as networks, hardware, software, IT personnel, and IT services:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:17'),(1550,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0498229e.png','/storage/tables/6802c0498229e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1551,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04998736.png','/storage/tables/6802c04998736.png','2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1552,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 77] Information System Hardware Configuration (Example)',NULL,'6802c049acf15.png','/storage/figures/6802c049acf15.png','2025-04-18 21:12:17','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1553,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A server is the most fundamental component required when implementing an information system, and devices,such as storage and backup disks, are added and configured as needed A server is a hardware platform that runs server application programs and is classified in various ways, according to performance and type as follows Classification according to performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1554,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Classification according to the configuration','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1555,'512','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Storage is classified into enterprise or mid-range storage, according to processing capacity It provides a large storage space, high performance, and high availability, compared to general disk arrays. space, high performance, and high availability, compared to general disk arrays. [Figure 77] below shows an example of an information hardware configuration, using a server ad various devices A system architecture or technical architecture design describes its details system [Figure 77] below shows an example of a information system hardware configuration, using a server and various devices A system architecture or technical architecture design describes its details','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1556,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 78] Webserver',NULL,'6802c049bad52.png','/storage/figures/6802c049bad52.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1557,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 79] WAS',NULL,'6802c049c6caa.png','/storage/figures/6802c049c6caa.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1558,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 80] DB Server',NULL,'6802c049d2fdb.png','/storage/figures/6802c049d2fdb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1559,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS: An OS is defined as system software that operates and manages a application platform and that provides an interface between an application program ad the platform The OS for the server includes Linux, UNIX (BSD, Solaris etc ), Windows, and macOS. The OS for the server market is quite different from the desktop market, which is dominated by Windows Linux and UNIX are the most widely used OS, followed by Windows. UNIX servers have replaced most mainframes, and they were followed by Linux,which is a UNIX-like OS. ebserver: A webserver provides media content, such as HTML and text, images, ad video, to web clients lik eb browsers It provides data through the HTTP protocol to enable a web browser to present information Leadin ebserver products include Apache, Nginx and IIS (see [Figure 78]). Web application server (WAS): A WAS is a middleware that enables the stable transaction processing of web client requests and helps develop the distributed systems It is an engine for database queries or business logic processing which supports component development and use, application development, web, distributed objects, security, IED, system management, ad interface to legacy systems Leading WAS products include Tomcat, Jetty, JEUS, JBoss, WebLogic, WebSphere, and Nodejs (see [Figure 79]).','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1560,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Transaction processing (TP) monitor: A TP-monitor is transaction management middleware that supports the distributed transaction processing and monitors transactions, which are the minimum processing units between active sessions and systems in various protocols, in order to maintain them consistently: Most TP-monitor products comply with the DTP (distributed transaction process) model specified by XOpen, the UNIX environment standardization organization The leading TP-monitor products include Tmax and Tuxedo. DB server (Database management system, DBMS): A DB server provides the database type, database management','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1561,'513','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','technology, and query language for the access to ad modification of structural data. It is large-scale storage of consolidated data with minimum duplication and is used by multiple users concurrently: It provides independence between application programs and data and efficient access to data through queries The system catalog is the tool for database administrators (DBAs) and & table that lists the definitions or statements of all data objects stored in the database The leading DBMS products include Oracle, MS-SQL, PostgreSQL, Maria and Cubrid (see [Figure 807) system DB,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1562,'407','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 76] 3-Tier Web System Architecture',NULL,'6802c049e16e6.png','/storage/figures/6802c049e16e6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1563,'407','App\\Models\\Section','Text','There are several types of structures for an information A web architecture and a client-serv architecture are leading examples The most recent information systems are generally composed of a 3-t web system architecture, and these information systems can be divided into physical areas (hardware) and progra areas (software) , as shown in [Figure 76], from a structural viewpoint system. system Isystem','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1564,'408','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 81] Comparison of Size Calculation Concepts',NULL,'6802c049f06b1.png','/storage/tables/6802c049f06b1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:41'),(1565,'408','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 82] Hardware Size Estimation',NULL,'6802c04a101ae.png','/storage/tables/6802c04a101ae.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1566,'408','App\\Models\\Section','Text','System sizing is to estimate or calculate a system\' $ size using a mathematical methodology, based on actual work and applications. It can be defined as a lower-level concept of capacity planning or capacity management to determine performance requirements and performance based on the system architecture application, as shown in [Figure 81]. Sizing is temporarily performed for a specific system or server, and it is also called size estimation because bac nradictiva natura','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1567,'408','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Sizing is a matter of prediction, and the calculation method significantly affects the accuracy of the calculation Hardiware size calculation methods are generally classified into the mathematical calculation, reference, and simulation methods, as shown in [Figure 82]. It is necessary to apply an appropriate sizing method to get accurate sizing: This guideline uses a mathematical calculation method However, it is necessary to use all three methods appropriately for cize calculation in order to increace the accuraci the calculation recultc and obiectii','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1568,'409','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 84] Performance Standard Applicable for CPU and Storage',NULL,'6802c04a201a8.png','/storage/tables/6802c04a201a8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1569,'409','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 83] Size Calculation Target',NULL,'6802c04a2b769.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a2b769.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1570,'409','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Generally, the target for sizing includes not only hardware, but also software or network As shown in [Figure 83],','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1571,'409','App\\Models\\Section','Text','the size calculation target in the capacity calculation guidelines is hardware, which is defined as servers, not PCs or other peripherals While there are several hardware configuration areas, the four areas CPU, memory disk, and storage are the most important in terms of system price and performance, and are defined by sizing areas they - CPU: Calculates the CPU size to process the necessary tasks and selects the server model that shows adequate performance Memory: Calculate memory usage by the software and applications programs for each server, based on the server configuration, according to the CPU size Disk: Calculates disk usage by the OS, system software, database, and database archive/backup for each server based on the server configuration, according to the CPU size Storage: Calculates the size of the needed storage, based on the server size, according to the CPU: system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1572,'409','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Then apply the performance standard for each size calculation target, as shown in [Figure 84]','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1573,'410','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 85] 3-Tier Architecture',NULL,'6802c04a3834d.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a3834d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1574,'410','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 86] Reference Model for 3-Tier Physical Server Configuration',NULL,'6802c04a4bea8.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a4bea8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1575,'410','App\\Models\\Section','Text','nce the size is calculated for each server the person who calculates the size needs to understand the conceptu odel of the overall system architecture that is to be implemented. Most information systems nowadays ha\' Jopted the 3-tier architecture, as shown in [Figure 85]. The government standard suggests three types of reference architectures, as shown in [Figure 86], to establish th standard for size calculation and presents the size calculation method for each layer in the architecture for eacl architecture type','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1576,'514','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Basic data on the tasks and system to be implemented are necessary to ensure the hardware capacity calculation accuracy: To accurate information,, cooperation with the users is crucial, and the basic task analysis and implementation direction are established through consultation with them get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1577,'515','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If necessary, analyze the newly added workload,as well as the relevance and complexity of each work, and determine each tasks expected load, through the basic data and task analysis results Calculate the reference load by calculating the sum of the expected load for each task Validate the basic data and task analysis,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1578,'516','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04a61e66.png','/storage/tables/6802c04a61e66.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1579,'516','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Select the reference model suitable for the architecture type of the calculation target system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1580,'516','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Select various correction coefficients, based on the task analysis data investigated in Step 2 Calculate the size for each component of the server in the reference model.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1581,'517','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','fter the capacity calculation of each item of the server in 3, 4 applies the weight factor for each server ccording to the architecture type Step Step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1582,'411','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04a7108c.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a7108c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1583,'412','App\\Models\\Section','Text','This section describes how to select the size for each server component. As mentioned in the section for the procedure for size calculation, determine the server, based on the architecture type, and calculate the CPU, memory, disk, and storage sizes for each server Refer to \"TTA Guidelines on Calculating Information System Hardware\" for how to calculate the detailed size of each element','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1584,'146','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','When implementing an information system, many hardware suppliers or system integrators use the items and rates for sizing calculation, based on their experience, leading to inaccurately calculated sizes Moreover, since the hardware size must be calculated according to the nature of the business, load increase rate, and use frequency by the users, it is difficult to determine the appropriateness of the hardware size in the information system implementation projects For that reason, hardware has usually been dependent o the project contractor or hardware supplier It has gained relatively low interest, compared to software development, although the share of hardware in the information system implementation project is very large in the total project cost. Therefore, there is no way to correct it, even if a sizing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1585,'146','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','hardware component is over or underestimated by a project contractor or a hardware supplier As such, this chapter reflects the government guidelines for calculating hardware size','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1586,'147','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 87] Conventional Infrastructure vs. Converged Infrastructure',NULL,'6802c04a88fd3.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a88fd3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1587,'147','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 88] Converged Infrastructure vs. Hyper Converged Infrastructure',NULL,'6802c04a9b92b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04a9b92b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1588,'147','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Information system infrastructure is generally implemented by separately purchasing servers, storage, and network devices from each vendor, then integrating them for the project Moreover also separately purchase software, thus need to test ad verify if it works properly with the hardware: However, such a complex structure and procedure inevitably have led to inefficiency from the implementation time and system management aspect The converged infrastructure is a concept introduced to solve the problem It integrates the hardware, like storage,, server, and network with the virtualization solution and the management software, supplied by each vendor into a product and validates it in advance for supplv to customers (see [Figure 871) . they they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1589,'147','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','However, despite the advantage that the converged infrastructure enabled quick service implementation, through the integration and validation in advance, it was not actually well received in the market,due to its poor performance compared to input resources Since the product integrates the server the network and the external storage, the cost waS exceptionally high, and the system had a problem with scalability: In particular the high-performance external storage was a severe burden from the cost and structural aspect. The hyper converged infrastructure (HCI) is a concept that overcomes the limitations of Cl by eliminating the','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1590,'147','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','expensive external storage. As shown in [Figure 88], HCI groups the direct attached storage (DAS), which is located under a general-purpose x86 server, with the software-defined storage (SDS) technology through the IP-based network and uses it as a storage pool, similar to a storage area network (SAN): The architecture eliminates the structural complexity and reduces costs most of all by eliminating external storage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:18','2025-04-18 21:12:18'),(1591,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1592,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Text','To be able to explain the HAVFT technology and operational principle To be able to explain the DR configuration and utilization','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1593,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1594,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Text','SPOF, Hot-standby, Mutual takeover, Concurrent access, Mirror site, Hot site, Warm site, Cold site, RPO, RTO, Fault-tolerant technique','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1595,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business Information system failure at Bank A lastir until late in the afternoon, \"Blocked wagesfer\"\' , The Hankyore','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1596,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business Information system failure at Bank A until late in the afternoon lasting','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1597,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1598,'37','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Information systems have the role of not only supporting business, but also creating business A failed bank information system can have an enormous impact. A fire at O0 Card\'s IDC center in 2014 is a similar case Enterprises must improve the availability of information system services, through a high availability (HA) configuration or disaster recovery (DR) center in order to ensure that their information safely and continuously provides service Most major information systems are basically configured with redundancy: An important banking has a spare system, in addition to redundancy, to ensure that the reserve system can continue to provide information services at the time of disasters, such as a earthquake or fire The DR center is a place that provides such a spare system: DR centers are configured in different ways, depending on the importance of the information When a failure or disaster occurs, the time required to recover in order to provide normal service is called the recovery time objective (RTO): Moreover, the tolerable level of data loss in a failure or disaster is called a recovery point objective (RPO): The DR center is classified into a mirror, hot, warm, or cold site, based on RPO and RTO. This section describes techniques for providing service continuity of information systems system system system','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1599,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 89] Availability Calculation Formula',NULL,'6802c04aa7d8e.png','/storage/figures/6802c04aa7d8e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1600,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 90] Availability Indicators',NULL,'6802c04ab2b83.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ab2b83.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1601,'413','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In information systems, HA refers to an uninterrupted service However, it is not easy to make a system,that consists of numerous parts and software, 100% available There must be no failure, or services must be available to users in a usable state, even at the time of failure, in order to guarantee uninterrupted availability In general, the system fails at some Therefore, the way to guarantee service continuity is to prepare for failure, rather than preventing failure HA prepares for failure by configuring two or more systems using clustering: A typical HA criterion targets 99.999% (called 5 nines) , representing less than 5 minutes and 15 seconds of unplanned service downtime per year The scale of the HA level is expressed by the number of nine, and the formula for calculating the availability is the mean time between failures (MTBF), divided by the sum of the MTBF and the mean time to repair (MTTR) point.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1602,'518','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 91] Hot Standby Configuration',NULL,'6802c04abd8ba.png','/storage/figures/6802c04abd8ba.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1603,'518','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Hot standby is the simplest structure of HA clustering implementation It consists of an active server and a standby server that are normally in a standby state The standby server is powered on, and the operating system is running In some cases, a standby server is used as a development system: If the active server fails, due to hardware, network or process problem, the failure is detected by the heartbeat network and all HA service operations are automatically switched to the standby server, through a fail-over operation,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1604,'519','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 92] Mutual Takeover Configuration',NULL,'6802c04ac7da9.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ac7da9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1605,'519','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The mutual takeover is the case of two or more systems operating with separate servers. When a server fails, its services are switched to the designated server (takeover) to continue the services Each server must have sufficient system capacity in order to provide services for the two servers, in preparation for a fail-over at the time of a failure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1606,'520','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 93] Concurrent Access Configuration',NULL,'6802c04ad1ec6.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ad1ec6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1607,'520','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a structure in which multiple systems process tasks in parallel in order to provide availability: All servers operat in an active state Even if a server fails, the service continuity can be guaranteed without a fail-over In this structur two or more servers perform load balancing, using a L4 switch to perform the same task','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1608,'415','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Table 23] Troubleshooting Steps',NULL,'6802c04adfbde.png','/storage/tables/6802c04adfbde.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:42'),(1609,'415','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04b00c25.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b00c25.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1610,'415','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A fault-tolerant system can continuously perform the functions specified in the design, even if a system part fails fault-tolerant system cannot use certain functions when a component fails. When components continue to fail, the unavailable functions gradually increase, and the system shuts down when a critical failure occurs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1611,'416','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Table 25] DR Center Types',NULL,'6802c04b1757c.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b1757c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1612,'416','App\\Models\\Section','Text','DRS is an overall plan and system to minimize the impact of a disaster on a business, by locating all or part of the information system infrastructure in a location different from the disaster point,then quickly recovering from a disaster','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1613,'416','App\\Models\\Section','Text','when it occurs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1614,'417','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'[Table 26] RTO and RPO',NULL,'6802c04b26a8f.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b26a8f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1615,'417','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The most important factors to consider when implementing a DR system are RTO and RPO. RTO represents the tin required to return to normal operation, When a disaster or failure occurs in the operating RPO represents indicator of tolerable data loss, i.e,the amount of data that can be lost. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:19','2025-04-18 21:12:19'),(1616,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1617,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Conventional IT environments, based on high-performance servers represented by mainframes,as well as UNIX servers, are rapidly transforing into cloud computing environments characterized by virtualization,, immediateness, and linear scalability (scale-out). The importance of cloud computing is increasing, particularly with the rapid growth of SNS and Internet services, ad big data and loT become keywords of IT: Understanding cloud computing is essential in order to respond quickly to rapidly changing business environments and to provide an IT environment with continuous scalability','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1618,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1619,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to distinguish and explain the characteristics, concepts, and types of cloud computing: 2 To be able to explain virtualization technologies and components that are the basis of clud computing: 3. To be able to distinguish types of server virtualization technologies for cloud computing and explain the differences','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1620,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1621,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Cloud computing, Cloud type Virtualization, OpenStack Docker, Linux container Mesos, Kubernetes','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1622,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1623,'38','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Gartner which annually publishes strategic technologies for the year began including virtualization in \"Gartner\'s Ten Strategic Technologies\" in 2006 and added cloud computing in 2009. AWS started its service in 2006, achieved annual sales of 5 trillion won in 2014, and generated tremendous sales growth every year Now, cloud services are becoming a necessity, not an option Most of the technologies, such as Al, data, and blockchain, which have recently become the subject of conversation, operate based on cloud services that basically provide scalability and It is why most cloud service providers provide platforms for new technologies The server virtualization is changing: In the past, server virtualization was performed using a hypervisor: In recent years, container-type virtualization has emerged. It is quickly establishing a position in the cloud service market because it is lighter ad faster than the existing methods Typical container technologies include Linux Containers (Lxc), Docker, Kubernetes, and Openshift Top big speed.','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1624,'521','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 28) Differentiation between Grid Computing and Cloud Computing',NULL,'6802c04b36c3d.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b36c3d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1625,'521','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Grid computing is defined as \"a structure for virtualizing ad resources, such as computers ad data, on a network for integration and dynamically creating virtual computers if needed \" Grid computing and cloud computing are similar in that use a distributed computing structure and provide virtualized computing resources. The difference is that computing uses all the computer resources on the Internet, while cloud computing uses only the computing owned hv the onerator they grid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1626,'522','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Utility computing is a type that provides computing resources and charges for the resources used Utility computing and cloud computing are similar, in that charge for the resources used. Cloud computing has developed the abstraction of computing resources, based on utility computing: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1627,'151','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'(Table 27) Definitions of \"Cloud Computing\" and \"Cloud Service\"',NULL,'6802c04b45b4b.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b45b4b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1628,'151','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Cloud computing was developed to efficiently utilize the surplus computer capacity of each server and to flexibly respond to the demand of uncertain services at enterprises While users had to own and manage resources in order to use computer resources before the advent of cloud computing, cloud computing allows them to use computing resources, provided through the Internet, in a virtualized form when need them The to cloud computing is that computer resources are available through the network and are provided in an invisible state so that users can work anywhere using the computer resources need, even without knowing the complex interior Around 2008, various services that utilize computing resources on the Internet were launched, and \"cloud computing\" began to be used as a comprehensive term. Users could access desired services from the Internet without requiring expertise in the technology infrastructure support: The following benefits are expected from cloud services. Costs: CAPEXS  reduction, OPEX\' increase, and TCO reduction Period: Reduced development time and product development Operation: Reduced operating personnel and strengthened resource efficiency Product: Improved product integration they key they they cycle 6 CAPEX (Capital expenditure): Expenditures spent to generate future profits OPEX: Operating expenditure 8 TCO (Total Cost of Ownership): Total cost of owning a system, including the initial investment and maintenance costs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1629,'151','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','elecommunication Association 9TTA defines them as follows:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1630,'523','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','laaS provides infrastructure resources (server, storage, and network) as a service through the Internet: Although the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1631,'523','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','infrastructure resources provided by laaS are generally in a virtualized environment, it is not a must for laaS. The service that provides non-virtualized physical infrastructure resources is called a bare-metal cloud. laaS users must directly manage areas beyond the OS The service is similar to receiving a server that is hosting from an existing service, provided from the users aspect.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1632,'524','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PaaS is a service method in which the concept of SaaS is applied to the development environment: It uses the necessary development and operating environment as a service without building a development and operation environment: The service scope of PaaS ranges, from the application development environment, to the service distribution and operation environment: PaaS provides the network infrastructure to the runtime for application execution, and the management scope of the user is the applications and data above the application runtime For example, a user developing a new Java web application that uses MySQL as a database, can quickly prepare a development/operation environment, and can quickly develop and service applications, by using PaaS service that provides MySQL and Apache Tomcat','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1633,'525','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 94] Management Scope of in Each Cloud Service Type',NULL,'6802c04b53f52.png','/storage/figures/6802c04b53f52.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1634,'525','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SaaS is a service that provides software and is a model that delivers software serviced from the center to users,, through a client, such as a web browser SaaS users can use functions need, without knowing where the software is located, which OS it uses, and in which language it is developed: Leading examples of SaaS include Google Docs and SalesForcecom: SaaS services generally have the following characteristics: Access with a web browser: Access with a web browser, instead of an installed software Usage-based cost: Paying fees, based on software use On-demand: Needed software available immediately IT requirement optimization: No management and scalability issues with the IT infrastructure [Figure 94] shows the management scope of laaS, PaaS, and SaaS users and service providers. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1635,'419','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Cloud services can be classified into laaS (Infrastructure as a Service), PaaS (Platform as a Service), and SaaS (Software as a Service), according to the service type','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1636,'420','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 29) Cloud Service Type Based on Disclosure Level',NULL,'6802c04b66676.png','/storage/tables/6802c04b66676.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1637,'420','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Cloud services can be classified into three levels, based on the service operation form: The following table shows th classification.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1638,'421','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In server virtualization, a host OS is a physical server and a guest OS is a virtually provided server Server virtualization technology can be classified, according to how a virtual server allocates physical resources in order to make it look like a physical server A hypervisor is a technology of virtualizing a physical server It is a logical platform for server virtualization It is also called a virtual machine monitor (VMM). The hypervisor can be classified by how it is installed and virtualized.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1639,'526','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 95] Native Type Hypervisor',NULL,'6802c04b73504.png','/storage/figures/6802c04b73504.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1640,'526','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This type installs a VMM on physical hardware and requires no host OS. It saves resources, compared to the virtualization requiring a host OS, since there is no host OS. The native type is also called typel . The leading native virtualization technologies include Xen, XenServer from Citri, ESXServerBMWare, Power Hypervisor from IBM, and Hyper-V and KVM from Microsoft','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1641,'527','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 96] Native Hypervisor',NULL,'6802c04b7d68b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04b7d68b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1642,'527','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The hosted hypervisor (see [Figure 96]) is software installed on an existing OS. The leading hosted type hypervisc includes VirtualPC Microsoft, Workstation from VMWare, and VirtualBox from Oracle from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1643,'422','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Hyperviors are classified into native types and hosted types, according to the installation method. The native type is installed directly on the hardware, while the hosted type (see [Figure 95]) is installed on an OS, like conventional programs,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:20'),(1644,'528','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 97] Full Virtualization Conceptual Diagran',NULL,'6802c04b888e6.png','/storage/figures/6802c04b888e6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:20','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1645,'528','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Full virtualization completely virtualizes the hardware Although the guest OS perceives that it owns ad accesses the hardware directly, the virtual server uses the resources that the hypervisor emulates to look like hardware: If the guest OS intends to monopolize the hardware, the hypervisor must handle these commands separately. A CPU (Intels VT or AMD-V) that supports virtualization is necessary to emulate hardware resources other than the CPU, fully: The performance has greatly increased since the hypervisor, included in the CPU, handles it at high speed. There is no need to modify the guest OS, since the CPU handles full virtualization: Therefore, there are no restrictions on the guest OS. Linux-based guest OS and Windows guest OS can operate simultaneously: The native hypervisor generally corresponds to full virtualization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1646,'529','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 98] Para-virtualization Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c04b936b1.png','/storage/figures/6802c04b936b1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1647,'529','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Para-virtualization does not completely virtualize the hardware, and the guest OS must operate through the hypervisor in order to access the hardware resources. It is a method of using the hypervisor API, without hardware emulation It is necessary to partially modify the guest OSs kernel to use the hypervisor API. It has the advantage of providing a high performance, since it can control it through a hypervisor, without hardware emulation.It has the disadvantage that it can use only an open-source OS as a guest OS, since the kernel of the guest OS needs to be partially modified,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1648,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 30) Comparison of Hypervisor Virtualization and OS-Level Virtualization',NULL,'6802c04ba27c4.png','/storage/tables/6802c04ba27c4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1649,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 99] OS-Level Virtualization',NULL,'6802c04bb00df.png','/storage/figures/6802c04bb00df.png','2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1650,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a virtualization technology that makes the system look like its another OS on the OS. It uses the virtualization technology included in the OS, instead of a hypervisor The container technology that allocates and isolates the resources included in the OS has gained interest The leading OS-level virtualization technologies include Solaris Containers, FreeBSD Jails, and Linux Docker: The guest OS must be the same as the host OS, since it uses the OSs container function, instead of a hypervisor Containers on the OS are allocated resources, such as memory, storage, and network which are independently operated between containers. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1651,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Container virtualization technology can be characterized as being lighter and more portable than existing virtualization technologies In Linux containers (LXC) , there is kernel space for managing physical resources, and a user space for executing user processes inside the OS. The container virtualization technology partitions the user space into ten and limits the resources visible in each user process:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1652,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','OS-level virtualization (container virtualization) has the following advantages: Quick start and finish: fast compared to hypervisor-based virtualization High density: Minimized resource consumption, since an OS can operate multiple containers Low overhead: Userspace isolated without emulation Very `','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1653,'530','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','level virtualization has the following disadvantages: st OS-dependent t possible to configure the kernel for each container','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1654,'423','App\\Models\\Section','Text','According to the virtualization method, server virtualization technology can be classified into full virtualization, para virtualization, and OS-level virtualization:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1655,'153','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The conventional computing environment generally installs an OS-dependent on single hardware and runs applications above the OS. Virtualization refers to the technology of abstracting the computer resources of multiple computers to make them look like servers or by abstracting the computer resources of a computer to make them look like multiple computers. Since the server virtualization technology makes it possible to run one or more operating systems on a computer it can maximize the utilization rate of computer resources and management efficiency: Cloud services generally use virtualization technology to provide abstract computer resources to users The x86 virtualization technology, in particular has been rapidly spread, based on the technology and market maturity and has become the basis of the cloud computing environment for the logic sharing and allocation of computing resources bevond the phvsical limitations','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1656,'424','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It enables service implementation by virtually allocating only the minimum space initially required, with thin- provisioning technology, instead of configuring the required storage space Moreover it provides a environment use heterogeneous storage system integration.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1657,'425','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It implements L2, L3, and L7 switches, network firewalls, and security devices that existed in the form of hardwar appliances as virtual machines It enables networking resources to operate separately through intemal virtualizatio even in a shared physical environment','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1658,'426','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A cloud platform is a cloud operation system to collect, control, and operate resources, such as servers, storage networks, and virtualization technologies','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1659,'531','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Nova: The core component for automatic control and the operation of large-scale virtual computer instances Swift: Implementation of large-scale, reliable cloud object storage services Glance: Storage, registration, management, and delivery of virtual disk image files Keystone: Integrated authentication and authority system Cinder: Volume replication, snapshot support, and block storage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1660,'531','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Ceilometer: Mirroring support HoriZone: Self-service portal Heat: Restoration and system recovery Neutron: Network service Trove: Delivery of database services Sahara: Support for Sparkldata process and Hadoo','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1661,'427','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Openstack is an open-source project that develops all software blocks needed to build public and private clou computing platforms It also refers to the community of open-source developers, enterprises, and users that want implement and operate cloud computing with open source: Moreover Openstack establishes industry standards cloud computing platforms, independent of the equipment type or vendors implementation technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1662,'428','App\\Models\\Section','Text','CloudStack is the cloud computing open-source project developed by cloud.com and managed by the Apache Foundation by Citrix','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1663,'429','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Kubernetes is an orchestration platform for container management and operation. Google open-sourced the operation know-how that was developed for its services. Developers can manage and schedule multiple containers from a node with declarative programming: When a specific configuration is specified through the Kubernetes Control Plane, Kuberetes utomatically maintains the state','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1664,'430','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Mesos is a resource management project that enables that integrated management of cloud infrastructure resources and computing engine resources. It provides a function to group distributed computing resources connected by a network into a resource pool and make it look like single computing resources When a user requests the execution of an application program, it allocates an instance and allows the application program to run: Mesos consists of the Marathon and Chronos frameworks. Marathon allocates resources and creates jobs, while Chronos is responsible for schedulino','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1665,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1666,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Modern society had passed the Big Data 1.0 era, when the quantitative explosion of big data began and entered the Big Data 2.0 era, which creates practical values from big data. The introduction of Hadoop 2.2 has made big data technology more sophisticated and diversified the professional services of the big data vendors from the big data supply aspect, leading to the emergence of companies that specialize in big data The demand for big data is rapidly increasing as large companies are quickly adopting the technology, mainly in the financial and services industries Companies that have adopted big data are practically using big data for business through pilot tests, beyond simply using big data for information collection: Governments are implementing policies to promote RRD and professional training, building industry-academia-R&D governance, and data disclosure Of course, big data expansion has produced side effects, such as privacy infringement and personal profiling: Therefore it is necessary to strengthen theflexibility of data use by establishing a new concept for personal data use. Comprehensive policy support that reflects the social and market environments is necessary for the data ecosystem to evolve: public big','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1667,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1668,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the concept of big data systems 2 To be able to explain big dala system structure and characteristics 3. To be able to discover the recent trends of big data systems','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:21','2025-04-18 21:12:21'),(1669,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1670,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Data acquisition, storage, processing, analysis, presentation, Hadoop ecosystem, HDFS, MapReduce,, Hadoop support program','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1671,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Practical preview','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1672,'39','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Company A is a online retailer Until recently, it competed for the No. 1or 2 position in the domestic market, but has experienced declining sales, due to the influence of cheap imports from China entering the domestic online market. Therefore, the company needs a new competitive edge. Firstly, it wants to establish a new marketing strategy by collecting ad analyzing customer data It intends to expand the infrastructure in order to collect big data beyond the existing database and to hire analysts from outside to analyze the collected data. This case shows why enterprises seek to find ways to collect, store, analyze, and utilize big data, This chapter describes the big data svstem in more detail,','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1673,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 100] Hadoop Ecosystem',NULL,'6802c04bc11c8.png','/storage/figures/6802c04bc11c8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1674,'431','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Understanding the big data system structure begins with understanding the Hadoop ecosystem Hadoop, the abbreviation of High-availability distributed object-oriented platform, refers to a Java-based framework for the distributed processing of a large volume of data in multiple distributed storage It is an initial solution and consists of the Hadoop distributed file system (HDFS) and Map Reduce: However, these two modules are based on open source, and it was difficult for non-: specialists to utilize big data: The modules are packaged with various peripheral modules, as shown in [Figure 100], to solve the problem: These peripheral modules support data integration and migration, application management, and system management, and have been developed as part of the Hadoop project they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1675,'532','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 101] HDFS Architecture',NULL,'6802c04bcf7f3.png','/storage/figures/6802c04bcf7f3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1676,'532','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','HDFS is a distributed file system to store data in the devices connected to the Hadoop network HDFS prevents data loss by also storing replicated data in multiple nodes. It is necessary to access data through streaming in order to store files in HDFS or query the stored files. The data integrity is ensured as stored data cannot be modified and can be read-only: (Version 2.0 or higher allows appending to the saved file) Although it does not allow data modification it provides an interface to move, delete, and copy files As shown in [Figure 101], HDFS consists of one NameNode serverthat serves as a master, and multiple DataNode servers, that serve as slaves. The NameNode server manages all metadata (the name of the directory where the blocks are stored, the file name, etc:) of HDFS, and the client can access the files stored in the HDFS by using it Hadoop applications use HDFS clients to store files or to read the stored files in HDFS, and provide the clients to users in API. The DataNode server periodically transfers a block report (information of the block stored in the node) from the NameNode, which helps the NameNode to confirm the DataNode\'s normal operation Therefore, the client can log in to the NameNode to check the blocks location that stores the file and directly query the data from the DataNode that stores the block they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1677,'533','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 102] Process of Outputting the Frequency of Words Included in a Character String through MapReduce',NULL,'6802c04bdfb63.png','/storage/figures/6802c04bdfb63.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:43'),(1678,'533','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MapReduce is a distributed programming model and software framework for processing a large volume of data The MapReduce framework makes it possible to analyze data in with a large-scale distributed computing environment MapReduce consists of two methods, Map and Reduce, that the programmer writes parallel Classifies scattered data into relevant data (key or value type). Reduce: Removes duplicate data from data output by the map and extracts the desired data Map: Reduce: Removes duplicate data from data output by the map and extracts the desired data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1679,'533','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Figure 102] below shows an example of MapReduce outputting the frequency of words included in a character string: The process consists of dividing the string data by line (splitting) 5 Receiving the string by line and outputting it in the form of Value  (mapping) 3 Separating data by the key (shuffling) ~Calulating the sum of the frequency of each and outputting it (reducing) Combines the output data and stores it in the Hadoop file system (final result) <Key, key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1680,'433','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 31) Hadoop Support Service Programs',NULL,'6802c04c02113.png','/storage/tables/6802c04c02113.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1681,'433','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04c1b58c.png','/storage/tables/6802c04c1b58c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1682,'433','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in <Table 31  , Hadoop support service programs to collect, store, utilize, process, and manage big data, are in development','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1683,'434','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04c324bb.png','/storage/tables/6802c04c324bb.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1684,'434','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04c425b8.png','/storage/tables/6802c04c425b8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1685,'434','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Leading companies that develop and distribute open-source commercial Hadoop solutions include Cloudera, Hortonworks, and Map R These companies create internal platforms, based on Hadoop, and distribute solutions through the strategic alliance with existing databases, data warehousing, and business intelligence solution companies :','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1686,'534','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Big data service providers form a corporate ecosystem by promoting strategies to solve problems, such as real-time processing, memory-based processing, ease of query, and accessibility to various file systems that big data must overcome system Companies like Amazon, that have already secured cloud capabilities, are trying to build unique platforms by their cloud and open source-based big data solutions. IBM, Microsoft, and others, that were leaders in corporate information systems, have modified their strategies to focus on big data, utilizing their existing competency Google, Apple, and other mobile-based emerging companies, are building big data analysis systems, based on existing servers and user data to provide their services linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1687,'535','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Companies that are implementing big data systems are divided into those that provide a total solution and those that provide solutions in a specific area. Companies like Amazon, IBM, and Google create internal platforms that support the entire process of big data analysis and provide consulting to other enterprises, based on them generating revenue Solution companies like Teradata and Good Data that implement functions, such as analysis and visualization for big data, also strive to implement unique performance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1688,'536','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many technologies related to Hadoop, the leading technology for big data, are currently being developed to the extent that it has the Hadoop ecosystem: However it is still technically too difficult for non-engineers to use, without significant help from engineers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1689,'537','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the growth of open source-based technologies, the competitive landscape has been established to facilitate small venture companies that provide user-centered customized software, as well as traditional cloud companies, to grow in the market','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1690,'538','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Starting with IBM Watson and Google AlphaGo, expectations for the industrial use of Al has risen significantly: Traditional cloud companies target consumers by linking their infrastructure and Al, and are building newly expanded ecosystems by cooperating with competitors they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:22','2025-04-18 21:12:22'),(1691,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1692,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Communication is established by transferring data through electrical or optical signals over physical media. In the OSI 7 hierarchy, the physical layer is at the bottom, and one can understand the mechanisms at the lower-level network by learning the media and standards for this physical layer Moreover, it is necessary to understand the datalink layer that connects the physical media and standards with the upper layers, and to further learn the media access control method and the logical link control method','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1693,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1694,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the sub-layer (datalink control and media access control) of the datalink laye 2 To be able to explain the error detection on the datalink layer and error correction techniques','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1695,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1696,'40','App\\Models\\Module','Text','LLC, Topology, CSMA/CD, CSMACA, ARP, RARP, Forward error correction, Backward error correction, Turbo code, Convolution code, BCH, Hamming code, Reed-Solomon, test, Checksum test, Cyclic redundancy check (CRC), Top-standby ARQ, Go-Back-N,, Selective-repeat, Adaptive ARQ, H-ARQ, VRC, LRC, Optical cable, IEEE 802.11, DSSS, OFDM, MIMO, 256-QAM, FHSS, Beamforming, UHD, IEEE 802.15, WPAN, ZigBee, Bluetooth, UWB Parity','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1697,'158','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 103] Operation Path of datalink Layer',NULL,'6802c04c526a6.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c526a6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1698,'158','App\\Models\\Lesson','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1699,'158','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','[Step 3-3] An initial packet that contains the information for routing between networks is created However, it must be further modified to be transferred between networks The IPv4 address of user A\'s computer is 192.168.11.5 and cannot be transmitted to myserver com directly: It must be transmitted to the computers gateway wiredjwireless router B (192.168.11.1). However, an IP address cannot be used for data transfer in a network, and the MAC address is needed for it. After the MAC address corresponding to 192.168.11.1, the gateways IP address, the packet is transmitted to wiredjwireless router B, through network broadcasting: [Step 3-5] Upon receiving the packet, router C recognizes that the packet is sent to network 220.17.23.0, to which the router belongs, and intends to transmit it to the webserver\'s IP address 220.17.23.15. As is in [Step 3-3], since the packet movement in a network requires the physical address of myservercom, the MAC address, it obtains the MAC address corresponding to myservercom\' s IP address,, 220.17.23.15, through the network broadcasting and transmits the packet finding','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1700,'159','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The datalink layer transmits data between peripheral devices on the network, the physical layer that transmits signals between devices, and is responsible for address allocation and error detection: The address allocation function ensures that devices properly receive signals the physical layer on the network, and the error detection function detects whether errors are included in the transmitted signals. using from Application software developers have no problem in programming without understanding the datalink layer and the physical layer However, a network product may need debugging for cases where there is no network connection or data error: If a product uses various medium access control (MAC) layers, it may be necessary to understand each standard protocol: Moreover, developing embedded software requires a basic understanding of drivers since it may be necessary to develop a driver If the embedded software does not operate normally after the program is ported to the test environment prepared by the hardware developer, it is necessary to perform debugging to determine whether it is a hardware or a software problem: The developer needs to perform debugging, JTAG, or in the case of a network environment, check whether an error occurs in the actual physically transmitted bit and datalink layer As short-range wireless communication technologies such as Bluetooth and ZigBee, have been recently widely applied, understanding the datalink layer has become more important using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1701,'437','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 104] Encapsulation of the Datalink Layer',NULL,'6802c04c608fc.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c608fc.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1702,'437','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in the following figure, the datalink layer frame adds a header and a trailer to the network layer packet: This process is called encapsulation of the datalink layerThe process is reversed on the receiving end ad is called decapsulation:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1703,'438','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The frame header includes a preamble for bit synchronization between hosts, a start of frame delimiter (SFD) that','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1704,'438','App\\Models\\Section','Text','indicates the start of a frame, and destination and source addresses, which are physical addresses Physical addresses have a 48-bit address system and have unique values for each device, unlike logical IP addresses. It is necessary to use the physical address to check a device location below layer 2, since IP addresses are used in layer 3. Trailers include a check sequence (FCS) to check for errors a data transfer frame during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1705,'439','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 105] Sub-layers of datalink layer',NULL,'6802c04c6e701.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c6e701.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1706,'439','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A datalink layer consists of two sub-layers: an LLC (Logical Link Control) sub-layer and a MAC (Media Access Control) sub-layer The LLC sub-layer is responsible for the connection between the MAC sub-layer &d the network layer (layer 3). The lower MAC sub-layers are responsible for control according to the topology on physical layers or other characteristics','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1707,'539','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 106] IEEE 802.3 Frame Structure',NULL,'6802c04c79b2b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c79b2b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1708,'539','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The sub-layer is located at a higher level among the sub-layers of the datalink layer: It is responsible for the data transfer between two adjacent nodes on the IEEE 802.2 or datalink layer network The adjacent nodes have the destination service access point (DSAP) and the source service access point (SSAP) on the LLC layer The LLC layer can use various MAC sub-layer protocols to facilitate the communication, regardless of the network topology:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1709,'540','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The LLC options include Type 1, Type 2, and Type 3. Type is a unconfirmed datagram service and called an unconnected service, as it does not require a receipt confirmation message Type 2 is a virtual circuit access type and, as a TCP service, transfers data after establishing a virtual session Type 3 is a confirmed datagram service and provides the receipt confirmed datagram in the point-to-point method.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1710,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 107] MAC Address Configuration',NULL,'6802c04c84264.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c84264.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1711,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The MAC sub-layer is responsible for determining how to transfer data through the physical media. The MAC layer includes the MAC addresses of the transmitting and receiving systems, as shown in [Figure 107] below: The MAC address is mainly divided into two addresses The first 224is OUI (Organizationally Unique Identifier), representing the manufacturer identification code, and the remaining 224 is the serial number of the NIC produced by the manufacturer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1712,'441','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The standardized MAC protocols include the CSMACD type IEEE 802.3,the token bus type IEEE 802.4, and the token ring type IEEE 802.5 for wired LAN The CSMACA type IEEE 802.11 MAC sub-layer is used for wireless LAN.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1713,'442','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 108] ARP packet structure',NULL,'6802c04c914aa.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c914aa.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1714,'442','App\\Models\\Section','Text','To transfer & packet to another host, requires the host\'s MAC address. ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) is responsible for it. The protocols to convert the IP ad MAC addresses are the ARP and RARP (Reverse Address Resolution Protocol): The ARP that has the following address checks the MAC address through the IP address, and RARP is the inverse address conversion protocol that checks the IP address through the MAC address The ARP packet is organized of the 6-byte destination MAC address, 6-byte source MAC address, 2-byte Etheret protocol type, 2-byte hardware type, 2-byte protocol type, 1-byte hardware address length, 1-byte protocol address length, 2-byte operation code, 6-byte sender hardware address, 4-byte sender protocol address, 6-byte target hardware address, 4-byte target protocol address, and 18-byte padding:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1715,'443','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since Router C and computer with user A are in the same network section, with user A, as shown in [Figure 103], the MAC address is required for communication In that case, the computer with user A sends & ARP request through broadcasting to all systems in the network section The data section of the frame, transferred through the ARP request, contains the ARP packet, as shown in [Figure 108]. On receiving the response, router  transfers its MAC address in the ARP packet to the computer with user A through unicast, to find each other\'s MAC address The MAC address is stored in each system\'s cache memory: In that case, wiredjwireless router B stores the port-MAC address table of the svstem connected to its cache memorv ports','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1716,'444','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 109] Error Control Types',NULL,'6802c04c9f327.png','/storage/figures/6802c04c9f327.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1717,'444','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Transferring frames through the data link layer can cause various errors, depending on the network condition or the operation of the transmitting and receiving device Types of errors include single-bit errors, in which only one bit of the data part is changed, multi-bit errors, in which two or more non-contiguous bits are changed in the data unit, and burst errors, in which two or more consecutive bits are changed Error control is the function of detecting and correcting errors when transmitted data does not arrive properly, or when an error occurs during transmission: Error control methods can be divided into two types, as shown in [Figure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1718,'444','App\\Models\\Section','Text','109]. Forward error correction (FEC) allows the receiving device to detect errors and recover from them by itself by transmitting a spare bit for error recovery in the packet Backward error correction (BEC) notifies an error to the transmitting device to recover from the error, when an error occurs during the data transmission','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:23'),(1719,'541','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 32) Error Detection Methods',NULL,'6802c04cadaa2.png','/storage/tables/6802c04cadaa2.png','2025-04-18 21:12:23','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1720,'541','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error detection uses the redundancy (spare) concept by adding a spare bit to detect the destinations error Errc detection methods include VRC (Vertical Redundancy Check), LRC (Longitudinal Redundancy Check) , CRC (Cycli Redundancy Check) , and checksum, <Table 32  shows details of each detection method,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1721,'542','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 33) Error Correction Methods',NULL,'6802c04cbeb48.png','/storage/tables/6802c04cbeb48.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1722,'542','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error correction methods include a method in which the receiving device requests the sending device to retransmit the entire data, or the receiving device automatically performs a correction using an error correction code','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1723,'543','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 34) ARQ Types',NULL,'6802c04cd3b43.png','/storage/tables/6802c04cd3b43.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1724,'543','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ARQ is an algorithm in Which the receiving side informs the sending side of the error and the sending side retransmit= the error to correct the error Typical ARQ methods include stop-and-wait ARQ, Go-back-N ARQ, and adaptive ARQ Details of each retransmission algorithm type are shown in the <Table 34  below: frame','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1725,'446','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 110] Services for Each Layer',NULL,'6802c04ce70c2.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ce70c2.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:44'),(1726,'446','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[Figure 110] shows the services for each layer ad defined by the IEE Committee The LLC layer includes, Type 3 unconfirmed datagram service, Type2 virtual circuit service, and Type 3 confirmed datagram service','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1727,'446','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The physical medium access control (MAC) layer includes the IEEE 802.3 CDMACD MAC, IEEE 802.4 token bus MAC, and IEEE 802.5 token ring MAC.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1728,'447','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 111] IEEE 802.3 Protocol Stack',NULL,'6802c04d0140d.png','/storage/figures/6802c04d0140d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1729,'447','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IEEE 802.3 protocol stack the most widely used IEE 802 standard, includes IEEE 802.2 that corresponds to the LLC layer of the datalink layer and IEEE 802.3 that include the MAC layer and the physical layer, IEEE 802.5 token ring and FDDI','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1730,'448','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 35) IEEE 802.11 Protocol Standards',NULL,'6802c04d10973.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d10973.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1731,'448','App\\Models\\Section','Text','EEE 802.11 is the name of the wireless communication standardization committee for wireless LAN, called Wi-Fi,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1732,'448','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It seeks to minimize work ad maintenance costs to compensate for the shortcomings of wired LAN-type Ethernet It includes IEEE 80211b using the DSSS modulation method at the maximum transmission speed of 11 Mbps, IEEE 802.11a supporting a of up to 54 Mbps by using the frequency of the 5 GHz band and the OFDM modulation method, and IEEE 80211g using the frequency of the 2.4 GHz band to support the speed of 54 Mbps. IEEE 802.1In uses the 2.4GHz and the SGHz bands and supports MIMO (Multiple-Input, Multiple-Output) to increase the transmission speed up to 600Mbps Wireless AP products supporting the speed of Gpbs have recently been introduced. IEEE 802.IIac supports a theoretical maximum speed of 6.93Gbps by applying the 80/16OMHz bandwidth, multi-user MIMOmulti-spatial stream MIMO, 256-QAM modulation, and beamforming IEEE 802.11ad is a standard that supports the speed of Gbps by applying various technologies in the 6OGHz bandwidth The standard for gigabit wireless LAN technology to transmitting UHD-level video and explosively increasing wireless data at high speed is in development wiring speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1733,'449','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 36) IEEE 802.15 Protocol Standards',NULL,'6802c04d1f94b.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d1f94b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1734,'449','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IEEE 802.15 is the name of the short-range wireless communication standardization committee separated from IEEE 802.11, which standardizes wireless LAN. It seeks to establish wireless networks for mobile communication devices, PCs, and other peripheral devices in the home. Sub-organizations include, the WPAN (Wireless Personal Area Network) research group, for a maximum transmission rate of IMbps, and WPAN HSRC (WPAN High Rate Study Group) , with a maximum transmission rate of 2OMbps. The leading WPAN technologies, corresponding to the IEEE 802.15 standard, are IEEE 802.15.1 Bluetooth, IEEE 802.15.3 UWB, and IEEE 802.15.4 ZigBee: IEEE 802.15.1 Bluetooth is a short-range wireless communication technology standard for exchanging information by connecting mobile devices, such as mobile phones and laptops. IEEE 802.15.3 UAB is a wireless technology that quickly transmits a large volume of digital data through a large spectrum frequency at low power in an ultra- broadband and short distance. IEEE 802.15.4 ZigBee is a standard technology for home automation and data networks with low data transmission rates: Embedded software developers should be able to select the chipset and the communication method to control the chipset, ad to check which development tools are available, and have a broad understanding of the chipset by reviewing the specification of ZigBee and Bluetooth In general,, the software developer should check the following in the chipset specification: Block diagram: Understanding of the overall configuration and of the chipset Communication method: Chipset control methods, such as SPI I2C, etc, Memory: RAM, ROM, and memory size available to developers, address methods, etc: GPIO: Port type and setting method for external signal input and output control Development tool: Tools necessary to develop with the chipset flow According to the application field, the hardware developer reviews the initial chipset to develop an embedded product and reviews the entire circuit configuration through the chipset. The hardware developer reviews the chipset in terms of electrical characteristics, reliability, complexity in circuit configuration, and chipset package according to device design, and cost The software developer reviews if the chipset meets the standard, whether the control method is convenient, whether the existing control method can be reused, whether the memory capacity is adequate, whether the number of ports for IO control required by the target product is sufficient, whether the chipset should be separated, and whether it is preferable to have multiple functions in a chipset The software developer should select the ontimal chincet after cufficient concultation with the hardiware develoner','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:24','2025-04-18 21:12:24'),(1735,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1736,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Text','A network layer is the most closely related to data transmission, among the network standard and plays an important role in efficient data transmission  Through this chapter, you will understand how IP-based packets are generated, how they are efficiently transmitted in the Internet network, and how to move and process data over the network This chapter describes the routers basic structure, which is a device of the network layer the principle of packet routing the routing algorithm, and the actual implemented routing protocol. layers','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1737,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1738,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the protocol concept and equipment of the nelwork layer: 2 To be able to explain the routing protocol concept, types, and algorithms 3 To be able to understand the IPVv4 address specitication system and subnetting:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1739,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1740,'41','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Router, Routing table, Packet, PDU, Datagram type, Virtual line type, APIPA , Segment, Metrics, MTU, STP, ARP, RARP, ICMP, IGMP, QoS, Bandwidth, IntServ, RSVP, DiffServ, Routing algorithm, Routing protocol, EGP, IGP, Distance vector, Link state, BGP RIP, IGRP, OSPF, IPv4 Subnetting, Supernetting, APIPA, CIDR, DHCP,, NAT','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1741,'450','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 112] Router Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c04d2fcf7.png','/storage/figures/6802c04d2fcf7.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1742,'450','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The above sections described the network layer operation and related scenarios, as shown in [Figure 112] [Step 3-2]) Information created by the TCP protocol is capsulized in order to be routed to the 220.17.23.0 network, in which my servercom is present, through several hops (IP): [Step 3-3] An initial packet that contains the information for routing between networks is created. However, it must be further modified to be transferred between networks. The IPv4 address of user As computer is 192.168.11.5 and cannot be transmitted to myservercom directly: It must be transmitted to the computer\'s gateway wiredjwireless router B (192.168.11.1). However, an IP address cannot be used for data transfer in a network so the MAC address is needed. After the MAC address that corresponds to 192.168.11.1, the gateways IP address, the packet is transmitted to wired ireless router B, through network broadcasting: Step 3-4] Upon receiving the packet user As computer, wiredjwireless router B, aware that the packet is not sent to the router as the final destination, examines to which address the packet must be transmitted The IP header indicates that the packet\'s final destination is myserver com, and since it does not belong to network 192.168.11.0 or 14.32.172.0, to Which wired/ wireless router B belongs, it transmits the packet to router C, to Which it belongs [Step 3-6] Upon receiving the packet, myservercom examines the IP address and recognizes that the packet was sent to it It removes the header data, such as the IP address, and sends the remaining data up to a higher layer finding from','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1743,'165','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Preview for practical business','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1744,'451','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 113] Network Layer in TCPIIP',NULL,'6802c04d3d25f.png','/storage/figures/6802c04d3d25f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1745,'451','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The network layer is the third layer of the OSI 7 model and TCPIIP and sends packets, from a transmitting side, to receiving side It receives a segment from the transmitting layer, encapsulates it, and sends it to the datalink layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1746,'452','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 37) Network Layer Functions',NULL,'6802c04d4bd70.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d4bd70.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1747,'452','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The transmitting side of the network layer performs payload encapsulation, and the receiving side performs payload decapsulation The packetizing function is responsible for ensuring that there is no change to the payload data transmission The routing function finds a through which packets can be delivered. The forwarding function is performed by a router when a packet arrives through one interface on the router When performing forwarding, the router creates a decision table by applying the routing rules The decision table is also called the forwarding or routing table during path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1748,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 38) Internetworking Equipment',NULL,'6802c04d5c4a3.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d5c4a3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1749,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 39} Protocol Layers and Device for Each Layer',NULL,'6802c04d6b0f3.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d6b0f3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1750,'453','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Internetworking refers to a connection between networks. The leading interetworking equipment includes repeaters, bridges, switches, and routers. This section describes for which of the OSI 7 layers and TCPIIP 4 layers these internetworking devices are responsible The router performs packet routing through the IP address on the network layer The bridge and switch are responsible for frame transfer on the datalink layer, while the hub and repeater transfer physical signals on the physical layer < Table 39  compares the function of each device with the protocol layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1751,'544','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 39) Router Shape [2]',NULL,'6802c04d7a620.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d7a620.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1752,'544','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 40) Routing Metrics [3]',NULL,'6802c04d8b082.png','/storage/tables/6802c04d8b082.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1753,'544','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 114] Router Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c04d9ddd9.png','/storage/figures/6802c04d9ddd9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1754,'544','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 114], a router mostly consists of a router control plane and a forwarding plane: The control plane, implemented in the software in a router determines where to send the packets it receives and uses tables to decide The forwarding plane actually sends the packets according to the requirements created by the control plane <Table 39  shows the shapes of a router: Small networks mostly use cisco 2500, while larger networks use cis 7300.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1755,'544','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It refers to the data collected by a router at a given time, when the traffic passes through the <Table 40 shows the metric types. path','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:25'),(1756,'545','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 115] Routing Table',NULL,'6802c04db1aee.png','/storage/figures/6802c04db1aee.png','2025-04-18 21:12:25','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1757,'545','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A routing table is a database that stores the output interface of each destination network and the next IP address, hop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1758,'454','App\\Models\\Section','Text','router forwards traffic and determines the optimal path, using one or more metrics In other words, it forwards packets one network, to aother based on the network layer information from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1759,'455','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 41) Main Switch Functions',NULL,'6802c04dbf9d8.png','/storage/tables/6802c04dbf9d8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1760,'455','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A switch is a device that connects network units, A switch device has a important role in MAC address learning filtering, and prevention: Other switch functions include port mirroring and VLAN. Port mirroring, also callec port monitoring, is the function of sending a replicate of the data sent from a specific port to a mirrored port: It is ar mportant function used by administrators to monitor network traffic through the mirrored port loop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1761,'456','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 42) Comparison of Switch and Router',NULL,'6802c04dcbb8b.png','/storage/tables/6802c04dcbb8b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1762,'456','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 116] VLAN Configuration [4]',NULL,'6802c04dda703.png','/storage/figures/6802c04dda703.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1763,'456','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VLAN is a method of configuring a logical network, desired by the user, to overcome the physical and regional constraints of the existing networks In other words, it uses the IP unit, protocol unit, MAC address, and connecting to configure a logical network instead of separating networks by and geographical locations The VLAN protocols of a switch include ISL, 802.1Q, and VTP ISL and 802.1Q are the VLAN tagging protocols, and VTP is a AN management protocol spatial port','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1764,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 117] Network Layer Encapsulation',NULL,'6802c04de4e3f.png','/storage/figures/6802c04de4e3f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:45'),(1765,'457','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As shown in [Figure 117], the packets on the network layer are configured by adding a header to the transmitting layer segment This process is called encapsulation of the datalink layer, and the process is reversed on the receiving end and is called decapsulation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1766,'458','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 118] Network Packet Structure [5]',NULL,'6802c04e0726c.png','/storage/figures/6802c04e0726c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1767,'458','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In [Figure 118] above, Version\" refers to the protocol version of the datagram, \"IHL\" refers to the header length, and Type of Service\" refers to which type of service the host wants in the subnet Total length\" refers to the sum of the header and data lengths in the datagram, \'Time to Live\" refers to the packet life limit, and Protocol\" refers to the notification of TCP or UDP for the recombination of the datagram on the network layer \"Source Address\" and Destination Address\" refer to the source and destination addresses of the 32-bit datagram:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1768,'459','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The methods of finding the packet in a packet-exchanging network, include the datagram approach and the virtual circuit approach: The datagram approach is a non-connected service that independently processes all packets Packets can be transferred through different paths, and the packet\'s destination address determines the forwarding The virtual circuit approach is a connection-oriented service It establishes a virtual for the datagram before the transfer, and all datagrams are transmitted to the same after the connection The forwarding is determined by the packet label (virtual circuit identifier): path path path: path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1769,'460','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 43) Network Layer Protocols',NULL,'6802c04e19746.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e19746.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1770,'460','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 119] Network Layer Protocols',NULL,'6802c04e27bc3.png','/storage/figures/6802c04e27bc3.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1771,'460','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The network layer protocols that convert the IP and MAC addressesinto an IP address, are the ARP (Address Resolution Protocol) and the RARP (Reverse Address Resolution Protocol): ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) is a protocol used to transfer the network error information, and IGMP (Internet Group Management Protocol) is the protocol for IP multicast transfer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1772,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 44} Network Layer Commands',NULL,'6802c04e3b350.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e3b350.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1773,'461','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Table 44  shows commands to check the network layer status or perform a specific actio','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1774,'462','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 45) QoS Measurements',NULL,'6802c04e4a1f5.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e4a1f5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1775,'462','App\\Models\\Section','Text','QoS is the technology of guaranteeing a service quality and performance of a communication service to meet use requirements. The attributes to determine the QoS include confidence, delay, jitter, and bandwidth, as shown <Table 45','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1776,'546','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 46} Packet Scheduling Methods',NULL,'6802c04e5aba9.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e5aba9.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1777,'546','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Routers are responsible for handling packets over the Internet  Therefore, the packet flow can differ according to the schedule:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1778,'547','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 47) Traffic Shaping and Traffic Policing',NULL,'6802c04e6a92c.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e6a92c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1779,'547','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a way to control the traffic speed and volume, traffic shaping is used when the traffic leaves the network, and traffic policing is used when the traffic enters the network','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1780,'548','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is the method of reserving resources, such as buffer, bandwidth, CPU, and time needed for data flowfor a specific service to ensure the service quality:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1781,'549','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is a procedure used by the control unit of a communication network to determine whether to accept a connection request.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1782,'550','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 48} Service Quality Model and Protocol [6]',NULL,'6802c04e79aab.png','/storage/tables/6802c04e79aab.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1783,'550','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Service quality models include the integrated service (IntServ) model and the differentiated service (DiffServ) mode The service quality protocol is the resource reservation protocol (RSVP):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1784,'464','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Routing protocol defines the types of messages exchanged between routers, exchange procedure, and actions when receiving a message, for efficient setting and updating of the routing tables.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1785,'551','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 120] Pseudo Code of Dijkstra\'s Algorithm',NULL,'6802c04e8c341.png','/storage/code/6802c04e8c341.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1786,'551','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Figure 120] shows the pseudo-code of the Dijkstra Algorithm, the leading link-state routing algorithm.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1787,'552','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 121] Bellman-Ford Algorithm\'s Pseudo-code',NULL,'6802c04e9c31d.png','/storage/code/6802c04e9c31d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1788,'552','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Bellman-Ford Algorithm is the leading distance vector routing algorithm. The shortest can be decomposed as follows, by expanding the optimal substructure of the shortest pat problem: The shortest the starting node s to V, is the sum of the shortest from s to U, and the weigt factor (distance) between u and v: D(s,v) = D(s, u)   w(u, v) The Bellman-Ford Algorithm performs edge relaxation of all edges in the graph, when calculating the shortest pat between s and u. Then, how many times should it be performed? The shortest between s and u may be only path path from path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1789,'552','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','and u, and all (VI-1) nodes of the graph, excluding u, can be the shortest distance between s and u. Therefore, Bellman-Ford Algorithm performs the edge-relaxation |VI- 1 times for all edges. [Figure 121] shows Bellman-Ford Algorithm\'s pseudo-code.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1790,'465','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 49} Routing Algorithm Types',NULL,'6802c04eac878.png','/storage/tables/6802c04eac878.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1791,'465','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The routing algorithm finds the low-cost between a source router and a destination router in a network connected by links with a cost between routers The low-cost refers to the of minimum value among the sum f link costs out of all possible paths from the source to the destination <Table 49  shows the type= of routing algorithms path graphica path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1792,'466','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 122] Routing Protocol Classification',NULL,'6802c04ebbc4b.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ebbc4b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1793,'466','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The routing protocol is classified into static routing and dynamic routing, depending the routing type, as shown in [Figure 122]. The dynamic routing method is divided into the EGP (Exterior Gateway Protocol) method and the IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) method,, according to the classification of AS (Autonomous System): The IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) method is further divided into the distance vector method, the link-state method, and the hybrid method, according to the routing setting method. on','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1794,'466','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The type of routing protocol can be divided into an internal router protocol and an external router protocol, based or the autonomous (AS): Here, AS refers to networks with an independent management system and the same operating policy: system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1795,'466','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When classifying routing protocols, based on AS, the routing protocol within the AS is called the inter gateway protocol (IGP). The leading IGP includes the routing information protocol (RIP) , using a distance vector routing algorithm, and the open shortest first (OSPF) using a link-state routing algorithm: The routing protocol between AS is called the exterior gateway protocol (EGP): The EGP is the border gateway protocol (BGP) that uses a path-vector routing algorithm path leading','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1796,'467','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 50) Routing Protocol Types',NULL,'6802c04ecf8c6.png','/storage/tables/6802c04ecf8c6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1797,'467','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The protocol includes RIP, which uses the distance-vector routing algorithm ad delivers the routing table information every 30 seconds through broadcasting, IGRP, which improves some of the RIP problems by reflecting the network state (bandwidth, delay time, load, etc ), OSPF, which uses the link-state routing algorithm, and BGP, whict connects between AS. <Table 50  shows the details of each protocol: routing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1798,'468','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 123] IPv4 Address Structure',NULL,'6802c04edd47f.png','/storage/figures/6802c04edd47f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1799,'468','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IPv4 address is the 32-bit address used on the IP layer, as shown in [Figure 123] It is an identifier that makes the router or host connection to the Internet unique and universal','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1800,'468','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The elements of the IPv4 address include an IP address, which is a unique identification address given to all communication networks that are connected to the Internet and computers connected to the network, a network ID, which identifies TCPIIP hosts in the same physical network, a host ID, which identifies the TCPIIP host on the network, and the 32-bit subnet mask, which specifies the network name for the iP address from the hostname CIDR (Classless Inter-Domain Routing, RFC 1519) is a method of expressing the IPv4 address and one of IP allocating methods that does not divide the network part from the host part in 8-bit units. Moreover, subnetting and supernetting can flexibly express the network and host Ips, according to the number of IPs required by the network without dividing the IPv4 address ad the network ID into fixed 8-bit units Here, subnetting refers to dividing a given IP address into small subnets, according to the network environment, and supernetting refers to combining multiple network IDs into one network Here, subnetting refers to dividing a given IP address into small subnets to suit the network environment, and supernetting refers to combining multiple network IDs into one network ID.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1801,'469','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 124] Network Using IPv4',NULL,'6802c04eea2d5.png','/storage/figures/6802c04eea2d5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:46'),(1802,'470','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04f0181d.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f0181d.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1803,'470','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Binary expression: 01110101 10010101 00011101 00000010 Dotted decimal notation','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1804,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 51) IPv4 Address Designation System [7]',NULL,'6802c04f0f1cf.png','/storage/tables/6802c04f0f1cf.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1805,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 125] IPv4 Address Designation System',NULL,'6802c04f1d511.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f1d511.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1806,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IPv4 addressing consists of a network address, assigned by an Internet address resource management organization, and a host address, assigned by a network administrator to identify individual hosts on the network As shown in < Table 51 ,it is divided Classes A, B, C, D, ad E, depending on the network size or the number of hosts. Classes A B, and C are for network configuration assigned to general users, Class D is for multicast, and Class Fis an address resenved for future use system into','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1807,'471','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In the IPv4 address designation method, subnetting is the address partition method used to separate a network ID into multiple network Ids, and supernetting is a method of integrating multiple networks into a large network The 169.254.0.0 network band is reserved for automatic private IP addressing: For versions after Windows 2000, DHCP automatically generates it to set the IPv4 address ad cannot be routed on the Internet: The addressing system is called the automatic private IP addressing (APIPA):','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1808,'472','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 52) Special IPv4 Address [7]',NULL,'6802c04f31094.png','/storage/tables/6802c04f31094.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1809,'472','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In IPv4, there is an addressing system in a different form from the conventional A B, and class addressing system: These addresses are called the special IPv4 addresses. <Table 52  below shows the special IPv4 addresses','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1810,'553','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 126] IP Address Applying Subnetting',NULL,'6802c04f40720.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f40720.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1811,'553','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Subnetting is a method of dividing a network address into multiple smaller networks. A subnet mask refers to a mas to separate the network address of the IP address [8]','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1812,'554','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 127] Addressing with and without a Subnetting Application',NULL,'6802c04f4b434.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f4b434.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1813,'554','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Adding : a sub-network generates an intermediate layer in the IP address in order to separate the address into the si subnet, and host','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1814,'554','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text',') Use of subnet (Results of subnetting using 2 or 3 bits in a class C address)','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1815,'555','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 53) Subnetting Results',NULL,'6802c04f59035.png','/storage/tables/6802c04f59035.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1816,'556','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CIDR is a method of combining multiple class  addresses into a network It can reduce the size of the table and use IP addresses in various subnet formats. routing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1817,'557','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Provides flexibility in IP address operation, by allowing users to freely specify the range of network identifiers without classifying the IP addresses for each A B, and C class. The network address can be set freely, preventing wasted IP addresses ad enabling effective network configuration It is an address allocation technique that enables the effective management of IP addresses used for routing between domains.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1818,'558','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 128] CIDR Notation',NULL,'6802c04f67436.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f67436.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1819,'558','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The subnet part of an IP address has an arbitrary length with a format of abcdx In the address format, X refers the subnet of the address','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1820,'559','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Supernetting is the opposite concept of subnetting, referring to the consolidation of several small networks into or large network: It is an address allocation technique that allocates consecutive class address blocks to an organizatic and enables routing from the outside, asifit were one address block [9].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1821,'560','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 129] Supernetting Method',NULL,'6802c04f7748e.png','/storage/figures/6802c04f7748e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1822,'560','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Grouping multiple class C addresses into a network Use of part of the network identifier as the host identifier The number of consolidated class C addresses must be a power of 2 and must consist of sequential addresse','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1823,'561','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 54) DHCP Message [10]',NULL,'6802c04f87e78.png','/storage/tables/6802c04f87e78.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1824,'561','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','DHCP is a protocol that provides a method of dynamically allocating IP addresses, and other related configuration details, to DHCP-enabled clients on a network using a DHCP server: The DHCP server can assign a default gateway, a DNS server address, local router a lease period, and a domain name as DHCP options, in addition to the IP address and subnet mask The IPv4 DHCP lease process is established through the exchange of four UDP messages The four UDP messages are DHCPDISCOVER, DHCPOFFER, DHCPREQUEST, and DHCPACK. <Table 54  lists the details.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1825,'562','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 55) NAT Type [11]',NULL,'6802c04f98e49.png','/storage/tables/6802c04f98e49.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1826,'562','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NAT is function that interconnects terminals on a private network to communicate with public networks, such as the Internet. It is defined in RFC 3022 and RFC 2663. The purpose of NAT is to hide internal IPs to defend them from outside attacks while solving insufficient IP addresses NAPT (Network Address Port Translation) is an extension of the basic NAT ad converts the packet\'s source port number The reason for using NAPT is to connect to multiple internal hosts with an IP address NAPT can theoretically process communication with up to 65,535 internal hosts with an official IP address using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1827,'477','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Pv6 is the next-generation Internet protocol with a 128-bit addressing system developed to solve the current IPv4 roblems, such as address depletion, security, and mobility support','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1828,'478','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The rapidly increasing hosts ad terminals connected to networks have led to problems with the existing IPv4 addressing system, such as a shortage of IP address space ad poor Internet security: The IPv6 protocol [16] was developed in the mid-90s to solve the problems. Compared to the existing IPv4, the most notable feature of IPv6 is the expansion of the address space, 32 bits, to 128 bits, to enable the use of approximately 3.4 x 1032 addresses, thereby fundamentally solving the problem of address shortage Moreover, it has simplified the head format, by removing header fields that IPv4 does not frequently use and supports effective QoS services While IPv4 does not include security functions, it is necessary to install a security protocol called IPsec (Internet Protocol Security) [17][18] separately: IPv6 has added security and personal protection functions, by providing the end-to-end encryption function in order to solve these problems from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1829,'479','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 56) Prefix of IPV6 Address Format',NULL,'6802c04fa905e.png','/storage/tables/6802c04fa905e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1830,'479','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 57) IPv6 Address Notation',NULL,'6802c04fc0c8b.png','/storage/tables/6802c04fc0c8b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1831,'479','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IPv6 addresses are 128 bit four times that of IPv4, and expressed in hexadecimal. It consists of the format fix (PFJthat describes the address format and the address field. colon separates each 16-bit field, and each field is expressed in hexadecimal to make it easier to read the addresses. The notation of the IPv6 address network prefix is similar to the CIDR notation of IPv4 The IPv6 address is followed by \"/, and the length of the network prefix is written in decimal. <Table 56  below shows an example of the IPvb address format prefix long, long The IPv6 addresses are classified into link-local, unicast, multicast, and anycast addresses, according to use: <Table 57  summarizes the IPv6 address notation.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1832,'480','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 58) IPv6 Basic Header Structure and Components',NULL,'6802c04fd3c1c.png','/storage/tables/6802c04fd3c1c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1833,'480','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04fe32c1.png','/storage/tables/6802c04fe32c1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1834,'480','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c04ff0af5.png','/storage/figures/6802c04ff0af5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:47'),(1835,'480','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'(Table 59} IPv6 Extension Header Structure and Components',NULL,'6802c05009002.png','/storage/figures/6802c05009002.png','2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1836,'480','App\\Models\\Section','Text','<Table 58  describes the IPv6s basic header structure and component IPv6 can have extended headers, in addition to the basic header IPv6\'s extension header is set to 64 bits ad configured in a chain type  <Table 59  shows the structure and type of extension headers. daisy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:26','2025-04-18 21:12:26'),(1837,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1838,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Text','As 4G wireless communication services have become popular, voice communication is also implemented through data communication, such as VoIP The protocol layer directly related to these applications is the transport layer, and the network can be used effectively, only by selecting ad an appropriate transport layer protocol, according to the application characteristics using','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1839,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1840,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to understand the purpose and functions of transport layer protocols and use them 2 To be able to understand the concepts, services, and control techniques of TCP and use them 3 To be able to understand the concepts, services, and control techniques of UDP and use them 4 To be able to explain the concepts and basic operations of SCTP.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1841,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1842,'42','App\\Models\\Module','Text','TCP, UDP, SCTP, Flow control, Error control,, Congestion control, Slow start, SNMP, Multicasting NTP, DHCP, Kerberos, Multi-homing:','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1843,'481','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c0501903b.png','/storage/figures/6802c0501903b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1844,'481','App\\Models\\Section','Header','Practical preview','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1845,'481','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The transport layer protocols operate between the computer of user A, and the webserver myservercom that requests data, ie, end-to-end service: Data packets are delivered through many hops between & client and a server The nodes, positioned between the terminals, such as the wiredireless routers, are not involved in the transport layer protocol operation TCP [1], UDP [2], and SCTP [3] are the transport leading','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1846,'481','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[Figure 130] Protocol Operation Path of Transport Layer','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1847,'176','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The transport layer protocol transmits application data between end-point hosts The server application running on the server side receives a request from the client side, processes it, and sends a response to the client: On the client side, a user selects an application to receive the service the user wants, makes a request to the server, and displays the response to the user Applications that traditionally use networks, operate in a client-server structure, and the lowest protocol, connecting the client application and the server application,, is the transport layer protocol. Transport layer protocols that have been widely used are TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) [1] and UDP (User Datagram Protocol) [2]. SCTP (Stream Control Transmission Protocol) [3], which combines the advantages of TCP and UDP, is a new protocol introduced after 2000. This chapter focuses on TCP ad UDP, which are currently widely','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1848,'176','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','UDP is usually referred to as a connectionless service However, it does not mean that the service is performed without a connection, but that the pre-configuration process for connection is omitted, and that data can be sent and received immediately On the other hand, TCP is a connection-oriented service and requires a pre-configuration process to connect before sending and receiving data. The connection is terminated in order to end the service between the client and server after completing the data transmission and reception Reliability is a factor mentioned, with the concept of connection-orientation, when referring to TCP and UDP UDP is generally considered an unreliable protocol, and TCP is considered to provide reliable interprocess communication: TCP uses an acknowledgment technique that uses sequence number and an acknowledgment number to check whether the receiving side has properly received the transmitted data along','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1849,'563','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Flow control controls the packet flow volume to prevent packet loss, due to packet inputs exceeding the reception limit when transmitting data packets The flow control uses transmission and reception buffers that can store packets at the sending/receiving sides, ad the sizes of the sending/receiving buffers are specified in the files Iproc/sysInet/ corelmem_max and Iproc/syshnet/core/rmem_max, respectively for Linux systems.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1850,'564','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Error control detects code errors, that occur transmission, and reproduces accurate information It detects anc liscards damaged packets, tracks and resends lost or removed packets, and checks and discards duplicate receivec ackets during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1851,'565','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 60) Well-known TCP Ports',NULL,'6802c05026a19.png','/storage/tables/6802c05026a19.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1852,'565','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Congestion occurs when the network load, representing the number of packets transmitted to the network per unit time, exceeds the network capacity, representing the number of packets that can be processed by the network per unit time: In TCP, the congestion control controls issues, such as end-to-end congestion, and ensures that the load is smaller than the network bandwidth,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1853,'565','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The following table shows well-known ports for widely used TCP services. These services include FTP, for file transfer SSH, for secure remote login, SMTP, POP3, and IMAP4, to send and receive e-mail, and HTTP for web services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1854,'482','App\\Models\\Section','Text','TCP is positioned between the application layer and the network layer in a TCPIIP model and provides communication between the application layer processes TCP is a stream-based protocol and has the transmission buffer ad the reception buffer to transfer data. IP at the lower layer of the TCP protocol, transmits data in a packet format, rather than a stream format, by partitioning the data into several segments Flow control, error control, and congestion control techniques are defined to reliably deliver data. TCP is numbered in units of bytes. When a byte is numbered, a sequence number is assigned to the segment The maximum value must be set for a header to include the sequence number of each packet If m bits are set for the sequence number in the packet header, the sequence number ranges from 0 to Zm-1. The sequence number is modular Zm.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1855,'483','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 131] Virtual TCP Operation Scenario',NULL,'6802c05037b1b.png','/storage/figures/6802c05037b1b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1856,'483','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The figure below shows a case of data transfer on the TCP protocol layer when user A enters the myservercor homepage and downloads the mypdf fileThe web browser exchanges requests and responses: the transport protocol,, TCP deliver an application layer program, ad the webserver Httpd. Here, the discussion focuses on t operation of the TCP protocol laye','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1857,'483','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The connection request in step 0 is actually a simple drawing of steps through  , and the connection termination in step is also a simple drawing of steps through Steps through and through are application layer data that is immediately appended after the TCP header According to the HTTP protocol, this data is generated by the web browser on user A\'s computer ad the myservercom web server program: The following section describes the TCP protocol and corresponding steps in detail, TCP flow control is important when a large volume of data, such as PDF files,, is transmitted simultaneously, as shown in through because IP packets can be transmitted through multiple network Error control is crucial to cope with transmission errors Moreover, it is also necessary to understand congestion control, since the transmission of more packets that can be processed per unit time in the network greatly affects TCP performance paths, steps','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1858,'566','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 132] Three-way Handshake for Connection Establishment [1]',NULL,'6802c050489b2.png','/storage/figures/6802c050489b2.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1859,'566','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The basic way to establish a TCP connection is with a three-way handshake procedure This procedure begins by sending &n SYN segment with a sequence number (SEQ) 100, one TCP endpoint, to another TCP end, as shown in the second step of [Figure 132] The SYN segment means that the SYN control of the TCP header is set to 1_ The ACK segment means that the ACK control is set to 1. The SYN and ACK segments mean that both the SYN control and the ACK control are set to 1 Upon receiving the SYN segment, TCP B sets the SYN control flag (SEQ-300), requesting connection establishment with TCP A TCP B, along with acknowledgment number (ACK) 1011, and sends the SYN and ACK segments, as shown in step 3 in [Figure 132] Upon receiving it, TCP A confirms the ACK control and ACK-101 to recognize that the connection request has been properly delivered: The SYN control set together indicates that TCP B sent the connection request The three-way handshake is complete when the ACK segment (ACK-3OI) is sent to TCP B, and the bidirectional connection, between TCP A and TCP B, is established. As described above, the three-way handshake for TCP connection confirms that the SYN segment, the SYN and ACK segment, and the ACK segment are transferred between TCP terminals At the same time, the sequence number (SEQ) that is transferred between TCP terminals plays an important role in flow and error controls to check whether the data streams are transferred properly in byte units. from flag flag flag \" flag = from flag flag','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1860,'566','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TCP manages connection by allocating a system resource, TCB (Transmission Control Block) , upon receiving the SYN segment for connection If a large number of SYN segments are sent in a short time for malicious purposes, the TCP end-host that has received it may not be able to allocate any more TCBs, resulting in the service unavailable This attack is called SYN flooding, and it can be referred to as a type of denial-of-service attack being )According to the TCP flow control method, the next desired byte sequence number 101 is sent as the acknowledgment number','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1861,'567','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 133] Typical Termination Sequence [1]',NULL,'6802c05058302.png','/storage/figures/6802c05058302.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1862,'567','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The TCP connection is terminated in the following sequence: The terminal TCP A that intends to terminate the connection, sends the FIN segment (SEQ-100,ACK-300) to TCP B, as in step 2. Here, the ACK control is set and sent a5 an acknowledgment response to the previous transmission Upon receiving it, TCP B sends an ACK segment (SEQ-300, ACK-101) in response, as in step 3. In response to SEQ-100 of the FIN segment, the ACK segment increased by increments of to 101 is transmitted. TCP B then sends the FIN segment (SEQ-300, ACK=101) to TCP A to terminate the connection, as in step 4 As in step 2, ACK is sent together for acknowedgment of previous data transmission Then, TCP A completely terminates the TCP connection by sending an ACK segment (SEQ-101, ACK-301), as in step 5. flag','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1863,'567','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In the virtual TCP operation scenario shown in [Figure 133], steps and through correspond to TCP connection termination','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1864,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 62) Sliding Window Protocol Open/Close Operation',NULL,'6802c0506cd8f.png','/storage/tables/6802c0506cd8f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1865,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 63) RWND and CWND',NULL,'6802c05080331.png','/storage/tables/6802c05080331.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1866,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 134] Example of Packet Sending and Receiving by Sliding Window Protocol',NULL,'6802c050924c1.png','/storage/figures/6802c050924c1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1867,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 135] Concept of Sliding Window Protocol',NULL,'6802c050a3a77.png','/storage/figures/6802c050a3a77.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1868,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The flow control balances the rate of data creation and use. TCP uses the window protocol The receiving TCF notifies it by designating the number of octets (1 byte) prepared in advance: The sending TCP may refer to it anc adjust the number of windows Since this field is 16 bits the maximum size of the window is 65,535 bytes sliding sliding long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1869,'568','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The sliding window protocol uses the receiver window (RWND) and the congestion window (CWND): The window size is the lesser of the RWND and CWND:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1870,'569','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 64} TCP Error Control Tools',NULL,'6802c050b3aaa.png','/storage/tables/6802c050b3aaa.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1871,'569','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','or control is activated when the transmitted segment is lost, damaged, out of order, or duplicated','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1872,'570','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 1362] Concept of Slow Start',NULL,'6802c050c52cc.png','/storage/figures/6802c050c52cc.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1873,'570','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 137] Concept of Congestion Avoidance',NULL,'6802c050d6656.png','/storage/figures/6802c050d6656.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1874,'570','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Congestion control is a mechanism and technique of maintaining the user traffic volume input to the network to ensure that it does not exceed the network capacity: TCP performs the congestion control, based on the slow start algorithm ad the congestion avoidance algorithm: The slow start algorithm exponentially increases the congestion window size for congestion control, until it reaches the limit','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1875,'570','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The congestion avoidance algorithm additively increases the congestion window size, until the congestion stat is detected.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1876,'571','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 65} Types of TCP Timers',NULL,'6802c050ec24a.png','/storage/tables/6802c050ec24a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:48'),(1877,'571','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TCP mostly uses four timers for its operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1878,'484','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 61) TCP Protocol Header Components',NULL,'6802c05113dc1.png','/storage/tables/6802c05113dc1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1879,'484','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The header format used in the TCP protocol is shown in the following figure [1]. When adding an option,, it is necessary to add a padding byte to fit the 4-byte unit When there is no option, the TCP header is 20 bytes, which is the same size as the IP header Therefore, the TCPIIP header is 40 bytes and must be sent, even when sending one byte of user data. For effective network transmission in an application layer program,, data larger than an appropriate size must be sent to the transport layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1880,'484','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The sequence number SEQ (sequence number) increases by increments of for each 8-bit octet and performs th unsigned module 232 calculation Therefore, the sequence value changes to make 0 _ 232_ 1-0 _ unsigned module 232 calculation Therefore, the sequence value changes to make 0 _ 232_ 1_0   The six for control have the following meanings The SYN, ACK ad FIN control are widely used in the TCP protocol:. URG: The urgent field is meaningful. flags ` flags pointer - The six for control have the following meanings The SYN, ACK, and FIN control flags are widely used in the TCP protocol. flags `','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1881,'484','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ACK: The acknowledged response field is meaningful PSH: Push function RST: Connection reset SYN: Sequence number synchronization FIN: No more data from the sender','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1882,'485','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 66) Well-known UDP Ports',NULL,'6802c05125fbf.png','/storage/tables/6802c05125fbf.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1883,'485','App\\Models\\Section','Text','User datagram protocol (UDP) provides a connectionless service for sending and receiving data without a pre configuration process for connection. Unlike TCP, it is a protocol that does not guarantee the reliability of the transport layer level Each user datagram of UDP is an independent datagram and is not assigned a number, unlike TCP UDP is a very simple protocol, and there is no control, so there is no window mechanism, and packet overflow may occur: Error Control also has no other error control mechanism, except for checksum: When the receiver detects an error through a checksum, the user datagram is removed, and congestion control is not provided. Due to this nature of the UDP transport protocol, the application layer may be necessary in order to define and implement the control and error control As described above, since the UDP has a continuous minimum transmission rate, despite some packet due to a lack of reception confirmation and retransmission function, it is suitable for video play service and is considered to provide the best effort service In particular, for playing video that is transmitted in real time, the transmitting side must separately include the image frame order in the data. The receiving side must store it in a separate buffer, according to the frame order and process it in order In the case of a streaming method, instead of a download method, if there is a delay for more than a certain time, or if only the B and P frames are received without the frame, the application layer needs to maintain the real-time property by destroying the data. flow flow loss, The UDP protocol is mainly used for the following purposes Aprocess requiring simple request-response communication, without flow and error controls A process with internal flow and error control techniques Multicasting transmission technology Management processes like SNMP <Table 66  below shows well-known ports for widely used UDP services. It supports the NTP service that corrects the host time through the network, the BOOTP and DHCP services that network IP management protocols, the TFTP service that is simpler than FTP, the RIP and OLSR services that are routing protocols, and the Kerberos service that is a computer network authentication protocol. are','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1884,'486','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 67  User Datagram Header Fields',NULL,'6802c05134d27.png','/storage/tables/6802c05134d27.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1885,'486','App\\Models\\Section','Text','UDP packet, called the user datagram, has a fixed-size 8-byte header made of four 2-byte (16-bit) fields, as show elow: Each field of the UDP header is used for the purposes shown in < Table 67  .','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1886,'486','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The source port refers to the port of the transmitting process, and the destination port refers to the port of a specific destination host The length is the sum of the UDP header (minimum 8) and the data size. The checksum is the result of adding 16-bit Is complement to the pseudo-IP header, UDP header, and data. The checksum field is filled with zeros before the calculation As described above, unlike TCP the UDP protocol is simple to implement because it receives data the application layer and sends it down to the IP layer: It also analyzes the UDP user datagram, that is received from the IP layer, and delivers it to an appropriate application program: from','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1887,'487','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 68) SCTP Service Characteristics',NULL,'6802c05146749.png','/storage/tables/6802c05146749.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1888,'487','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c05156600.png','/storage/tables/6802c05156600.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1889,'487','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The stream control transmission protocol (SCTP) is a new transport layer protocol designed by combining UDP and TCP advantages for multimedia communication [3]. The service characteristics of the SCTP are described in the following table The SCTP association is a broader concept than the end-to-end TCP connection In an SCTP association, one or more IP addresses can be connected at each endpoint: It is called multi-homing, and it enables network-level fault tolerance: SCTP is called association in order to highlight its multi-homing nature While a stream is transmitted and received to an end-to-end connection in TCP, multiple streams can be transmitted and received per association in SCTP The number systems used by the SCTP include the transmission sequence number (TSN), the stream identifier (SI), and the stream sequence number (SSN): The data units in TCP are bytes, whereas data chunks are data units in SCTP A transmission sequence number (TSN) is used to number data chunks. The SCTPs TSN plays a similar role to the TCPs sequence number: Moreover, since multiple streams may exist per SCTP association, a 16-bit stream identifier, starting from 0, is used to distinguish them.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1890,'572','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An association begins with an SCTP user\'s request When end-point A sends an INIT chunk to end-point Z, in order to prevent a SYN attack (synchronization attack) end-point Z sends the INIT ACK chunk containing cookie information Upon receiving it, end-point A copies the received cookie and sends the COOKIE ECHO chunk back to end-point Z to inform that it has been properly received, and end- 2 sends the COOKIE-ACK chunk to complete the four- way handshake Generating a transmission control block (TCB) , which is the main resource, only when the normal COOKIE ECHO chunk is received at end-point Z, solves the denial of service (DoS) problem caused by a SYN attack, due to generating a TCB as soon as the SYN segment is received during the TCB connection establishment point again, system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1891,'573','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In SCTP a stream means a series of user messages The SCTP user can set the number of streams that can be supported when setting the association, and these streams are identified by the stream identifier Sl. Moreover assigning the SSN to the user message in the stream, enables the delivery of data chunks in normal order: Other streams can be transmitted even if one stream is blocked to deliver the next sequence of user messages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1892,'574','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Is in TCP, user messages are limited by a maximum transmission unit (MTU) in SCTP and a fragmentation path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1893,'574','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','echnique is provided to resolve it Each fragment that has been divided and transmitted is reassembled in the SCTP ayer to become one user message','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1894,'575','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SCTP transmits a data chunk by assigning a TSN to it, regardless of the stream. The receiving side separately secures the transmission reliability from the sequenced stream transmission by acknowledging (ACK) all the received TSNs Acknowledgment and congestion control functions are related to packet retransmission if an acknowledgment is not received within a given time. Packet retransmission is performed according to a congestion avoidance procedure, similar to TCP congestion control:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1895,'576','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','chunk with multiple user data or SCTP control information may follow an SCTP packet\'s common header An SCTF ser can request to bundle multiple user messages in a single SCTP packet The SCTP chunk bundling function is sponsible for assembling multiple chunks into one SCTP packet and decomposing it','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1896,'577','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The SCTP common header has a verification (VT) and a 32-bit checksum field. The VT is a value selected each endpoint when setting up the association. the set association, SCTP packets must be transmitted using the same VT, and if an SCTP packet with a wrong VT is received, it is discarded. Moreover, generating a CRC32 checksum and transmitting the SCTP packet prevents data corruption in the network tag During -','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1897,'578','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 69} SCTP Protocol Header Components',NULL,'6802c051677d2.png','/storage/tables/6802c051677d2.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1898,'578','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 70} Chunk Types',NULL,'6802c05177c37.png','/storage/tables/6802c05177c37.png','2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1899,'578','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The transmitting SCTP user can use the management function to manipulate the transport address, SCTP port number, and IP address, used in the SCTP packet destination When the association is established, the primary of each SCTP endpoint is defined and used to transmit and receive SCTP packets However, if there is a problem with the current and available transmission address among the addresses, defined by multi-homing, can be designated as an alternative The management ad the packet verification that uses the VT ad checksum are performed simultaneously: SCTP packets have a general header and set of blocks called chunks. There are two types of chunks: control chunks and data chunks. Control chunks are delivered before data chunks The general header defines the endpoint of each association of the packet, guarantees a packet belonging to a specific association, and preserves the integrity of the contents of the packet, including the header itself path path path, path path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1900,'578','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Control information and user data are carried in chunks, and three fields of Type,, and Length are common in all Flag,','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1901,'578','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','chunks The information field indicates the type of the chunk, ad the Type field is defined up to 256 bytes of chunk but only some are defined, and the rest are reserved for future use. The Flag field defines special flags may require special chunks. In some chunk types, the data chunk is identified as the control chunk <Table 70  shows major chunk types','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1902,'488','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Since it is not feasible to discuss everything about SCTP this section briefly describes the SCTP transmission service, as shown in the following figure SCTP functions can be classified into the following eight types. Association start and eni Sequenced delivery User data fragmentation Acknowledgment Congestion avoidance Chunk bundling Packet validation Path management','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:28','2025-04-18 21:12:28'),(1903,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 138] Operational Path of Application Layer Protocol',NULL,'6802c0518a60c.png','/storage/figures/6802c0518a60c.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1904,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 139] Virtual Scenario of Application Layer Operation',NULL,'6802c051a2671.png','/storage/figures/6802c051a2671.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1905,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1906,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','With the advent of mobile platforms, such as Android and iOS, since the mid-2000s, society has rapidly transformed into the mobile era, as applications useful for work and personal leisure have emerged. Some programs use standard application layer protocols such as SMTP, POP3, IMAP, ad FTP, and some others, Iike SNS, use their own application layer protocols, such as KakaoTalk, Line, and Facebook Developers can only develop user-friendly application programs when have a understanding of the concept and operation method of the application layer protocol operating on the transport layer they good','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1907,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1908,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to understand application layer protocols and design or utilize them 2 To be able to understand HTTP protocols for data exchange belween clients and webservers and utilize them 3. To be able to understand FTP protocols for file exchange belween clients and webservers and utilize them for program development Moreover, they will be able to use open-source libraries in order to increase the productivity of application program development 4 To be able to understand JSP_based server programming techniques and client programming techniques for web application program development and develop software_','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1909,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1910,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Application layer protocol, HTTP, GET method, POST method, FTP Control connection, Data connection General transport mode, Passive transport mode, Apache 2.0 license, Web application program, serve programming technique, client programming technique, JSP, HTML , JavaScript, AJAX, Scriptlet expression Scriptlet, Instruction, Standard action, Expression language, extension Tag','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1911,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1912,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','[Figure 138] shows the operational of the application program over the Internet It shows that application programs, like transport layer protocols, operate on the service end-to-end. In other words, Iike transport layer protocols, such as TCP, the nodes like wiredjwireless routers positioned between end- points, do not affect the operation of transport layer protocols. Although users can generate and exchange them as needed, the most widely used application programs tend to use the internationally recognized standard application layer protocols in order to ensure compatibility: path layer','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1913,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','[Figure 139] shows the operational procedure between the application layer and transport layer protocols, according to user As web use scenario described in \" Network concept\". It shows user A logging into the webserver, myservercom,, and downloading the mypdf file Although this section focuses on the operation of the application layer protocol, HTTP it also shows interaction with the transport layer protocol for better Underctandino','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1914,'43','App\\Models\\Module','Text','This section describes the part related to the HTTP protocol in [Step 1] and [Step 3-4] of the network operational procedure in user A\'s web usage scenario 0 in \"1. Network concept\". A web browser and an application program are connected to the web server program, httpd, through a TCP connection and plays the role of fetching the web content that is desired by user Athen converting it user-friendly form: The web browser uses the HTTP/I.1 protocol for communication with the webserver The HTTP/I.1 protocol is a text-based application layer protocol [8] Text data created, according to the HTTP/I.1 protocol, is delivered to the other application layer program through the transport layer protocol: The application layer program uses socket programming to transmit and receive user data through the transport layer Socket programming is a programming technique that is crucial for implementing the application layer protocol, but it is out of the scope of this guide s contents. Refer to other books for more details into','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1915,'180','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Anyone managing a network system or developing a network application program often encounters application layer technology: The application layer protocol is used to exchange necessary information between application programs Widely used application layer protocols include FTP [1] for file transfer, telnet [2] for terminal connection, SMTP [3], POP3 [4], and IMAP [5] for e-mail transmission and access, DNS [6] for mapping hostnames and IP addresses, ad SNMP [7] for network management. HTTP [8], which is used for data transmission between web clients and webservers, is also an application layer protocol. The Bit Torrent protocol is also a widely used application layer protocol, although it is a PZP (peer-to-peer) protocol,, not a method of accessing network infrastructure, as conventional communication protocol does','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1916,'181','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) is an application layer protocol for a hypermedia information system that connects text with video and audio files. It has been used for transferring web contents since the early 1990s [8]. The first version, HTTP/0.9, was simple protocol for low-level data transfer through the Internet, but MIME-type messages have been defined and used since HTTP/I.O (RFC 1945). HTTP/I.I is the current version in use and is designed to be more reliable than HTTP/1.0. Like most standard application protocols, the HTTP protocol implements a request/response protocolthat is suitable for a client-server environment. Since web browsers, such as Microsoft\'s Interet Explorer, Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, and web servers, such as Apache HTTP Server, implement the HTTP protocol, users generally have no difficulty using the web without fully knowing the HTTP protocol implementation. However, when developing an Internet application or a new application protocol, it is helpful to know text-based application layer protocols, such as HTTP, since they are design and implementation tools good The HTTP protocol uses a request/response protocol. The client sends a request message, in the form of <request method, URI, protocol version, MIME type information message  , to the server, and the server responds with a status line that includes protocol version, success or error code, MIME type server information, etc, to the client as a response message  Here, the current HTTP/I.1 version is mainly used The method, designated in Request-Line of an HTTP request message, specifies the HTTP protocol operation. Although RFC 2616 defines eight methods, can be extended as needed. The most commonly used methods are GET and POST The GET method is mainly used to search for content in the server after accessing a website The POST method is mainly used to deliver user input information, such as a form, to a webserver Refer to RFC 2616 for more details on the HTTP response message The Status-Code information of a status line informs how the HTTP request message has been processed Codes starting with 2, such as 200 (OK) or 206 (Partial Content), indicate that the request was processed successfully, while codes starting with 4 or 5 indicate client or they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1917,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c051b6ce1.png','/storage/tables/6802c051b6ce1.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1918,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c051c5ef4.png','/storage/figures/6802c051c5ef4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1919,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c051d1bd0.png','/storage/figures/6802c051d1bd0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1920,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c051deb20.png','/storage/figures/6802c051deb20.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1921,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c051e9b98.png','/storage/code/6802c051e9b98.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:49'),(1922,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c05200cf0.png','/storage/code/6802c05200cf0.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1923,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','FTP uses the control connection to facilitate communication between a server control process and a clier control process','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1924,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It is processed interactively and is divided into a command that a user to the server as well as recnonse to gives','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1925,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Command types included in FTP command messages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1926,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The general transfer mode and passive transfer mode operate in the time sequence shown in the figure below:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1927,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','General transfer mode operation','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1928,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1) The client connects to the server\'s port 21 and informs the server of the second port it intends to 2) The server responds with ACK 3) The servers 20 attempts to connect to the second port informed by the client The client responds with ACK port','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1929,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Passive FTP mode operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1930,'489','App\\Models\\Section','Text','1) The client attempts to connect to the command port 2) The server informs the second it intends to use 3) The client opens another port and attempts to connect to the informed by the server The server responds with ACK port port','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1931,'182','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'(Table 71) Comparison of General Transter Mode and Passive Transfer Mode',NULL,'6802c0520d462.png','/storage/tables/6802c0520d462.png','2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1932,'182','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','FTP is a protocol for transferring a file, or part of a file, from one system to another [1]. Unlike other application protocols, FTP has two connections are control connection and data connection, which use ports 21 and 20, respectively: The control connection is maintained until the client or FTP session is terminated. The data connection establishes a TCP connection when a file transfer starts. The data port number can be a number other than 20, depending on the method used. FTP connection is largely divided into general transfer mode and passive transfer mode (PASV): The general transfer mode requests a connection to a client to establish a data connection, and a problem occurs when it connects with an external server system through a system, such as a firewall: In contrast, the client first requests a connection to the server through a channel other than the basic data channel in the passive transfer mode. Since the client requests to establish an FTP connection, it can pass through the firewall without a problem: It is applicable, even when the client\'s IP is not visible from the outside because the client network uses a proxy server layert They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1933,'182','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','This section describes the FTP command processing and available FTP commands.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:29','2025-04-18 21:12:29'),(1934,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1935,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Text','As high-speed data transmission becomes possible and various convergence technologies emerge, cutting-edge technologies are also appearing in the network field. With the advent of technologies that guarantee traffic quality in Internet networks, multimedia and Internet telephony services have been launched: In recent years, Internet of Things (loT) network-based technologies are expanding together with standardization organizations and groups Moreover, software-based networks, that are differentiated from the existing network structure, are being introduced This chapter discusses the recent network trends and major issues.','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1936,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1937,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to understand the concept of multimedia nelworks and Internet telephony and explain the related protocols: 2 To be able t0 explain loT network-based technologies: 3 To be able to explain the concept of sottware-based networks,','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1938,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1939,'44','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Lossless compression, lossy compression, QoS, SIP, H.323, RTP, RTSP, RTCP, IMS, CSCF, HSS, 3GPP, SDN, Openflow, Control plane, Data plane, NFV, Virtualization function, MQTT, CoAP','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1940,'579','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 72) Lossless Compression',NULL,'6802c0522188b.png','/storage/tables/6802c0522188b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1941,'579','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Since the compression and decompression algorithms are the exact opposite of each other the compression method preserves the original data\'s integrity, and no of the data is lost processing: Leading lossless compression methods include run-length encoding, dictionary decoding, Huffman coding, dictionary coding, ad arithmetic coding: during part','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1942,'580','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The compression method compromises some accuracy in order to increase the compression rate, by allowing the loss of redundant or unnecessary data. There are two types of lossy compression methods: prediction coding and transform coding: The prediction coding method is used for digitizing the analog signal. Instead of separately quantizing the PCM (Pulse Code Modulation) samples, it quantizes the difference: The difference values are smaller than the actual sample values, so fewer bits are required. The transform coding method transforms a signal, from one domain (mainly time ad space domain) , to another domain (mainly frequency domain), then compressesit lossy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1943,'490','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data compression, which accounts for most of the traffic in a multimedia network, can be divided into lossless compression (reversible compression) and compression (irreversible compression): Lossless compression, also called reversible compression, refers to restoring a compressed image, without information loss of the original data when decompressing: It is characterized by a lower compression rate than compression Lossy compression, also called irreversible compression, refers to a compression method that the restored data, when the compressed data is restored, does not match the original data before compression because some data is lost lossy lossy \' from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1944,'491','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 140] Image Data Transformation Process',NULL,'6802c0523292a.png','/storage/figures/6802c0523292a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1945,'491','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Multimedia data includes text,, image, video, and audio data. The text has the form of plain text and non-linear hypertext, and the basic language is Unicode for expressing symbols and uses a lossless compression method. In multimedia,an image is called a still image and refers to a photo, fax page, or video frame. As shown in [Figure 1], an image is transmitted as binary data, through a transformation process, a quantization process, ad a encoding process. The data is converted back into an image, through the reverse process:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1946,'491','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In the transformation process, the JPEG uses DCT (Discrete Cosine Transform) in the first stage of compression, and the decompression uses the inverse DCT method. The transformation and inverse transformation apply 8 X 8 blocks The quantization process integerizes the real number of the DCT transform output and converts some values to zero. The coding process arranges data in a zigzag order after quantization and before encoder input, and lossless compression is performed using run-length decoding and arithmetic coding [1].','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1947,'491','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Video data is composed of several frames Since each frame is an image, a video file requires a high transmission rate Video data can be compressed with a compression or a temporal compression method. JPEG performs spatial compression of each frame, and each frame is compressed independently: Temporal compression removes redundant frames ad configures each frame into I-frames, which are independent frames and B-frames ad P-frames, which reference other |-frames in order to compress data temporally: audio signals are digitized an analog-to-digital converter (ADC), and ADC consists of two processes: sampling ad quantization spatial Analog using','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1948,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'(Table 73) TOS Field Values [4]',NULL,'6802c0523f37f.png','/storage/tables/6802c0523f37f.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1949,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 141] QoS Utilizing RSVP',NULL,'6802c0524ca20.png','/storage/figures/6802c0524ca20.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1950,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Methods for guaranteeing QoS in a multimedia network include the RSVP (resource reservation protocol) and th TOS (type of service) field utilization As shown in [Figure 141], the RSVP method processes data transmission wit fixed network bandwidth allocation from the source to the destination. The TOS field utilization designates the TO field class in each packet to determine the processing priority:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1951,'492','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RSVP is one of the IETF signaling protocols, and data flow is allocated by a static bandwidth by signaling from end-to- end. It basically uses the method of reserving the queue space [2]. The RSVP message starts from the source device and is delivered to all the receiving devices on the It is a message that contains the necessary information for the receiver and a message sent by the receiver upon receiving the message A RESV message reserves the resource of a router that moves toward the source device (upstream) to support RSVP If a router on the does not support RSVP, packets are delivered, based on the best-effort delivery method The priority method, the TOS field of IP datagram, checks the I-byte TOS field, as shown in [Figure 140], and determines the processing priority according to the set value: The TOS class is divided into eight levels from class 0 to 7,and the higher the number the higher the processing priority: Precedence, the first field, indicates the priority or importance of the packet, and the TOS fields indicate whether the network maintains a balance between throughput, delay, reliability, and cost: The last MBZ (must be zero) field is a field that is not currently The TOS field is expressed asa 4-bit binary number <Table 73  shows the meaning of each value path: path path path using used','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1952,'493','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 142] VolP System Structure',NULL,'6802c0525dc63.png','/storage/figures/6802c0525dc63.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1953,'493','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VoIP is a communication technology that facilitates voice calls through packet data, based on the IP network [Figure 142] shows the VolP system structure: The main service components are the media gateway and the signaling gateway The media gateway exchanges multimedia data, delivers the changed date to the corresponding network and controls it through the media gateway control protocol (MGCP): The signaling gateway performs call signaling, protocols, such as H.323, SIP, MGCP, and MEGACO, and converts the signals of the PSTN and IP networks, so thev can be used with each other using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1954,'581','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 74) SIP Protocol Components',NULL,'6802c0527246b.png','/storage/tables/6802c0527246b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1955,'581','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 143] SIP Protocol Stack',NULL,'6802c05281a16.png','/storage/figures/6802c05281a16.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1956,'581','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SIP is a application layer signaling protocol, used to establish, modify, and terminate multimedia sessions. It operates independently of the lower-layer transport protocols and has scalability as an HTTP text-based protocol It controls sessions to enable call control in a circuit-switched data network in packet-switching network and multimedia applications on the Interet, which is a packet network It can support text-based addressing methods in URL and E-mail format and message parsing or extension. [Figure 143] shows the SIP protocol stack located on of the transport layer protocols TCP and UDP< Table 74  shows the SIP protocol components top','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1957,'582','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SIP uses a SIP uniform resource identifier (URI) , similar to an e-mail address, to identify users to provide services without dependent on IP addresses. A SIP message contains the START LINE to describe the method type to request ad SIP URI, the HEADER to set the value to control the session, the BODY containing the type set in Content-Type, and CRJLF a blank space between HEADER and BODY: being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1958,'494','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VolP call signaling protocols include SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) and H.323. The SIP protocol is an application layer signaling protocol that specifies a procedure for intelligent terminals that are communicating on the Internet in order to identify each other, find their locations, and create or delete a multimedia communication session between them. The H.323 protocol is an ITU-T standard for providing voice, data, and video services on a LAN that does not guarantee quality Startup VolP service providers use it widely because it can provide multimedia services without changing the existing network\'s underlying structure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1959,'495','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 144] H.323 Network Architecture',NULL,'6802c0529606e.png','/storage/figures/6802c0529606e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1960,'495','App\\Models\\Section','Text','H323 is an ITU-T standard for providing voice, data, and video services over LAN where quality is not guaranteec Startup VolP service providers use it widely because it can provide multimedia services without changing the existine network\'s underlying structure [Figure 144] shows the H.323 network architecture. The service components include terminals, such as genera telephones, fax machines,, and PCs equipped with multimedia equipment that are used by end users. Othe components are a gatekeeper that converts between E.164 and the IP address, performs redirection anc authentication for calls, and manages the components and bandwidth, and a gateway that performs the logica connection mapping (encoding, protocol,, and call control) of different networks (IP network PSTN,, ISDN, ATM, etc):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1961,'496','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 145] VoLTE Service Model on 36 Networks',NULL,'6802c052aafa8.png','/storage/figures/6802c052aafa8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1962,'496','App\\Models\\Section','Text','VoLTE is a technology that provides data and voice through the LTE network It provides voice services in the LTE environment, the next-generation wireless broadband network technology: Although VoLTE refers to the voice service domain, since LTE technology is based on an all-IP, data-only network the VoLTE service is implemented in the form of digital data Therefore, it transmits voice, text, video chat,, and multimedia content in the SIP which is the main solution for Internet telephony services. It provides voice and text services, which exist as data, through the IMS (IP multimedia subsystem) architecture These VoLTE technology solutions were not implemented flawlessly at the beginning It was because the LTE infrastructure was not yet fully equipped, so voice services could not be transmitted over the WCDMAGSM networks freely: The problem was that while roaming and interconnection were required between LTE and 36 networks to provide seamless communication services, there was no standard agreement on roaming and interconnection between new and old networks The following two steps can be considered to resolve the problem Firstly, the circuit-switched fallback solution establishes calls, mainly over the WCDMA/GSM circuit network, and LTE terminal vendors and mobile telecommunication carriers perform minimal roaming: However, multimedia communication service is not implemented at this stage Secondly, if the coverage is established to some extent after the initial stage of LTE network construction, it evolves into the stage of implementing a multimedia communication service, through an appropriate solution, such as 3GPP MMTel (Multimedia Telephony): [Figure 145] shows how VoLTE services are implemented over 36 networks. calling','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1963,'497','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RTP is designed to process real-time traffic over the Internet: It is mainly used to transmit video or audio data in real time over the Internet It is performed over the UDP (user datagram protocol) of the transport layer In the RTP protocol, the transmitting side that sends the media file, converts the media unit data compressed with the codec into an RTP packet and sends it to the receiving side, using UDP Since it is transmitted using UDP, RTP does not guarantee that packets are delivered within a specified time and are not lost: Therefore, the video and audio applications must process packets, using information included in the RTP packet header RTCP can ensure the QoS of RTP and synchronization of media streams','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1964,'498','App\\Models\\Section','Text','TCP controls RTP, a protocol for streaming video or audio over the Internet: It is an IETF standard defined togethe ith RTP in RFC 1889 RTCP packet types include the sender report packet, receiver report packet, source descriptio essage, bye message, and application-specific packet','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:30','2025-04-18 21:12:30'),(1965,'499','App\\Models\\Section','Text','RTSP is an application layer protocol that transmits real-time media. The communication protocol developed by IETF in 1998 is defined in RFC 2326. It is a communication protocol for transmitting ad receiving audio and moving pictures in real time,as well as a standard protocol for controlling streaming data on the Internet It is used to remotely control media servers Its commands are similar to VCR operations, such as \"PLAY\" and \"PAUSE\" , and it accesses the server, based on time information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1966,'583','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MS is a communication platform defined by 3GPP to control multimedia sessions &nd provide services, based on the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1967,'583','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SIP It is a core network for providing integrated services in wired [wireless multiple access network environments','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1968,'584','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IMS provides multimedia content, such as voice, audio, video, and data, based on the IP protocol, and it supports quick service development and change It uses general-purpose Internet-based technology to improve the price competitiveness of services and enable easy interface with various 3rd party applications, based on an efficient session management function and expansion of business areas, through global between services, linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1969,'585','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The logical structure of an all-IP network is divided into a radio network domain, a GPRS-based packet-switching service domain, and an IP multimedia service domain. The GPRS-based packet-switching service domain can be replaced with an IP network by a packet router outside the 3GPP scope. The wireless domain can be replaced with other wireless network access domains and data network access domains, as Wibro and mobile-LAN that are out of the 3GPP scope The IMS service domain consists of the call session control function (CSCF) that registers and processes multimedia calls the IETFs SIP protocol and the home subscriber server (HSS) that integrates the home location register (HLR) function of the legacy mobile network with the function to mobility management ad authentication of IP multimedia users. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1970,'586','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ID and authentication system in the convergence environment, using the IMS infrastructc Bidirectional channel for service control Service session connection, through the independent service infrastructure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1971,'500','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IMS was first proposed by the 3GPP (3rd Generation Partnership Project) group that develops international standard in the wireless communication field. It is an infrastructure for providing IP multimedia services and uses SIP protocol based call control as a core technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1972,'185','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Media transport protocols include RTP (Real-Time Transport Protocol), RTCP (Real-Time Control Protocol) , and RTSP (Real-Time Streaming Protocol): RTP is designed to process real-time traffic over the Internet: It is mainly used to transmit video or audio data in real time over the Internet. RTCP is a protocol to control the RTP (Real-time Transport Protocol) for streaming video or audio over the Interet: RTP and RTCP are specified in the IETF standard document RFC 1889. RTSP is designed for use in entertainment ad communication systems to control streaming media servers RTP is used to establish ad control media sessions between endpoints, and it does not actually transmit media streaming data. Most RTSP servers transfer actual audiojvideo data to the transport layer, using the RTP protocol.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1973,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1974,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Text','As high-speed data transmission becomes possible and various convergence technologies emerge, cutting- edge technologies are also appearing in the network field. With the advent of technologies that guarantee traffic quality in Internet networks, multimedia and Internet telephony services have been launched. In recent years, loT network-based technologies are expanding together with standardization organizations and groups Moreover software-based networks, differentiated from the existing network structure, are being introduced. This chapter discusses the recent network trends and major issues','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1975,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1976,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 TTo be able to explain loT nelwork-based technologies: To be able to explain the concept of software-based nelworks,','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1977,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1978,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Lossless compression, lossy compression, QoS, SIP, H.323, RTP RTCP, IMS, CSCF, HSS, 3GPP, SDN, Openflow, Control plane, Data plane, NFV, Virtualization function, MQTT, CoAP','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1979,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Practical preview','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1980,'45','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Network technologies are changing with new technologies, such as loT artificial intelligence (AI), and cloud computing: The recent topic of the new network technology is the software-defined network (SDN) . SDN is a technology for standardizing software that is dependent on existing hardware manufacturers and providing flexible network services. It is the core technology of a software-defined data center (SDDC): Cloud computing is aother core technology of SDDC. As such, the network is the infrastructure ad core of new technologies Even in Al, the network performance determines the Al performance: Therefore, the Al network uses InfiniBand, which is a short word for infinite bandwidth The existing network Ethernet can communicate with one device at a time, but InfiniBand can simultaneously handle communication between multiple devices It can reliably operate, even if there is a problem with some equipment This section discusses new network technologies that have recently become a hot topic','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:31'),(1981,'501','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 146] loT Applications',NULL,'6802c052d608b.png','/storage/figures/6802c052d608b.png','2025-04-18 21:12:31','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1982,'501','App\\Models\\Section','Text','loT (Internet of Things) is a concept that embeds sensors and communication functions in various objects to connect to the Interet It refers to the technology that can perform sensing, networking, and information processing, through cooperation, without explicit human intervention. At the same time, the ubiquitous technology that allows access to information and communication networks, regardless of time and place as a concept that exists anywhere at the same time and is ubiquitous and the machine-to-machine (MZM) technology that enables intelligent communication between objects have evolved further As such, loT enables all things to exchange information through the Internet, without boundaries between people and objects.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1983,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 147] Standard Scope of Each loT Standardization Organization [10]',NULL,'6802c052f2d46.png','/storage/figures/6802c052f2d46.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:50'),(1984,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Text','3GPP and ETSI have established mobile communication-based IoT standards, but since 2012, have been led by an international consultative body called, oneMZM The Open Mobile Alliance (OMA) proposed a communication method, based on a server-client structure, by establishing the Lightweight MZM (LWMZM) protocol: oneMZM has released LWMZM, which CoAP (Constrained Application Protocol) and HTTP for data transfer, as the latest standard, they applies','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1985,'502','App\\Models\\Section','Text','[Figure 147] shows the standard scope of each standardization organization for protocol layer','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1986,'587','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Sensors collect object information. Various sensors, such as temperature, humidity, heat, gas, illuminance, and ultrasonic waves, are installed in the object to obtain information about the surrounding situation Sensors are needed to minimize power consumption in order to operate for & time Physical sensors have evolved into smart sensors with a standardized interface and information processing capability, ad include a virtual sensing function that extracts specific information from the sensed data. As the sensor layers role has increased, the hardware platform market is evolving to facilitate connecting various sensors, control, and communication, using open-source hardware long - they CHM','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1987,'588','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Although objects generally use wired means, such as Ethernet or power line communication (PLC), to access the Internet, wireless communication is more efficient when considering the installation convenience and mobility: Short- range wireless communication, such as WLAN, Bluetooth, ZigBee, and UWB, and mobile communication, such as 36 and LTE, are available Moreover, new technologies for sensor networking are constantly proposed BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy): Also called Bluetooth Smart, it is low-power, short-range wireless communication that is not compatible with existing Bluetooth but is compatible with Bluetooth 40. Z-Wave: It is a protocol for devices that use intelligent mesh network topology, do not have a master node, and reauire low power and low bandwidth being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1988,'589','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','It is necessary to use ontology-based semantic web technology, cloud computing for large-scale distributec processing, and open API for accessing various services, to automatically analyze and share data collected from the sensor of an object','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1989,'503','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Ts main technologies are a sensing technology, a wired and wireless communication ad network infrastructure chnology, and an loT service and interface technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1990,'590','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 148] CoAP Conceptual Diagram',NULL,'6802c05310da4.png','/storage/figures/6802c05310da4.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(1991,'590','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CoAP is lightweight application layer protocol, developed by the IETF CORE Working Group, for communication between objects. Although it uses the UDP transport layer above the IP layer it is designed independently of the lower layers and can operate in other networks and transport layers. It has reduced the message size to reduce end- point load and uses binary encoding to facilitate encoding and decoding:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1992,'590','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CoAP has attracted attention as the main protocol for loT, since it communicates with endpoints using Zigbee, rather than fast and stable Ethernet or Wi-Fi.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1993,'591','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 75} Comparison of MQTT and CoAP',NULL,'6802c05321238.png','/storage/tables/6802c05321238.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(1994,'591','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 149] MQTT Applications',NULL,'6802c053344e5.png','/storage/figures/6802c053344e5.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(1995,'591','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','MQTT is publish-subscribe-based protocol for delivering lightweight messages at low in high-latency and unreliable networks speed MQTT is a flexible data transfer model between multiple endpoints and multiple servers and operates by publishing and subscribing to necessary topics [Figure 149] shows a conceptual diagram of transmitting the topic of the door opening ad closing, by sending pressure sensor data to the access control system, video security system, and building energy control system, Arduino and the metadata topic that is generated by the camera\'s image sensor to multiple systems, using MQTT: Although the protocols based on CoAP and HTTP are widely used currently, the standardization organizations are still suggesting architectures using MQTT and REST. OASIS continues to update the MQTT standard: [14] using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1996,'504','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Protocols for loT require lightweight the most, and since have been commonly used for some time, protocols that feature compatibility and scalability are preferable. In particular CoAP and MQTT are suitable for small devices that need to connect to the Internet and transmit data, due to the nature of loT, and are proposed as communication protocols in various architectures they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1997,'592','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Current applications generate a large volume of traffic, by accessing various application servers and databases before providing users data. The environment is changing from the limited communication between the client and the serve to access between various systems','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1998,'593','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Virtualization technology has dramatically increased the number of servers connected to the network fundamentally changing the assumptions about the hosts physical location','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(1999,'594','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Network structures are becoming more complex, as a large number of computers are configured of discrete protocol sets:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2000,'595','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Initial designs use a link oversubscription method that considers the expected traffic patterns and the numbe of concurrent users However, it is becoming more difficult to predict the network size, as traffic patterns chang dynamically:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2001,'596','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','particular, the core network has had difficulties in introducing new services or technologies as certain majc uipment manufacturers dominated the communication market','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2002,'597','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SDN was first proposed at the Open Network Summit, conference specializing in SDN and open flow, held at Stanford University in October 2010. SDN and OpenFlow are technologies that program and configure or operate networks, like computers have attracted attention as new innovative communication environmental technologies. In March 2011, ONF (Open Networking Foundation) was formed to promote and standardize OpenFlow and SDN They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2003,'598','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 150] SDN Architecture [5]',NULL,'6802c05344b1e.png','/storage/figures/6802c05344b1e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2004,'598','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 150], SDN enables programming networks by separating the control plane (to guide the networ to which it goes) from the data plane (to send packets to a specific destination). The basis of SDN is a switch tha uses industry standard control protocols, such as OpenFlow, and can be programmed through an SDN controller','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2005,'599','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 151] Main Components of OpenFlow Switch [6]',NULL,'6802c0535176e.png','/storage/figures/6802c0535176e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2006,'599','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 151], the OpenFlow technology separates the functions to control and transfer the packets and controls the network through programming: OpenFlow consists of a controller and a switch The controller issues commands to the switch, and the switch performs tasks related to data flow, such as sending or modifying packets to the destination according to the commands','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2007,'600','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 152] Network Structure beforelafter SDN Application',NULL,'6802c0535fbd6.png','/storage/figures/6802c0535fbd6.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2008,'600','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in [Figure 152], network devices have had a control plane and a data plane implemented in one device now: However, when SDN is applied, the controller performs the control plane function of each network device, only the data plane function remains in the actual physical network device Here, OpenFlow plays a role as an interface standard technology for SDN operation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2009,'600','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','For example, it removes computational operations in medium and large routers and leaves only a simple switching function Each router simply operates according to a command issued by the controller','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2010,'506','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SDN is a next-generation network technology that can set the network routing and control and complex operation management through software programming: The technology attracted attention when ONF introduced the OpenFlow technology, ad international standardization organizations, such as IETF and ITU-T, began to develop standards for SDN-related core technologies. There is heated competition in the industry for securing leadership in','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2011,'506','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SDN technology standards','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2012,'601','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the increase in network speed and the emergence of various services, securing space and power to accommodate the rapidly increasing network equipment has become a crucial issue for Interet service providers Moreover the lifespan f network equipment is shortened, making it increasingly difficult to secure profits after introducing new equipment NFV was introduced to solve these problems through virtualization technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2013,'602','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NFV runs on & high-performance x86 platform and allows users to activate the necessary network functions a5 needed. It creates a VM (Virtual Machine) or service profile and implements virtualization on the network by utilizing the x86 capabilities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2014,'603','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'(Table 76) NFV Architecture Framework Configuration',NULL,'6802c053708c8.png','/storage/tables/6802c053708c8.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2015,'603','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c05387a6a.png','/storage/figures/6802c05387a6a.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2016,'603','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in <Table 76  , the NFV architecture framework consists of three function groups: VNF group, NFL infrastructure, and management and orchestration','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2017,'603','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Figure 153] NFV Architecture Framework (Five VNF Interface Types) [7]','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2018,'604','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 154] NFV Implementation',NULL,'6802c0539cda7.png','/storage/figures/6802c0539cda7.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2019,'604','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','NFV uses virtualization to implement network equipment functions It not only operates on specialized equipment but also implements the network equipment functions in a general high-performance x86 server platform, as showr in [Fioure 1541','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2020,'507','App\\Models\\Section','Text','NFV has emerged as a new topic, thanks to the high interest of network operators. Moreover, the NFV Group is preparing standards for major telecommunications operators and equipment manufacturers and is promoting a PoC (Proof of Concept) to check the feasibility of the technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2021,'605','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 155] Relationship between NFV SDN [8]',NULL,'6802c053ac44e.png','/storage/figures/6802c053ac44e.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2022,'605','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SDN enables faster change by creating a abstracted network, ad NFV reduces capital expenditures (CAPEX), operating expenditures (OPEX), and space and resource consumption NFV and SDN have a complementary relationship and can be independently configured.','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2023,'606','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c053c46ed.png','/storage/tables/6802c053c46ed.png','2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:51'),(2024,'508','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Initially, SDN was developed mainly by researchers and data center designers, and NFV was developed by Interne service providers (ISPs): However, SDN and NFV technologies are complementary to each other and ISPs currenth combine the two technologies and apply them to networks','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2025,'187','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The technologies that have recently received the most attention in the network field are software-defined networks (SDN) ad network function virtualization (NFV): Network openness and virtualization technologies are expected to change the era when certain large equipment makers dominated the global network equipment market and increase 3rd party software providers and equipment makers to enter the market: Korea has planned smart Interet-related R&D and standardization projects focusing on SDN and NFV to enhance national SDN technology competitiveness, led by ETRI, since 2012. Organizations, such as the TTA Future Internet Project Group (PG22O) and the Smart Internet Technology Standardization Council actively promote domestic standards and reflect international standards,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:12:32','2025-04-18 21:12:32'),(2026,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Subject','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2027,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2028,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Text','IT-related technologies, such as the popularization of the cloud, promotion of data, and the artificial intelligence industry, are gradually advancing, as well as full-scale development of the loT industry: Various convergence technologies and services are also emerging: However, as information security technology is not applied to pace with this, various incidents of security infringement, using new technology and convergence technology, are expected to increase. As a result, various security technologies and security services need to be urgently developed for the information security of new technologies and convergence technologies. Therefore, we need to understand the concept of information security, which becomes the foundation big being keep','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2029,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2030,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Text','To be able to explain the concept of information security: To be able to explain the and importance of information security: goal','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2031,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2032,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Information security, administrative/technical/physical information security, confidentiality, integrity, availability, non-repudiation, authentication, access control','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2033,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2034,'46','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Assistant manager Kim, working for company A has overseen the development, deployment, and maintenance of Java source programs. He used to check web pages and servers on a regular basis. In this process, he should ensure the availability of numerous source codes that he is managing, and he should manage the performance and capacity to ensure the availability of the server, so that the applications can work properly: He should also take technical protection measures, like encryption, to maintain the confidentiality of customer information that is saved by the application He is trying to ensure confidentiality, integrity, and availability of business information Let\'s take a closer look at the concepts and of information security: goals','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2035,'607','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Information security refers to protecting information administratively, physically, and technically in order to prevent damage, alteration, and leakage of information while being collected, processed, stored, and transmitted information,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2036,'608','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The need to guarantee privacy and prevent crimes on the Internet is gradually increasing: Concerns about the leakage of major domestic technologies and information are also increasing, due to globalization, as the entire world is connected through the Internet','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2037,'609','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 1] Three goals of information security',NULL,'6802c9af9dbc0.png','/storage/figures/6802c9af9dbc0.png','2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:47'),(2038,'609','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The three of information security are confidentiality integrity, and availability: Efforts should be made to administratively, physically and technically ensure these attributes goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2039,'609','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Contidentiality means that the original information is not exposed to unauthorized users while stored and transmitted. Integrity means that the original information is maintained while sending and receiving it, without illegal creation, modification, or deletion, Availability means that authorized users can access and use the requested information when necessary: being','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2040,'510','App\\Models\\Section','Text','uthentication refers to a method of verifying whether the information exchanged between the sender and eceiver, who are the subjects of the information, has not been altered or deleted, and whether the subjects sender and receiver) are legitimate:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2041,'610','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Non-repudiation of origin refers to the prevention of the sender\'s claim that the message was not received after actually receiving the message.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2042,'611','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Non-repudiation of delivery refers to the prevention of the receiver\'s claim that the message was not delivered after actually sending the message.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2043,'612','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Non-repudiation of receipt refers to the prevention of the receiver\'s claim that the message was not receivec after actually receiving the message.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2044,'511','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Non-repudiation refers to security technologyto prevent the repudiation after receiving and sending a message, by verifying the fact of message receiving/sending: Non-repudiation can be classified into the following three categories:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2045,'614','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cryptographic techniques can be divided into the symmetric cryptosystem, in which the encryptior and the decryption are the same,while in the cryptosystem, the encryption key and the decryption are different, depending on whether the encryption and the decryption are the same key public key key key key key key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2046,'615','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cryptographic protocols refer to the protocols that use cryptographic techniques As a protocol means a series of finite phases where more than 2 persons participate to achieve a certain purpose, the cryptographic protocol should prevent repudiation by a participant, or a third party, to ensure a certain purpose of the concerned cryptographic protocol (authentication, confidentiality, integrity, non-repudiation, etc ), as well as the meaning of each message.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2047,'512','App\\Models\\Section','Text','yptography is largely classified into cryptographic techniques and encryption protocol techniques','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2048,'513','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A digital signature is the method of providing both data integrity and signature authentication, by performing a hash operation on a specific document, using the signature\'s private key: Signing the entire message is very inefficient because the public key operation should be performed on all message blocks repetitively: Therefore, an electronic signature can be efficiently generated by calculating a hash value for the message, then signing on that value Although the signature is on the hash value, instead of on the message itself it is recognized as a genuine signature for the message because another message with the same hash value is difficult. finding','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2049,'514','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A hash function, or hash algorithm, is a mathematical function that converts a random of various sizes into a short hash value (hash code) of fixed length, then outputs it. That is, the function compresses an input of a random length into & with a fixed, short length: Unlike an encryption algorithm, the hash function does not use a therefore providing the same output for the same input: Thanks to this property, the hash function can be used for integrity verification, which can detect an erroneous or altered input message: string string string key,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2050,'616','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Malware that runs independently: This malware replicates itself and spreads to other computers.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:34','2025-04-18 21:52:34'),(2051,'617','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ruses refer to malicious codes that are inserted into the code of another independent program, then make e program perform malicious behavior and spread on its own.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2052,'618','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A program with hidden codes. Although it looks like a normal program, malicious code is executed when the user executes the program.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2053,'515','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Malware is an abbreviation of malicious software and refers to software designed to perform malicious actions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2054,'515','App\\Models\\Section','Text','against computers, file systems, or networks. Malware can be classified into the following types:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2055,'619','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','firewall refers to a security solution installed between the network and the private network to protect the private network from the outside In general, there are two types of firewalls. The first type is a packet filtering gateway, which determines whether to pass the packet, based on a series of rules The second type is a proxy server that provides authentication to specific hosts to access a private network and allows them to pass the packet However, a method with increased security is also used, which combines these two methods. public','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2056,'620','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A security system that blocks intrusions in real time by detecting unauthorized and abnormal behaviors for the target system (network detection area) , and by distinguishing detected illegal behavior It can be assumed that the characteristics in the common area between the average area of the behavior of the intruder, and that of the behavior of the authorizer make intrusion detection difficult. The intrusion detection system is built along with a firewall, when implementing a general security system. The purpose of building the intrusion detection system includes real-time detection ad blocking of illegal activities, such as hacking, and defense against attacks performed by the packet, allowed by the firewall. first, using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2057,'621','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A technology that enables to safely use access control, authentication, and confidentiality services, like a private network when using a network, without building a physical private network between remote sites IPSec and SSL are the representative technologies for implementing a VPN. The VPN can be implemented in a dedicated system, router, or firewall public','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2058,'622','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Single sign on enables the user to access another site without a separate authentication procedure after logging in on one site. In general, different systems and sites manage their user information separately: However, it is necessary to link user information on occasion. In this case, SSO can be used for the integrated','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2059,'622','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','authentication of multiple systems, based on the information of one user:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2060,'623','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Located in front of the web server this security solution monitors incoming traffic with the HTTPIHTTPS protocol and blocks malicious attacks detected against the web application, such as the SQL Injection attack or XSS attack before it reaches the web server','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2061,'624','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When at the endpoint, when a user computer attempts to access the internal network for the first time, the system checks whether the accessing user computer complies with various security policies, such as network user authentication, anti-virus program installation, etc and controls network access according to the pre defined security policy, when security policies are not observed.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2062,'625','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The WIPS automatically detects and blocks access from unauthorized wireless devices by continuously monitoring the wireless LAN operated of a specific organization,, and it improves the stability of wireless LAN and enables integrated management: The WIPS provides a function of detecting and blocking an intrusion attempt an unauthorized AP or user device in the exposed wireless network using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2063,'626','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ESM is designed to provide a consistent and intuitive administrator and user interface by integrating security management functions modularized by function and product. This security solution aims to build an integrated security management system for all systems, according to standard policies, by building a efficient, policy- oriented, and systematic security management system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2064,'627','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The SIEM solution establishes an early warning ad monitoring system for intelligent threats, which provides correlation analysis and forensic functions in the vast information of big data, by extending the role of the existing ESM from the security domain to the entire enterprise, and by adding corporate compliance response functions, so that those threats can be traced later instead of only collecting and analyzing logs.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2065,'517','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c9afbcc57.png','/storage/tables/6802c9afbcc57.png','2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:47'),(2066,'517','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 2] Conceptual diagram of the blockchain',NULL,'6802c9afdf8fa.png','/storage/figures/6802c9afdf8fa.png','2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:47'),(2067,'517','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The Bitcoin cryptocurrency system and all transactions occurring in the network are recorded in one public ledger, distributed, and stored in a single ledger: Blockchain is a distributed ledger and is designed with a structure that enables network participants to store and verify data. When transactions occur, transactions that have occurred for a certain period of time (10 minutes) are collected to create a block in order to verify transaction information, then the blocks are sequentially connected to form a chain. That\'s why it is called &','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2068,'517','App\\Models\\Section','Text','DTo_ Ju A copy of the transaction ledger is distributed among network members. Whenever a new transaction occurs, the transaction is verified by the consent of the members. The blockchain uses a PZP network method instead of depending on the existing centralized system. Therefore, it is not necessary for & transaction broker to intervene As a result, the efficiency and transparency of transactions are increased, and transactions can be made faster and safer, at a low cost, In addition, as transaction information based on the blockchain cannot be forged and altered, transaction reliability increases, and transaction information can be easily traced.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2069,'628','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Even though FIDO 1.0 is similar to existing biometric authentication, it provides two authentication methods: the UAF (Universal Authentication Framework) protocol that does not store the user\' s personal information on the server and the UZF (Universal 2nd Factor) protocol that improves security two-factor authentication using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2070,'629','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','FIDO 2.0 provides a convenient authentication and payment environment bio-information, instead of the password in the PC and web environment: It is expected that more biometric authentication devices will be installed in PCs and laptops, and various device authentication methods the smartphone as a can be provided. FIDO 2.0 is a universal authentication technology standard that is developed to provide the FIDO clients and ASM on the platform. Here, the platform largely means the operating system platform, including using using key,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2071,'629','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Windows and Android, and the web platform based on the web browser FIDO server, RP server, and RP client are the components that should be provided by the server Therefore, if are regarded as & part of the server, the standard protocol is not needed anymore. Therefore, FIDO 2.0 does not use the UAF protocol, but exchanges messages, using its own protocol defined by the server The FIDO client, which was provided as an Android app in the existing FIDO 1.0, will be provided as a API by the operating system, or as a JavaScript API by the web browser they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2072,'518','App\\Models\\Section','Text','FIDO was established in July 2012 to set the technical (De facto) standard for the authentication method, biometrics in the online environment. The FIDO standard separated local user authentication in the user device from remote authentication performed by the service providers server using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2073,'519','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 1  Physical network segregation and logical network segregation',NULL,'6802c9b009b6d.png','/storage/tables/6802c9b009b6d.png','2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:48'),(2074,'519','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Vetwork segregation refers to network blocking, which separates the business network from the externa etwork in order to block illegal access from the external Internet network and to prevent the leakage nternal information. There are two types physical network segregation and logical network segregation:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2075,'630','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The FDS collects user media environment information and accident type information by collecting information on user information and behavior','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2076,'631','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The FDS detects abnormal behavior by analyzing various correlations by user type and transaction type, and by testing the pattern, based on the analysis of abnormal behavior, using the collected information:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2077,'632','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The FDS blocks a illegal transaction by blocking the transaction or by requiring additional authentication when abnormal behavior is detected.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2078,'520','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The FDS is a system that detects suspicious transactions and blocks abnormal financial transactions by comprehensively analyzing device information, access information, and transaction details used in electronic financial transactions. Pattern analysis is the core engine of the FDS because the usual transactions of the user are analyzed, and abnormal behavior is detected when an action that violates the analyzed pattern is taken: The FDS has the following functions','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2079,'521','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Quantum cryptography is a cryptographic technology that utilizes the characteristics of mechanics. Unlike existing cryptosystems that are based on mathematical complexities, quantum cryptography is based on the characteristics of quantum A quantum cannot be copied or returned to its original state. Due to these properties, the receiver can detect an eavesdropping attempt when a third party measures the quantum for eavesdropping because its state is changed if measured.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2080,'522','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The trusted platform module (TPM) is a standard established by the TCG (Trusted Computing Group), an international industry standard organization, to overcome the limitations of security technology that only operates with software. This module provides a strong security environment that stores important data that requires security in a secure space separated by hardware, such as the encrypted password, digital certificate. It ensures that management,, encryption processing, etc_, are only handled inside the security device: The latest TPM 2 was released in September 2016,which includes the Mobile Trusted Module (MTM): key, key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2081,'523','App\\Models\\Section','Text','De-identification is the process or method of converting data in such way that a individual cannot be identified. Re-identification is the process or method of identifying an individual from the de-identified data by combining, analyzing, and processing it with other information Personal information may be disclosed, due to intentional or accidental re-identification, while collecting information from SNS or websites, like search engines, or while companies that handle personal information, such medical and financial institutions, are analyzing data. Recently as big data is used in various fields, there is concern that personal information mav be leaked indiscriminatelv due to re-identification: being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2082,'633','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Whereas the previous EU Directives were the regulation at the recommendation level, the GDPR is quite different, in that it is a mandatory regulation that all member states must comply with (Penalties are imposed if violated )','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2083,'634','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The GDPR applies not only to the company operating a business site in the EU, but also to the companies that process the personal information of EU residents in overseas countries through e-commerce, etc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2084,'635','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The increased responsibility of the enterprise, such as the designation of the Data Protection Officer (DPO), and the increased rights of the information owner, such as the right to data portability, have been added.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2085,'524','App\\Models\\Section','Text','EU-GDPR is the personal information protection law of the EU (European Union) that took effect from 25, 2018. Since administrative measures, such as penalties, may be imposed if the law is violated, Korean companies need to pay attention so as not to violate this law The EU has enacted the General Data Protection Regulation to protect personal information and to provide opportunities for the utilization of personal information at the same time, using the concept of general personal information, anonymous information,, and pseudonvm information: May','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2086,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Subject','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2087,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Jnderstanding cryptography, authentication technique, and access control','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2088,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and major issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2089,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Text','The seriousness of the problems caused by the expansion ad development of the cyber world are increasing by day: Even Windows and anti-virus programs are sometimes distributed after infection with a virus or alteration. From the viewpoint of information security, various security threats can be actively responded to by ensuring confidentiality and integrity: Confidentiality is based on the concept that data should be viewed only by authorized and legitimate users who hold the right to access the data, whereas integrity is based on the concept that data should be the original data without forgery or alteration: Therefore, it is very important to individually or collectively ensure confidentiality and integrity in information security, by applying them while considering the characteristics of each piece of data. day patch','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2090,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2091,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Text','To be able to explain the concept of ciphers and classical ciphers to support confidentiality: To be able to explain private encryption and encryption algorithms To be able to explain the hash function to support integrity: To be able to explain the hash function to support integrity: To be able to explain the electronic signature and public key infrastructure (PKI) for secure transactions, To be able to explain authentication techniques and authentication methods to control access. public key key','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2092,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2093,'47','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Encryption algorithm, private encryption, public encryption, hash function, authentication, digital signature, PKI, access control, cryptographic protocol, DES, AES, RSA, ECC, hash collision, certificate, multi factor authentication, session key key public key','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:35','2025-04-18 21:52:35'),(2094,'191','App\\Models\\Lesson','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:36'),(2095,'191','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Assistant manager Kim, working for web application program development company A has been in charge of developing, deploying, and maintaining Java-based source programs He should check the web pages and servers on a regular basis when processing his work. However, he is not safe from various security threats that are becoming diversified and intelligent by regular check only: He also should exchange source programs with