5-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:36'),(2100,'636','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cryptographic techniques can be divided into the symmetric cryptosystem, in which the encryption and the decryption are the same, and the public cryptosystem, in which the encryption and the decryption are different, depending on whether the encryption and the decryption key are the same key key key key key key key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:36'),(2101,'637','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 4] Classification of cryptographic techniques',NULL,'6802c9b0404a1.png','/storage/figures/6802c9b0404a1.png','2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:48'),(2102,'637','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cryptographic protocols refer to the protocols that use cryptographic techniques As a protocol means a series of finite phases in which more than 2 persons participate to achieve a certain purpose, the cryptographic protocol should prevent repudiation by a participant, or third party, to ensure a certain purpose of the concerned cryptographic protocol (authentication, confidentiality, integrity, and non-repudiation, etc ) , as well as the meaning of each message','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:36'),(2103,'527','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Cryptographic techniques are classified into the cryptographic technique and cryptographic protocol techniqu','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:36'),(2104,'638','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 5] Cryptographic algorithm',NULL,'6802c9b055aeb.png','/storage/figures/6802c9b055aeb.png','2025-04-18 21:52:36','2025-04-18 21:52:48'),(2105,'638','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The cryptographic algorithm that uses an encryption can be described as [Figure 5]. In the figure, P is text, E is the cryptographic function, and K(KE, KD) is the key value As in the method, the encryption key and the decryption key can be different. In that case, keys are expressed KE a