into the search programs and files box, by selecting [Start], and delete guest accounts and unnecessary accounts from local users and groups.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:44'),(2440,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 51] Setting account lockout',NULL,'6802c9b79781d.png','/storage/code/6802c9b79781d.png','2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:55'),(2441,'763','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The account lockout policy should be checked and set to respond to the brute force attack or password crack attack, by setting account locks, according to the number of logon failures in the security policy settings to improve system security: It is desirable to set \"Account lockout duration to 60 minutes, Account lockout threshold\" to 5 times, and Reset account lockout counter after\" to 60 minutes in Account Lockout Policy: How to set account lockout Input secpol.msc into the Search programs ad files box by selecting [Start]: Click the  Account Lockout Policy\" sub-menu under the [Account Policies] menu: Set \"Account lockout duration\" , Account lockout threshold , and \"Reset account lockout counter after\"','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:44'),(2442,'764','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Figure 52] Stop sharing unnecessary shared folders',NULL,'6802c9b7a45c0.png','/storage/code/6802c9b7a45c0.png','2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:55'),(2443,'764','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ince malware and viruses may spread through unnecessarily shared folders, unnecessary shared folders should e removed: If a shared folder needs to be used, only authorized users should be allowed to access the shared lder: Also, check the shared folder fsmgmt.msc and stop sharing if unnecessary: using How to stop sharing unnecessary shared folders Input fsmgmtmsc into the search programs and files box by selecting [Start]: Check unnecessary shared folders and sharing if sharing is not necessary: stop','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:44'),(2444,'765','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If the automatic logon function is used, an attacker can check the login account and password in the Windows registry, hacking tools. Therefore, the automatic logon function must be disabled by setting the AutoAdminLogon value in the Windows registry to  0\". How to turn off automatic administrator logon in Windows Input regedit into the Search programs and files box by selecting [Start], and Set the AutoAdminLogon value in the HKLMI Software  Microsoft| WindowsNTI CurrentVersion| Winlogon to \"0\". If there is a DefaultPassword entry\" , delete it, using entry -','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:44'),(2445,'766','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Startup programs include the programs that are executed when the computer boots. However malware can copy its code in this folder so that it is executed when the computer starts. Therefore, delete any unauthorized or unnecessary programs from the Startup programs How to delete startup programs Input msconfig into the search programs and files box by selecting [Start]: When the System Configuration dialog box opens, click the Startup tab. Check for unauthorized or unnecessary programs and click the check mark on the program to remove anc then, click the [OK] button. When pop-up window appears, prompting that the computer needs to be restarted, click the [Restart_ button,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:44','2025-04-18 21:52:44'),(2446,'767','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Unnecessary services should be stopped, because unnecessary system services can be installed and executed by default, and these services can become a security vulnerability in the system, or can waste system resources. It is recommended not to use the service installed by default, or the services that are not used for specific purpose. The system administrator should accurately identify the purpose of the target system and remove unnecessary