5-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2452,'770','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Inetd daemon executes the Internet service daemon, which is an internal program registered in /etc/inetd. conf, when requested by the external network If the access rights of inetd conf(xinetd.d) are incorrectly set, unauthorized persons can register a malicious program in this file and execute it with root privileges Therefore, include those who will be allowed to access in the /etc/hosts. allow and include those who will be denied in the letchhosts. file. deny `','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2453,'771','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If timeout is not set for a session that is not in use, it may cause problems, both in confidentiality anc availability: Therefore, the connected session should be set in way that it is blocked from the server question, if not used for a specified period of time How to set session idle timeout Add \"TIMEOUT-300\" (stop sessions if not used for 300 seconds) to the \"/etc/default/login\" fil Add TMOUT-300, export TMOUT\" to the /etc/profile or.profile file in HP-UX, AIX, and Linux:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2454,'772','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','he /etc/profile file is a login script for setting the default use environment of all the in users. If the access ght of the /etc/profile is incorrectly set, unauthorized users can cause a breach incident by changing the user vironment, using various methods. Therefore, remove the writing privilege for the /etc/profile from the users, her than the root (bin). log-1','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2455,'773','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To check the umask setting details of the current user, run the \'umask\" command at the command prompt The umask value should be set to \"027\" or \"022\". If the umask value is set to \"027\" , a file is created with the access rights of \"rW-r-- and if the umask value is set to \"022\" , a file is created with the access rights of \"rw-r--r- Therefore, the umask value should be set to \"022 So as not to allow unnecessary access: In SUN, uncomment the UMASK option in the /etc/default/login file and set it to 022. For other UNIX operating systems, add \"Umask 022\" in the .profile','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2456,'593','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Setting privileges to the users default configuration file','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2457,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 34  List of daemon services and check ports',NULL,'6802c9b7d101a.png','/storage/tables/6802c9b7d101a.png','2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:55'),(2458,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c9b7e8d1b.png','/storage/tables/6802c9b7e8d1b.png','2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:55'),(2459,'774','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If unnecessary service ports are open, it can cause security vulnerability: Therefore, unused services should be removed. <Table 34  shows a list of daemon services and service ports that should be checked for stopping:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:45'),(2460,'775','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c9b8098db.png','/storage/code/6802c9b8098db.png','2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:56'),(2461,'775','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'6802c9b81c99e.png','/storage/code/6802c9b81c99e.png','2025-04-18 21:52:45','2025-04-18 21:52:56'),(2462,'775','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Anonymous FTP allows a malicious user to obtain information about the system: Since various attacks can be made if writing permission is set in the directory, the use of anonymous FTP should be restricted by setting it in such a way that only necessary users can access. Also, secure FTP should be used, rather than FTP with weak security: gain When general FTP by anonymous FTP or by setting u