 company analysis, and competitor analysis In customer analysis, the market size ad market growth rate are estimated by identifying the customer target, product positioning, and customer demand hierarchy: In company analysis the internallexternal environment surrounding the company, as well as its strengths and weaknesses are examined (in conjunction with the SWOT analysis technique) and used in setting the companys and developing its strategies In competitor analysis, current competitors and potential competitors are identified by using market analysis and the competitors\' financial data and business portfolios The 4Ps consist of product, price, place (place of sale) , and promotion: In product analysis, the design, brand, characteristics, brand power, performance, ad quality of the product concerned are analyzed: In price analysis, the product price, discount condition, and demand as a function of price levels are analyzed, and the is compared to the prices of the competitors, and the price flexibility is examined In place analysis, the region of product sales, distribution, logistics, and inventory levels are analyzed . In promotion analysis the advertising, promotion, marketing, and customer communication strategies are analyzed goals price','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:37','2025-04-19 12:44:37'),(2627,'810','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.14] 7S Analysis Method',NULL,'68039add97e95.png','/storage/figures/68039add97e95.png','2025-04-19 12:44:37','2025-04-19 12:45:17'),(2628,'810','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The 7S model used to analyze a companys internal environment is an internal environmental analysis technique created by the McKinsey consulting firm. This is a method of diagnosing a company by identifying its core competency components It defines the core competency components of a company in terms of 7 items that start with the letter S:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:37','2025-04-19 12:44:37'),(2629,'810','App\\Models\\Subsecti