valuate a companys portfolio of products and business services, and also to evaluate single company or a single department within a company:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:37','2025-04-19 12:44:37'),(2636,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2637,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Text','IT business planning starts with an understanding of the company\'s vision, goals, strategies and tasks, and the first step is to build enterprise architecture (EA) In addition, companies also turn to information strategy planning (ISP) when deploying information systems for their IT division: It is through IT governance, which stands at the center of this trend, that companies establish their system of managing their IT businesses Companies that adopt EA are also deploying an enterprise architecture management system (EAMS) for managing the continuous upgrading of the EA, and are working hard to close the gap between strategy ad IT business In recent years the public sector has begun to require a detailed list of specifications (ie a list detailed enough to calculate functional scores) by including it in the request for a proposal (RFP) when awarding a contract ISP is often carried out for each type of job to enable companies to produce this detailed specification list Dusiness: In recent years,, the sector has begun to require a detailed list of specifications (i.e. a list detailed enough to calculate functional scores) by including it in the request for a proposal (RFP) when awarding 3 contract ISP is often carried out for each type of job to enable companies to produce this detailed snecification list public','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2638,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2639,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain IT governance 2 To be able to explain Enterprise architecture 3. To be able to explain Information strategy planning (ISP)','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2640,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2641,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Text','IT governance, enterprise architecture (EA) information strategy planning( ISP)','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2642,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2643,'56','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Company A_ is a company whose main focus is its financial business As the companys capabilities grew, so did its size, leading each department and team to begin installing its own small systems here and there This in tum led to overlapping developments and other difficulties associated with development Compared to the allocated budget, the level of informatization attained was disappointingly low: Thus, company A\' decided to adopt an EA after recognizing the need to establish a plan-based informatization strategy aimed at preventing or eliminating development efforts that could overlap or be carried out indiscriminately: It conducted inspections of and reengineered its current business processes, and established mid-to-long-term plans for the job responsibilities each of its stakeholders, as well as its applications, data, and technologies Furthermore, the company established information strategy planning in order to develop informatization strategies at the division level When establishing the ISP, the company devised a plan that used the current information of the EA to prevent any overlapping of development activities and indiscriminate development: The adoption of ISP made it possible for the company to derive the detailed requirements of each individual system and to set up a system for the efficient calculation and verification of the business','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:39','2025-04-19 12:44:39'),(2644,'222','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','IT business must begin with the establishment of a strategy before moving on to planning: The two main activities performed during the IT business planning stage are the enterprise architecture (EA) and information strategic planning (ISP): This is one of the ways of planning the macro perspective and serves to prevent indiscriminate and overlapping development activities when a company is pursuing an IT business IT goverance provides control over the implementation of the EA and ISP ad secures the linkage of the IT business strategy with IT values It also provides risk management, resource management, and performance measurement systems The section on IT goverance describes the concepts and frameworks of IT goverance and introduces the areas of focus of IT governance The EA section describes the concepts ad components of the EA and introduces the EA framework The ISP section introduces the concept of ISP and explains the ISP deployment procedure as well as the main outputs of ISP deployment: These plans - generated during the IT business planning stage are first created for the deployment of IT business and then for the operation of IT business processes ad services, eventually leading to their utilization in evaluations of IT business performance from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2645,'624','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table5 Definitions of IT governance',NULL,'68039addd7c4c.png','/storage/tables/68039addd7c4c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:45:17'),(2646,'624','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The aim of IT governance is to implant a for controlling and managing a companys IT to the same degree as corporate governance In other words, IT governance can contribute to realizing business targets by aligning IT resources with a companys and strategies By defining the roles &nd responsibilities within an organization, goverance creates a control and management structure for handling the performance results ad risks of IT The table below gives some concrete descriptions of IT. system goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2647,'813','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The governance area consists of 5 processes (evaluation (E), directive (D), monitoring (M), etc ), each of which comes with its own work procedures EDM 1. Establish the measurement standard with the governance framework EDM 2 Provide profits EDM 3. Minimize risks imize rickc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2648,'814','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The management are consists of 4 process phases: planning (APO), deployment (BAI), operation (DSS) , monitoring (MEA) The management are consists of 4 process phases: planning (APO), deployment (BAI), operation (DSS) , monitoring (MEA) Planning (APO) phase: planning Deplovment (BAI) phase: deploving acauiring configuring linking, (MEA) Planning (APO) phase: linking, planning Deployment (BAI) phase: deploying, acquiring, configuring Operation (DSS)phase: transferring, service, support Nonitorino AFAInhace- monitorino evaluationc raviiem The IT governance framework is linked to the international standard ISOJIEC 38500, which simultaneously provides','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2649,'814','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','the principles and frameworks required to evaluate, direct, ad monitor the utilization of IT by companies','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2650,'625','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.17] COBIT 5,a reference model for IT governance',NULL,'68039addeffc3.png','/storage/figures/68039addeffc3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:45:17'),(2651,'625','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Due to the alignment of IT with the business of a company, in IT governance, the value of IT contributes to the attainment of business performance and results, Through the management of risks and core IT resources for the efficient operation of IT,the roles ad responsibilities related to IT resources are clearly defined. IT governance is structured to ensure reliability and transparency: The following figure shows the governance framework reference model of COBIT 5 (Control Objects for Information and Related Technology 5): This framework is widely known as the \"IT goverance framework\". In the reference model, the governance and management processes of a company are kept separate. goals good Business needs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2652,'815','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The planning stage involves linking business with IT, setting the of IT, establishing the structures, activities ad mechanisms regarding the rules on organizing IT related activities, using resources, managing risks, the governance structure, and measuring performance goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2653,'816','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The monitoring of IT resources, IT risks ad IT management involves all the structures, activities and relatec mechanisms for helping companies to monitor their IT resources, IT risks and IT management The monitoring IT performance measurement involves the structures, activities and related mechanisms for helping companies to set target levels (for their performances related to IT resources, IT risks ad IT management) and measure their attainment of such targets','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2654,'817','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IT value is evaluated through the earings ad costs of the future business opportunities delivered to the compar IT value includes strategic, economic, and risk management, as well as technical, social and quality benefits. To arri at the IT value, the costs of business risk ad other potential risk costs are subtracted from business opportunities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2655,'818','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ased on the results of the evaluation of the feedback information and the need to prioritize this information, during his stage a company takes corrective measures aimed at improving its IT governance activities Included in suct','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2656,'818','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','corrective measures are the structures, activities and procedures for improving the IT governance process and the related jobs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2657,'626','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 18] IT governance process',NULL,'68039ade132dc.png','/storage/figures/68039ade132dc.png','2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2658,'626','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IT governance process is composed of the planning stage, operations stage, evaluation stage, and feedback stage','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2659,'627','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 6 Focus areas of IT governance',NULL,'68039ade34d0f.png','/storage/tables/68039ade34d0f.png','2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2660,'627','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT governance has five key areas of focus, all of which are linked to the strategies of a company: IT governance looke at how a companys strategies are used in conjunction with IT value, and also includes the management of risk factor and the management of resources, as well as a performance evaluation system on activities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:40','2025-04-19 12:44:40'),(2661,'819','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','EA stands for \"enterprise architecture\" It is a blueprint that explains the IT business of an enterprise in a way that is easy for the stakeholders to understand, so that the enterprise can achieve its strategic and the of its information resource management Enterprise architecture is a blueprint that defines the current state of the relationship between information technology and an enterpriselas well as the activities carried out by the enterprise) and the state that the enterprise must strive for in the future \"-United States Office of Management and Budget (OMB) goals goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2662,'820','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Currently, enterprises ae enthusiastically introducing information systems to cope with the rapidly changing business environments but if information systems are deployed without proper planning at the macro level, enterprises will be confronted with a redundant system ad an inability to collaborate Such enterprises will fall into the so-called \"IT Productivity Paradox\"1 which can be described as the continuous adoption of information systems without seeing any benefits in the form of increased corporate profits','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2663,'820','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There may be several causes of this paradox, but in most cases it is attributable to the lack of a system for clearly explaining companys business and IT operations to its stakeholders from an overall perspective For these reasons, enterprises need an EA, as it can provide a bird\'s eye view of the enterprises business while simultaneously creating close working relationships between different information resources','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2664,'821','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 19] The concept diagram of EA',NULL,'68039ade4d013.png','/storage/figures/68039ade4d013.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2665,'821','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The deployment of an EA starts with the enterprise business strategy The enterprise business strategy is converged with the IT strategy, and the EA is the fruit of this convergence','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2666,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 7  Components of an EA',NULL,'68039ade62b04.png','/storage/tables/68039ade62b04.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2667,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ade7fdca.png','/storage/tables/68039ade7fdca.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2668,'822','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An EA is delegated or inherits the IT governance control system. To be more precise, the establishment of an EA itself is both an act of IT governance and an instrument of IT governance control. In addition to IT governance, the components of an EA are business architecture (BA), applied architecture (AA), data architecture (DA), and technology architecture (TA): The standard profile (SP) is a sub-structure of the technology architecture and can be understood as the detailed specifications of a list of technologies key There is a reference model for each individual architecture, namely the performance reference model (PRM) , service component reference model, data reference model, and technology reference model,, respectively: The reference model provides early reference cases in an identical business sector or similar industries that a company could use as a guide when it seeks to deploy an EA There is also a goverment EA reference model for government-wide EA which is used as a reference When EAs are deployed at the departmental level As a side note, the government-wide EA includes security architecture in addition to the four abovementioned architectures','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2669,'630','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table8  Types of EA framework',NULL,'68039ade9f95e.png','/storage/tables/68039ade9f95e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2670,'630','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039adeb9a19.png','/storage/tables/68039adeb9a19.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:18'),(2671,'630','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The Zachman Framework, TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture) , and FEAF (Federal Enterprise Architecture Framework) are some of the leading EA frameworks in use today: The Zachmann Framework is the one used most often when establishing a EA TOGAF,, created by The Open Group, is an open framework that focuses on interoperability between companies FEAF is also a framework developed in 1998 by the US. CIO Council with the help of the Jacquesman Framework and Spewak','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2672,'631','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The literal meaning of the acronym ISP is \"Information Strategy Plan\" . Generally, the term \"ISP establishment\" is used more frequently as an overarching concept: ISP can present a vision for the information system and information management structure that can support an enterprise or organization when it is developing its mid-to-long term vision and goals and business plan In other words, it can be understood as a plan that provides a rough sketch of the direction of information system deployment to aid the enterprise in realizing its term objectives long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2673,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 9 Basic composition of ISPI',NULL,'68039adf1e22e.png','/storage/tables/68039adf1e22e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2674,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In order to deploy an ISP, the externaljinternal environment of the company and the information environment must be analyzed first of all When analyzing the environment of a company, tools like SWOT, 5-Force,7S and 4C are commonly used. In addition, when analyzing the information environment, the technology requirements corresponding to the purpose and background of a project must be reviewed in detail by studying the technology trends and analyzing the application of new technologies The next step consists in analyzing the current operation of the company: The most important item that must be checked in this analysis is the business process. A careful study of the business process in its current state will reveal various factors at work in a company or an organization In addition, analyzing the information systems scattered throughout the company and drawing out the requirements of stakeholders and the improvement agenda are also important tasks to be undertaken at this stage. Also, through the benchmarking of earlier cases in the same or similar industries, missing or distorted information can be corrected to some extent guide on information strategic planning (ISP) , National Information Society Agency,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2675,'632','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The results of the analysis of the enterprise environment and the current state of the enterprise constitute & important resource when determining directions for improvement,, developing improved job procedures, and creating an informatization plan in the last stage of ISP establishment:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2676,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 10  Output of each ISP stage (example)',NULL,'68039adf4af56.png','/storage/tables/68039adf4af56.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2677,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 11  Comparison of ISP and EA concepts',NULL,'68039adf6ffcb.png','/storage/tables/68039adf6ffcb.png','2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2678,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The ISP deployment process comprises a set of activities that must be performed at each stage, ad the results hese activities become the output of the deployment. An example of a list of typical outputs that could be used in ISP is shown below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2679,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Although the actual implementation of ISP produces far more diverse and complex outputs, the most valuable output has to be a blueprint for a process for a future model and a set of activities for attaining a companys This content must feature sufficiently in the output When comparing ISP to the EA described earlier it can be said that ISP deals with plans that fall within the scope of EA but which are more microscopic than the EA An examination of the scope of ISP as described in the table below indicates that its scope, When compared to the EA, is more focused on the informatization strategy: goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2680,'633','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In other words, the EA is deployed under a companys target architecture ad incorporates the latest information technology so that it can align the direction of its IT with its management strategy: Therefore, the EA must be managed in a way that allows a company to respond quickly to changes in the business management environment,, and must be flexible, so that the companys agenda can be implanted quickly through continuous updating, and in a way that ensures that the roadmap is shared with the rest of the organization','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:41','2025-04-19 12:44:41'),(2681,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent Trends and Major Issues','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2682,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Text','When a company is contemplating the deployment of an IT business, the decision to develop it in-house or outsource its development has always been a difficult decision to make from a corporate perspective It is also difficult to choose whether to use package products or to develop systems from scratch When the decision is made to outsource IT For these reasons, whenever a company pursues the deployment of an IT business, it has to make an in- depth study of what method would enable the company to respond actively to changes in the environment and be of help to the continued existence and development of the IT business There is a growing awareness that,, in order to strengthen corporate competitiveness, specific procedures must be developed for the adoption of an IT business, and that, at the end of its deployment, comes the building of the information system. As a result, for the adoption of an IT business to produce the maximum effect, a company must set up an organizational structure and process for the many different standards involved in the building and operation of the information system','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2683,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2684,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Text','To be able to explain the method and process of IT business adoption To be able to explain IT business outsourcing:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2685,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2686,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Method of IT business adoption, IT business adoption procedure, IT business outsourcing','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2687,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2688,'57','App\\Models\\Module','Text','According to a 2010 survey by the Ministry of the Interior and Safety, 44 percent of the additional costs incurred due to excessive work changes were borne by central administrative agencies while 15.3 percent were borne by local governments. These results have raised concerns that the planning ad design information systems for deployment in the public sector are performed poorly: Legislation has been passed requiring the issuance of a detailed RFP and the PMO program when ar organization seeks to deploy an IT business. However, the findings from surveys like the one described above suggest that people are still not aware of the benefits of deploying an information system and that most people also lack expertise. Recently, the government has been working on introducing & split order process\" for the purpose 0 Incurred que tO excessive wOrK cnanges were porne py central aaministrativve agencies, wnile 15.3 percent were borne by local governments These results have raised concerns that the planning and design of information systems for deployment in the sector are performed poorly: Legislation has been passed requiring the issuance of a detailed RFP and the PMO program when a organization seeks to deploy an IT business. However, the findings surveys like the one described above suggest that people are still not aware of the benefits of deploying an information system and that most people also lack expertise Recently, the government has been working on introducing a split order process\" for the purpose of preventing irresponsible work changes ad eradicating the unfair subcontracting structure which involves the ordering agency, bidding company and sub-contractor The split order process roughly means that when an IT business is adopted, planning/design is split from deployment/development: In the planning/design phase, a more detailed requirement analysis of the Information Strategy Plan (ISP) is carried out with the information master plan (ISMP) and the basic design (logical design) : In the deployment/development phase, detailed design (physical design) , system development (coding) , and testing are carried out Many have voiced their concerns about the adoption of the split order process. Nevertheless, it is significant in that an environment can be created in which planning and design can be done more meticulously and systematically: This environment can also overcome the invisibility of software ad lead people to understand how frequent changes in requirements can act as impediments to the adoption of IT public from system','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2689,'226','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The adoption of an IT business must be executed in alignment with a companys IT business strategy and plans Methods and procedures of IT business adoption must be created in accordance with the size of the organization and changes in the external environment of the company: The utsourcing of IT services should be considered for the non-core areas or processes of the company: The IT business adoption process utilizes the ordering process and the software development life cycle of ISOJIEC 12207. This is because the core value of IT is implemented in software, and the success of software development is the key to the successful adoption of IT business IT outsourcing helps with improving a companys competitiveness because it relies on external expert resources However, the work-related and technology-related lock-in that outsourcing entails is a problem that must be addressed through the introduction of regulatory measures','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:44:42'),(2690,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 12  Detailed description of examples of ordering processes',NULL,'68039adf9299a.png','/storage/tables/68039adf9299a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:42','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2691,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'20] IT business ordering process [Fig',NULL,'68039adfa745a.png','/storage/figures/68039adfa745a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2692,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The IT business ordering process defines the activities and tasks of the orderer and describes a set of processes for deploying systems or software or services The process also includes such activities as concept definition and detailed specification of the requirements concerning the items ordered, preparation of the RFP, evaluation of the proposal, contracting, supplier management,, and acquisition of the end output,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2693,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Text','By using the IT business ordering process, a company can define the activities of the contractor and supplier that must be performed when deploying a information system and also enhance the success rate of the information service business The ordering process provides a means of communication between the orderer and the supplier, and lends visibility to','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2694,'634','App\\Models\\Section','Text','T business adoption, resulting in a predictable procedure','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2695,'823','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 13  Detailed process of the basic lifecycle process',NULL,'68039adfb8862.png','/storage/tables/68039adfb8862.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2696,'823','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039adfca47e.png','/storage/tables/68039adfca47e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2697,'823','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The basic life process consists of five sub-processes and provides support to the stakeholders participating the software lifecycle process. cycle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2698,'824','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table14 Detailed process of the support lifecycle process',NULL,'68039adfe2c86.png','/storage/tables/68039adfe2c86.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:19'),(2699,'824','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The support lifecycle process consists of eight sub-processes and plays the role of supporting other processes. It contributes to the quality and success of the outputs','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2700,'825','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 15  Detailed description of the organization lifecycle process',NULL,'68039ae0068df.png','/storage/tables/68039ae0068df.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2701,'825','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The organization lifecycle process consists of four sub-processes which serve to configure the underlying structure of the organization lifecycle process for the business, without constrained by a specific project or informatior system deployment contract, being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2702,'635','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ISOJIEC 12207 is an international standard for the software adoption lifecycle. It provides a standardized and systematic process for acquiring, supplying, developing, operating, and maintaining software ISOJIEC 12207 consists of three main processes and a detailed procedure for each process. ISOJIEC 12207 defines all the processes activities, and tasks that can be applied to the adoption and development of many different forms of software, but it contains no specifications regarding the naming, form, and contents of the output. Therefore, if ISOJIEC 12207 is used together with SPICE (Software Process Improvement and Capability Determination) or CMMI (Capability Maturity Model Integration), not just the WHAT but the HOW of the SW adoption process can be learned.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2703,'636','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 16  Important considerations for the tailoring process',NULL,'68039ae01e535.png','/storage/tables/68039ae01e535.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2704,'636','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In addition to the main processes described above, there is also the tailoring2 process. The tailoring process defines the basic activities required for tailoring: It is the process of eliminating activities ad tasks that are not applied or perceived as unnecessary in the life cycle process Although the tailoring process is generally known as the optimization of the software development methodology, this','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2705,'636','App\\Models\\Section','Text','section explains the part of tailoring that has to do with software adoption Before software is adopted, the adoption procedure, method, and outputs must be optimized to accommodate changes in the internal and external requirements. The need for tailoring becomes most acute for unit-level projects In these situations, the best software adoption environment can be created through tailoring','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2706,'227','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','A companys ordering process is used as the basic procedure for adopting an IT business. The agent that places an order is the department or person responsible for issuing the requirements, while the agent of development is the companys computer department or an external expert on outsourcing: Furthermore, it should be mentioned here that the lifecycle (SDLC, Software Development Lifecycle) of SW after adoption must follow the standard procedures defined in ISOJIEC 12207.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2707,'826','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This is a form of adoption that allows companies to set up and develop information systems their owr manpower resulting in a system that is faithful to the internal requirements of the company While know-how can be accumulated with this method, it involves relatively higher adoption costs, while success cannot be guaranteed. using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2708,'827','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 17  Comparison of in-house development and package purchase',NULL,'68039ae0455ba.png','/storage/tables/68039ae0455ba.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2709,'827','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','This is a form of adoption under which a company can easily absorb the know-how gained from early cases of IT business adoption: By adopting a system that has undergone many tests and adoption verifications uncertainty about success can be eliminated. The adoption is short and the cost is relatively low, but the maintenance costs are likely to increase period From the perspectives of the IT business, in-house development and package purchase have their own distinct advantages and disadvantages. IT business used to be adopted using either one of the methods, but these days companies frequently opt for a hybrid approach to adoption In other words, the in-house development method is used for the overall approach while the packaged product method is chosen when acquiring the component technologies This method results in reduced costs and helps reduce risks when adopting IT businesses.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2710,'228','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','There are two distinct methods of adopting a IT business: in-house development and package purchase. The advantage of in-house development is that it allows a company to fully reflect the needs of users by utilizing its own internal personnel A purchased package has the advantage of being based on a standardized advanced process which is conducive to improving work efficiency:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2711,'638','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A company can turn to several strategies when it has to respond quickly to changing internal and external environments For operational areas and processes where a company is certain that it holds a competitive edge, it will try to improve and develop further in order to strengthen its competitive advantage For non-strategic areas or processes where it is weak however, a company may tur to excellent outside resources For this reason, a company may seek to perform important activities (or those value chain activities where it enjoys competitive advantages) in-house, whereas for non-strategic areas and areas where it is weak, it will subcontract out the work to outside experts or third-party companies This is what is meant by \"outsourcing\" and, to be more exact, \"IT business outsourcing\" when IT resources are involved In IT business outsourcing, companies outsource IT resources, IT management, &d IT operations and usually focus on their core operational areas, thus enabling them to retain their competitive advantages','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2712,'639','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 21] Conceptual diagram of IT business outsourcing adoption process',NULL,'68039ae06336c.png','/storage/figures/68039ae06336c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2713,'639','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When a company opts for IT outsourcing, it begins by identifying its core competencies and selecting the tasks to be outsourced. Once the target task has been selected, the vendor will be chosen, and negotiations will proceed until a contract is signed  The most important task is for the company and the vendor to reach a clear-cut agreement on how the index for service levels will be managed','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2714,'640','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 18  Forms of IT business outsourcing',NULL,'68039ae081f85.png','/storage/tables/68039ae081f85.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2715,'640','App\\Models\\Section','Text','T business outsourcing can take one of four forms.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2716,'641','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Tablel9 Issues and considerations when adopting outsourcing',NULL,'68039ae09fd02.png','/storage/tables/68039ae09fd02.png','2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2717,'641','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In the course of outsourcing a IT business a company will come across many types of problems: To address these problems, the following steps could be considered:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2718,'641','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT outsourcing requires continuous oversight of the outsource vendor (company) . Standards like eSCM and ISO/ IECZOOOO can be used for the oversight. It is necessary to establish a security system to prevent leakages of critical corporate information while managing the level of and continuously monitoring changes in, the service so as to secure optimal service quality When it is not a specific job category, but the whole or a part of the business process has to be outsourced, a company needs to adopt and operate business process outsourcing (BPO):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:43','2025-04-19 12:44:43'),(2719,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae0b2fce.png','/storage/figures/68039ae0b2fce.png','2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2720,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2721,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Text','F_ \"p# Cf- ~p_ quickly to changes in its environment. After the initial set-up, a process becomes optimized with the passage of time, with changes in the business environment playing a important role as an optimizing factor To improve the IT business process on a continuous basis, it is critical to monitor bottlenecks in the process. Companies in this situation usually turn to BPR or PI to rectify the bottleneck issue The most challenging task when pursuing BPR or PI is to persuade and convince a companys own employees This is because it is humans who operate the process and humans who are also the subjects of any process innovations. Therefore, ceaseless persuading and the creation of an atmosphere in which employees feel they can share in the companys growth are critical elements to the success of the process.','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2722,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2723,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the constituent elements of the IT business process 2 To be able to explain the various methods of improving the IT business process','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2724,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2725,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Text','BPM, BAM, BRE, ILM, IRM, BRP, PI, 6 Sigma, Trees, Servqual, SPC','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2726,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Text','BPR Case Study: Information technology It strategy of Starbucks','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2727,'58','App\\Models\\Module','Text','tne unitea States, 1,550 in Canaaa, 1,088 In Japan, ana 544in Korea. A unique experience, high-quality coffee ad beverages friendly employees, TM and friendly coffee shop interior are just some of the differentiating factors that set it apart from the rest of the competition, and which have propelled the company to its commanding market position However, the economic downtum that began in 2008 also affected Starbucks, whose sales dropped by more than 50 percent by the end of 2008. However, Starbucks used this seemingly disastrous market situation as a opportunity to transform its business by integrating wireless technology ad the mobile digital platform into its business process As of this endeavor, the company conducted a customer analysis whose results indicated that more than 1/3 of its customers were enthusiastic users of smartphones. This finding led the company to introduce a smartphone app-based payment technology with which customers could pay for their purchases using their prepaid cards or rechargeable cards. It also created the \'Starbucks Digital Network\' in partnership with Yahoo after noticing that visitors to its stores were regularly using its free WiFi service This network, through its content portal function, provides free Wall Street Joural articles for customers to read and free downloadable tunes iTunes for customers to enjoy: Furthermore, the company internally worked on its business process more efficient Now, Starbucks baristas no longer have to bend down when making coffee, while the total time spent waiting for the coffee to be made has been minimized and the time spent on making drinks has been reduced. To this end, the company formed the Lean Team to advise the company on benchmarking the lean manufacturing method pioneered by Toyota Motor Company: What\'s more, the company built a smart work environment with wireless technology that maximizes the work efficiency of its employees Within this smart work environment,, Starbucks employees can do their work in any store across the nation. This has resulted in about 25% longer store visiting times by the companys regional managers Howard Schultz, the CEO of Starbucks said, \"Most of the cost savings _ come from new ways of operating our stores and new customer services\" . Successful changes like this have helped Starbucks to recover its profitability and maintain its growth. part from making gained','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2728,'642','App\\Models\\Section','Text','From 2010 to 2011,the Korea Workers Compensation & Welfare Service (COMWEL) built an advanced administration through a wide-scale process innovation (PI) project. Process innovation (PI) cannot be realized simply by setting up a system or with training alone: It can only be successful when there is a company-wide consensus the top management level to the working-level staff of the organization and when the best practices are applied to the organization process and fully interalized. For this reason, it is very difficult for conservative institutions to implement project innovations. However, with COMWEL\'s systematic project management ad utilization, it has so successfully implemented process innovation that it has become a benchmark for other institutions to follow: COMWEL pursued process innovation under the banner of \'job efficiencies through process innovation\' because it wanted to improve the quality of its public services despite having limited human resources It began the task of increasing job efficiency with interal discussions over those areas most in need of improvement Starting with AS-IS process diagnosis consulting, COMWEL next studied the end-to-end process of each job, and then selected the processes requiring process innovation (PI): The requirements at the working level were identified and extracted, and the information thus obtained was used in setting up the BPM, the process-based knowledge management (PKMS) , and the enterprise information display (EID) system. Among 50 core processes, systemization was completed for the 25 processes that were expected to produce the greatest effects once the process innovations were up ad running: COMWEL focused on improving its public service by eliminating unnecessary procedures and simplifying unnecessarily complex ones Process innovation (PI) was continuously performed around the framework of process establishment monitoring improvement activities- process establishment Through process innovation, when a user searches for reference data, the system provides to the user the information that is most relevant to the user\'s query: As the amount of information accumulates in this system,, the relevancy of the information multiplies In addition, the management was able to reduce risks by quickly modifying the management strategies after identifying the management plans and core information of all the business units at a glance In addition, management was able to a quick view of the business plans of all business divisions and the key information of the COMWEL ad make quick changes to its business management strategy so as to reduce risk system from public system top get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2729,'231','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The IT business process is both a set of tools for implementing IT business and a procedure that allows companies to continue with their activities The IT business process can be divided into people, organizations, and job process, and is intimately tied to the core components of enterprise management IT business processes consist of business process management (BPM) for managing processes, business activity monitoring (BAM) for monitoring process bottlenecks, the business rule engine (BRE) for managing the business process task rules, and BPRIPI, an innovation tool for processes The IT business process tools described above form mutually dynamic relationships with each other, and through these relationships the process undergoes continuous improvements. The value of business process improvements plays an important role in enhancing a companys competitiveness because a system is created that can respond Jicklv to chanoec in itc internal and extemal environmentc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:45','2025-04-19 12:44:45'),(2730,'643','App\\Models\\Section','Text','People participating in an enterprise as members of the organization, and the organization that carries out the function of dividing, consolidating, and connecting different jobs, are the elements of IT business execution: An organization is a activity or system consciously created by more than two people As such, it is important to maintain internal and external balance, effectiveness, and efficiency to fulfill their desires and common objectives of communication, volunteer work, and collaboration Through the division of functions and responsibilities, an organization allocates human resources so that it can fulfill the agreed-upon objectives more effectively: key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2731,'644','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 20  Relationships between the functions and business processes of an enterprise',NULL,'68039ae0cd0ad.png','/storage/tables/68039ae0cd0ad.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2732,'644','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An enterprise is a formal organization whose objective is the pursuit of profits through the sale of or services at prices higher than the costs required to produce them: Furthermore, an enterprise can be viewed as a collection of interrelated business functions (or activities) defined by various business rules with the aim of realizing some objectives. Here, the term \"business rules\" refers to the rules that determine when, how, in what order, and which rules should be Business rules (e. processes) have a significant impact on an organization s management, performance, and value creation The of describing the method and the job of organizing work in a enterprise is called the \"business process\". Examples of common business processes by function (such as manufacturing and production, sales ad marketing, finance and HR management) are described in the table below goods applied step','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2733,'232','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','(Business Model)A strategic blueprint for organizing and implementing an enterprise organization\'s structure, processes, and systems to create value for the enterprise is called a business model. Made up of core business areas such as customers, order, infrastructure, and business feasibility analysis, a business model can enhance the value of Dn (Business Execution)To remain agile in a rapidly changing business environment, the core business processes of an enterprise must be integrated across its various departments to give the enterprise the increased flexibility it needs to survive: An enterprise also has to take care of the underlying assets that it needs to operate, such as core competencies, finance, and human resources, and have the infrastructure to make decisions quickly There are the basic elements that a enterprise must possess to operate its business, and these include the people who make up the organization, the job for managing the operation, and the tools for managing the business of the enterprise system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2734,'233','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae0ddda0.png','/storage/tables/68039ae0ddda0.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:20'),(2735,'233','App\\Models\\Lesson','Tables',NULL,'[Fig: 22] Examples of the IT business process',NULL,'68039ae10552a.png','/storage/tables/68039ae10552a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2736,'233','App\\Models\\Lesson','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae126c48.png','/storage/figures/68039ae126c48.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2737,'233','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The figure below is a diagram of the typical service process of a company that sells multifunctional printersIf a customer encounters a problem with the multifunctional printer he/she has been using, helshe requests a repair service by contacting the customer center The center assigns a member of the service personnel if a visit to the customer\'s site is deemed to be warranted. The service personnel assigned to the task talks to the customer to determine the svmptoms and schedule the visit.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2738,'233','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','The service personnel will then visit the customer at the appointed time to examine the problem with the printer and repair it The service personnel will request the customers signature as confirmation of completion of the repair work In the case of repairs, the customer will be billed for the repairs, which translates into revenues for the company: When the sales amount and service fee are settled and a sale is confirmed, a tax invoice is issued and delivered to the customer Upon receipt of the tax invoice, the customer proceeds with the payment paid repair it The service personnel will request the customers signature as confirmation of completion of the repair work In the case of repairs, the customer will be billed for the repairs, which translates into revenues for the company: When the sales amount and service fee are settled and a sale is confirmed, a tax invoice is issued and delivered to the customer Upon receipt of the tax invoice, the customer proceeds with the payment: The money received and deposited by the customer is settled by crediting the accounts receivables through the deposit process. This series of processes enables the enterprise to perform two activities. First, it can provide customer services through service activities &d, second, it can generate profits. The processes involved in the payment-based service fall under the following job domains: service, accounting materials, and revenue (sales): While some of these business processes are firmly cemented, most of them have to be improved and be able to adant flexiblv to changes in the business environment An environment must be created wherein waste and paid The money received and deposited by the customer is settled by crediting the accounts receivables through the deposit process. This series of processes enables the enterprise to perform two activities First, it can provide customer services through service activities and, second, it can generate profits. The processes involved in the payment-based service fall under the following job domains: service, accounting, materials, and revenue (sales): While some of these business processes are firmly cemented, most of them have to be improved and be able to adapt flexibly to changes in the business environment An environment must be created wherein waste and bottlenecks can be constantly identified and jobs quickly processed.','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2739,'828','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 21  BPM design stages',NULL,'68039ae149605.png','/storage/tables/68039ae149605.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2740,'828','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business process management (BPM) is a technique for the consolidated management, optimization and automation of the flow of people, information resources, and tasks associated with IT business processes It is also an important means of implementing IT business processes: How well the overall process is managed can have direct repercussions for business performance Hence, it is essential to take a logical ad structured approach to managing the IT business process. BPM must be capable of handling changes in the management environment and should be designed to be capable of responding activelv to changes in business processes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2741,'645','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 23] Conceptual diagram of IT business process management',NULL,'68039ae15ad3e.png','/storage/figures/68039ae15ad3e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2742,'645','App\\Models\\Section','Text','BPM is a technique of IT business process management that consists in optimizing and automating business processes In addition, BAM is a technique for discovering and managing bottlenecks in business processes, while BRE is a business rule engine that sets and manages the flow of business processes key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2743,'830','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 23  Component elements of BRE',NULL,'68039ae1717d0.png','/storage/tables/68039ae1717d0.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2744,'830','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business rule engine (BRE) is a technique for effectively managing, automating, and optimizing processes by formalizing the complex business rules and process flows of an enterprise: The ever increasing volume of information processed by IT business processes and the increasing complexity of process flows have led to the need for rule- based management. Rule-based management is also needed for service improvements and cost savings. For this reason, the adoption of BRE can help enterprises to proactively manage changes in, and reduce the operating costs of, business processes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2745,'646','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 22  Base technologies of BAM',NULL,'68039ae1879af.png','/storage/tables/68039ae1879af.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2746,'646','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Business activity monitoring (BAM) is technique for optimizing IT business processes It detects ad controls','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2747,'646','App\\Models\\Section','Text','process bottlenecks by monitoring processes in real time and recognizing risk factors in advance BAM also uses extended business intelligence (Bl) techniques for real-time analysis, and monitors and manages the process flow for business process monitoring (BPM):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2748,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 24  Constituent elements of ILM',NULL,'68039ae1a2056.png','/storage/tables/68039ae1a2056.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2749,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 24] Conceptual diagram of ILM',NULL,'68039ae1b693a.png','/storage/figures/68039ae1b693a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2750,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Information life cycle management (ILM) is a series of processes for separating and managing storage media, which is necessitated by ongoing changes in the value of data or information throughout its life cycle As the volume of data increases, so does the cost of managing data In contrast, the value of data changes as it goes through its life cycle: Thus, enterprises are turning to ILM in order to reduce their data management costs and manage data in a more systematic way:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2751,'831','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The constituent elements of ILM belong to one of two categories ie the management policy category or the technology element category:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2752,'832','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 25  IRM process for EA',NULL,'68039ae1d4e58.png','/storage/tables/68039ae1d4e58.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:21'),(2753,'832','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The purpose of information resource management (IRM) is the efficient and integrated management of IT resources Here, efficient and integrated management means preventing redundant investments in IT resources and increasing returns on investments It also means managing all types of IT resources HT resources to IT equipment, budgets and outputs from Ciilcipisc F Cuiccc DA: As one of the component elements of the EA, the DA describes the architecture of data','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2754,'832','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Faced with the increasing complexity and scale of enterprise information systems and the growing need for the systemized management of information resources, enterprises have become dependent on IRM because it provides a common standard and management system for the entire range of informatization procedures (informatization planning, development, and performance evaluation): The IRM informs the EA of its framework for information resources, and the EA presents the IRM with guidelines for enterprise resource schemes and reference schemes That is, IRM and EA exist in a complementary relationship:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2755,'647','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As IT business processes become ever more complex and have to respond rapidly to environmental (both external and internal) changes, there is a growing need for the systematized management of the data generated by such processes The data generated by IT business processes can be managed either by information life cycle management (ILM) or by information resource management (IRM):','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2756,'833','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','BPR is a technique for redesigning business processes in a fundamental way in order to bring about a radicz improvement in such performance indicators as cost, quality, service, and quickness. There are four attributes of BPF that should be mentioned here The first attribute is \'Basic: In BPR, activities are performed to address the basic problems of an enterprise Through BPR, answers are sought to such questions as \"For what purpose is a business task performed?\" \"What are the current problems?\" and What are the inefficient elements of an enterprise\'s operations?\" The second attribute is Zero Base\' BPR is all about designing a new way of performing business tasks by abandoning existing task procedures or processes The third attribute is \'Dramatic Improvement: BPR is used only when an absolute innovation is needed Thus, BPR signifies a radical improvement rather than a gradual improvement The fourth attribute is \'Process: The targets of BPR are mainly task processes BPR strives to resolve problems through process-centric thinking, without relying on jobs, workers, or organizational structures The aim is to','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2757,'834','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 26  BPR implementation procedure',NULL,'68039ae200d5f.png','/storage/tables/68039ae200d5f.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2758,'834','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae213d23.png','/storage/tables/68039ae213d23.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2759,'648','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The concept of business process reengineering (BPR) was first introduced in a paper published by Professor Michael Hammer of MIT in 1990. As products from Asian countries began to penetrate the US market, US products began losing their competitiveness, so Professor Hammer sought to address the root causes of this problem in his paper After analyzing the causes of the decline in U.S competitiveness, Hammer found that U.S products were not actually lagging behind in terms of product competitiveness, but that were losing competitiveness in terms of price and quality: For American companies to provide the product values that customers were looking for Hammer felt that the solution lay in resolving the problems in the overall business process, and thus proposed the concept of BPR as a solution to those problems in his paper they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2760,'835','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Process innovation (PI) is the activity of improving the business environment to maximize corporate value. PI seeks to eliminate unnecessary elements (across all aspects of corporate activities ranging from business process to organization and IT) and rebuild effective business processes Pl is similar to BPR, but it was introduced in 1993 when David Port of the United States published his paper titled \'Process Innovation\' PI can be understood best as BPR, but with a greater emphasis on the integration of information technology The objective of Pl is to build a structure that can respond to changes in the business environment surrounding a enterprise by improving the current business processes and the flow of information logistics and values in a direction that is more customer-centric Internationally, the concept of BPR developed by Michael Hammer is used widely: But in South Korea, the concept of PI became more popular after it was first used by Samsung Electronics and after POSCO adopted a PI-based ERP as a strategy for improving its business processes. In South Korea, PI is used in a broader sense than BPR','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2761,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae2298ff.png','/storage/figures/68039ae2298ff.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2762,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae240d38.png','/storage/figures/68039ae240d38.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2763,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Generally, PI is implemented in conjunction with the deployment of information technology: typical situation is when an enterprise carries out sudden improvements of its business processes through integration with ERP The PI develops into a system that performs improvements to plans and processes, establishes an information service plan, and then realizes the planned items as a means of execution, whether ERP or CRM The implementation of PI begins with improving the processes and systems of an enterprise, after which an informatization plan is established through the improved systems and processes, followed by the deployment of a system that is capable of executing the plan through FRP or CRM','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2764,'836','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The relationship between PI and ERP can be explained as follows. First, PI is implemented to bring abol improvements to an enterprise\'s systems, processes, and workforce and to lay the groundwork for the integration data and processes This is followed by the procedure for constructing the integrated system:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2765,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'27] Change management with PI [Fig',NULL,'68039ae25eb8b.png','/storage/figures/68039ae25eb8b.png','2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2766,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Once the process of an enterprise has been innovatively improved, the enterprise must grant itself sufficient time to adapt to the changed process In such a situation, the organization\' s productivity drops rapidly, and in order to ensure the success of PIl projects and mitigate the decline in productivity issues like expectations, resistance, insecurity, and motivation must be effectively managed at each stage of the project.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:46','2025-04-19 12:44:46'),(2767,'837','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','For the efficient implementation of Pl, all executives and employees of the enterprise must be familiar with and share in the vision of change The activities and resources needed for implanting change must be organized and strategies must be developed. The CEO must display strong leadership and active participation. Leaders should encourage the completion of changes, take responsibility for activities, ad encourage active participation by the stakeholders Leaders must also turn the management vision into reality and increase the ability of individuals and teams to perform their jobs effectively in the new environment PI can be established stably only if change management with PI is successful. An organizations ability to adapt to change eventually determine the success or failure of the project will','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2768,'650','App\\Models\\Section','Text','With PI, IT business innovation can be approached in two different ways: one method consists in adopting ERP through PI, while the other consists in using ERP to accelerate the implementation of PI. Irrespective of which approach is taken, an enterprise must strategically establish an adoption plan and a direction that reflect the circumstances of the enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2769,'838','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','\"Six Sigma\" is a quality innovation movement that was started by Motorola in 1987 with the aim of achieving a defect rate of less than three out of one million products and of reaching the so-called \"6 Sigma\" level of quality by analyzing and quantifying the causes of inefficiencies in management. Thus, the three main pillars of Six Sigma are statistical measurement, business strategy ad philosophy (transformation of the way work should be performed)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2770,'839','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The statistical measurement of process innovations IS critical. Quantitication and objective measurements are performed It is an enterprise-wide process innovation activity that is not limited to a specific department, team or area Its ultimate goal is to improve the value and satisfaction perceived by customers who are at the end of the value chain, \"Six Sigma\" strives for a passionate organizational culture in which all members of an organization participate in the rc continuouc imnrovementc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2771,'840','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 27  Six Sigma Hierarchy',NULL,'68039ae27fcc8.png','/storage/tables/68039ae27fcc8.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2772,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae2aacc8.png','/storage/tables/68039ae2aacc8.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2773,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'<Table 28  Six Sigma implementation methodolog',NULL,'68039ae2c7956.png','/storage/figures/68039ae2c7956.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2774,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Six Sigma implementation methodology can be separated into the design program and the manufacturing program: The design program uses the DMADV methodology, while the manufacturing program uses the DMAIC methodology Another characteristic is that the design program is focused on preventing errors and defects, whereas the manufacturing program is focused on reducing defects and preventing recurrences.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2775,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The design program is for designing a process that surpasses the core requirements and the customers\' program expectations The design program is focused on preventing errors and defects It is suitable for MADV) developing new products or processes, and for redesigning existing products or processes. (Define) Establish the of design activities that satisfy the requirements put forth by users: (Measure) Select factors that impact quality in a critical way: (Analyze) Assess the feasibility of the design and conduct analysis for development of the best design (Design) Detailed agenda, optimize design, and plan for design verification (Verify) Activate testing of the design and verify the application of the product development process. goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2776,'841','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The manufacturing program makes repetitive improvements while focusing on reducing defects to the levels required by manufacturing, production and mass production The manufacturing program also nufacturing program improves existing products and processes (DMAIC) (Define) Define the problem, set the and estimate CTQ(Critical to Quality): (Measure) Select theitems for measurement, establish the method of measurement, and analyze the current status: (Analyze) Analyze the causal relationship of the identified problem and determine the root cause (Improve) Derive the optimal method for eliminating the root cause and improving manufacturing: (Control) Prevent recurrence, maintain the improved condition, and analyze the effects of imnrovemantc goals,','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2777,'842','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 29  Four important discoveries',NULL,'68039ae2da992.png','/storage/tables/68039ae2da992.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2778,'842','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae2ec391.png','/storage/tables/68039ae2ec391.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:22'),(2779,'842','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TRIZ is a systematic methodology for solving the problem of invention, which was developed in the Soviet Union by Genrich Altshuller5 In the 1940s, Genrich Altshuller worked for the Soviet Navy as a patent examiner He discovered that there were some common rules and patterns in inventions. Out of 1.5 million patents worldwide, 50,000 creative patents were extracted and analyzed, resulting in four important discoveries which are summarized in the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2780,'843','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 30  Types of contradiction',NULL,'68039ae30bbd9.png','/storage/tables/68039ae30bbd9.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2781,'843','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In TRIZ, contradictions are classified as either a physical contradiction or a technical contradiction. Physical contradictions are mainly solved using the principle of separation, whereas technical contradictions are solved with 40 inventive principles, 76 standard solutions, 8 laws of technology evolution, and various effects of natural science','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2782,'844','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 31  Management technique using TRIZ',NULL,'68039ae3266de.png','/storage/tables/68039ae3266de.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2783,'844','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','TRIZ has been widely recognized for its effectiveness in management as well as in engineering Furthermore, many studies and cases of its application are being reported','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2784,'845','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SERVQUAL is a technique for analyzing the gap between the level of service quality expected by users and the actual level of service quality provided by an enterprise Using the following five dimensions, SERVQUAL prioritizes the relative importance (as felt by the user) of service attributes, thus making it possible for an enterprise to provide a service based on its scale of priority: SERVQUAL was first proposed by Parasuraman, Zeithaml, and Berry in 1985.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2785,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 32  5 dimensions of SERVQUAL',NULL,'68039ae33e49c.png','/storage/tables/68039ae33e49c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2786,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SERVQUAL consists of 5 dimensions: tangibles, reliability, responsiveness, assurance, and empathy','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2787,'846','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The 5 dimensions of SERVQUAL are often subdivided into the following 10 categories ad utilized in investigations and evaluations: Tangibles: Physical facilities, equipment, employees, outward appearance of data. Reliability: Ability to perform a promised service in a manner that can be trusted and is accurate Responsiveness: Readiness to assist users and provide quick services Competence: Possession of the technology and knowledge required for the provision of services Courtesy: Courtesy, respect, consideration, and friendliness of front-line workers Credibility: Credibility and honesty of the service provider Safety: Absence of the likelihood of risks and doubt Accessibility: Accessibility and ease of access: Communication: Communication with users in a language that is easy to understand, listening to What users have to say: Customer understanding: Making the effort to understand what customers want and evaluations Tangibles: Physical facilities, equipment, employees, outward appearance of data. Reliability: to perform a promised service in a manner that can be trusted and is accurate Responsiveness: Readiness to assist users and provide quick services Competence: Possession of the technology and knowedge required for the provision of services Courtesy: Courtesy, respect, consideration, and friendliness of front-line workers Credibility: Credibility and honesty of the service provider Ability','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2788,'847','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SPC stands for \"Statistical Process Control\": This term contains the word \'statistical\' because it relies on statistical data and analysis techniques, the word \'process\' because it represents a given product quality specification and the capacity of the process, and \'control\' because the technique allows enterprises to control the condition of the product when it is produced: SPC is a management technique that allows enterprises to make repeated improvements to a process and maintain high rates of production of goods of satisfactory quality: SPC allows enterprises to conduct an engineering analysis of the causes of defects and establish the best way of rectifying the problem in a reasonable manner:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2789,'848','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The objective of using the SPC technique is to produce of uniform quality within a narrow range of quality distribution. Therefore, SPC-oriented management reduces process variations and ultimately stabilizes each goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2790,'848','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','processthus laying the foundations for the production of zero-defect goods With SPC, enterprises can produce high-quality goods and enhance their productivity to levels that will lead to significant cost reductions, thereby contributing to higher profits.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2791,'849','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 33  Constituent elements of SPC',NULL,'68039ae35f16a.png','/storage/tables/68039ae35f16a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2792,'849','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Besides the component elements described above, statistical data must be collected for the variance analysis The instruments used in data collection include the work checklists,, and inspection device data among other The statistical techniques used in SPC analysis include the control chart, histogram, scatter plot, Pareto diagram, and cause-effect diagram: log\' things: 1s). e statistical techniques used in SPC analysis include the control chart, histogram, scatter plot, Pareto diagram, and use-effect diagram','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2793,'235','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','Improving business processes is seen as an essential means of securing competitiveness in a rapidly changing business environment, All enterprises are committed to maximizing their operational efficiency by structuring their organizations in order to respond quickly to the market environment and price competitiveness over their competitors. also focus on technology innovations for the purpose of developing new business models and services To realize these business objectives, enterprises try to improve themselves by adopting a number of innovation techniques Despite these efforts, many companies often suffer from weakened market competitiveness and economic losses. This is because the larger the scale of the enterprise or the number of employees, the harder it becomes to manage the organization, while the ways in which business tasks are carried out in practice often contain unrealistic or inefficient elements Innovative techniques such as BPR and PI described below, along with management tools like 6 Sigma, are used strategically by enterprises as a means of improving their business processes gain They being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:47','2025-04-19 12:44:47'),(2794,'59','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae376a30.png','/storage/figures/68039ae376a30.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2795,'59','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2796,'59','App\\Models\\Module','Text','The most important thing when providing an IT business service is the quality of that service Quality comes from the customers eye level, that is, the customer\'s requirement level. Therefore, if you want to rovide an IT business service, it is imperative to understand precisely what the customers requirements comes from the customers eye level, that is, the customers requirement level. Therefore, if you want to provide a IT business service, it is imperative to understand precisely what the customers requirements are: IT business services are intricately intertwined. There are customers who from the company to which one belongs, ad there are also partner companies (suppliers) who do business with the company: Sometimes partner companies can be important customers. As a result, the many stakeholders in the value chain must be linked to the companys solution, making it absolutely necessary to conduct an integrated analysis In the past, the operations of systems for delivering IT business services were fragmented. However, in recent years the trend has switched towards operating the of \"purchase-production-sales-post management\" as a single connected process: Consequently, because the quality of a service from the suppliers is virtually equivalent to the quality of service from ones own company, continuous quality control is something that is required from the very beginning to the very end of a service. For this purpose, the flow of information between the general- purpose systems (which function like the \"blood vessels\" of the organization) within a company must be managed in a systematic manner buy cycle','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2797,'59','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives:','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2798,'59','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the general-purpose work support system for IT business can be explainec 2 To be ab