he malfunction status of each server by the type of malfunction and the level of severity: Through the dashboard, company K is made instantly aware of individual events It provides a Tramework for quickly recognizing and responding to various situations that may arise during the delivery of T services T services As a result, company K is able to quickly respond to malfunctions that occur during IT service delivery by communicating them to the malfunction manager almost as soon as occur Furthermore, by building knowledge DB of malfunctions, the company is able to establish measures for averting the recurrence of similar mishaps in the future: In addition, ITSM enables the company to carry out service-level management (SLM) using a system, thereby greatly contributing to the comprehensive evaluation of service levels and the building of trust with customers they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2803,'236','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','T business services consist of a general-purpose work support that assists in performing some of the tasks involved in running a business, a system that assists decision makers When making decisions, and IT service management (ITSM), a management technique for the systematic management of IT services The general-purpose work support system is composed of ERP (enterprise resource planning) , SCP (supply chain management) , and CRM (customer relationship management), all of which can help an enterprise to maintain close elationships with its customers by analyzing their needs. system The decision support system consists of the business intelligence (BI) unit ad the decision support system (DSS) for providing support when making decisions In both units, the backbone is the enterprise data warehouse (EDW) that collects data internally and externally and analyzes the data. ITSM, the IT service manager leverages the IT Infrastructure Library (ITIL) in defining the processes ad activities of the IT services. ITSM, when used in combination with international standards like ISOJIEC 20000, can improve and enhance the quality of IT services It can also provide IT services that will satisfy the users, but only when the definitions of service levels and the management of service levels are installed in advance','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2804,'655','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 34  Key roles of enterprise solutions',NULL,'68039ae3988d2.png','/storage/tables/68039ae3988d2.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2805,'655','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT business is a enabler of enterprise competitiveness and continuous innovation In the past, it was simply a tool for supporting business activities, but today it plays an important role as a tool for survival within a highly competitive environment During the short 30-year period since the introduction of enterprise computing in the early 1980s, the power of computers has grown exponentially and enterprises have left many examples of how computers should be used in the business environment These examples have now evolved into formal solutions key An \"enterprise solution\" is a collective term for the information systems that support the management activities which an enterprise must perform in order to maximize business efficiency and competitive advantages in its business environment. The value ad utility of a enterprise solution will vary depending on the business processes ad activities to be defined, and not by the function provided by the information system Enterprise solutions are a broad concept encompassing advance IT planning, job specific solutions that will be configured together for building a business operation system using IT systems, and maintenance& repair for directly Ct Stinc LO ~foronontioned Cucton gain','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2806,'655','App\\Models\\Section','Text','As such, enterprise solutions are focused on maximizing business efficiency: Work efficiency directly leads to productivity improvements and also plays an important role in strengthening the competitiveness of an enterprise The following table summarizes the role of these enterprise solutions. key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2807,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae3b7c2c.png','/storage/figures/68039ae3b7c2c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2808,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The various solutions needed for an enterprise\'s activities must be used in a way that is appropriate to the enterprise $ purpose and objectives Looking at some of the leading enterprise solutions, the first that comes to mind is enterprise resource management or ERP ERP provides enterprises with a means of optimizing, distributing and properlv deplovingloperating its entire resources, An information system that effectively aggregates management information','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2809,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Text','An integrated management system of enterprise functions for the optimal operation of enterprise-wide resources [Fig.28] Types of enterprise solutio','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2810,'656','App\\Models\\Section','Text','There is the supply chain management (SCM) system, which integrates the entire supply chain from purchasing to production and eventual delivery to customers. With SCM, an enterprise can manage how many raw materials to purchase, sort them into product groups, and manufacture products in a timely manner ready for delivery when the customers need them. Because the analysis of customers is a critical factor of competition, the customer relationship management (CRM) system is a solution on which enterprises depend to properly analyze customer needs, enhance the service for customers, and strengthen customer relationships for additional value delivery:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2811,'657','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'1 [',NULL,'68039ae3cfc0e.png','/storage/figures/68039ae3cfc0e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2812,'657','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In enterprise solutions, communication with customers, product management, and process integration should be organically linked. These aspects must be comprehensively managed so that enterprises can execute their business strategies efficiently and achieve their business The environment surrounding an enterprise changes fluidly every minute as such, enterprises are always faced with the challenge of responding nimbly in order to survive: Thus, companies have no other choice but to tailor and their strategies to fit the environmental changes The adoption of enterprise solutions that satisfy the strategic goals of an enterprise is an unavoidable choice: There are countless enterprise solutions required by businesses However the solutions that most enterprises absolutely need to deploy or need to develop on their own in one form or another can be defined using just a handful of solutions. There are also situations in which enterprises, as grow in scale, are forced to adopt a particular solution to meet the IT compliance requirements. goals change they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2813,'658','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The figure above illustrates the interrelationship between a business strategy and various enterprise solutions For each application and purpose, an enterprise solution is tied to a particular strategy item: In other words, enterprise solutions are adopted in a manner befitting a particular strategy (as well as the sub-details of each strategy) of an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2814,'850','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 35  Characteristics of ERP',NULL,'68039ae3ec308.png','/storage/tables/68039ae3ec308.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:23'),(2815,'850','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ERP (enterprise resource management) is a system that maximizes enterprise productivity by integrating the various management resources of an enterprise into a single system: The goal is to maximize enterprise-wide business efficiency by integrating the company\'s key business processes and sharing information Integrated work-related support for various aspects of business operation and the systematic of different aspects of business operation contribute to the efficient sharing of data and increased organizational flexibility: linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2816,'851','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.30] Configuration of ERP',NULL,'68039ae42279b.png','/storage/figures/68039ae42279b.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2817,'851','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Most operational functions of an enterprise, from purchasing to production, distribution, marketing, sales, service, finance, accounting and human resources, are organized in a way that ensures interdependencies between the functions and a balanced distribution of resources For example, when a customer places an order, the sales representative enters it into the ERP system and the finalized order data (how much, where and when the delivery must be made) are communicated to the department which requires the data. To meet the order the data concerning raw materials (when, how much and at what price were procured) are also sent to the relevant department in a similar fashion. The factory will produce the order on schedule, and the production data will be entered into the ERP and transmitted to the shipping department The shipping department will then deliver the goods to the customer on the desired date The ERP system provides an environment in which these operations can take place organically: they system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2818,'852','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 36  ERP deployment process',NULL,'68039ae442e47.png','/storage/tables/68039ae442e47.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2819,'852','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae4581c0.png','/storage/tables/68039ae4581c0.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2820,'852','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The deployment of ERP should be approached as a concept of enterprise business innovation, and not just as the simple introduction of a system. The legacy operating procedures of the enterprise must be analyzed, and any problems and improvement points must be identified Through process innovation (PI) activities, the enterprise must undergo a radical transformation. Job activities must be innovated so that can be performed by employees from a common perspective and handled using standardized procedures that are integrated across the enterprise. To this end, the ERP implementation project must be wholeheartedly supported by the CEO and pursued at the company level in order for it to be successful. The typical ERP implementation process includes the following: they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2821,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 37  ERP deployment strategy',NULL,'68039ae4747e1.png','/storage/tables/68039ae4747e1.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2822,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There are three approaches to ERP deployment. With the Big Bang method, all modules and functions of the ERP system are deployed across the place of business at the same time: In the phased and function-based approach, the ERP system modules are separated by their functions and the ERP system is deployed only on some modules. In the phased and place of business approach, the ERP system is deployed in phases at each place of business. When the operation of ERP is shown to be stable, its deployment is then expanded horizontally through the remaining phases','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2823,'853','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ERP solutions are supplied by both domestic vendors and foreign global vendors. Depending on the deployment strategy, the ERP solution could also be developed in-house. Leading foreign ERP solutions include SAP ERP and Oracle ERP while domestic ERP solutions include Younglimwon ERP and Douzone ERP Commercial ERP products offer the advantages of ERP deployment using standardized processes, however, customized development to match the environment of an enterprise is somewhat difficult, Another worth mentioning is that when adopting an ERP solution, an enterprise must check whether compliance with the IFRS (International Financial Reporting Standards)5 must be observed. leading thing','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2824,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 31] Bullwhip effect in supply chains',NULL,'68039ae494406.png','/storage/figures/68039ae494406.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2825,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 32] Conceptual diagram of supply chain management',NULL,'68039ae4b0e9f.png','/storage/figures/68039ae4b0e9f.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2826,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mrefers to supply chain management solutions To understand SCM, one has to understand the supply chain: The IFRS: The International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) published by the International Accounting Standards Board to ensure international acceptance of enterprise accounting standards.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2827,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','supply chain encompasses the entire process from order placement and the supplying of raw materials needed for the production of goods, to the production process, distribution network and final delivery to the customer The biggest problem with the supply chain is the whipping effect, a phenomenon in which decisions that are made further up the supply chain result in a sudden expansion of demand. What this means is that a small change in the end-consumer demand for a product will cause a chain reaction furtherup the supply chain, increasing the demand from retailers to wholesalers then to manufacturers and finallv to narts sunnliers','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2828,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As shown in Figure 31 above, if a consumer places an order for 10 goods to a wholesaler, the wholesaler will place an order for 12 just in case The manufacturer will in turn manufacture 15 goods just in case. In this way, the supply chain will become overstocked and resources will be wasted, with unnecessary investments in manpower and 6? goods _ If market demand is transmitted in this way to the upper level of the supply chain, the demand distorted a increases variance at each step In addition, the supplier who supplies the raw materials at the end of the val chain becomes exposed to huge risks, which seriously increases the inefficiency of the entire supply chain du to the imbalance in demand across the supply chain, ultimately resulting in surplus orders, excess inventory, overinvestment Therefore, supply chain management is a strategy that aims to maximize efficiency by rectifying whipping effect problem and by eliminating waste throughout the supply chain. gets To be more specific, in supply chain management the players in the supply chain cooperate with each in managing materials, funds and information, with the objective of linking and integrating the flow of all goods, services and values (purchasing, manufacture, allocation and distribution) from the suppliers to the end customers The effects of these activities manifest themselves as a shortened lead time and reduced uncertainties and variabilities It is the of supply chain management to support these activities and address the issues that arise in the supply chain goal It is a management technique that seeks to optimize inventory management ad other such supply chain decisions','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2829,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','through the sharing of information and collaboration with suppliers throughout the entire process from production to distribution','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2830,'854','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To implement supply chain management (SCM), an enterprise must have in place some crucial functions in suppl chain planning (SCP) and supply chain execution (SCE):','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2831,'855','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table38 Functions of supply chain management',NULL,'68039ae4ccbb9.png','/storage/tables/68039ae4ccbb9.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2832,'855','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','SCM carries out the 3 functions of supply chain planning, supply chain execution, and supply chain visibility: These three functions form a positive feedback cycle, a structure in which their functions can be improved when the working environment changes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2833,'856','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 39  Comparison of SCM and ERP',NULL,'68039ae4e9998.png','/storage/tables/68039ae4e9998.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:24'),(2834,'856','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','CM and ERP are the parts of the work support system operated by enterprises Logistics and distribution nanagement are the critical areas of SCM that are intimately tied to ERP In recent some ERP have been mplemented with a part of the functionality of SCM, but the detailed flow is managed by SCM years,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2835,'857','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Dell Computer, the most successful company in introducing SCM, said that after adopting SCM it became possible to link information between customer, company, and component suppliers in real time, and reduced its inventory 8 weeks\' worth of supplies to 12 15 days\' worth of supplies. The introduction of supply chain management can improve customer satisfaction by increasing transportation delivery capacity ad reducing inventory, reduce logistics costs, and reducethe customer order processing time through strict adherence to delivery schedules It can also improve the efficiency of fund flow by standardizing work and by reducing the product delivery time and the order processing time from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2836,'858','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The CRM defined by Gartner is a strategy for optimizing corporate sales ad expanding the customer base by creating ad supporting relationships with profitable customers\'. In other words, CRM is a management technique that integrates and analyzes customer data across the enterprise and customer-related data inside and outside the enterprise, and then provides the findings to customer points of contact for use in interactions with the customers This is an integrated process that enables enterprises to continually deliver the products and services customers want, based on an accurate understanding of the customers, thereby maximizing customer lifetime value and increasing profitability:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:44:50'),(2837,'859','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae50d7eb.png','/storage/figures/68039ae50d7eb.png','2025-04-19 12:44:50','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2838,'859','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','From a process perspective, CRM collects and analyzes the various data generated by the entity and provides it with meaningful information CRM can be classified as analysis CRM, operations CRM,, or collaboration CRM With analysis CRM, information generated through interactions with customers is gathered,, and meaningful insights are derived and then supplied to the enterprise With operations CRM, these insights form the backbone of marketing, servicing and sales activities Finally, with collaboration CRM, the enterprise engages in interactions with the customers through a diverse range of channelc','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2839,'661','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 33] Life cycle of enterprise customers',NULL,'68039ae522940.png','/storage/figures/68039ae522940.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2840,'661','App\\Models\\Section','Text','CRM stands tor customer relationship management It IS & management strategy system tor studying customers tendencies and requirements in advance in order to create the products that customers want and to develop marketing strategies Because todays customers\' knowledge of product and service information has vastly increased and customer expectations ad customer churn are higher than ever before, enterprises are compelled to establish new business management strategies, such as adopting a customer-centric corporate structure, establishing diverse customer interface channels, and implementing customer management that leads to better earnings To implement these strategies, enterprises must analyze customer behavior patterns and consumption patterns In recent years, enterprises have felt the need to consolidate internallexternal data and analyze markets and customers to derive insights Big Data analysis is a good example of this, Enterprises can opportunities to acquire new customers through focused marketing or promotional activities that target responsive customers among potential customers in the target market who show interest in their products Enterprises should strategically manage customers who purchase their products as well as high-value (highly loyal) customers To this end, enterprises should have a in place that can sort their customers based on such criteria as personality, type, and interests, and provide their services and conduct their marketing accordingly: This requires a entity to establish a strategy for maximizing customer lifetime value, ie the total value generated throughout the customers lifecycle, rather than the temporary profitability generated by individual transactions: This is the goal of CRM gain system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2841,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table41 Components of the CRM system',NULL,'68039ae53ed35.png','/storage/tables/68039ae53ed35.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2842,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 35] Configuration of the CRM system',NULL,'68039ae5671be.png','/storage/figures/68039ae5671be.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2843,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','n CRM, information begins to flow from the customer point of contact and ends at the customer point of contact','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2844,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Amid this flow of information,, the information generated by the work support system utilized and the operation of the work process occurs at the same time: gets','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2845,'860','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In CRM, the customer point of contact has huge significance The customer of contact or channel collects the customer\'s VoC and communicates the results produced by the interal process to the customer Therefore, when the component elements of CRM must be identified, it is advisable to investigate the channel first of all, since this is the of contact with the customers. Also, if information analysis is conducted, followed by information utilization, it becomes very easy to understand the constituent elements of CRM point point','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2846,'861','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 42  Benefits of CRM deployment',NULL,'68039ae586b81.png','/storage/tables/68039ae586b81.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2847,'861','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the introduction of CRM, enterprises can improve their relationships with their customers and prevent custome churn,, thereby increasing customer loyalty: Furthermore, enterprises can provide high-quality services by analyzin customers\' tastes, and can also induce linked sales and realize upstream sales. Furthermore, they can build competitive edge in terms of customers through differentiated policies in products and services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2848,'662','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 40  Comparison of CRM classifications',NULL,'68039ae5ac6e6.png','/storage/tables/68039ae5ac6e6.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2849,'662','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Categorizing CRM in this way is only done for the purpose of increasing peoples understanding of CRM: In fact, the ultimate target of CRM is to inside the minds of the customers. In order to accurately read the customers\' minds, data analysis has to be performed,, while assistance from a business support system is also helpful. A diverse set of customer points of contact (channels) for interacting with customers has to be secured as well: get','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2850,'862','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PLM can be defined as a support system that integrates and manages information related to products such as drawings, documents, CADICAM information, basic parts information, design changes, and process information These forms of information are generated throughout the entire product life cyclesof the products that are developed and manufactured by an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2851,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 43  PLM components',NULL,'68039ae5d22c3.png','/storage/tables/68039ae5d22c3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:25'),(2852,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 36] Diagram of the configuration of PLM',NULL,'68039ae603204.png','/storage/figures/68039ae603204.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2853,'863','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Recently, PLM has come to be understood as a concept that includes not only product planning, but also the post- sales services provided to customers Managing the entire cycle of an individual product from the planning stage until it is sold is the role of PLM However, organic support from other work support systems is a prerequisite for fulfiling this role To understand the components of PLM, it is sometimes helpful to visualize the flow of a product s entire life key cycle, The main components of the process presented in the PLM configuration diagram shown above are derived and described in the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2854,'864','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Product development was always a collaboration-centered effort To more effectively manage product developmen activities, beginning in the 1990s, enterprises began to operate storages in which kept the system desigr information of their engineering teams. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2855,'864','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As the number of projects and products in need of development increased and became more difficult to manage, it became necessary to consolidate the scattered information Included in the centralized system were a number of items that served as important reference data when designing items and products, such as BOM (bill of materials) management,, development process standardization, and the workflow-based change management function, etc, The inclusion of these items made it possible to maximize the efficiency of product development Recently, the trend among companies has gravitated towards consolidating the PLM through the integration of ERP and MDM solutions for the purpose of managing the reference data from the enterprise-wide perspective: In the future, PLM will be expanded to include the social PLM area by linking it with external data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2856,'663','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Product lifecycle management (PLM) is a product life cycle management solution It is a production/design process that increases a product\'s added value and reduces costs by uniformly managing the entire process creation of the product design drawings to production of the final product. PLM provides product information data management server system, both of which are related to the product life cycle and the network of multiple client systems. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2857,'865','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The enterprise data warehouse (EDW) is a system that can address, by subject matter information analysis requests by users, through the integration of internal and external data. The EDW requires the construction of infrastructure that serves as the backbone of enterprise data. This infrastructure touches every area and aspect of an enterprise\'s pucinocc Tne enterprise aata warenouse (ELW) IS a system tnat can adaress, Dy subject matter, Intormation analysis requests by users, through the integration of internal and external data. The EDW requires the construction of infrastructure that serves as the backbone of enterprise data This infrastructure touches every area and aspect of an enterprises business: In the beginning, the EDW mostly encompassed the internal data of an enterprise Today, however, it is evolving into a forecasting system that integrates both the internal and external information of an enterprise business: In the beginning the EDW mostly encompassed the internal data of an enterprise: Today, however, it is evolving into a forecasting system that integrates both the interal and external information of an enterprise','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2858,'866','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','II an enterprise wisnes tO maintain unliormity Or viewpoint across ItS entre Organization, IC must consolldale lne information that it possesses and any external information it needs from an enterprise-wide perspective and keep it as the master information In today\'s rapidly changing business environment, enterprises have to extract enterprise-perspective data by conducting diverse data analyses for users in diverse sectors. This is because enterprises need to have sufficient forecasting capability for making strategic choices and responding to changing user requirements brought about by changes in the business environment Enterprises also have to integrate their information resources and reorganize their management system as part of redesigning their to prevent data duplication: system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2859,'867','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 44  Characteristics of the EDW',NULL,'68039ae6213ca.png','/storage/tables/68039ae6213ca.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2860,'867','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The EDW was created with a clear purpose for its use The concept explains a very import characteristic of the EDW, namely, that of being topic-centered. Upon adopting the EDW, critical data within and outside the company become concentrated and consolidated in one place, and data are loaded and used in a time-based order Once stored, data will not be destroyed or changed unless there is a particular reason for doing so These characteristics of the EDW are described in detail as follows.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2861,'868','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 37] Concept diagram of the EDW',NULL,'68039ae63cbdc.png','/storage/figures/68039ae63cbdc.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2862,'868','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The EDW is configured so that the work support system collects, transforms and loads data during operations, analyzes data that meet the given requirements, and visualizes them in such a way that will be of assistance when making decisions From a macro perspective, all these processes are referred to as the EDW, and from a microscopic point of view, the repository for storing data is referred to as the EDW. they As shown in the figure above, transaction data are acquired from the legacy system of the enterprise and stored in the data warehouse. The analyzed data carry considerable value as information and are made visually presentable by using Bl solutions.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2863,'869','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a system that supports decision making, the Decision Support System (DSS) provides interactive dialogue support to decision makers during the decision-making process This is an interactive dialogue-based system that assists decision-makers with solving semi-structural and non structural problems using data and analytical models. The core elements of the DSS are the enterprise data (both internal and external) and the analytical model for processing quantitative data. These perform a critical role in decision making:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2864,'870','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 45  Characteristics of the DSS',NULL,'68039ae65437a.png','/storage/tables/68039ae65437a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2865,'870','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae66a13e.png','/storage/tables/68039ae66a13e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2866,'870','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The key feature of the DSS is its ability to solve non-structural problems through interactive dialogue Here, \"interactive means that issues can be explained or expressed from many different angles as desired by the user The focus of the DSS is on how analyzed data should be represented','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2867,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 46  Constituent elements of the DSS',NULL,'68039ae67e9fe.png','/storage/tables/68039ae67e9fe.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2868,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae69839c.png','/storage/tables/68039ae69839c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2869,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 38] Configuration of the DSS',NULL,'68039ae6b575b.png','/storage/figures/68039ae6b575b.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2870,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The configuration diagram below shows how the DSS is made up of a document system, a model system, ad a knowledge system These components interact with each other to deliver the necessary information to the user:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2871,'871','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The user obtains the information required to make decisions by accessing the knowledge system through th user interface In addition, for model system management and database management,, the user must access th respective system to perform necessary tasks','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2872,'872','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 47  Types of DSS data models',NULL,'68039ae6cf1cd.png','/storage/tables/68039ae6cf1cd.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2873,'872','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The data model in the DSS provides a framework for analyzing data, with the data with which decision makers can make rational decisions Different types of data models are generated from different types of algorithms and are continuously being developed and improved: In recent years, the DSS has been evolving in the direction of actively employing Al for better forecasting, ad the types of models are also diversifying: along','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2874,'873','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Business intelligence (Bl) is a set of processes that seeks to improve the quality of business decisions and business performance through the summarization, analysis and use of enterprise data and information. If the DSS is the system for decision makers, and the traditional concept is support system for decision-making, then Bl is the decision support system that can be adopted for use by regular employees In the narrow sense of the term, Bl is a system that improves the quality of decision-making in business management ad improves the performance of a business by summarizing and analyzing enterprise data and information Intelligence is the ability to understand the interrelationships between given facts, which could produce guidance for achieving a desired goal. (Hans Luhn, IBM, 1958) The general consensus is that todays Bl evolved from the DSS. Analysis technologies such as data warehouses, OLAPs, and BIl began to be developed in the late 1980s based on the DSS.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2875,'874','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 39] Configuration of Bl',NULL,'68039ae6e985d.png','/storage/figures/68039ae6e985d.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:26'),(2876,'874','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Bl provides ETL (Extraction, Transformation, Load) operations on data with which enterprises can maintain the consistency and compatibility of OLTP (Online Transaction Processing) data: These features, naturally enough, are also included in the EDW described earlier, and, as indicated by the component elements, it needs to be understood that the set of processes for collecting, analyzing and visualizing data, as well as the functions for supporting decision-making are in an organic relationship with each other Bl consists of a data warehouse that stores data, a data mart where different perspectives can be applied a analyzed in multi-dimensions, analysis tools, and dashboards that generate charts, simulations, statistical analys and predictions for visualization In addition,, for decision makers, Bl can supply them with a visual presentation of an analysis of key management metrics that would normally be released as a standardized summary report. For managers in the field, Bl provides multidimensional analytical tool called OLAP with which can perform expert-level analyses they','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2877,'875','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 48  Types of Bl',NULL,'68039ae7146df.png','/storage/tables/68039ae7146df.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2878,'875','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The types of Bl can be explained by separating them into 3 following areas are Bl, which represents the and strategies of an enterprise, analysis Bl, which is about data-driven analysis Bl, and operational Bl, which is centered on the day-to-day operations of the personnel in charge of a specific operation: These types of Bl are summarized in detail as follows They goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2879,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 40] Example of Bl dashboard',NULL,'68039ae72a3d3.png','/storage/figures/68039ae72a3d3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2880,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The Bl dashboard is one of the most important elements of the Bl functions because it permits users to make intuitive judgments. This is a data visualization tool that displays in one glance the status of quantified metrics and performance metrics for an enterprise Through dashboards, metrics such as sales, costs, profits, and risk levels in various areas are presented on a single screen so as to help decision makers make quick decisions by making it easier for them to idontf  Lc arocc  LoCLCudpa clocc 3 tontion to key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2881,'876','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In general, the screen configuration of dashboards is easy to customize as it supports easy customization and easi integration with tools such as spreadsheets and real-time data analysis.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2882,'238','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','In order for an enterprise to make a business decision, it has to have access to internallexternal information, as the collection, analysis and processing of such information is critical to making a rational decision: Data generated by a general-purpose work support system are simply too voluminous to be analyzed by hand in the expectation that some meaningful implications could be derived them: In particular, there are many times when decisions have to be made within a limited timeframe, and, in recent years, the fast changing nature of business environments has Ied to rising uncertainties, which has in turn forced companies to frequently conduct complex analyses, increasing the demand for svstems capable of supporting decision making from The two leading information systems that provide such support to enterprises are the decision-making support system and the business intelligence system: The decision-making support is used when making make decisions that require a quantitative analysis, such as an analysis of a company\'s retur on investment and its break- even Meanwhile, business intelligence systems enable companies to respond with agility by monitoring the business operating environment and detecting changes through the discovery, extraction, and analysis of business data. Before at the two systems, lets start with the concept of the enterprise data warehouse (EDW) , an enterprise data repository that underpins enterprise data analytics system points, looking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2883,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 41] Interrelationships of IT service management technologies',NULL,'68039ae73f137.png','/storage/figures/68039ae73f137.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2884,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT service management is commonly referred to as ITSM ITSM is used as a systemized method of managing IT services and the quality of such services,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2885,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ITSM uses ITIL (IT infrastructure library) , which is the standard model (best practice) of the IT service Depending on the form of trade between companies, ITSM could be outsourced. An IT service can only be realized when a service level agreement (SLA) has been signed. The signed SLA becomes the standard for measuring the quality of the IT service, and systematic management of the IT service can be pursued SLM The customer service reauest (CSR) process is for reauesting an T service using ITSM uses the ITIL (IT infrastructure library), which is the standard model (best practice) of the IT service: Depending on the form of trade between companies, ITSM could be outsourced: In addition, an IT service can be only realized when a service level agreement (SLA) has been signed. The signed SLA becomes the standard and the baseline for measuring the quality of the IT service Therefore, it is important to establish and manage these standards Once the level of a service has been decided between the user and service supplier, the IT service is delivered at thae level User requests for IT senvices will be handled bv the CSR (Customer Service Request) nrocess level. User requests for IT services will be handled by the CSR (Customer Service Request) process. Some of the leading standards associated with IT service management include eSCM and ISOJIEC 20000. These standards are all rooted in ITIL, The eSCM (eSourcing Capability Model) is an international quality assessment model used by service providers to objectively evaluate quality ad capabilities in order to provide IT services to customers. It provides guidance on imnlomonting ITconiicoc at allnbacoc Of tho bucinocc','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2886,'667','App\\Models\\Section','Text','ISOJIEC 20000 is an international standard which clearly defines the requirements for IT service managemen activities It was developed by modifying the BSISO00 certification of the BSI (British Standard Institute), the facto international standard and certification specification on IT service management','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2887,'877','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The IT Infrastructure Library (ITIL) is a guideline for IT management developed by the Central Computer & Telecommunications Agency (CCTA) of the UK for public agency users in the late 1980s. ITIL is an IT service management framework which is a compilation of the best practices in IT service management, and which provides standard guidelines for IT service management It also provides a process for clearly and transparently identifying the complex IT service framework so that enterprises can realize their business objectives','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2888,'878','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL is an intellectual property ad a registered trademark managed by the British government, but it is effectively used as a de-facto global standard for managing IT services Version 1: In the 1980s, the British government\'s CCTA developed a standard reference document to address its reliance on IT In this version, several books on the specialized field of IT services were collected and published: Version 2: the period 2000~2001, ITIL version 2 was announced and an ITIL v2 glossary was published. Version 3: Version 3 was anounced in 2007 by the OGC, an organization under Her Majestys Treasury, and is known as the ITIL 2007 edition In July 2011, ITIL 2011 was published as an improved version of ITIL 2007. Cinco  bon  ko Wnonbin Cf bachelonced   ko Dritick CTOonanao During','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2889,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 49  Component elements of ITIL v2',NULL,'68039ae755c77.png','/storage/tables/68039ae755c77.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2890,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae76c2ba.png','/storage/tables/68039ae76c2ba.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2891,'879','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The component elements of ITIL v2 are service delivery and service support key Besides the two areas mentioned above, there is also the Business Perspective area, which deals with business continuity management and partnership outsourcing, and ICT Infrastructure Management, which deals with network service management and operations management, computer installation and accessibility, and system management','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2892,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'[Fig: 42] Overview of ITIL Version 3',NULL,'68039ae78bd0e.png','/storage/tables/68039ae78bd0e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2893,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 50  ITIL v3 process',NULL,'68039ae7b38a9.png','/storage/tables/68039ae7b38a9.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2894,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 was born as a business value model from ITIL v2. It supports IT governance (lacking in ITIL v2), and extend service management to all areas of a business. (NOTE: In the box above, capitalization of names is inconsistent, eg Carnegie Mellon University)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2895,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 strengthens the service support area and service delivery area of v2 and includes the Requirement Process of ISOJIECZOOOO. The of v3 are to formulate strategies for alignment with business through a lifecycle perspective goals ,','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2896,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','and to improve the IT service life cycle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2897,'880','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ITIL v3 consists of 5 process areas This 5-step process of continuous service improvement (Service Strategy Service Design Service Implementation Service Operations) is a continuous, repeated cycle. In particular the performance evaluation (ROI) area was strengthened in ITIL v3 because it was deficient in v2 By reflecting the performance results back into service strategy, ITIL v3 further strengthens the IT service capabilities of an enterprise','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:44:51'),(2898,'881','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 51  Comparison of ITIL v2 and v3',NULL,'68039ae7d9387.png','/storage/tables/68039ae7d9387.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2899,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae7ef99c.png','/storage/figures/68039ae7ef99c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:51','2025-04-19 12:45:27'),(2900,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 43] Chart showing the flow between SLA and SLM',NULL,'68039ae812fd2.png','/storage/figures/68039ae812fd2.png','2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2901,'669','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The quality-of-service issue between a company that supplies IT services and its customers can become a sensitive subject during the servicing Therefore, there is a need for clear guidelines on the level of service between the party supplying an IT service and the party using that service The agreement between a IT service provider and its customers on the scope, item, form, performance, measurement methods, and price of the provided service is called the SLA The framework for continuously monitoring ad changinglmanaging the SLA (Service Level Agreement) is called SLM (Service Level Management): period,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2902,'882','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Seamless communication: Used as a communication tool between consumers and of services Prevention of conflicts: Narrows the expectation gap (vs reality) for service levels ad the foundation for resolving the gap. Objective evaluation: An objective and quantitative evaluation of service quality is possible Continuous control: Provides a control system for managing services suppliers lays','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2903,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 52  Component elements of the SLA',NULL,'68039ae828fea.png','/storage/tables/68039ae828fea.png','2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2904,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 53  Examples of SLA metrics',NULL,'68039ae849810.png','/storage/tables/68039ae849810.png','2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2905,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An SLA sets the service target levels for service level management metrics, provides performance measureme standards for the objectives of the service, and has a for reporting service levels. system','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2906,'883','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','ome examples of metrics defined in the SLA are shown in the table below In particular the items described usir netrics are also called \"service level items\" or \"configuration items\" (Cl):','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2907,'670','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Statement of Work (SOW) is a work statement that specifies the details of a service or the work described in the SLA that must be performed. It is also used in project management as a work statement that describes the requirements of the project','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2908,'671','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae8657e1.png','/storage/figures/68039ae8657e1.png','2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2909,'671','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SLM (Service Level Management) is one of the core processes of ITIL, The use of SLM ensures that the level of service quality agreed upon with the customers can be delivered and that the process for increasing customer confidence and improving service levels can be managed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2910,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 54  Component elements of SLM',NULL,'68039ae8867ba.png','/storage/tables/68039ae8867ba.png','2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2911,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Text','SLM provides the ability to manage service level objectives (SLO) , which are the contents of an SLA and to notify an enterprise of any infringements of the SLA  Therefore, the implementation of SLM is essential for managing the IT service levels:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2912,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Text','When operating SLAs and SLMs, the evaluation criteria for established service levels must be specific, quantitative, and objective The evaluation criteria must be verified, and seamless setting of the baseline and smooth management of any changes must be ensured .','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2913,'672','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In addition, the responsibilities under each item should be clearly specified in anticipation of potential disputes. In this regard, the use of a automated and reliable management tool for managing the service level can be of great assistance when executing tasks.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:52','2025-04-19 12:44:52'),(2914,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:53','2025-04-19 12:44:53'),(2915,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Text','The IT business performance evaluation is a procedure for reviewing how IT has contributed to the growth of an enterprise. In the past, IT business performance evaluations were mainly performed on the financial aspects of a business This made it easy to quantify the results of ITs contribution to the earnings of an enterprise and its affiliated organizations However, this type of evaluation failed to cover all aspects of how IT husiness could contribute in the aforementioned reoard n recent years, enterprises have been expanding the scope of their IT business performance evaluations ith the aim of creating a more comprehensive evaluation Current evaluations cover not only financial spects, but also non-financial areas such as efforts to enhance the corporate image or raise employees\' norale or satisfaction with their work When evaluating the performance of IT business, one particularly important consideration is the degree to which enterprises can align individual performance with the enterprise\'s performance goals. To this end, communication among employees is of paramount importance, and enterprises must utilize various techniques for bringing into alignment top-down setting and bottom-up setting When they operate their businesses goals goal goal','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:53','2025-04-19 12:44:53'),(2916,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:53','2025-04-19 12:44:53'),(2917,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the various types and methods of IT business performance evaluatior','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2918,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2919,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Financial performance evaluations, BSC, IT-BSC, KPI, MBO','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2920,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2921,'60','App\\Models\\Module','Text','toundations tor customer-oriented administrative services, the Korean Intellectual Property Office (KIPO) declared its core vision of \'Promoting Technology Innovation Korean Intellectual and Establishing a Environment Conducive to Innovation by Effectively Protecting Property Office and Promoting the Use of Intellectual Property\' and its mission of \'Becoming an Intellectual Property Powerhouse through the Innovation of Patent Administration\'. Based on this vision and mission statement,, the patent office developed five strategic objectives taking into account the unique nature of public institutions and the two conflicting interests of public benefit and financial In 2005, the patent office created the BSC system, which links the performance targets of individual employees to the five strategic objectives of KIPO. The Korean Intellectual Property Office developed the BSC system in three phases, as follows In the Ist phase (second half of 2004), KIPO established the performance management model for each department It also established its mission, vision, and strategic goals, and then derived the key success factors (19) and the key performance indicators (32) for realizing those_ Thus the strategic framework of the office was completed by November 26, 2004. Based on this strategic framework, and in alignment with its strategic goals, the office announced the performance goals, key success factors and key performance indicators that each department/bureau must pursue, on December 21,2004, These factors and indicators were the core areas of the one-year job performance agreements signed between the commissioner and the bureauldepartment heads, and between the bureauldepartment heads and the team managers, on December 28, 2004. In the Znd phase (first half of 2005), the organization-level BSC design was followed by the individual-level performance management model design. The organizational performance indicators were distributed to individual employees, who were asked to align organization-level performance with individual performance by reflecting the organization s performance score in the individual performance score By April 30,2005,an individual performance and competency evaluation system had been established through which employees could be motivated to meet their job goals At the same time, as part of its effort to introduce a more performance-centered HR policy, the office announced a new plan in which the result of each individual employee s performance evaluation would be more closely linked to the compensation system: In the 3rd phase, deployment of the information system began on April 1, 2005, and was completed by the end of June Concurrently, the information system construction work was carried out from April 1,2005 and completed at the end of June The performance management system was implemented using the best solution so as to enable the office to manage performance as a whole A strategic operational system was also in place to monitor the execution of the strategies at all times, and thereby permit the office to respond quickly profit. goals put','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2922,'240','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','When pursuing an IT business investment in IT must be executed in accordance with the business strategy of the enterprise in question, and analyses of the effectiveness of IT investments must be fed back into the IT business performance evaluation. The evaluation of IT business performance can be broadly divided into financial performance evaluation and balanced score card assessment: Financial performance evaluation is a technique for quantitatively evaluating the performance of a financial investment by analyzing the financial benefits. In addition, the balanced score card assessment complements the financial assessment by providing the qualitative elements which are missing the financial indicators The balanced score card to the table many non-financial perspectives which could peak the interest of the enterprise Enterprises can develop very clear indicators for IT business performance evaluations by setting up the performance indicators (KPI), which measure the attainment levels, and by utilizing the management by objective svstem (MBO) which sets the obiective levels of emplovee skill develonment from brings ` key goal . erprises can develop very clear indicators for IT business performance evaluations by setting up the ormance indicators (KPI) , which measure the attainment levels, and by utilizing the management by objective em (MBO) which sets the objective levels of employee skill development. key goal','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2923,'673','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Financial performance evaluations are done using financial indicators the traditional performance evaluation metrics_ They are also called \"quantitative performance evaluations\" because use a common unit called \"currency\" , and can evaluate products or services with different characteristics in quantitative terms. they The reason why financial performance evaluations are used is because the shareholders and managers of companies are more interested in the financial results than in the specific production process involved in producing the results, and, with the financial indicators, it is easy to understand the management situation in one glance Financial indicators have a strong result-oriented nature and tend to ignore the process involved in attaining the results For this reason, financial indicators are not great boosters of employees\' motivation. Because financial indicators are abstract accounting figures it is difficult to accurately convey their meanings to all the members of an organization','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2924,'674','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'Table 55  Types of financial performance evaluation techniques',NULL,'68039ae8b0fbc.png','/storage/tables/68039ae8b0fbc.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2925,'674','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Some of the most well-known techniques for evaluating the financial performance of an enterprise include return on investments (ROI), net present value (NPV)  internal rate of retumn (IRR), and payback period (PP): These financial performance evaluations can be used to evaluate performance for both a specific period of time ad a specific point in time','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2926,'675','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 56  Characteristics of BSC',NULL,'68039ae8cdac6.png','/storage/tables/68039ae8cdac6.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2927,'675','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae8e587a.png','/storage/tables/68039ae8e587a.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:28'),(2928,'675','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The balanced performance evaluation technique is referred to as BSC (Balanced Score Card) BSC is a technique for managing balanced performance by evaluating not only financial performances but also non-financial performances It was introduced to the world by Harvard Business School Professor Robert Kaplan and consultant David Norton in 1992 in the Harvard Business Review: The traditional performance management system is so restricted to financial indicators that enterprises experience difficulties in executing their strategies in a systematic manner This has raised the need to consider non-financial evaluations BSC is utilized as a tool for maintaining  a balance between indicators, for the concretization and of strategies, and for communication within the organization. linking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2929,'676','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 57  Component elements of BSC',NULL,'68039ae90a9e5.png','/storage/tables/68039ae90a9e5.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2930,'676','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In BSC, performance is evaluated from four different perspectives It contains elements for managing enterprise goals and elements for ensuring that the are met. A balanced performance evaluation is possible with BSC goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2931,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 58  Description of the 4 BSC perspectives',NULL,'68039ae926af4.png','/storage/tables/68039ae926af4.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2932,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 45] Four perspectives of BSC',NULL,'68039ae9406b1.png','/storage/figures/68039ae9406b1.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2933,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The BSC is composed of four perspectives: Financial, Customer, Process, and Learing & Growth The BSC manages hotb financial and non-financialviowic','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2934,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The four perspectives are managed in organically interconnected relationships. For example, i) new product development is managed from a learning and growth perspective, () product quality and production efficiency','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2935,'677','App\\Models\\Section','Text','improvements are managed from an internal process perspective, (i) customer satisfaction and delivery time compliance are managed from a customer perspective, and (iv) shareholder dividend income is managed from a financial perspective','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2936,'678','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT-BSC (IT-Balanced Score Card) is a performance management tool that helps enterprises to achieve their goals by introducing the concept of BSC in the evaluation of investment performance in the IT sector The growing importance of IT in corporate activities has led enterprises to recognize the need for a method of systematically evaluating IT investments. With the traditional finance-based investment evaluation technique, it is difficult to quantify intangible IT investments, and hence enterprises have rushed to adopt IT-BSC','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2937,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 59  BSC link structure of IT-BASC as seen from different perspective',NULL,'68039ae959442.png','/storage/tables/68039ae959442.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2938,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 46] 4 perspectives of IT-BSC',NULL,'68039ae970a37.png','/storage/figures/68039ae970a37.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2939,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Text','IT-BSC has four perspectives as its constituent elements, and are linked to the enterprise BSC. That is, causal they','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2940,'679','App\\Models\\Section','Text','relationships exist among the indicators within a structure where results are shared. IT-BSC and BSC not only hel managers to make decisions, but also provide a balanced view of performance evaluation in the IT sector because are ultimately linked to the financial indicators they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2941,'680','App\\Models\\Section','Text','KPI stands for performance indicator and is a quantifiable indicator that contains the critical success factor (CSF) of an organization The KPI is used to measure the achievement of a goal. Therefore, KPIs must accurately reflect the of the organization and must be selected from among the elements that are critical to realizing those goals. KPIs are the factors (means or determinants) that could determine victory in competition as well as the factors (ends or results) related to the success of the selected strategy: Generally set by the organization and its employees, KPIs are important indicators that are widely used in performance evaluations Therefore, depending on which KPIs are selected, the emplovees could start behaving differently at work key  goals they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2942,'681','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 60  KPI establishment procedure',NULL,'68039ae99046f.png','/storage/tables/68039ae99046f.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2943,'681','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The right KPIs should be compatible with the vision and objectives of the organization, should function as strategic drivers, and should allow the members of the organization to move forward in accordance with the same purpose and strategy: Therefore, KPIs should be able to provide guidance for the entire organization, and should not be limited to specific areas. The derived KPIs should be made to match the strategy and of the organization after undergoing validation process goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2944,'884','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','KPIs should be kept separate from legacy processes ad instituted as an internal process that could lead to the bes performance from the organization as a whole The task of managing the KPIs should not be delegated to a tas force composed of middle-level managers, rather, it should be the responsibility of the top management, who mus make sure the strategic vision of the organization, is reflected in the KPIs.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2945,'885','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Even a set of KPIs from a great company is of no use to aother enterprise because the and strategies are different for each enterprise Therefore, an enterprise must develop its own KPI which matches its strategies goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2946,'886','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Starting with a balanced set of KPIs, the KPIs should be derived in gradual steps so as to allow them to evolve a mature set of KPIs. It must be possible to modify a set of KPIs in order to allow enterprises to respond promptly to changes in the business environment into','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2947,'683','App\\Models\\Section','Text','30 (Management by Objective) is a for managing the of an organization MBO is also a busines anagement technique for setting and controllinglmanaging the to meeting those goals for the purpose improving individual performances and capabilities goals system path goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2948,'683','App\\Models\\Section','Text','MBO sets goals whose levels can be measured quantitatively by the employees through their own decision Because, in MBO, achievable goals are set in a bottom-up fashion, employee are not necessarily in full alignment with the enterprise goals. However, employees finalize their through discussions with their supervisors Therefore, when individual employees do meet their individual goals, this can have a sufficiently positive effect on how close the enterprise comes to reaching its corporate goals goals goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2949,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 61  Main reasons why enterprises are adopting MBO',NULL,'68039ae9a7335.png','/storage/tables/68039ae9a7335.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2950,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Text','MBO begins with a clear understanding of an enterprise s objectives and makes each individual responsible fc meeting their own individual goals Also, under the MBO system, efficient organization management can be secure since the members of the organization work hard to achieve their respective _ goals.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2951,'684','App\\Models\\Section','Text','However, the goals set by MBO will likely not align with the goals of the enterprise if the enterprise does not set the of MBO or provide ay guidelines Consequently, the have to be revised through a separate discussion process In addition, special care must be taken when adopting MBO, because if the goals of individual employees conflict with each other, it could lead to serious disputes goals goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2952,'685','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 62  Component elements of MBO',NULL,'68039ae9bc83b.png','/storage/tables/68039ae9bc83b.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2953,'685','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae9cd8f3.png','/storage/tables/68039ae9cd8f3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2954,'685','App\\Models\\Section','Text','From the very goal setting stage, MBO encourages the participation of supervisors and subordinates. Therefore, the MBO approach works interactively to align the goals with the enterprise strategies In addition, continuous feedback in the form of evaluations and encouragement is needed to align the MBO of employees to the of the enterprise goals','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:54','2025-04-19 12:44:54'),(2955,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039ae9e637d.png','/storage/figures/68039ae9e637d.png','2025-04-19 12:44:55','2025-04-19 12:45:29'),(2956,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2957,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Text','In recent years, the IT business environment has been transformed rapidly with smart mobile as the base This is a transformation that has IT in a position where it can lead business as the core service of many different business models The role of IT is no longer limited to just supporting business Rather, IT is increasingly accelerating the transformation of the business environment as mobile, open-source, &nd social services are combined with infrastructures such as cloud, big data, loT,and AI. put','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2958,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2959,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1. To be able to explain the trend in the transforation of the IT business environment 2 To be able to explain enterprise activities for responding to transformations of the IT business environment:','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2960,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2961,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Disruptive innovation, crowd sourcing, open innovation, business platform, API economy, servitization','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2962,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Kiva, the robot responsible for Amazon\'s delivery of goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2963,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2964,'61','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Amazon, the giant conglomerate that operates 109 delivery centers around the world, has managed to reduce its shipping center operating costs by 20% by using a warehousing robot called Kiva. Amazon developed a plan to deploy the robots in its shipping center and acquired the Kiva system in 2012 for $775 million: Over the two years, the number of robots deployed has exceeded 15,000,resulting in savings of up to KRW 990 billion in human labor costs. This is one of the best examples of a company maximizing past','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2965,'887','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aea0e056.png','/storage/figures/68039aea0e056.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2966,'887','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aea21563.png','/storage/figures/68039aea21563.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2967,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'48] Business environment transformations and trends [Fig',NULL,'68039aea47d96.png','/storage/figures/68039aea47d96.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2968,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','To respond to the ongoing transformation of the business environment, companies are diversifying their businesses to a competitive advantage in the market through new business models. Among the approaches that companies employ to develop new business models are specialization, modularization, scaling up, interationalization, and networking The rapid development of IT technology and the advent of the smart era are also driving the latest shifts gain To respond to the ongoing transformation of the business environment, companies are diversifying their businesses to gain & competitive advantage in the market through new business models. Among the approaches that companies employ to develop new business models are specialization, modularization, scaling up, interationalization, and networking The rapid development of IT technology and the advent of the smart era are also driving the latest shifts in the business paradigm. Changes in the internal and external environments surrounding corporate business activities are accelerating, manifesting themselves in the form of endlessly evolving IT, changes in consumption patterns, diversification of platforms, and increasing calls for innovation from companies The gradual blurring ad disappearance of business boundaries (occasioned by offline companies\' entry into the online market, the growth of mobile businesses, and the emergence of convergent businesses, etc )which previously guarded different areas of competition, have diversified business channels by, for instance, paving the way for the rise of the online market. Through the online market, enterprises have the opportunity to meet diverse customers and create new synergies In addition, new business concepts have emerged that reflect the latest consumption trends, such as SNS-based smart shopping ad the growth of one-person Internet companies and crowd sourcing: gained','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2969,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Customer-oriented marketing is becoming more popular and more free services are being offered to customers Furthermore, value-oriented businesses such as social work businesses that could support the sustainable busines= activities of companies are also growing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2970,'888','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The trend in business transformation brought about by the smart society is progressing rapidly: As such, enterprise should react proactively to this trend and work hard on strengthening their IT business capabilities s0 that cal provide a broader range of products and services they','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2971,'687','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Many companies that have entered the global market are now experiencing difficulties because of the global economic downturn and low growth. As domestic growth slows and direct overseas investments increase, the costs that companies have to bear are increasing, while the corporate business environment is becoming ever more complicated due to the opening of markets and fluctuations in currency exchange rates. To overcome this situation, large companies are implementing a number of different strategies such as expanding global sourcing and entering the service industry in the case of manufacturing companies. long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2972,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 63  Latest technology for disruptive innovation',NULL,'68039aea78b67.png','/storage/tables/68039aea78b67.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2973,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aea981e8.png','/storage/tables/68039aea981e8.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2974,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 49] Relationship between disruptive innovation and sustaining innovation',NULL,'68039aeab09c1.png','/storage/figures/68039aeab09c1.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2975,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'[Fig: 50] Disruptive innovation method',NULL,'68039aeac846b.png','/storage/code/68039aeac846b.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2976,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Disruptive innovation is receiving a lot of attention as the solution to the persistent problem of slow growth and depression in the business market. Disruptive innovation is a technique for destroying existing markets ad creating new marketsIn essence, it consists in dominating the market with technological innovation/price destruction or in pursuing a business strategy aimed at beating the market leaders: Disruptive innovation is a innovation technology that can alter the hierarchy of competition in existing industries, have impacts on other industries, and produce new markets and businesses by changing consumer behaviors and ways of thinking, Disruptive innovation has the potential to surpass the performance of existing technologies in an instant, just like smartphones did when appeared in the late 2000s ad quickly revamped the existing mobile they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2977,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','pho JUI To understand disruptive innovation, one also has to understand the meaning of \"sustaining innovation\" . Sustaining innovation is the strategy of continuously improving existing products to satisfy and retain key customers in the market, with the of providing high value at a high price through gradual improvement: In contrast, disruptive innovation is the strategy of targeting niche markets by creating low-priced but good-quality products through simplified functions and enhanced convenience goal In other words, the market targeted by disruptive innovation is the overshot customer7 base. This market has emerged from the argument that there is a limit to the performance that customers are willing to use or accept. Overshot customers are not in favor of paying for high-end features that they do not need. There are two approaches to introducing disruptive innovation: low-end disruption and new market disruption: Low- end disruption is the strategy of entering the low-end market by resolving the product complaints of overshot customers and entering the market through low-priced products that perfectly match the satisfaction levels of the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2978,'889','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In new market disruption, enterprises target non-customers who consciously reject the products in the market or customers who are dissatisfied with existing products. By launching innovative new products that utilize new technologies, the enterprises try to build a presence in niche segments of the market dominated by existing leading e= In low-end disruptive innovation, enterprises target customers who have been overserved by leveraging a new process and by employing a financial approach By a combination of low margin and high utilization of resources, enterprises provide customers with discounted prices that are critical to succeeding in the business. In new market disruptive innovation, enterprises target non-consumers who previously could not afford to purchase a product or who had no access to the technology with low-feature products that are simple and convenient to use This is business model in which enterprises make money with loW-priced products that are mass produced in small volumes. The total takeover of the mobile phone market by smartphones is a great illustration of disruptive innovation at work The traditional industry shifted from a voice-centered industry to a data-serviced industry and hardware centered (i.e mobile terminal) industry to a platform-based market structure: In addition, if one examines the impact on other industry sectors, the high-performance functions installed in smartphones have obliterated the markets for conventional MP3, digital cameras, game consoles car navigation equipment, and tablet PCs Smartphones also created a variety of new markets and business models, including app stores, location-based using from Smartphones also created a variety of new markets and business models, including app stores, location-basec services, SNS, social commerce, social games, Big Data, and smart services Naturally, there have to be some core technologies for such disruptive innovations to occur Some of the latest technologies driving disruptive innovations that racantl attncted attontion include bave Disruptive innovation can be leveraged as a strategy for overcoming the barriers to technological innovation and reshape future industries. Enterprises that are planning disruptive innovations must clearly specify the target technology and its area of application, and seek outside resources in order to lay the foundations for dominating market opportunities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2979,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 51] Crowdsourcing business model',NULL,'68039aeadf80e.png','/storage/figures/68039aeadf80e.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:30'),(2980,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As a composite word coined py combining crowa and outsourcing , crowasourcing IS the concept of opening up phases of an enterprise\'s operations to the participation of consumers and the general public alike If the activitie of an enterprise or its revenues improve, the revenue is shared with the participants With the recent developmer of SNS, companies have been using social networks a lot more, and crowdsourcing has traction as an activit that can generate ideas by exploiting the power of the masses using these new channels of communication with public Dell Computers succeeded in collecting 10,000 ideas during an 18-month period after starting a wher consumers could exchange business-related technologies directly: Like Dell, crowdsourcing allows an enterprise present some very creative ideas for solving a enterprise issue to a group of specialists. The enterprise can the receive help from the specialists, which can then translate into time or labor cost savings In recent years crowdsourcing services have begun to partner up with professional technology brokerage firms successfully complete diverse types of crowdsourcing, and, in the process, have begun to build an ecosyster with a positive virtuous cycling structure: gained blog they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2981,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Furthermore, because it is so well coupled with information technology (IT), the rapid advancements in IT have made crowdsourcing one of the elements for success in business. By allowing consumers or the public to directly key','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2982,'890','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','participate in the manufacturing of products or the service delivery process, enterprises are creating better products and services The profits generated in this way are shared with the participants, while the enterprises themselves are able to obtain creative ideas potential future consumers at very little or no cost at all Therefore, through crowdsourcing, enterprises are able to acquire insights about consumers in a rapidly changing market, and, through the success of early adopters, can also ascertain the need for their products or services: For this reason, the utilization of crowdsourcing bv companies is expected to increase in the future from they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2983,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aeb0da5d.png','/storage/tables/68039aeb0da5d.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2984,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aeb2baf3.png','/storage/figures/68039aeb2baf3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2985,'891','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Open innovation is a method of enterprise innovation. During the research and development and productizatior processes, an enterprise can open up the whole process and invite outside experts to share their ideas anc knowledge: Through this form of sharing enterprises hope to reduce costs and increase the likelihood of success the past, enterprises approached R&D activities more as a opportunity to augment and boost the efficiencies their R&D manpower and their technological prowess, rather than as a chance to cooperate with outside parties fact, enterprises kept the lid on the output of their development activities firmly sealed This kind of corporate activity had its limitations when it came to responding to the rapidly changing marke environment, and it became more difficult to launch products on time and satisfy the changing needs of consumers In traditional R&D, the size of investments grew year by year but the chance of succeeding was small and the risk borne by enterprises wereon an upward trend. In order to address these problems, enterprises began to activel explore the option of developing new products or services in collaboration with outside experts, institutions anc organizations that held the required core capabilities Today, the sources of technology development (venture companies, SMEs, research institutes, and universities) have become even more diverse and the scope of potential technologies has expanded, and the development of networ) infrastructures has led to an era in which business connections with the outside world can create ever greater value Thus, enterprise improvements triggered from the outside are accelerating more than ever before:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2986,'689','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Open innovation can be divided into inward open innovation and outward open innovation: In inward open innovation, an enterprise obtains know-how or ideas an outside company, research center or university during the course of researching, developing  and commercializing a specific item. In outward open innovation, a company sends its knowledge or ideas to the outside world in order to commercialize them through other business models. There are six main forms of inward open innovation: technology purchase joint research, sub-contracted research, establishment of a joint venture, venture investment, and acquisition As for outward open innovation, technology sale and spin-off are its two main forms, With the rapid advances made in IT technology, convergence as a trend is gaining momentum and the pace of development of new products through convergence has become much faster than before, making it difficult for companies to keep up with the pace of market changes simply by dint of their own R&D efforts. Open innovation capability as a means of strengthening innovation capability in the face of structural transformation of technology and business management is expected to have a huge impact on the growth of companies in the coming years. from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2987,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 64 Major functions of the business platform',NULL,'68039aeb45056.png','/storage/tables/68039aeb45056.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2988,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'[Fig: 53] Types of business platform',NULL,'68039aeb66b05.png','/storage/tables/68039aeb66b05.png','2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2989,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A platform is a basic structure commonly used to produce or sell various products. as competition among corporate ecosystems in the business market intensifies the platform is increasingly viewed as a strategy for securing a competitive edge using one s enterprise ecosystem. This signifies that as and services become ever more complex and the network effects between suppliers and consumers increase, the pattern of competition is changing from competition between companies to competition between corporate ecosystems The platform is the foundation for creating and delivering values to the participating companies, ad its role as a medium can determine the fate of the enterprise eco-system. The main functions of a business platform are described below: Today, being key goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2990,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The importance of the platform is clearly illustrated by the examples of Apple and Nokia. Although Nokia entered the smartphone market earlier than Apple, its platform was edged out of the market by competition with Apple Symbian, Nokia\'s operating system, had a very complex development environment because it was geared for the enterprise market and focused on enterprise application It failed to become a standard because the entry barriers to developers were too high: However, in the case of Apple, it emphasized the entertainment functions of the iOS and built an online contents-centered ecosystem (App Store) which attracted the participation of numerous developers In other words, the platform became a medium that connected and complemented the values produced by','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2991,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','stakeholders As shown in the figure below, the business platforms that companies build to a business competitive edge can be classified into three categories: product platforms, customer platforms,, and trading platforms, gain','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:56','2025-04-19 12:44:56'),(2992,'892','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The product platform is a platform of the common parts used in the production of a final product  The purpose of such a platform is to reduce costs The customer platform is the core customer group targeted by a company from which more can be made: Finally, the trading platform is an infrastructure that supports a trading relationship with external suppliers. Through customer entrenchment ad cooperative relationships, an enterprise can become leading player in the market by leveragingits trading platform Many companies try to create various business models and build a stable business ecosystem based on their own platforms. As a result, it is reasonable to predict that the business model will expand and the size of the platform market continue to grow in the future, and that it could in fact see accelerated growth profits','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(2993,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 54] API value chain',NULL,'68039aeb87986.png','/storage/figures/68039aeb87986.png','2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2994,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A company may disclose its internal business assets or services to a third party in the form of an application programming interface or API and create additional business values through the production of new assets and consumptions The series of activities involved in this effort are collectively called \"the API economy\" . In an age when API open data constitute a new form of business, if companies wish to respond effectively to market demands, must be able to apply assemblable business models in all channels and improve their operational and business agility This means that the APIs can provide an environment (platform-neutral environment) where various they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(2995,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','applications can be connected As the characteristics ad purchasing patterns of customers who seek and pay goods using their smartphones are accumulated, are released through the API and all the member companie get to jointly use the marketing data collected by each of the other members they App developers will also be able to utilize the API open data as a business asset to build new applications and provide variety of customized services to consumers Since 2010, E Trade has been providing its stock trading service to partner companies through an API. Its partner companies have been able to sell, order or view a portfolio on behalf of itc Cuctomerc In addition, E Trade has made it possible for its customers to use the companys service without requiring them to visit its website. Through this strategy, E Trade has elevated the quality of its service and is providing it very stably: In the United States, IT companies such as Amazon, Twitter and Google are also generating revenue by releasing their data and services through APIs. By sharing their APIs (their core assets) through their respective business ecosystems, these companies are able to maximize their internallexternal efficiencies and raise expectations of new revenue generation But the task of developing and managing APIs is not easy and even after APIs are released, essential management tasks such as account management, authentication, and security management have to be taken care of Since the number and diversity of APIs released by companies are increasing every year, systemized management of APIs is something that companies are being called upon to commit to.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(2996,'893','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The API value chain must be understood before API can be used as a business model. In other words, enterprise dat and services are released through APIs, and third-party developers create innovative applications by using the ope API. Companies that provide APIs must also understand the requirements of third-party developers who use APE directly and the even the needs of the application users Internally, an enterprise must have a system in place for monitoring and managing the released APIAn enterprise should also be able to provide formal documents or websites where developers can contact each other s0 that exteral developers can easily understand and use the APIs. In an era when mobile devices ranging from smartphones to tablets and smart watches are deeply embedded in daily lives, companies should be able to manage different forms of customer contact points through strategic A management','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(2997,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 65 SW convergent model of products',NULL,'68039aeb9c3c3.png','/storage/tables/68039aeb9c3c3.png','2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2998,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 66 Examples of convergent products and services of major companies8',NULL,'68039aebb5d3c.png','/storage/tables/68039aebb5d3c.png','2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(2999,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term \'servitization\" refers to a fundamental transformation of the business model in which a product evolves into a service bundle that continues to deliver value throughout the lifecycle of a customer experience. This means that the system of competition has shifted to around service whose revenue generation potential is intimately tied to the availability, reliability ad performance of the companys assets. In particular, this phenomenon is expected to accelerate in the traditional manufacturing sector where revenues are generated from the sales of As the traditional product sales model gives way to a service model and as companies find it increasingly difficult to differentiate themselves on the merits of their products alone, many are striving to differentiate themselves through servitization, ie by combining their products with software The software model for the servitization of a product can be one of three types,as shown below: goods','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(3000,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Many companies are strengthening their software convergence capabilities so as to be able to respond flexibly to the changing environment and secure a competitive edge in the market through servitization. Software convergence capabilities are becoming a factor in determining the value of products and corporate performance Many companies are converging their products &d software to optimize their business models ad respond to the rapidly changing consumer environment key','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(3001,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Source: KIET, New Growth Strategies of Major Industries in Korea through Servitization, 2008','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(3002,'894','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Built a service ecosystem using iTunes, App Store Transformed itself from a facsimile manufacturer into a supplier of document management systems Acquired Health Watch in 2006 to venture into the healthcare service market Acquired 5.5 million customers through OnStar its subsidiary company which telematics services Through a GPS-based remote management system, Caterpillar provides a service for analyzing the status and history of excavator equipment, replacing parts, improving fuel efficiency, and monitoring illegal use Airport/road/parking operation services account for 56% of operating profits although only bring in 14% of the total revenues: supplies they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:44:57','2025-04-19 12:44:57'),(3003,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Recent trends and issues key','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3004,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Text','The rapid development of IT network and IT infrastructure technologies has not only brought about a revolution in the IT industry, but also introduced IT-based innovations across all industries. Existing products are reborn as products with new values through convergence with IT technology while technologies that received little or no attention in the early stages of their development are now becoming a reality and attracting renewed interest due to their integration with other technologies Meanwhile, public services built around smart infrastructures have greatly improved efficiency in managing services, Diverse industries are constantly turning out new products that feature convergence services However it must be understood that these market changes and paradigm shifts would not have occurred without the latest IT business services and technologies being public','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3005,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Learning Objectives:','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3006,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Text','1 To be able to explain the latest web and mobile services. 2 To be able to explain convergent/integated business services 3. To be able to explain the smart infrastructure 4 To be able to explain the latest IT business services','',4,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3007,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Keywords','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3008,'62','App\\Models\\Module','Text','0 HTMLS, SNS, responsiveladaptive web, open API, semantic web, OSS(open source software) MEAP(mobile enterprise application platform), MDMmobile device management system) , mobile commerce, LBS(location based service) Internet of Things (loT), cloud computing service, virtualization service, Block chain, smart city, smart smart education, smart health care Open data, Iinked data, Al, Fintech, Big Data, 020, O4O(Online for Offline), virtual currency, 3D printing, CA~~ 6 CLa SCal A S grid,','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3009,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aebe8a70.png','/storage/tables/68039aebe8a70.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:31'),(3010,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','AlphaGo, the Al that beat one thousand years of human learning','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3011,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3012,'895','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The match pitting Lee Sedol (a Go player with the 9 \'dan\' rank) against AlphaGo\'s Deep Mind Challenge,, held from March 9 to 15,2016, was shocking event that showed how artificial intelligence could far surpass human learning ability The fact that AlphaGo defeated Lee Sedol, the world s No 1 player for more than a decade and also one of the strongest players in the world of Go since 2014, was a clear sign that artificial intelligence can overcome human learning skills that have evolved over many thousands of years.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3013,'896','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Typically, a separate program must be installed when a person wants to use a particular service or program on a smartphone or PC. Kakao Talk is a messenger program that is widely used in South Korea and exists in different versions for PC, Android and iOS. As such, a separate program must be installed for each type of OS in order to use Kakao Talk However if HTML5 is used, there is no need to install a separate program, and Kakao Talk can be accessed directly through the web browser Furthermore, word processors and games can be used without having to inctall witb the heln of HtM 5 leading The HTMLS standard is a next generation HTML standard that overcomes the limitations of previous HTML standards, allowing rich web applications such as video, voice, and 2D graphics, without requiring a separate plug-in and Active X control were very popular as solutions for overcoming the limitations of the previous HTML: However, each came with its own set of problems, which could only be overcome through functional expansion and combination through the advanced CSS3 and JavaScript APIs. Plug-! -ins HTML5 was designed around the principles of compatibility, practicality, interoperability, and universal access. The contents of the HTML standard cover the document structure, markup standards, and API standards When the semantic markup part and the API part of the HTML 5 standard are examined separately, 26 new markups have been added to the semantic markup to enable much clearer semantic representation than conventional HTML4. HTMLS allows various services or applications based on web content, such as search engines, to provide improved functionality In the case of APIs, new functions such as web form, canvas, and web socket were added to support the development of web-based applications. HTML5 uses much less JavaScript code than HTML4 to support the same functionality, making it easier to use in mobile environments where network speed is a sensitive factor Recently, a growing number of cases have arisen in which corporate business solutions are transitioning to an HTML5-based environment so as to maximize scalability and efficiency: part','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3014,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig 55] The responsive web can configure the same contents in different ways.',NULL,'68039aec0910e.png','/storage/figures/68039aec0910e.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3015,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the growing use of mobile devices such as tablet PCs and smartphones, interest in the mobile web is also increasing Users want to enjoy the same web contents at the same level of quality, irrespective of the type of mobile device or PC being used. However, it was not easy to provide the same quality of service for different environments resulting from different mobile phone specifications and the restrictions that come with different mobile phone screen sizes It is also impossible to develop a web that is optimized for all types of mobile devices The responsive web emerged as one approach to solving this conundrum, The responsive web is an approach to web design that results in the most optimal user environment, i.e. one that meets the requirements of many different devices from desktops through monitors to mobile phones In other words it is a web whose size changes to fit ay device environment, making it easy for users to read the contents With the recent trend towards carrying mobile devices as the primary or first device, the number of mobile wel users has grown to exceed the number of regular Internet web users Web designers have responded by minimizing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3016,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','unnecessary elements of regular web pages for the sake of improving the screen size, network speed and quality, and the user mode of the mobile devices (the common limitations of the mobile environment), that is, have begun to focus more on the functions that should be provided on the mobile web. While responsive webs typically focus on how changes in layout ad style take place from one device to another, there also exist responsive webs that reconfigure web contents strictly from a mobile first perspective. they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3017,'897','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In addition to the responsive web, adaptive web technology is attracting a lot of interest as a technology that enables websites to provide a seamless transition of information for different screen sizes The adaptive web is a server- based or client-based technology that checks the device that is trying to access the web By using images tailored for the device of the user, the adaptive web allows website access on a mobile device at high speeds','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3018,'898','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'Table 67 Application areas of semantic web',NULL,'68039aec1d788.png','/storage/tables/68039aec1d788.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3019,'898','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Web that enables intelligent data processing and the accumulation of knowledge through the defining ad building of structured data (ontology) and data among the structured data is called semantic web: The web, which only displays web documents in HTML language, has severe limitations in expressing resources, and the relationship between web documents is defined. Hence computers cannot understand semantic. Since there are problems in recognizing all objects with just URL alone, semantic web was developed as a way to efficiently use information from distributed webs, extract meaningful data from flood of information,, and as a means for structuring and interpreting the amounts of data produced on the web linking huge','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3020,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table68  Main functions of SNS',NULL,'68039aec3609a.png','/storage/tables/68039aec3609a.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3021,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aec51109.png','/storage/code/68039aec51109.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3022,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Social Network Service (SNS) refers to a service that helps people continue their personal relationships online or tc establish new relationships Early SNSs began in the form of online communities on websites, such as The Well which began in 1985, and \"Theglobcom,\" which started in 1994. These are the first examples of SNS that provide services in the form of early communities','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3023,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Facebook, the global SNS site with the largest number of users, has about 2 billion (September, 2017) monthly users_ WhatsApp,, another global SNS site, has acquired about 1.3 billion users.','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3024,'899','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','[Fig 56] Number SNS users each month (as of September 2017, units: million peop igures for the sites marked with  were not updated for the past 1 ye','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3025,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table69 Component elements of Open API',NULL,'68039aec68fe8.png','/storage/tables/68039aec68fe8.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3026,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 70  Examples of REST API Method',NULL,'68039aec7e091.png','/storage/tables/68039aec7e091.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3027,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Open API is a free public API that is free for use by anyone including users and developers By using the API providec to the free of charge by websites, users are no longer confined to receiving ad consuming services. car now develop their own service and use them: public They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3028,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Cllal aclenislcs ui Open AFi Using the open API, people can gain access to the functions of a website New service can be designed by connecting several APIs. factor in the emergence of mashup sites? People who were just users of a service can become service providers Key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3029,'900','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','(cpesciluliuniui OluCC cnsic / REST API is currently the most widely used Open API. REST API is a network-based architecture published in 2000 by Fielding, one of HTTPs leading authors, to properly utilize the superiority of the Web (HTTP) REST is a web service architecture based on the Resource Oriented Architecture (ROA) and it is composed of HTTP URI HTTP Method. HTTP URI is used to specify the target resource, and the designation of actions for that resource utilizes the HTTP Method Roy','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3030,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table71  Network based location determination technolog)',NULL,'68039aec98403.png','/storage/tables/68039aec98403.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3031,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Location-based services are growing together with the smartphone market, which has seen exponential growth since 2010, and are evolving into a broad category of services by merging location information, commerce, and entertainment Due to the mobile Big Bang, the availability of location detection capable devices greatly increased and the location determination platform became open: This led to the rapid evolution of location-based services (LBS) In the case of location detection mechanism used in smartphones location detection technologies like base stations Cell-ID, GPS, and Wi-Fi were combined with motion sensor-based precision navigation. Furthermore, by adopting maps like Google Map and Apple location-based services began to be used for many general purposes guess Map, 9 Mashup site ~Websites that use APIs for product information, map information, etc from Microsoft, Google, Yahoo, Amazon, ad others and combines them with their own user interfaces to come up with new services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3032,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','These technologies in combination with services such as social network services, augmented reality, mobile games, and advertising, are boosting the utilization of the services Network-based location detection technologies include the following:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3033,'901','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','With the advancements in IT technology ad mobile communication technology, the technique of location determination has also evolved. In the 2G era, location determination was based on the principle of simple cell-based positioning But for 3G location determination, the Global Positioning System (GPS) was adopted In the 4G era, location determination has become highly precise with very narrow error margins because the technology has greatly improved the high error margins that had been the weakness of base stations and the difficulty of determining positions in indoor areas and areas with many impediments to GPS. And wherever an access (AP) exists, location determination has become possible with Wi-Fi, point','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3034,'902','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table72  Comparison of M-Commerce and E-Commerce',NULL,'68039aecb0900.png','/storage/tables/68039aecb0900.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3035,'902','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table73  Key technologies of mobile commerce',NULL,'68039aecd22cc.png','/storage/tables/68039aecd22cc.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3036,'902','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mobile technology can be characterized by 3 words: \"Anytime\", \"Anywhere\", and Device\". It is these characteristics which has made mobile technology the essential backbone of mobile businesses from mobile based commerce to mobile based entertainment, communication, search, and location information Mobile commerce is mobile business that utilizes mobile devices like smartphones, tablets, and smart for trading goods, services, and information \'Any pads','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3037,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 74  Component elements of MEAP',NULL,'68039aecefed4.png','/storage/tables/68039aecefed4.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:32'),(3038,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aed116f2.png','/storage/figures/68039aed116f2.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3039,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Mobile Enterprise Application Platform (MEAP) is a platform that can support a wide range of different device environments and permit the sharing and the reuse of applications The main reasons behind the need for MEAP are reuse and cost savings. Allows the same code to be reused for different smartphone OS/smartphone HWIservice provider environments Through the sharing of a common platform, companies can save money that would others have to be spent on duplicate infrastructure and middleware required for services Support for developing the mobile screens for different types of devices.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3040,'903','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','comporiells ui IVICAF MEAP covers the entire life cycle from mobile development to execution and operation: It is composed of a integrated development environment (IDE), an execution environment framework that acts a middleware, standard interface for integrating with legacy system, and a mobile device management (MDM) for device management and security:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3041,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 75  Main functions of MDM',NULL,'68039aed2840e.png','/storage/tables/68039aed2840e.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3042,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table76  Component elements of MDM and roles',NULL,'68039aed46e56.png','/storage/tables/68039aed46e56.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3043,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'58] Configuration of MDM [Fig',NULL,'68039aed64c88.png','/storage/figures/68039aed64c88.png','2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3044,'904','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','IDM is a solution for efficiently managing all the diverse mobile devices and applications used in enterpris perations It is a system that can be used to manage mobile devices anytime, anywhere through over-the-air (OT, ansmissions (although the device must be in the power on state): MDM aeployment ettects By deploying MDM, enterprises will gain flexibility &nd expandability They will able to connect to diverse services, manage devices at PC level, ensure consistency in security, provide remote support easily, trouble shoot issues and provide OS/languagelsystem support','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:00','2025-04-19 12:45:00'),(3045,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig: 59] Types of machine-to-machine services and market status',NULL,'68039aed81a20.png','/storage/figures/68039aed81a20.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3046,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.60] Component elements of MZM',NULL,'68039aed9c092.png','/storage/figures/68039aed9c092.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3047,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Machine-to-Machine (MZM) refers to machine to machine communication MZM integrates information to network and platform to provide a service that monitors the status of objects, controls the situation and sends information about the status of objects to users Network communication networks are used to provide people or intelligent devices with information about objects or to let them control the objects Typical types of MZM services are described below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3048,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There are three reasons driving the spread of the infrastructure for MZM communication: The first reason is the expanding wireless networks The coverage of wireless networks and the guaranteed service stability greatly facilitated the growth of MZM communication The second reason is the declining prices and increasing availability of telecommunication modules. The telecommunication module market is growing at more than 30% per year but are gradually decreasing, ad market penetration is rapidly increasing: The third reason is the declining price of sensors As the market expands, sensor technology is getting more sophisticated, but prices are falling, allowing companies that provide sensing-based services at low cost: These sensors are expanding from simple monitoring to fault and accident detection, asset management, and customer usage management information. Furthermore, the applications of these sensors are becoming increasingly diverse Starting first with simple monitoring, sensors are now being used to detect malfunctions and accidents, manage assets, and extract data about customer usage levels Typically, the process of developing a MZM device first begins with developing a module that contains a mobile chipset: Then the device is developed using the module. An MZM device can be roughly designed as an object consisting of a chipset and a module and largely divided into three parts: a sensor/input&output unit, a data processing unit, and a communication module, prices','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3049,'905','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The data acquired through the input&output uniit is processed by the data processing unit before it is sent to the communication module RS-232 or USB is used when sending the data from the processing unit to the communication module The technology used in MZM communication defines the technology needed for services at the service layer and takes a typical top-down approach to design the the lower layer to follow the definition set by the service layer: However, this approach can disrupt the standardization and public sharing of the technology ad hinder the growth of the market Therefore, standardization of the MZM environment is a critical task for stimulating the growth of the market','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3050,'906','App\\Models\\Subsection','Code',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aedb63f7.png','/storage/code/68039aedb63f7.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:33'),(3051,'906','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The diffusion of MZM technology has opened wide the era of loT which creates an environment where communication takes place not only between objects but everything from people to objects, spaces are connected to the Internet to create, collect, share, and utilize information about everything: Unlike the recent explosion of public interest in loT,, the idea of loT was already commercialized a time agolts just that loT has been spreadinglevolving gradually long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3052,'906','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','due to a combination of factors at play such as the technology development levels and the economic conditions. In recent years, buzzwords describing a completedly connected world (MZM, loT and Internet of Everything) are being discussed so much that it has become rather diffcult to distinguish the difference between such words The difference between the approaches taken by MZM and loT is in how connections are made As mentioned earlier, as MZM evolved in each industry sector, it became specialized to the particular sector it served. loT is the effort to connect these disparate MZM technologies under the universal communication network umbrella we call the Internet so that businesses could offer more diverse and dynamic services. There are many different perspectives to MZM, but if are grouped by different types of services, some of the typical examples can be listed as follows. they\'','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3053,'695','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Internet of Things(loT)','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3054,'