rastructure as a Service) SaaS is service that lets people use applications through the Internet ad web browser Saas is one of the tier services that cloud service companies can provide and leading services include Google s Gmail and MS Office 365. PaaS is a service that lets companies provide as a service, an environment for developing and running web applications In order to provide this kind of service, the technologies for app development must be modularized and standardized. Leading Paa include Salesforce com s Forcecom and Google\'s Google App Engine: laaS is principally an enterprise service that provides a virtualized environment of resources like servers, storages, ad networks to companies who are permitted to use the resources whenever needed laaS service requires the ability to build and operate servers for large data centers, capital, and a very electrical environment: Examples of laaS include Amazon EC2 and S3,as well as Gabia\'s cloud hosting service top good grid Cloud service can be divided into one of the following categories, depending on how it is configured Public Cloud public cloud is a service shared by multiple users over the Internet, and a cloud service provider provides the services and has management responsibilities A private cloud is an IT environment that is exclusively deployed on a companys or an organization s intranet It is controlled by the company or organization Hybrid cloud is a form of cloud service that has scalability and combines the best of public cloud services and private cloud services It can be used in parallel for special purpose applications With cloud computing, users can directly purchase, design and install without the need for intervention by an IT manager By sharing IT resources that could be used by everybody, cloud computing improves efficiency and the cost associated with owning IT resources could be avoided Due to these advantages, cloud computing can be merged with different types of services and evolve into new business models','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3062,'909','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table78 Virtualization functions',NULL,'68039aee2ff01.png','/storage/tables/68039aee2ff01.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:34'),(3063,'909','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Virtualization is the abstraction of computer resources on a computer and it could be defined as a technique for hiding the characteristics of physical computer resources the method other systems, applications, and end users use when interact with the resources\". It is a technology that can create multiple logical resources from a single physical resource or create a single logical resource from multiple physical resources from they Application virtualization Through the virtualization of applications installed in individual PCs, users immediate access to needed applications without to install them on their PCs every time Desktop virtualization Server-side desktop virtualization allows users to virtually own another heterogeneous desktop, such as Windows Vista and Windows 7. Client-side desktop virtualization enables heterogeneous virtual desktops in PCs Desktop virtualization allows the separation of personal and corporate workspaces. gain having','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3064,'909','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Server virtualization By consolidating dozens of physical server workloads within the data center on to several virtual servers, the utilization of server resources can be improved (physical rack costs, administrative costs, and green IT): Storage virtualization In place of the physical storage space required, a technology called Thin-Provisioning virtually allocates only the initial minimum required space to enable service implementation It also provides an environment where heterogeneous storage systems can be integrated and used: Network virtualization 13 | 7 switches network firewalls and securitv