timulating the growth of the market. key -','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3070,'911','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aee90384.png','/storage/tables/68039aee90384.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:34'),(3071,'911','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aeeafb92.png','/storage/figures/68039aeeafb92.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:34'),(3072,'911','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There is much news and interest around the concept of smart cities. A smart city can be defined as an \'urt model that can solve various urban problems and improve the quality of life in a city through the adoption of n \"12 technologies like ICT and Big Data. Smart cities are seen as an answer to the problems of aging infrastructures, energy shortages, environmental pollution and crime faced by cities around the world. To build such a smart city, the latest technologies like Al, Big Data, 5G mobile technologies are employed in the development of \"smart traffic\" ,  smart environment\" , \"public safety\' , welfare\" and \"smart energy\" services Smart city concept is the leading example of smart infrastructure \"public','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3073,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 79  Comparison of traditional electric power grid and the Smart Grid\"3',NULL,'68039aeece3b5.png','/storage/tables/68039aeece3b5.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:34'),(3074,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.65] Smart Grid configuration\'',NULL,'68039aeee49f4.png','/storage/figures/68039aeee49f4.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:34'),(3075,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Smart refers to a next-generation power system that combines IT technologies with existing power grids to monitor and control the supply & demand of power supplies in real time to match the production and consumption of electric power In traditional power systems the generation of power is centralized which means power producers unilaterally supply power to consumers. Power plants are built to meet the estimated maximum consumption level, grid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3076,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','but are less efficient because cannot flexibly handle fluctuations in demand. However, in a smart power suppliers are able to flexible set the power prices and control the supply and consumers can check their cumulative power usage levels and the power prices These two aspects result in efficient consumptions of power A smart can also benefit producers of renewable energy sources whose supply of power can often be unpredictable because power from renewable energy sources can be sold at high prices when the demand for power is at its peak comnarison of traditional electric nower orid and the Smart Grid reveals the following differences they - grid, they\' grid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3077,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Smart reduce greenhouse gases, induce voluntary energy savings, and improve the quality and reliability of electricity through improved energy efficiency and expanded installation of distributed energy sources such as new renewable enerov courcec grids mart reduce greenhouse gases, induce voluntary energy savings, and improve the quality ad ectricity through improved energy efficiency and expanded installation of distributed energy sources newable energy sources: he characteristics of smart are as follows. Consumers can actively participate Supports many ways of generating and storing electric power: Leads to the creation of new products, services and markets, grids grids In a smart consumers receive information about their energy usage pattern so could change their energy consumption habits In this way smart enables people to realize energy reductions and gives them options when consume electricity: Furthermore, smart grids can be connected to distributed power generation sources through renewable energy while connected to centralized large-scale power generation sources grid, they grid they being','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3078,'912','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Technologies that make up smart can be largely grouped under smart platforms and smart applications. The platform has intelligent devices, bi-directional communication and sophisticated control system for managing distributed and intelligent power The platform is configured to operate renewable energy applications, intelligent electric vehicle charging stations, smart metering applications power grid monitoring applications, demand response applications. Intelligent storage devices have electronic sensor ad meters that monitor the current state of the smart and has digital intelligent devices that can make basic decisions on their own. grids grid grid grid, grid The IT infrastructure attached to the power act as the IT elements that are critical to the operation of the smart It optimizes energy efficiency and people to consume energy through bi-directional exchange of real time information (about the supply and demand for electricity). Therefore, the smart must be equipped with open system networks and protocols so that its value-added services could create new products, services, and markets and not limited to just providing power The communication infrastructure should provide end-to-end services between intelligent devices and maintain a reliable and steady supply of electric power: Furthermore, development must abide by standards to support interoperability for various interfaces. grid grid, gets grid','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3079,'913','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'66] Concept diagram of Korea Electrical Safety Corporation\'s micro system\' [Fig grid',NULL,'68039aef1afbc.png','/storage/figures/68039aef1afbc.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3080,'913','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Microgrid is an extension of a smart The US Department of Energy (DOE) defines a microgrid as \"a group of interconnected consumers and distributed energy resources (DERs) under a clearly defined electrical specifications that can be controlled by the asa single entity and that could be connected to the system or made independent\' An easy way to understand micro is to view it as power constructed for a local area that connects electricity users with distributed energy resources such as wind and solar power It is a power that can make & owner become self-sufficient in power by operating independently of existing electric grid and still connect to the regular grid when necessary: In South Korea, microgrid pilot testings are underway in Jeju Island\'s smart complex Canado Mardo ana Mlouin grid system grid grid grid grid grid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3081,'914','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aef37c7e.png','/storage/figures/68039aef37c7e.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3082,'914','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Due to climate changes that affect the management of water, there is growing interest in smart water grid, the technology for managing water with ICT technology: Smart water grid is a smart technology that leverages ICT technology for the management of water that essential substance for humanity as well as the water supply and sewage water: ICT is used for informatizing the entire process of handling water from the production of drinkable water, the transportation of water, the processing and reuse of water: Utilize traditional water','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3083,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'68039aef55a8a.png','/storage/figures/68039aef55a8a.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3084,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.68] Smart traffic service classification',NULL,'68039aef74366.png','/storage/figures/68039aef74366.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3085,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'70] VZlservice [Fig',NULL,'68039aef90499.png','/storage/figures/68039aef90499.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3086,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Fig.71] VZN service',NULL,'68039aefad4be.png','/storage/figures/68039aefad4be.png','2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:35'),(3087,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Smart transportation is an intelligent transportation service that improves traffic safety, improves the efficiency traffic flow, and provides user convenience through the exchange of information among different vehicles, among vehicles, base stations and infrastructure, and among vehicles and traffic control servers. Source: Trends and Prospects of Smart Water Grid Technology for Water Resources Management, National Environment Information Center, 2016.11 <Source: Smart traffic cyber security guide, Ministry of Science and ICT, VZV service The VZV service is a service in which vehicles, the main agents of the traffic system, exchange information via wireless communication with their surrounding vehicles The service allows vehicles to send/receive messages about their positions, traffic flow information, and road traffic information Major VZV services include roadside information and obstacle notification services, road construction notification services, intersection traffic signal notification services, nearby vehicle information notification services, and emergency vehicle access notification services','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:01','2025-04-19 12:45:01'),(3088,'915','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','V2I service V2I service refers to communication between vehicles, the main agents of the traffic system, and the traffic support infrastructure: Vehicles equipped with an on board unit (OBU) trans