bles/68039af64a2ff.png','2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:42'),(3231,'941','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The OECD Privacy Guidelines is named the Recommendation Concerning Guidelines Governing the Protection of Privacy and Transborder Flows of Personal Data, which were established in 1980 as guidelines for the cross- border transfer of personal data in 1980. Since then, it has been revised to reflect the opinions of the intemational community on the collection and management of personal information, and is currently used as basic data for the development of laws and guidelines related to personal information in countries around the world,','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:08'),(3232,'941','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','32 Officially named \"Recommendation Concerning Guidelines Governing the Protection of Privacy and Transborder Flows of Personal Data','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:08'),(3233,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 82] GDPR system diagram',NULL,'68039af666706.png','/storage/tables/68039af666706.png','2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:42'),(3234,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'[Figure 83] GDPR penalty calculation criteria',NULL,'68039af684a5c.png','/storage/tables/68039af684a5c.png','2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:42'),(3235,'942','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The GDPR is a unified rule created by the European Parliament to strengthen the privacy of European citizens. It was promulgated by the European Parliament in 2016 (Regulation (EU) 2016/679) , and after a grace period of about two years, it took effect in each EU member state from 25,2018. When data of EU citizens, you must comply with the GDPR For example, even if there is no business establishment in Europe, any company that provides goods and services to residents of the European Union (EU) must comply with the regulations of the GDPR In addition, when a company violates the right of personal information, it is required to notify the supervisory authority within 72 hours, The main contents of the GDPR are the expansion of the application of personal information processing (for all companies that process personal information), enhancing the rights of data subjects, strengthening the responsibility of data controllers prohibiting the transfer of personal information abroad in principle, and taking measures to protect information the processing design stage when processing personal information In GDPR, the three entities involved in the process of processing personal information are defined as the data subject,, the controller and the processor Data Subject: Refers to a natural person\" who creates personal information and has the right to the personal information created by himher Controller: As a subject responsible for processing personal information, it controls personal information according to the type thereof determines the purpose of processing, and is in charge of processing means: Even if the data is the same, the controllers can be differentiated if the purpose of processing is different: Processor: Refers to an individual, corporation, or institution entrusted with processing personal information on behalf of the controller, and processes personal information as directed by the controller May using from \"living public The EUs GDPR reinforces the rights of data subjects compared to existing data protection guidelines by newly guaranteeing the right to be forgotten and the right to transfer data, and strictly restricts the transfer of data of EU citizens abroad The main items to guarantee the rights of data subjects in GDPR are as follows. the right to be informed the right of access the right to rectification the right to erasure the right to restrict processing the right to data portability the right to object The right to erasure (right to request erasure) has been renamed the right to forgotten in the previous GDPR draft, and the right to erasure and the right to data portability are items that reinforce the rights of data subjects. The rights in relation to automated decision making and profiling refer to the right to notify the user who is the data subject and to let them decide whether their information will be used or not, when an individuals occupation, hobbies, and location are automaticallv collected and used as nart of marketino from 3 Korea Internet & Security Agency, Guidance on \"General Data Protection Regulation\" for Korean Enterprises, 2017','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:08'),(3236,'943','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Individual Control: The right of the data subject to control personal information Transparency: Transparency in access to information Respect for Context: The right to know the context and reason for the act of collecting, using, and disclosir information Security: Strengthen the security of personal information Access and Accuracy: The right to access personal information as the data subject and to its accuracy Focused Collection: The right of the data subject to personal information collected and held by businesses Accountability: Data collecting agencys compliance with legislation and actions taken accordingly','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:08'),(3237,'944','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039af6a0383.png','/storage/tables/68039af6a0383.png','2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:42'),(3238,'944','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039af6c3b7b.png','/storage/tables/68039af6c3b7b.png','2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:42'),(3239,'944','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','34 Korea Internet & Security Agency, EU Privacy Policy Status, 2018. 35 US White House(wwwwhitehousegov), \"Consumer Privacy Bill of Rights','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:08','2025-04-19 12:45:08'),(3240,'945','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039af6e4ede.png','/storage/tables/68039af6e4ede.p