ears for overseas cases. Along with imprisonment, there are fines: In addition  ven if trade secrets are not actually leaked, any person who has attempted, or intends or conspires to ommit a crime can be punished ven if companies reinforce security technologies to protect technology trade secrets are leaked by people, 0 it is necessary to prepare for them. Violation of trade secrets is subject to criminal penalties Imprisonment for up to 5 years is imposed fo domestic cases and up to 10 years for overseas cases with imprisonment, there are fines. In additior even if trade secrets are not actually leaked, any person who has attempted, or intends or conspires commit a crime can be punished Along\' Even if companies reinforce security technologies to protect technology trade secrets are leaked by people, so it is necessary to prepare for them:','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3266,'719','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Intellectual property rights mean rights to intellectual property recognized or protected by laws or treaties include knowledge, information and technology created or discovered by human creative activities or experiences, expressions of ideas or emotions, representations of business or objects, varieties or genetic resources of living organisms, and other intangibles of realizable property value They','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3267,'720','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Intellectual property rights are largely divided into the following three types Copyright: Exclusive rights recognized for academic research findings or literary creations Industrial property rights: Industrial property rights are rights recognized for new industrial inventions, practical inventions, product forms or trademarks New intellectual property rights: New intellectual property rights are rights to intellectual property that emerges in new fields due to economic, social, or cultural changes or development of science and technology:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3268,'951','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'68039af81782c.png','/storage/tables/68039af81782c.png','2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:44'),(3269,'951','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Copyright is a right arising to a person who created a work, and generally refers to an exclusive right granted tc the author of a work by law The copyright applies the time the work is created, and follows the non-formality principle, meaning that it is automatically generated even without formal requirements or registration procedures for from copyngii 15 a ng\'i 015ing IU a peisuii Wiio Cicalcu WvuiK aru gericraiy iCicis IU al exciusive \"griL gralileu lu the author of a work by law The copyright applies the time the work is created, and follows the non-formality principle, meaning that it is automatically generated even without formal requirements or registration procedures for the work Copyright is largely divided into moral rights, authors economic rights, and neighboring rights. Copyrights which are the rights of authors, can be classified into moral rights and authors economic rights. In the case of moral rights, it is a non-monetary right to protect the author\'s honor ad character and is non- transferable (the right under exclusive belongingness of oneself). The moral rights include the right of attribution, the right to have a work published anonymously or pseudonymously, and the right to the integrity of the work Authors\' economic rights are related to the property of the author, are monetary rights and are transferable Authors economic rights include the right of reproduction, performance, broadcasting, transmission rights, exhibition, distribution, production of derivative works. The copyright holder may allow other people to use the work, and a person who has obtained permission to use the work may freely use the work within the scope of the permitted use methods and conditions. In addition, even if a work has been licensed for use, it cannot be transferred to another person without the consent of the copyright holder, so it is necessary to pay attention to the use of the work Meanwhile, neighboring rights refer to the rights of neighbors such as performers, record producers, and broadcasters Neighboring rights are given differently to each neighboring right holder ad since it is usually a secondary right to from','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3270,'951','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','create added value by using the work, more restrictive rights are given to the copyright holder','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3271,'952','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 106  Types of Recognized Works',NULL,'68039af84ac4a.png','/storage/tables/68039af84ac4a.png','2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:44'),(3272,'952','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term \'\"work\" means a creative production that expresses human thoughts and emotions Copyright is established only when a work with originality and externality is created, and the types of works recognized are as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3273,'722','App\\Models\\Section','Text','If it is difficult to know who actually created the work, any person who falls under any of the following subparagraphs shall be presumed to have the copyright for his or her works as an author: (Copyright Acty Article 8 (1) A person whose real name or well-known pseudonym (referring to the stage name, pen name, abbreviated name, etc , hereinafter the same shall apply) is indicated as the name of the author in a usual manner on the original or copies of a work, A person whose real name or well-known pseudonym is indicated as the name of the author in the public If the name of the author is not indicated as prescribed under any of the subparagraphs of paragraph (1), the perso who is indicated as a publisher, public performer or a person making the work shall be presumed to have th copyright: (Copyright Acty Article 8 (2)) public PPj\"6\' Public performance\" means to present to the public works performances, phonograms or broadcasts by acting, musical playing, singing, narrating reciting, screening, playback or other means. \"Public transmission\" means transmitting works, stage performances, phonograms, broadcasts or database by making such available to the public by wire or wireless means so that the public may receive them or have access to them: \"Publication\" means a reproduction and distribution of the works or phonograms to meet public demand \"Making works public\" means to make the works open to the public by means of public performance, public transmission, or exhibit and bv other means and to publish the works','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3274,'953','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The term work made for hire\" means a work made by an employee of a legal person, organization or other employe (hereinafter referred to as \"legal person, etc\" the course of his or her duties and on the initiative of leg person, etc\"7 The authorship of a work made for hire which is made under the name f such a legal person, etc. as the auth 38 shall be attributed to that legal person,, etc, unless otherwise stipulated in the contract or work regulation, etc In order for a legal person, etc: to become the author of a work made for hire, it must meet all of the followi requirements (Korea Copyright Commission\'s Consultation Case Book) The work must be initiated by a legal person or the like It must be written by a person who is engaged in business such as a legal person: It must be a work written for business. It must be publicized in the name of a legal person, etc, during public 37 Copyright Act, subparagraph 31 of Article 38 Convrioht Act Article','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:11','2025-04-19 12:45:11'),(3275,'954','App\\Models\\Subsec