-19 12:45:13'),(3325,'974','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 114  Examples of the trolley dilemmz',NULL,'68039af9bfa4c.png','/storage/tables/68039af9bfa4c.png','2025-04-19 12:45:13','2025-04-19 12:45:45'),(3326,'974','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','There is a trolley dilemma suggested by Philippa Foot, a British ethical philosopher, as a thought experiment related to the ethical dilemma of self-driving cars and drones The trolley dilemma is an experiment on whether it is morally permissible to sacrifice five workers on the rail on which the train travels, or one other worker on the other rail, in a situation where the trolley train with broken brakes is running: This experiment is often cited in relation to which of the drivers or pedestrians to protect in the accident of an autonomous vehicle','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 12:45:13','2025-04-19 12:45:13'),(3327,'975','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','~Ouiuai ICCiui Ciouu Cumtiputns  Ci viccniuviuci Cloud computing service providers shall endeavor to protect user information and provide reliable cloud computing services, Cloud computing service providers shall endeavor to enhance the quality and performance of cloud computing services and the level of protection of information. In case of an infringement accident, user data leakage, or service interruption without prior notice, the cloud computing service provider must notify the relevant users without delay: Where a cloud computing service provider intends to provide any user information to a third party or to use the user information for any purpose other than for the purpose of providing services, it shall notify the user of the following matters and shall obtain consent thereto. Where the contract made with a user terminates, the cloud computing service provider shall return the user information to the user and destroy the user information possessed by the cloud computing service provider Where a cloud computing service provider intends to close its