ing can be defined as a process in which the moderator presents a certain topic and the relevant stakeholders at a set time to discuss and reach an aoraomant gather As the various viewpoints of meeting participants collide and converge, creative ideas can be derived and unexpected risks can be reduced Meetings are the most effective way to use collective intelligence In order to take advantage of these meetings more systematically, efforts should be made to take minutes as much as possible. As the Annals of the Joseon Dynasty, the UNESCO World Heritage, retain various minutes of state management for more than 500 years, helping to study the history, organizations can accurately understand the history of work and various decisions through meeting minutes','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:14','2025-04-19 14:05:14'),(3426,'1014','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','1 other words, meeting minutes are documents that clarify communication by organizing meeting results. In ase of collaboration, it is very important to organize meeting minutes because the content of communication nay be subtly changed later due to differing interests The specific method of writing the minutes is as follows case of collaboration, it is very important to organize meeting minutes because the content of communication may be subtly changed later due to differing interests. The specific method of writing the minutes is as follows Record the date and time, place, theme of the meeting, participants, discussions, and decisions. If the meeting lasts for a time, you can use an electronic recorder: Minutes are basically written in accordance with the SWIH principle: When, where, who, what, how, and why: It is of utmost importance to record the summarized opinions presented at the meeting: As described above, minutes serve a role as the official letter that prevents you overturning what was previously agreed. The completed minutes are circulated via e-mail to the attendees of the meeting, and opinions are 