42','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When designing the main body, be aware of the following matters. Contain the content targeted at the audience (readers, reviewers, Schematic and simplifying expression Use commonly used schematics Use original images Use proper fonts and colors Utilize the message (or feeling) that colors convey writing','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3512,'1043','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The heading (leading message) plays a very important role in the preparation of presentation material. This is because the message is determined first and the materials that can further explain the message are placed at the bottom: The key tips for writing the heading are as follows. key Pi Cp 78 One message per page: The heading should contain only one topic explaining the rest of the contents below: More than one topic in a single heading sentence can be distracting: It shouldn\'t be too short to understand what it\'s about, and too to read. It should be written in an appropriate length: The length of the heading is usually one or two sentences More than two sentences undermine readability: The content to be included in the heading is what to do (What) or why, summary of the conclusion, description of key points, and the facts of information or data Avoid ambiguous content that is not specific It is necessary to reflect specific content as much as possible. long','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3513,'1044','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 25  Types of Charts',NULL,'6803adbb4e947.png','/storage/tables/6803adbb4e947.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3514,'1044','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6803adbb63f6e.png','/storage/tables/6803adbb63f6e.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3515,'1044','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When preparing a presentation, it is important to have a variety of charts to present as the basis for your argument. Charts are very important element in the presentation, as the appropriate form must be selected according to the characteristics of the item to be displayed to make the audience understood and convinced of VOI rouma Most of the charts fall into the five types below You should use the chart well according to your message','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3516,'1045','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 26  Basic Patterns of Visualization',NULL,'6803adbb7b070.png','/storage/tables/6803adbb7b070.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3517,'1045','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Visualization is a way of using schematics to better understand the subject, and appropriate schematics is much more effective than writing verbosely: For visualization, the items go through the process of structuring the message using the following pattern: using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3518,'1046','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','First Principle: With a suitable structure-Selection of shape types according to the description method of keywords Second Principle: Easy to understand-structured logic for intuitive understanding Third Principle: Highlight points-Highlight to be emphasized with color or other shapes points','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3519,'775','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'',NULL,'6803adbb9620b.png','/storage/figures/6803adbb9620b.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3520,'776','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 27  Review of Briefing Session Materials',NULL,'6803adbbbf5a4.png','/storage/tables/6803adbbbf5a4.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3521,'776','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6803adbbd8942.png','/storage/tables/6803adbbd8942.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:47'),(3522,'776','App\\Models\\Section','Text','It is good to have a third party review the contents after completing all the materials for the briefing sessior from an objective perspective','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3523,'777','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 28  Presentation Tools',NULL,'6803adbc1115a.png','/storage/tables/6803adbc1115a.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3524,'777','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tools that are often used to create technical documents include PowerPoint, Keynote, and Prezi, and the fea- tures and strengths and weaknesses of each are as follows.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3525,'778','App\\Models\\Section','Text','On the actual presentation site, such as a proposal briefing session,, a business briefing session, and a presen tation within the organization, the presentation material has an effect, but the presenter\'s presentation has a more significant effect: Even if the presentation material is insufficient, if the presenter responds well, it will be finished well: Even if the presentation material is well-designed, if the presenter cannot answer an im ability','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3526,'778','App\\Models\\Section','Text','portant question, it may lead to poor outcomes. Likewise, the important points for on-site presentation are as follows: Frellminary inspection 0r tne Presentation venue It is necessary to look around the presentation venue in advance, visualize a scene in which the audience is seated, and simulate the range of motion, gestures, and a simple practice of presentation It is necessary to look around the presentation venue in advance, visualize a scene in which the audience is seated, and simulate the range of motion, gestures, and a simple practice of presentation Be familiar with the order of presentation material Check whether you are familiar with the sequence and flow of the presentation material. Glancing over at the material while speaking may often make you look less confident because you do not make eye contact with the audience, which may undermine credibility in what you say, and make the presentation itself boring: Therefore, you should always be familiar with the order of the presentation material and maintain a natural flow so that you can continue your presentation even without reading the material. Appropriate and Interesting Opening Comments You should start your presentation with a story that can relate to topics such as simple weather, current status, and recent issues, and that can arouse the audience\'s interest If you go straight into the topic from the beginning, the atmosphere may become rigid and the relationship between the presenter and the audience may become awkward. It\'s okay to talk lightly, so prepare a comment that can help create a comfortable atmosphere of the first encounter with the audience Presentation Material Review Tcociucioi vulcniaiC Check the prepared presentation material for any errors. Since the style in which the prepared material is displayed may vary depending on the version or font of the presentation tool software, it is recommended to bring with a laptop, etc. to be ready for an unexpected situation: points of each sheet and appropriate examples to promote understanding Check the key points to be presented for each sheet once again, and whether the cases prepared to promote better understanding are well connected. It is also to make use of presentation tools or prepare a simple cue sheet Key good good Impressive closing comments At the end of the presentation, prepare a closing comment so that you can leave an impressive message to your audience. It is also to use aphorisms or quotes related to the contents of the presentation, or to convey impressively the words you saw in the book The important is that the closing comment is well linked to the subject so that the subject content can be more deeply relatable good good point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3527,'1047','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Your appearance and image is also very important factor to win the audiences trust: In order to make a impression, you need to have a neat appearance, hairstyle, and attire. It is difficult to make a impression and look trustworthy when you look messy: And you should have a smiling face. If you are gloomy or stiff, you may present a negative image good good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3528,'1048','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','You must keep your eyes clear and bright: Insecure eye gaze cannot make you look confident or trustworthy: Eye contact is a very effective way to make a presentation successful. When giving a presentation, it is most important to make eye contact with the people who make decisions. Look at one person at a time, but distribute your visual attention about 60% to the decision maker and 40% to the rest of the audience It is necessary to observe the other person\'s reaction and develop a connection through contact\". key \"eye \"','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3529,'1049','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','You must explain with correct pronunciation and appropriate speed, and presenting with a resonant voice helps to enhance delivery: Rather than keeping the of voice constant,, you should immerse the audience by controlling the such as making it slow, fast, or a pause, etc speed speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3530,'1050','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Body language is effective to use when emphasizing important points. If you take too much exaggerated motion, you can make a negative impression. It s a idea to use the proper hand movements at the right timing: good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3531,'1051','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If you emphasize something with your voice, and make a gesture afterwards, it may not be effective. It is effective to make a gesture at the same time or slightly ahead of an utterance. Make eye contact and use your hand gestures together while vocalizing as if pressing the voice slowly:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3532,'779','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 17]',NULL,'6803adbc2e658.png','/storage/figures/6803adbc2e658.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3533,'779','App\\Models\\Section','Text','According to The Law of Mehrabian, 93% of non-verbal body language such as gestures ad tone of voice is used to persuade the other person in actual communication The logical explanation occupies only 7%. Here, body language includes voice. For example, we think that an actor with voice is at acting: No matter how well you act, if you cannot speak well, you may be seen as if you are not at acting How to effectively use body language in your presentation is as follows good good good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3534,'780','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Scenario is a kind of simulation of using a given time in a certain way: No matter how the presentatic material is, if you aren\'t prepared to when to throw a certain message, the presentation is highly likely to fail. Therefore, it is good to write a message to explain in a slide note and print it out for rehearsal. Rehearsal good to practice once or twice by imaging as if there is an audience to hear you: good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3535,'781','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tension is the greatest enemy of the presentation, and lowering tension is a very important factor in an actual presentation. An example of how to reduce tension before a presentation is below: presentation: An example Of how to reauce tension betore a presentation IS below: Clench and unclench your fist repetitively: Do a belly breathing: Repeat inhaling deeply and exhaling Go to the presentation venue early to ready: Do more rehearsals to enhance confidence. Having a chat with a colleague before the start can reduce the tension Encourage yourself by saying \"It\'s to make a mistake \" and \"Right nowl Im okay:\" in your mind long: get okay','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3536,'782','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Most novice presenters are not at first greeting: That\'s why you may feel nervous throughout the entire presentation, as if the first button was misplaced. For example, let\'s say you made your first greeting as fol lows. good Good morning: Im A from O0 department at O0 Company: (Greeting at the same time) Good morning:\" (Greeting), \"Im A from O0 department at O0 Company It\'s nice to see you, Which would be better? In the first case, there are too many words to say before bowing: The timing to make bow may not coincide with the applause of the audience: As in the second example, if you greet the audience with a short greeting message to the audience, and after receiving applause, look around and introduce yourself, you will be able to give a more relaxed presentation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3537,'783','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'Table 29  Response of the presentation',NULL,'6803adbc41319.png','/storage/tables/6803adbc41319.png','2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3538,'783','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The presentation is present You make a connection with others and communicate with them, and the pur pose is to draw empathy and make the other person make decisions. You should be able to think about the voice tone, speed, content, emphasis, and story transition from various angles while monitoring the reaction of the other person. The positive and negative reactions of the audience are as follows When negative reactions appear, you need to quickly judge and transition the story, or use humor for a mo ment,, or adjust the tone and of your speech to retain the audiences attention: Be aware of the above reactions as it is very important to track of and control the situation in the middle of the presentation: speed keep','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3539,'276','App\\Models\\Lesson','Text','So we have looked at various processes and techniques for preparing the presentation Here we will look at some of the important things to consider when executing your presentation: far, key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:21','2025-04-19 14:05:21'),(3540,'72','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Recen Trenas ana Major issues It is important to understand the concept and characteristics of project, organizational structure for project execution, and the areas of activities of project managers and participants, for the successful execution of a project, given that all business activities including software development are operational and project-based Le 706 = 1. To be able to explain the concept of project. 2 To be able to describe the organizational structure and roles of participants for project executior cuiicepl summmtiay Project characteristics: temporary effort, provision of a unique product or service, purpose, progressive elaboration Similar concepts: program, portfolio Organizational structure: functional organization, matrix organization, projectized organization Project Roles: Project Manager Project Leader, Quality Assurance Team, Architect Team, Development Team, Support Team, Sponsor Corporate projects are increasingly operated through PMO organizations or similar organizations that manage enterprise-wide projects and portfolios. Projects are activities to achieve organizational requirements, and PMOs prioritize projects and programs that become the organization\'s strategy and supply and manage necessary resources','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:22'),(3541,'72','App\\Models\\Module','Header','Preview for practical business','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:22'),(3542,'72','App\\Models\\Module','Text','As all projects are original without being uniquely the same, and the environment in which are conducted is all different, project management techniques cannot be applied in a uniform manner: Still, it is necessary to know what standards and guidance exist in the project knowledge, skills, techniques, and tools, and which situation are applicable, in order to make the project successful. Representative knowledge systems and standards of projects are as follows: they they successful. Representative knowledge systems and standards of projects are as follows: PMP is professional qualification for project management supervised by the PMI (Project Management Institute): It has a project management knowledge system called PMBOK , consisting of 5 process groups, 49 processes and 10 knowledge areas. PRINCE2 is project management method based on project management qualifications and procedures created in the UK ISO 21500 was developed by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO) in 2012, from the existing private project management into a global project management standard system, consisting of 11 important cases of project management, 5 process groups, 10 subject groups, and 39 processes','',2,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:22'),(3543,'784','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 30  Comparison of project, program, and portfolio',NULL,'6803adbc5898d.png','/storage/tables/6803adbc5898d.png','2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3544,'784','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 18] Relationship between project, program, and portfolio',NULL,'6803adbc6ff4c.png','/storage/figures/6803adbc6ff4c.png','2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3545,'784','App\\Models\\Section','Text','According to The Mythical Man-Month by Frederick Brooks, the Tower of Babel was man s first project and Noah\'s Ark was the first successful one As such, a project refers to a sum of efforts to mobilize resources to achieve a specific goal. Recently, projects are being carried out for the purpose of developing various products or services by investing limited resources within a predefined period, both inside and outside the company: As such, a project refers to any activity in which limited human and physical resources and efforts are put into place at a set (temporary) time to create a unique product or service, or for a specific purpose.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:22','2025-04-19 14:05:22'),(3546,'784','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Similar terms to the project include program and portfolio. A program is a set of interrelated projects It aim to integrate multiple projects into a single program in order to achieve a common in consideration of cor- relations between projects, and to manage individual projects in an effective manner goal Oilal leiins lu lrie prujecl iciuue pi0gr am aliu poi liuiio. A pi0grali 1S a Sel ui ililettelaleu piujecls: Il aits to integrate multiple projects into a single program in order to achieve a common goal in consideration of cor- relations between projects, and to manage individual projects in an effective manner: A portfolio is a set of programs and projects undertaken to achieve an organization\'s strategic goals. Portfolio management is carried out the strategic perspective of the organization, including prioritizing programs nroioctc dinc Jnnronriato FoCO from portfolio is a set of programs and projects undertaken to achieve a organization\'s strategic goals. Portfolic management is carried out from the strategic perspective of the organization, including prioritizing program and projects and providing appropriate resources:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3547,'784','App\\Models\\Section','Text','These terms have the following commonalities and differences, depending on the size, relevance, and the profits of the project in the business organization The comparison of project, program, and portfolio is as fol lows,','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3548,'785','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Temporary: A temporary activity that has a specific beginning and end. Uniqueness: Every project is unique, offering a unique service to the customer Progressive elaboration: An activity to specify the product or service to be created from constructing th general meaning at the beginning Constraint of scope, cost and time: The most comment constraints are scope, cost, and schedule. Resource and quality: A service that provides quality through resources to customers and stakeholders.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3549,'786','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 31  Examples of Practical Project',NULL,'6803adbc9b1c6.png','/storage/tables/6803adbc9b1c6.png','2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3550,'786','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In business, projects are being planned or undertaken even today by countless organizations with a wide var ety of and objectives: would like to briefly examine the purpose of projects in practice, example of several projects that are actively carried out these goals taking being days:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3551,'786','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Numerous projects are planned or conducted with their own and objectives This is a natural response of organizations or companies to survive in the business ecosystem as the existing business environment, customers, and markets change from moment to moment. goals','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3552,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 32  Project Organizational Structure',NULL,'6803adbcbed28.png','/storage/tables/6803adbcbed28.png','2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3553,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 19] Project Organizational Chart',NULL,'6803adbcd9208.png','/storage/figures/6803adbcd9208.png','2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:48'),(3554,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Organizational structures related to project execution can be divided into functional organization, matrix orga nization, and project-oriented organization Functional Organization: It is a conventional corporate structure in which an organization is divided into smaller groups based on each task or function, and the project of a group is conducted independently from other groups. In a functional organization, there is no separate project manager, but the manager of each functional group performs responsibilities ad roles. If there is a project manager in the functional organization,, Source: eGovernment Standard Framework (https:/lwwegovtrame gokr) Source: Smart factory expansion and advancement strategy jointly with related ministries, led by the Presidential Committee on the 4th industrial revolution, 2018-03-08','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3555,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Text','he or she does not have decision-making authority in the project and plays a facilitating role Projectized Organization: It is a organizational structure in which the project manager is responsible for decision-making and has total authority for project execution It shares the same physical space by project, allowing prompt communication and decision-making: Matrix Organization: Matrix organization is a complex form of functional organization and project-oriented organization, and can be divided into weak, balanced matrix and strong matrix structure. The weak matrix organization is similar to the functional organization, and the project manager acts as a facilitator The balanced matrix organization is a structure in which members of the functional organization play the role of project managers The project manager acts as a coordinator with the right to decision-making ad partial authority: The strong matrix organization is similar to the projectized organization, and a separate project manager apart from the functional organization focuses on project management ad is responsible for much decision-making and authority:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3556,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Text','In general, when a project for software development or system construction is undertaken, project managers of the client company and staff of the IT development company are combined to form a project organization:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3557,'787','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The project organization consists of project managers (PM) , project leaders (PL) who lead each development team, developers, quality assurance (QA) staff under the direct control of PMs, SA (software architect) for ar- chitect support, PMO (Project Management Office) for project management support, project support groups (Ul design, testing, etc ) , architect team, PM, etc__ as well as steering committees and sponsors who support higher-level decisions, such as changes in the scope and schedule of the project Of course, the project orga- nization may vary depending on the goals and characteristics of each individual project.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3558,'788','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 33  Classification of PMs Competencies',NULL,'6803adbd12f1b.png','/storage/tables/6803adbd12f1b.png','2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:49'),(3559,'788','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Who is the project manager and what does the person do on the project?\" \"The project manager is the person responsible for the entire scope and schedule of the project: In other words, the person oversees ad communicates the progress of the project, as well as resolving issues and risks to quality ad stakeholders from the initial stage to the end of the project \" Project managers need to understand and be able to exert the following three distinct competencies in order to carry out a project','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3560,'1052','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When the PMO organization is composed of internal project managers, it becomes an internal organization, an external organization if composed of external project managers, and a mixed type in case of skill mix','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3561,'1053','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','As the PMO is affected by the corporate structure, it is classified into the weather station model that acts as a facilitator according to the roles and responsibilities of the project manager, the coach model that is responsible for guides and processes, and the control tower model that has a great influence on the overall responsibility and process for the project Weather Station Model: Operated by a small number of professionals, secure and provide information only on progress, distribute project management knowledge, develop and disseminate methodology Coach Model: An extended concept of the weather station model, distribute the use of common methodologies and software tools within the organization, operate a community to relay communication between the project team, recording and monitoring project performance, and supplying project management experts Control Tower Model: Involved in all projects, deeply engaged in decision-making, the same methodology applied to all projects, centralized management, coordinate ad determine resources to be put into the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3562,'1054','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','project manager may be in charge of one project and manage it intensively, but one project manager may be in charge of two or three projects at the same time If the person has full control, it is classified as a full-time type, and if multiple projects are managed together, it is classified as a time type part-\'','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3563,'1055','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','PMO is an organization made up of project managers, and individual project managers are experts in fields such as development, consulting, project evaluation, database, quality management, ad development methodology: The technical type of the PMO organization is determined by the specialty of the project manager','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3564,'789','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 20] PMO Classification',NULL,'6803adbd46788.png','/storage/figures/6803adbd46788.png','2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:49'),(3565,'789','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Many companies have thought about how to conduct an effective enterprise-wide project management for several decades. As a result, an organization dedicated to the project called the Project Management Office (PMO) has come into being: In Korea,, PMO functions a5 a system that entrusts persons with professional knowledge and technical skills to efficiently perform e-government projects in accordance with Article 64-2 \"Entrustment of Management of','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3566,'789','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Electronic Government Projects of Electronic Government Act, It plays the role of overseeing and the entire project, mediating issues, and consulting, from the standpoint of complementing the client\'s expertise, In the case of intangible informatization projects requiring a high level of credibility, PMO is needed for pre-di- agnosis, thorough planning for each stage of the project, quantitative process management, periodic commu- nication and quality assurance of outputs. PMO can be classified according to the type, responsibility, and role of PMO, time horizon of the project, and skill division of PMs, into 4 types as follows.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:23','2025-04-19 14:05:23'),(3567,'73','App\\Models\\Module','Text','Recent renas ana Major issues Project management process cannot be applied to all projects in a uniform manner Appr