3,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3700,'811','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 36] Types of Functions',NULL,'6803adc18a8a8.png','/storage/figures/6803adc18a8a8.png','2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:53'),(3701,'811','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Function Point is a method of estimating the cost by measuring the scale of software development as a Func- tion Point (FP) and multiplying the unit price per function It is an international standard (ISO/IEC 14143) that quantitatively calculates functions requested by and delivered to users from a user\'s of view, and is a cost calculation method for software development, maintenance and operation. Compared to the LOC (Line Of Code)-based COCOMO method or the ManjMonth (MM) method, it has the characteristic of grasping the size of the development project before initiation by identifying the required function of the user point point Software functions are divided into Data Functions and Transaction Functions, and more specifically, data functions are subdivided into Internal Logical Files and External Interface Files, and transaction functions are subdivided into three types: External Inputs, External Outputs, and External Inquiries','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3702,'1090','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 47  Average Wage for SW Engineers in 2017',NULL,'6803adc19eafb.png','/storage/tables/6803adc19eafb.png','2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:53'),(3703,'1090','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',NULL,'6803adc1b631e.png','/storage/tables/6803adc1b631e.png','2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:53'),(3704,'1090','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When the required labor is allocated for each work package, the unit price per labor must be determined In the case of Korea, the average wage of a software engineer published by Korea Software Industry Association is applied, which is determined by referring to the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3705,'1091','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Overhead cost is indirect expenses incurred in the areas of planning, management, and general affairs for the administrative operation of the software developer Usually, it is calculated as 110 to 120% of the direct labor cost. Royalty is an amount in exchange for the use and accumulation of technology developed and owned by the software developer and it is calculated as 20 to 40% of the sum of direct labor cost plus overhead cost. paid','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3706,'1092','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Direct cost refers to expenses directly required for software development, as royalties for comput system or software tools, software, professional expenses, travel expenses, and materials costs, etc. direct incurred for the software development project. such In the field of private projects, the man month calculation is used to calculate project development cost, and also for mutual verification interchangeably with the function analysis, which has recently become mandatory in public projects. point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3707,'812','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Man/Month is a method of measuring how much labor is consumed in a project based on previous experience in similar projects, and calculating the cost based on the manpower put into the project Mvuntiui| Ju 47\"6 Id Tuo 0Jui pUj- Dul Ui P ~ 4o Capc~ in similar projects, and calculating the cost based on the manpower put into the project Project development cost direct labor cost   overhead cost Royaltyt direct cost Generally, required manpower resources are allocated for each work package, the lowest unit of the WBS derived from scope management','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-04-19 14:05:31','2025-04-19 14:05:31'),(3708,'813','App\\Models\\Section','Text','COCOMO is one of the estimation methods of the cost of a software development pro